Dishes are large, for sharing family style.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh47H4b5M3p4oLwEBzGBMrbzU3qK2h-KPSu2KN&fid=0x0:0x8696cccf7f56bf5a"],"When":"2021-3-29"},{"Name":"John Mavrick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtlxEpvwpVyyZ_gqkRZIRms95G82FFcYgvYajFPC85ahCpMFWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly staff and good portions, perfect for a late night out with friends or family :) We had the padak, army soup, cheese corn with butter, kimchi pancakes, and galbi !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvz-HlCZdR0BcWNOBwpX0B07pAr6Lg5gumGyf7&fid=0x0:0x8696cccf7f56bf5a"],"When":"2021-9-25"},{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to this restaurant with a few buddies after exercising at the aquatic center. It was about a 2 minute walk from the nearest free parking around 7:00pm. It was decently cold but I was well-dressed so it was okay.

We sat down and got the booth which had more than enough room for our party of four and the menu was very easy to understand with pictures and a small but tasty selection. We ended up getting the Tebboki or however you say it, some honey butter chicken, some fried squid, as well as the kimchi.

The chicken gave me a mouth orgasm, although, this could have been because I was rather inebriated on various cannabis products. However, I blinked and the food was gone. My spice tolerance is also decently high, so beware people that are not used to spicy food the tebboki might be a bit much. However, the rice offset the spicy flavour and made the meal a very good combo to eat together.

5/5 would recommend to people. Good service as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQw8Rxz6aZZbrvFM_nKo_4BWjpM-J0jxH9gM-o&fid=0x0:0x8696cccf7f56bf5a"],"When":"2023-1-21"}]

Toilet is clean! Waiter and waitress crew are all very nice and professional too! Love this restaurant very much‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPza0ew2GjCDcnw3yaVoLhK8iMmk0FFxjlS2rw5&fid=0x0:0x1d1cd1ad544caa40"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Kai-Chun Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjTiDNcTKlmyRrDWdGPFt530dlO3QJbviz_GUObBc3bQ0rNmRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of my favorite restaurants in Coquitlam as it's a place where I'm guaranteed to have a good time.

Food - the food isn't the most amazing thing I've ever tasted, BUT every single one that I've tried was at least good or better. There's basically no bad choice in the menu.
Service/atmosphere - the seats are spacious and comfortable, the waitresses are always friendly (even more so to kids!), we never had to wait too long for our food... it's just a great experience all around.
Price - with the above points, it would've already been one of my restaurants of choice, but then they went ahead and kept the price reasonable and that just seals the deal for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN90L9zlD4vK0EDnXwB3NnlbNYPDfIUE5NcHqHh&fid=0x0:0x1d1cd1ad544caa40"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Omid Dadgari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXY5oTTgmTf1M1XQYNbrrLX-SdVGDzUB3Iw3aDSyAgQLf2_BwYgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I visited Coquitlam Grill for breakfast today and ordered Steak and eggs. The overall quality of the ingredients was very good. However, I ordered my steak medium, but it arrived well-done. Despite this, the quality was still good. The quantity of the food was very generous, offering great value for the price. It made me full, even though I hadn't eaten dinner or supper yesterday. The servers were attentive and friendly. The atmosphere was typical of a North American restaurant and quite enjoyable. Overall, a decent experience with room for improvement on the steak preparation."","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNT61QeH3ufJtT_GqPt1Sg0rufpTlP24BeUhlEu&fid=0x0:0x1d1cd1ad544caa40"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Julie B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4pd43YT5KSqkORSPaVbra7_KcodZ1kkwID5yaolZD_WuCOEiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an amazing restaurant. Food was Ultimate Omelet

Tex Mex Omelet
Eggs Haida Benny
Drinks were margarita, mimosas and a Ceasar.
The service was fantastic and Susan was amazing.
Everyone raved about their dishes and everyone cleaned their plated and both styles of harsh browns by far were the best we have ever had.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNatRTF11J76msxdL31ksun0mlD6h6LFwhaBmNW&fid=0x0:0x1d1cd1ad544caa40"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Thomas Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUITuDRjw9J9Us45xAUXKSfp8lG2sJ2s04TW_lNAi_G6a5d62ur=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just came here for a dinner. [{"Name":"Kim Withers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKKnnFnw4jT31ns6Kf5JAE_mqFWTs-3cVvpPNOg1rsbgYPYGl3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The staff are very friendly and the service was fast. The portions are size is huge. Unfortunately, the food was just ok. My beef broth was warm water and the spring roll was abandoned after one bite.  I love Pho with usually great layers of flavour but this was not it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVHQeNQdBSdRvMLithlCAHQ5clg64xex06Ja41&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5pgqDcV4jXxCDs44gFpKqBE7-kpDe9pqH0qySpykt9h70rZWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Pho Super Bowl in Coquitlam and decided to try their pork vermicelli (#66), and it did not disappoint! The portion was generous, with a perfectly grilled, tender, and flavorful pork that had a deliciously caramelized edge. The vermicelli was fresh and well-cooked, served alongside crisp vegetables like bean sprouts, cucumbers, and lettuce, which added a nice crunch to the dish. The fish sauce was light and tangy, complementing the savory pork perfectly without overwhelming the flavors.

The balance of flavors in this bowl was spot on, and the accompanying spring rolls were crispy and packed with flavor, a fantastic addition. The presentation was also great‚Äîvery appetizing with vibrant colors.

Service was quick and friendly despite the restaurant being busy, and the atmosphere was casual and inviting. Whether you‚Äôre a fan of pho or looking to explore other options on their menu, I highly recommend giving their pork vermicelli a try!

This captures the key aspects of your experience while emphasizing the flavor and overall atmosphere of the restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5qsIkpneH8Vr6cu3bOhK43yolHJZKWNakgeS-&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Brandon Collins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJftMou5k5OJyPtZPxUAjCRk0hWFHK-OghGtQJYsSNzGar9YlLzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Saw this place on an Instagram reel showing of the variety of traditional veitnamese dishes , all of the meals looked amazing so I had to try it for myself . My son ordered a banh mi ga ( veitnamese sub with chicken) it was ok at best I probably wouldn't order it again . My wife ordered the gom ga ( chicken and rice) she said it was ok also.  We ordered the appetizer of chicken wings they were great ! And for myself I ordered the pho thai bo vein ( pho beef ball and steak ) and yes it was definitely a homerun not only a large quantity but good broth and lots of meat . I'd definitely come back but I'd stick to the pho as that's what this place does best at .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtldi51cOIJHaWHgfDa1MC5B_neT-gvoQ0M2R3&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"jay Ko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKx55LCvOrGRPp-bz8WbkRCn4gZDlDBBz0K8yV1EKgnLoTqXw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is good and the price is reasonable. BUT I AM NOT COMING BACK, for sure, because they keep messing around with the bill. This is the third time it‚Äôs happened to me. Yesterday, I paid, left with my receipt, and noticed something was wrong‚Äîthey charged way more than the listed prices. I went back to the store with the bill, and they just said, ‚ÄòSorry about that,‚Äô and handed me back $19 in cash. At this point, I have to say this feels intentional because it‚Äôs happened three times now.

Be careful about overcharging here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXU-etp9J401XNl8xOiZZVO7Htrv6WKijYtByj&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Shivanie Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFbollGMNfPGQeQeE1iu9uspIWWpZ_q45kMCmZRZ6VvynDEjM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"WORST FOOD EVER!!! Its not even cooked properly. The first wing was okay but others are like they just served it as undercooked tried checking it with fingers before eating. I guess Getting order in 5 mins is no surprise that they serves u raw. And servers are talking to each other and I am seeing the man using his hand to clean his teeth I am not sure if he has tooth pick or what.. NEVER GOING BACK HERE!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhaby_MvrAfawZ9TQcyI0HYpdTLgg7iknx9dta&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Jade Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJWSVoZW1CCY-_xhdgdeWOnL28P_e39FAE_t38PKZ_hYo17g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Comfortable dine in experience. Washroom was clean. Food was fantastic. Service was top notch, fast and efficient. Had the beef stew, large, great portions. Reasonable price. The appetizer fried spring roll was done perfectly. The fried chicken wings were fantastic -- crispy, tasty, not overly salty, lots of meat, juicy. Strawberry smoothie was excellent. Nothing bad to complain about.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Huang Recca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDF647f8wTC9xYKRRSNQV8CPkQJrc1Y81nFNPZerRiknh_jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Heard raving reviews about this and came to try. Portion is big. So you might want to have a take away container just in case. Noodles and soup were on the bland side. But to make up for it, the lemongrass chicken was kinda salty. Fried squid tentacles were replaced with non tentacles part and it didnt even fill up the plate that was served with, so lowkey felt scammed. Service was ok, just that had to call out a few times to get too up for tea (as the chicken seems to have overdosed on salt) , it is also in a busy complex so it depends the time you arrive to snag a parking spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCYENXaTqEtkYSY2lS33ozYXVgNFIqK7rnSj28&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Hannah DG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU037jR4UWeBkpznNrgaH8CsxofxgLROiN8hrJaQSHBDftuIk7R=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"SPOILED MEAT- DO NOT COME HERE AND RISK GETTING FOOD POISONING.
My boyfriend and I have been loyal to Pho Superbowl for over 2 years since moving to the area. I have also been to their new location on Kingsway. We have tried many different dishes from their House special pho, spicy beef pho, house special with sat√© broth, their rice dishes, vermicelli dishes, chicken wings, salad rolls, and their bahn mi. We have brought our friends and family several times to eat at Pho Superbowl because we loved their food and generous portions.

Today, I ordered #66 grilled pork and spring roll vermicelli which I have had plenty of times before, but for some reason, the grilled pork tasted sour and off, like the meat had already gone bad. I waved down one of the servers to let them know and she was nice enough to offer to change it to a different meat. I picked out all of the spoiled meat into a small bowl which she took back to the kitchen. Then, I heard the head cook angrily yell in the background. Shortly after, a different lady came back with the same bowl with the spoiled pork and said they can't give me a new one because "I already ate it". What do you mean I already ate it? It wasn't like I finished all the food and asked for a new bowl for free! I just took out all of the spoiled pork out of my vermicelli bowl and planned to eat the rest of the food!

I am beyond disappointed especially since we loved coming to eat here and we were always generous with tipping.... but we are not coming back. I understand that restaurants can sometimes have a one-off, and I am usually willing to give another chance. However, since they did not want to fix the issue after I brought it up (especially regarding food safety like spoiled food), Pho Superbowl doesn't deserve another chance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmdrUm8xnjIm9gt1H0Nz5JcPG-4epoJmnZ1RFQ&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-4-28"}]

Venue is not fancy, but everything was solid for a quick bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvcn6yIw2DQtkJaRluT_9hjJOBh6Dz8lZiNwOY&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Jun Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL47AHOHCYDKEAbEAKPJ80TxGYhPvE0xJ8NC0flA2gu-YScsEc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly, it's such a nice place to eat. The people here are very nice too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIQoXlh2Ile21EfKoc7X2bkzU2S_YAR0KQBAh4&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Mia Phung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUahhblwNBiEAwk94mdJWBHUNijQ6eiD0coiuxNtVCY2uF3K0RbzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A clean restaurant with friendly staff and good service. They also offer good prices with many combo options, allowing you to enjoy different items in the same bowl. They are kid friendly as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnSv1CsIFMgGKRQb3GmRJIMypPEKJZ0VkVoXz-&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Connie Ono","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu3GznhECwzkHA0nAaCaXgrK62cXqxAJUyd4pU08WzBpBTTJeG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great menu, lots to choose from.

Spring rolls were crispy and delightful with the fish sauce. The Rice with Pork Grilled Chops had the perfect combination of lemon grass and sesame seeds. Moist and flavourful!  Decent size for your buck as well. My husband got the Seafood with Pho Noodles, and the bowl is pretty big for a regular size. (Plus it's filled to the brim).

The owners were really nice! Great service! Close to our hotel we stayed at.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1eXlq47aU1BKxDH8DB2lg8w_8QaRNjx4ysjMa&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-5-24"},{"Name":"Alice Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSabLEqcemt-2KAauM2vbbDg67dC-dDk8Gyg-Xtd1xlnwMUara=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It was an ok pho place. I wouldn't say it's the best nor the worst. We ordered two pho and a salade roll, the salade roll had hair in it, definitely not pleasant, but they did changed it for us right away. The ingredients weren't fresh, the veggies had black edges. The soup base was ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSd77Sg5MRPM2pPnpzHtp-9ZRd8sdvHJoKJXzx&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Ardalan Audine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIttLHSciNI5QVvmbvKNCuAe1rkdKd0slBlW9_P847CRy5giA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Pho place I've been to in Vancouver. Service is super friendly, food is absolutely amazing and I just love these guys.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4Kd4rYCMLXUx4aDXsApl5YkJhzr-9zqIwDehv&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-5-16"},{"Name":"A T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgNmuu8n6BZgKwXYt3MmpIV8oem7hLJh3eeyvqe5_e1DpzrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I‚Äôve been coming here for years even when it was under old ownership. The new owners have been running Friday discount for quite sometime and we decided to go there as kids had a day off which was a big mistake, as it was busy.  We ordered 2 special chicken pho. Depending on the day you go, you get either boiled chicken or grilled chickenüôÑ. When we received our order, we noticed that it has 2 different broth. One chicken and one beef. On top of that, the noodles weren‚Äôt fully cooked. As a non beef eater, I approached the owner and told her. She assured me that it was chicken. It was when I told her to smell it, then she agreed to change it. This wasn‚Äôt the first time that it has happened. When she brought out the replacement, I noticed that it wasn‚Äôt a whole new order. In fact, it looked like they had drained and rinsed the old noodles and meat and put chicken broth in it. How I knew was that I had already taken a bite out of the chicken. I honestly enjoyed the food here despite of the inconsistency but don‚Äôt think I will be going back. Maybe the owners, shouldn‚Äôt rush and maybe have more helpers in the kitchen to avoid mistakes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy Chiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Ytd6jvLjiUIKjc2DLdidLuwgHbgPUD4GPhFuPOLEoqlZ2vbh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A good, authentic Pho place tucked in a busy and hard to turn into complex. Many come here for the Korean soup, karaoke, or bar, but there‚Äôs a great pho place here called Pho Capital.

They are extremely generous on their portions, and by portions, I don‚Äôt mean they give you a large bowl or extra noodles, but they give you a ton of meat! Regardless of small or large bowls, you‚Äôre going to get a lot of meat. If you‚Äôre not too hungry then a small is more than enough as they give you a huge amount of portion. This is probably the most meat I‚Äôve seen in a pho bowl for a regular bowl of pho.

The food comes out quick, they accept credit cards, and best of all, there‚Äôs 15% off on Fridays!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK6-75GQpmta8oheQv6JKZbt_zMzA2hREfbihy&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-11-19"}]

It is recommended to order before picking up as you will have a slight wait if you walk in and order.

The food has been great each time I ordered. Portion sizes are not bad and the food is always fresh.

Lots of parking available outside and at times they can get busy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Candice C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwFBBjzDK0K147Ahvw56fgZp0Wzk8W8u0zo_aJQ425Hu_MYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Take out restaurant, the place appears clean and tidy. The staff are welcoming and friendly. Had the beef kebob small platter and that was more than enough. Lots of options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOshxNmRcFxtlY7YaQH-8G5BG1zitn4SatKU0Pb&fid=0x0:0xfe535cce35f49e37"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Reza Az","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8VOIYGmudwFgomghjsI628UIOyauu99PTTRqvMp19GbPgNp4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Grab and go Coquitlam is an unforgettable experience! From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm hospitality that made me feel right at home. The ambiance was cozy and authentic, transporting me straight to Iran.
The food was absolutely incredible. Every dish was bursting with rich, authentic flavors, showcasing the true essence of Iranian cuisine.
Whether you‚Äôre familiar with Iranian food or trying it for the first time, I highly recommend Grab and go Coquitlam for an authentic and delicious culinary journey. I‚Äôll definitely be returning soon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Reza Beik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAk5FOTBi4eYl4XJK_pY6EefWdKrL0UdJY6hMoW801u1k_XvKn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I called and ordered 45 minutes before the scheduled pickup time, and the person on the phone assured me that the food would be ready on time. However, for the third time in the last two months, I had to wait an additional 15 to 20 minutes at the restaurant to pick up my order. I understand that they are busy and that it may take longer for orders to be prepared, but when a customer orders ahead, it's because they don't want to wait‚Äîthey want to pick up their order and go.

The restaurant should ensure that they provide customers with an accurate pickup time. If you're busy and the order can't be ready in less than an hour, just let the customer know. But most importantly, make sure that when the customer arrives, the order is ready and properly packed.","Images":null,"When":""}]

On a positive note, she did give us a complimentary dessert‚Äîa slice of cake with a candle‚Äîsince I was celebrating my birthday. Overall, it was a great choice for a dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQMZ8Ffd-cqer3BB8ck4z2tpthF000_2uW65dk&fid=0x0:0x8a834a2eb78c2221"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"John Cantillas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcyiYFg8BGPrNb-kZxFHp3rbTEqWVw5CXGDd2KlPDKQrWr3m8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my wife celebrated our wedding anniversary here at The Keg last night. The complimentary Billy Miner Pie was so freaking good that I want to order another one.

Also, that awesome guy Alex, he is very informative and his service was great. We had an awesome night because he always provide what we need.

To sum up everything, we just had a great experience and definitely going back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMf39Ur7X14QdujZ1BLpm4yOKMxM-heMK5-5tlC&fid=0x0:0x8a834a2eb78c2221"],"When":"2024-7-10"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Keg is our go-to to celebrate special occasion in our lives. French Onion Soup ($14) - I liked this and it was cheesy but it was a bit light with the actual amount of onions in the soup.
10 Oz Prime Rib ($42) - Super thin slice of prime rib. They said they were running out if prime rib and I'm wondering if this was actually 10 oz or if they were just trying to stretch it out so bit.
Brussels Sprouts - One of the better items we had on this day.

My husband can‚Äôt have seafood and the dish had shrimps in it, that‚Äôs how I knew for sure we didn‚Äôt order that dish.
The second dish we didn‚Äôt realize until the end.
The quality of their food was really bad. We went there for all the good reviews and we were super disappointed. Will never return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-wQu4pwQGfRKnSX8sP3y7dUGvJGajvqAJG35E&fid=0x0:0x318b3df216b4a874"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"KA T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaR7ml2dkrIOrwgU_-kQ-HRh1gdXFY-Mwfz5VTGuLsK_EtLSkR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We stopped in here for breakfast as we were staying at the attached Ramada. There was 4 of us (two young kids and two adults). The breakfast itself was ok, nothing special at all. The coffee was really good though. The service was embarrassing. The server walked away without taking one of our orders and seemed almost bothered that we would come in to have breakfast. The prices are definitely not worth the quality of food. When we received the our bill, the prices were higher than what was noted on the menu, so this was quite alarming. They need to update their menu to reflect what they charge because that was really shady. Our bill was over $80 for four simple breakfasts. Save your money and go somewhere else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike Medcalf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1rixyxiw07idcZpYCUo6royGxGKqfnZDSFo9vAAuERRuqgDflAA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing prices. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0E5mjnxKtwgfWXwsftGkVtde8Fcyw_qHRefWm&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a wonderful family dinner at this restaurant! The ambiance is truly lovely, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. The staff went above and beyond, being both accommodating and welcoming throughout our meal. We highly recommend the Baked Chicken Parmesan‚Äîit was absolutely delicious! A great experience all around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMC3AKdGWBqxc-jukm25cD5f_HXE9kVmRakX-oM&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Nathan Ferlan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBBwm7N9m9VsEZe8oXWT3QVjEQHlJhduQ22vfMGOziLtc2Ouo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Culinary Experience to Remember!

‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è

If you‚Äôre looking for a dining experience that leaves you craving more, look no further. I recently had the pleasure of indulging in the most exquisite Pasta & Prawns, and I‚Äôm still savoring every memory of it. Each bite was a masterpiece‚Äîperfectly cooked pasta with tender, flavorful prawns, all bathed in a rich, savory sauce that danced on my palate. The balance of flavors was simply divine, making it one of the best dishes I‚Äôve ever had.

But what truly made the night unforgettable was the outstanding service. From the moment we arrived, the staff made us feel like we were more than just customers‚Äîthey made us feel like family. Our server was down-to-earth, warm, and attentive in a way that made the whole evening feel special. Every request was met with a genuine smile and care that is rare to find.

The ambiance, the incredible food, and the impeccable service all came together to create a perfect dining experience. I had such a great time, and I‚Äôm already counting down the days until my next visit. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6ocpt4jzjfqUqjB2OE7Fa55VrOmI8L5U_KNDR&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pasta Polo is an exceptionally great Italian restaurant that serves quality food. You know the workers take pride in their food and service when they post the restaurant's review articles on the walls.

I ordered the Osso Bucco with the Virgin Purple Sour drink. I was served complimentary bread with my entr√©e that included butter and a bottle of fermented garlic. The bread tasted pretty great on its own while the garlic made it taste much better. The Osso Bucco was delicious with the Bolognese sauce. The side pesto pasta was very good and was well seasoned with parmesan. The non-alcoholic Purple Sour tasted excellent with its exceedingly sweet flavours.

The servers were very formal with their customers when it comes to preparing their tables. They check on me as often as possible during busy hours while maintaining a positive attitude. The establishment was dark yet classy and clean.

I look forward to eating as this restaurant again to try their other entrees.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXlV9QLG73dgmJm2MgWDAp3IaT80Wb7UqKSEgR&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"S Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDCpcHtfixdQ1nlZ-cnjxErMYcSiJY3vif9B2kRQjg0W11mPsG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It‚Äôs been a few months since we were here last. We ordered the chicken Marsala and gnocchi.  Both were delicious!  I love the Marsala sauce!  My husband enjoyed the garlic oil that was served with a bun.  The bun was ok. Could have been tastier.  I enjoy good bread and this wasn‚Äôt anything to write home about.  Service was excellent. We had Thea and she was great!  I also enjoyed their art gallery.  So much talent.  We will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZaMW99B_vyd2v_54Cdz758FoKxJtAP-r08b85&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Y Man","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB62F2-VitrTkpd3TexeBmDt6LJ-Ec6lzQvbbyCIp7HJAIiB3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely Italian restaurant. The carbonara was tasty and creamy,  pasta is fresh and the sauce was enough to cover all the pasta and not drenched in it.  The meatballs were tender and mixed with fresh herbs,  a perfect meat side to the pasta.  The tiramisu was delicious,  creamy melts in your mouth.  Definitely coming back to try other dishes","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdg_N9cATCFpMd2RK_yR7Qj4KSOp6mP1XOgxD7&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Marnie Eudela-Umlas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXg_gVRD_Hd9V3XIUh6_P71KHCryea9xsHYGqrZHTuXW_jdxEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Spent our Mother‚Äôs Day celebration in this restaurant and we had a great time. Pastas were yummy and their desserts too were all a treat. We will surely be back :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbGw58cAzM4X4wXEw-LloHV5v2YTXfNlioydQo&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-7-2"}]

[{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We visited on a weeknight for dinner. There was only us and 1 other table, but the delivery pickups were constant. On a rainy night, I can understand why.

The food is fresh, hot and delicious. Super comforting flavours.

When delivery people arrived without their warming bag, staff would ask them to retrieve it. This ensured the food would stay warm.

I would highly recommend the seasonal specialty, Khao Soi. This was our first time trying it, and I'd definitely order it again. This dish comes with crispy and soft noodles. When you stir it into the sauce, the fried noodles stay crispy, giving you an amazing combination of textures. Beautifully balanced and satisfying dish.

We also enjoyed the crispy wraps, chicken satay and Pa-Nang Curry.

Very relaxing environment, and I'm glad we popped in. Chada Thai is a fantastic local Thai restaurant that has been in the community for many years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgs6Rb5cfnF84J2qgMTdFMob8BlMuzG2vmaGLv&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Tiffany Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTMFXTr99Nvibpsf_X84FJETCu3bBQbDSclTYmi4Zeid_pQeVX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely scrumptious authentic Thai food!!! It is a stable restaurant on our family‚Äôs go-to bi-weekly!! The air in this local mom-n-pops Thai restaurant is always filled with the most delicious-food-heavenly-aroma flowing from the kitchen :)
Top notch service, monthly and seasonal special menu items, always a good surprise, keeping the customers‚Äô dine in and take out experience exciting!
Love it. Will be back again next week!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5i0hMWKO1NoxYJ1hz-r9q_LAgP16LoMW8IBlT&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Kareen Cadiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw3OKuvTnvabIzBQ3y_Jc5m3vIpEHN-6lVpcIUOUmxioiQzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of our go to places for Thai food in Tri-cities, can‚Äôt go wrong with either dine in or takeout. Their lunch specials are such a good deal (pictured here). And of course the food is consistently yummy, fresh ingredients and good portions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-5cRjh_efXpw9-7c5P9WAgZ6JpuWrYyw4MPJE&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Charmaine Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMK-vcbBIxyt_pQwyKQmCk5dMi5qXNyvwWP-HdCaK4MzQ7dCIb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the authentic Thai food here! The Tom yum soup is irresistible. Green curry fragrance is very good that I can finish the bowl of rice. So far this is one of the best Thai cuisine I have in Vancouver. The lunch menu is still very decent in price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTDJde8-gQXH92NluWv3gqrtQt309FXJTYEGFh&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Parichat B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3tpKxJcU4Lx_ecgrcufj6LfbAj_OdEqTtupyTak05ILPS6QkOMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best thai food in town, really yummy authentic dishes in affordable prrice.
All staff was so nice, great in recommendation for a menu and spicy level.
The restaurant is clean and easy to access by walikng from Lincolne station.
I definately go there again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqEm0G5fpF7dbYNyoStcPpYC-5skgUuqbPXtJY&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Aidan Siu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWc1EBOVHC3agFY5CmQn_KE37Zb3iZR8UikBgzoOS_YFnx5fxiO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden Thai Gem in Coquitlam! For a delightful Thai culinary experience, try Beef Pad Thai, a perfect balance of savory and sweet with tender beef, stir-fried rice noodles, and crunchy peanuts. Pineapple Fried Rice with Shrimp is another must-try, offering a vibrant mix of succulent shrimp, sweet pineapple chunks, and fragrant jasmine rice. Finally, savor the rich and aromatic Red Chicken Curry, where tender chicken pieces in a creamy, spicy coconut milk sauce infused with red chili. Each dish is a flavorful journey that will leave your taste buds tingling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuMZvozTcY-cgvXAYiOFiAAv451NQXKZubUuHV&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Dan Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbNeFUlLkRmjcX25zxpAW7H_0IDjY0P_SfdPGvxnigSNv-OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Met up for lunch with a friend and we shared two items-shrimp pad Thai ($15 off the lunch special menu) and chicken yellow curry (the sauce was sooo good)
Portions are generous, food was delicious and the service was terrific.
The food was so good that we both ordered additional menu items togo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDrQcz7So_FgPV4M_TJ8yvUjsUhEaOgy7ohjCm&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my mother-in-law's favourite Thai food whenever she visits from Ottawa. We've been here a few times already, and we all believe the presentation of the food is on point every time.  Their flavour is great as well. We always order the Thai chilli sauce and crispy wraps. Their noodle soup dish was good too, but I forgot its nameüòÖ unfortunately, this dish was a monthly special. I wish it came back though. Hopefully it will :) The only downside of the restaurant is that when we pick up the food, it  isn't as good as eating in at the restaurant. But that's the case for all restaurants so. Still, I would say the best Thai in Coquitlam. Just make sure to get their coconut rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOb87rj0mXOnoCwN0B8gg8gk6BIrvt8yWQgk5EI&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-7"}]

The Pork Hock was amazing and I had to order it twice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkeN1QD0k77gLzuWNTChtSslZ8MsYKszhisKyY&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Ewa Jagla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt2Lx4cSyXVMUtHz5GqW2QX5giQiHT25H1LY2KPyEyH86PMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food freshly cooked from scratch, awesome atmosphere, superb customer service. The best place to have Christmas party as well as small gatherings.
Highly recommend üòä","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhWkgmxDtyb6rEjrVCF6m82pasIw5N0DVS3SmQ&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Angela Jeffery","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtGyld6d4wIU2Lb7oe7xsoiq4r77iaBdF6nkFQ8ek01eF1q7c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ate here as we stayed at the hotel for work, and I may come back to try some of the other menu items, based on the compliments of the others in the group.

The server was pleasant, as well as enthusiastic and knowledgeable about his menu recommendations. He was courteous about checking in and giving us space for our meeting.

The seating was comfortable, and even when it got busy at dinnertime, the ambient noise level still leant to easy conversation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqeLGhHKnP50PS663FCp_-g_jpbS2XjZyg9vTH&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Laura Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJ1taLWiLR5Kqy6TcBzB6ZWgyoj4UBO3ZptGvBaE7P-Aow2HBl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We visited Izba last week and while it's a regular in our family gtg's I'd be remiss if I didn't brag about this terrific PoCo restaurant, with its cosy, modern, diner feel. They have booths and tables and they can easily accomodate large groups.

I am hearing sensitive and I find the noise volume in this restaurant to be perfect for my needs. I can hear my company's conversation, while not being too quiet. It's a great place to eat & catch up with family or friends.

While they have a terrific  breakfast & dinner menu, we usually visit at lunch. While we've tried many delicious items (shout out to their pierogies, schnitzel & cream of carrot soup!) we tend to have our favourites on their menu. Their chicken tacos are a huge hit with our family, although I lean towards their chicken club sandwich myself. Yum!  And for the late in the day breakfast lover amongst us, the brie & berries stuffed french toast is ah-mazing.

This is a great lunch spot with great service and great food. We love this local gem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR6It5KMGfKdXdWFlwEe9CsEMI6164BfCS_2qP&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"K Kunz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJritYkEeakN5S6DMeaooDNRMG4rg18kYdKvuJy7Hp_4TwqoG2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our first time at Izba Bistro and we loved it! Our server Brenda was great! She was nice, attentive but also let us sit for awhile. Food was excellent. We started with the battered brie that came with fruit and a spicy berry compote. I then had the spinach and feta chicken and it was SO good. I loved that it came with spaghetti squash as well. You don't see that too often. My partner had the Vienna schnitzel with an egg on top. My partner being Austrian said it was different than what he's used to, but still enjoyed it. Lastly we had the sacher Austrian chocolate cake and that was also really fantastic! We definitely will be coming back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTHEmdhYUMMgbRx5jBghp47Wwy64aw3PImFw7B&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Varoujan Makdesian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfL2mqaxtwIkiG0HlyGX_xrPtFgM36rEWRUZvaEgqUWz0Duw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"****AVOID AT ALL COSTS****
I was really excited to try Izba, given its reputation for authentic Polish cuisine, but unfortunately, my experience was far from what I had hoped for.

First, the service was extremely slow. Despite the restaurant not being very busy, our server seemed disinterested and hardly checked on us. We had to flag them down multiple times just to get basic things like water refills.

The food, which I was looking forward to the most, was underwhelming. The pierogi were bland, lacking any real flavor or seasoning, and the filling was far too dry. The borscht was greasy and tasted more like something that had been reheated multiple times rather than freshly made. It was also way too salty, which made it hard to finish.

The manager/owner, when I raised my concerns, was dismissive and unhelpful. Rather than apologizing or offering a solution, they seemed indifferent to our experience. It‚Äôs always frustrating when management doesn‚Äôt take feedback seriously, and it only made the situation worse. It felt like they weren‚Äôt interested in improving their service or maintaining customer satisfaction.

Overall, I won‚Äôt be returning. There are plenty of other places offering better Polish food and a much more welcoming dining experience. I would not recommend this place to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tones Jyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKK4GXgTVLnajqhYm0hfamOs6EgRB-CcfZKNyrEZSlfbU3odg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have driven by this place so many times and wanted to try it. Really glad I finally did and you should too! Had the platter for 2 and it came with everything in the picture for 47$ (2 potatoe pancakes that are so crispy and delicious, polish sausage, a huge amount of perogies with lots of chopped bacon and sausage to go with it, 2 large cabbage rolls, salad, and some kind of carrot mango salad) me and my wife both left stuffed and our baby even had his fill too! It was so delicious and you can tell everything is home cooked with care! I highly recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNF0XwsVtW1OfgUUiRRKbghfLTu0ovz1VSWdmvU&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Kat s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2PheeHlSTOrgESZq7PphUL-4YpUmC6odPCrLoBmlFoDLLyzPn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had breakfast almost every day here while on our trip. Service was great, waitstaff was kind and accommodating of food allergies, and the food was always high quality. This will definitely be a spot we continue coming back to whenever we're in PoCo!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKp-lMImM02uuFAI1z4isRNhCXkLkbDt4Yr4Xj&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-7-22"}]

[{"Name":"Melinda Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMsYIuruesNJ4fTjqy4yNevJthJq9c29QqfPxA8x09D9sg2sf9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really happy to see that Lucky Gate is still going strong. Have come here several times with family over the years and it‚Äôs always pretty solid every time we are back. The portions are very generous and they have pretty great pricing for what you get. I recommend the noodles as they are made fresh and although you may not get to see them working on pulling the noodles live anymore (maybe?) they still taste great!

I believe the place is still family run and the service seemed like it could be a bit shorter in staff but our food still came out pretty quickly.

Parking can be a bit tough but there‚Äôs definitely options around if you‚Äôre willing to walk a block down or from across the street.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPnOMGANJo8pzJjrZkT8WZQR_RyL8W6C9TGCb-&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2023-6-23"},{"Name":"Gen Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0x4Eq9GRWvX9EA38H3GMWPqz4gj6UZw48zS61frnmQ0-oj3E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our first time here, nice little restaurant. We arrived just before 6pm on a Friday and there was only 1 other table besides us but was a full house by the time we left. We ordered the Dan dan noodles, Yangzhou fried rice, crispy fried egg rolls, pork & cabbage dumplings and lucky gate home-style steamed pork dumplings. We enjoyed everything except the dan dan noodles, there was no flavour just a peanut sauce. The dumplings and rice were delicious, the rice was light and not greasy at all. The egg rolls came with a plum sauce but not the typical commercial plum sauces you normally get, it seemed like a fresh plum sauce which I liked. Portions were a decent size too for all dishes we ordered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS27P4BQWVnSHMAnwA5wqppr5AdBBJUJsnmZTO&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2023-5-27"},{"Name":"Emmanuel Carino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ9g6OsewbE5PvEJQG0W2MrejjY87xqZcS0O_-lbnLLATuQeGq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lucky Gate Chinese Restaurant is a fantastic spot for anyone craving authentic and delicious Chinese cuisine. The menu offers a wide variety of classic dishes, from flavorful stir-fries to savory dumplings, all made with fresh ingredients and traditional recipes. The portions are generous, and each dish is packed with flavor, making it a great value for the price. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for both casual dining and special occasions. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring a pleasant dining experience. Whether you're dining in or ordering takeout, Lucky Gate Chinese Restaurant delivers consistently excellent food that keeps you coming back for more. Highly recommended for anyone who loves great Chinese food!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fred Knupp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUukGkp9y-x2yZPZA7UpSYDaw9shX_weiqhl3K6mxZFUB86kG1k9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time visiting here and I must say that the portions are pretty big and filling. Came with our relatives and can say that we left with a food coma lol. Food tasted great too.  If you like spicy food, then you should definitely come here as they have a lot of really tasty spicy options.

Decor is rather dated and they could do with some updated furniture and table coverings and interior decorations, but that's about it.

Come here with an empty stomach and you'll be leaving here plump full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5h7HK0Jls9TeWZ_CN7AYJ14359C466YiC59-5&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2023-6-11"},{"Name":"Renee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkzdRYtGC8A0TF24pm1Lc0U46vrj9wBR19gGcg-qACTmqRO0ZbaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lamb. You come here and order their cumin lamb or lamb skewers. Pair it with an order of the hand rolled pancake in Shangdong style and hot and sour soup. Divine. Oh the deep fried fish is pretty good too!

If you enjoy refreshing xiao long bao, as in not heavily flavored with spices, salt and sugar, but just a light fresh soupy dumpling you dunk into black vinegar, this is the place to get it.

Very family style, all their Shangdong dishes hits home! Did I mention their cumin lamb and lamb skewers are amazing?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8DGOkHLaZiX5Rb_9P484kxeoFOQ4L5JCjZoGd&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2023-5-20"},{"Name":"J C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRid-486EHf3vFFlqzxc7hc71kbL9n1FDLFiUelrs10b7uY4If=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The adventure of finding the best hole in the wall resto continues and this unfortunately don‚Äôt measure up.  Maybe we ordered the wrong dishes but there really wasn‚Äôt any flavours outside of salt and pepper.  Don‚Äôt expect service as there usually is only one server.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrW5KZ_mt9LNWaGpNqvIFnX_n0YZbijxm5bgpM&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2023-6-28"},{"Name":"Happy Heart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzxNDbSKqtfYHxkSt0sGCFHw-pDCXZ21NYpof7TRuf3xeLpw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stumbled upon Lucky Gate Chinese restaurant in Coquitlam. Their north eastern Chinese food is very authentic and the dishes are mouth watering. This place has signature fulfilling hot pot with big pieces of meat and handmade dumplings are very delicious. I would recommend this place over and over again for a taste authentic Chinese food. Its warm welcoming environment feels like eating at home. The best Chinese food taste you can find in Coquitlam and Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHYmh_Cm20IKF_lrIOeXVoHZjcgZUCjC9TMKtI&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2019-11-8"},{"Name":"connie leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWI_fB6SeIS1ikGv2RhsDMCQCtWDrdYAq-3-mCPCW07YzB6KIPIbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food was not bad. The skin of the siu long bao was pretty thin which was good. But the meat was on the bland side. And so was the green onion pancake, it looks perfect but they forgot to put salt or any taste in it. But the price of the dim sum is quite reasonable. The pan fried rice cake was bland too. The salty soy milk and lamb skewers was the two items that was really good and tasty. But the waitress do not speak English, but u can order by the number of the items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuOVzgHTJrYiKk0_2O0njg7EIEQZMrBkdq_Zks&fid=0x0:0xaccdb034586d1c2"],"When":"2021-11-28"}]

[{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here with the fam for Father's day.
1st time trying Philippine cuisine and what an exceptional experience. Kind and attentive staff and most importantly the food was incredible. This was actually one of my favorite dining experience.
Food was exceptional! Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMU95rTTAV0BK_cbFii3d-jihpq23PAOpy9xa0y&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Julie Yan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfTkMTfEdPNgUhYXY4I0LrmLHMmd9enIo7z2jv5BbsNTul6Qf7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and friendly staff. The Vegetable Kare Kare is divine and get some rice with that. The BBQ pork ribs were an easy runner-up, charred in the best way. Definitely a healthier option if you‚Äôre eating out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCb3iU50OU-tLuL6jf7CVMEQ2_QnwtSdpzDiR5&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"LSP LSP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4u7ZczctbKDKn8CXvFXOwDtsUnW_BDkhdSdynFH0H1WLLxvs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For someone who cannot cook or even attempt to cook Filipino food but still misses eating good home cooked meal this place is a "God of Happy Tummies" sent. I visited the Coquitlam branch of Kulinarya. They don't skimp on food portions or presentation for to go orders. I have tried many Filipino restaurants in lower mainland but we always leave disappointed or underwhelmed. The food tasted freshly cooked, homey and quite nostalgic and there's no feeling of "Tirang ulam" from the previous day like most Filipino restaurants we have tried. I highly recommend this place. Worth the price and the team who works at the front are friendly as well. Will return again for more happy tummy days.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMk6DJZJCSJedM8CG8N-34GOqp-B3UnV0nhJJu7&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a Filipino residing in Coquitlam, I‚Äôm delighted to have this place so conveniently nearby. My partner and I continue to favor the sisig, and we love the store‚Äôs ambiance, which wonderfully showcases Filipino culture.

UPDATE: We recently dined in to savor the experience, and it genuinely felt like home with its authentic Filipino atmosphere. The adobo served in a wok was a highlight, and we also loved the lumpiang shanghai. Although they removed the canton from the menu (which was my favorite), my partner tried the bihon and found it delicious. We‚Äôre still loving it here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCb7sUWiebYL7XEM_jEOXkmRJ2oLf7OB8OBjAP&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Mav Bayer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7pHDDvwX22QLIg_Qg1Pd0y5ez5B3UjogKyDHPkds6Co5966k=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently ordered the pancit canton platter from Kulinarya  Coquitlam for a party, and I was quite disappointed. The menu indicated it would include a mix of chicken, shrimp, and veggies, but there was no chicken in the dish at all. The topping only had about 6-8 medium-sized shrimp, which felt inadequate for the price. Overall, it didn‚Äôt live up to our expectations, and I don‚Äôt feel it was worth what we paid. I hope they can improve their portions and accuracy in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjJR7sTInjkmRWeZrEMluZvnGV1z71iHTrtvKb&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"8T8","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaHAe29LTwj-kDB4Rxp2LPyCtNn-xUw5U4xwT2905ny-JNkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You'll be happy!  Each dish prepared with much attention and care.  Had a wonderful dining experience.  The place is small and just perfect, gives them more opportunity to pay close attention to you.  They'll come over and ask you how your meal was, very hospitable and beautiful atmosphere.   A definite great experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWFkcyhOUeQnxgY1JQAY3t3VydDgxTDn9_oz2O&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2023-6-26"},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great meal and experience here, a hidden gem I didn‚Äôt realize was 15 mins from my house, will definitely be back. Came by recommendation of my Filipino friends so I already expected it to be good and it didn‚Äôt disappoint. I had the Manok sa Gata with Garlic Rice upgrade and it was absolutely delicious üòã. Finished off with my favourite Halo-halo and it was fantastic as well. Cozy old school style family restaurant vibes with great service. Plenty of free parking outside in the plaza and directly in front of the restaurant as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM3Zt6AMTJSHSA1TqVXRm03Np3YoxVKdfPoUq4&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This appears to be the only place serving Filipino food in downtown Coquitlam. I started my meal by trying Talong Salad for the first time, it was amazing! The grilled eggplant added a meaty texture to the raw pineapple, tomato, and onions. The grilled squid was good too, but hindsight I should have ordered something else as the flavours overlapped with the salad. Their house-made vinegar is probably one of the best condiments ever, it will go well with pretty much anything. Halo-halo is super sweet and refreshing. The restaurant is fairly small and the tables are closely placed, making space quite tight.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0cQnjf8fh_fY4nULnWtnvDlSWVvnao3F1-E1P&fid=0x0:0xad7ac43de48b0ec0"],"When":"2024-3-27"}]

They even gave us an on the house appetizerü•π so sweet","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOV91eWDjKKY1SgnCnMR4z3HVoODoxI60aU2tZD&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Really had high hopes for this place but left feeling a bit disappointed. We arrived around 8:45 PM, and the service was quite slow, taking 25 minutes to get our meals.

The takoyaki was served cold, and our appetizers arrived after the main courses. On the bright side, the sizzling beef and chicken teriyaki, tuna and salmon sashimi, and California roll were all delicious. Unfortunately, we never received our full order as the rice and ice cream never came.

Given the high prices and the incomplete order, it was a letdown despite the quality of the food. Hoping they can improve their service because the food itself has great potential.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG6r9BYhd4HoE6LklkdFF6nNhF-MRr2p-wh2Ft&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Dessi Vali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLbnNa8FC81KTFWEURLNTbG0_BnJUUgdBXPsBEM8zfX8u28A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything about this sushi restaurant is just amazing. From the moment you walk in, you're greeted with a warm smile and friendly staff. The chef's skills are out of this world, creating beautifully presented and delicious sushi rolls. He even has made his own special rolls on the menu. Pae is number 1. And let's not forget about the manager who ensures that everything runs smoothly. It's clear that they truly care about providing an exceptional dining experience! üç£üòÑ absolute favourite spot in BC!!! ‚ù§Ô∏è They have private rooms and they provide customer comfort and satisfaction. I would recommend everything on their menu but their moody fever is to die forüòç","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNO0ZO6M0KnoILEwOj-eDWjbf1TTC7dgghD8Fnh&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-1-26"},{"Name":"Brianna Zavala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIf9OdjmIMd3AWmzZ5YjwB3w5wYRGHZIefs8YIoz5D0NWTe24c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve been going to Nagano since I was 16 and a friend introduced me to the restaurant, the atmosphere has never changed in the 7 years I have been there. The service is always friendly, welcoming, and efficient! The manager Susie is absolutely lovely and is amazing at recommendations! Every time my boyfriend and I come here we always have the freshest seafood, and the most attentive service from the staff members. I couldn‚Äôt recommend them more! I always bring all my family members and friends here, it‚Äôs a personal favourite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAhFR5DgPCNAsm5HNOZpFWkDu0W6IpFtmG5Z5y&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Sarah Hunter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVyE789GJWN_zr7DV0XfjroxqIDs6F_d6oaWdcqc-O4m-SHiM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"By far the best food I‚Äôve had!  What  an experience sitting at the sushi bar.  Pai,  the owner and chef is amazing.  He makes it an event.  All the staff is top notch.  There‚Äôs something to be said about a place that has been here so many years and keeps their  staff happy .  Will be coming back again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Mak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ7vrBokgq5LSIpG2NE2vKzOyvms_kUiL7U4mZHpmIqLf-ArufGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last night, we had the pleasure of dining at Nagano Japanese for the first time. The restaurant offers a traditional North American Japanese menu with no fusion or modernized dishes, nor any super high-end options. However, the craftsmanship of the food, its presentation, and the exceptionally friendly atmosphere make Nagano Japanese stand out.

Our meal consisted of several small dishes that we shared, all of which were expertly prepared with fresh ingredients. The raw seafood, including uni, salmon, toro, fish roes, and tuna, was especially delicious and fresh. But it was the cooked dishes that really impressed us. The fried softshell crab had a thin, crispy batter, yet the crab itself was still tender and juicy. The fried salmon cheeks were also fantastic, with succulent, tender meat clinging to the jaw bones. And the grilled mackerel was cooked to perfection, with crispy, thin skin that was perfectly browned and charred.

However, what really made the dining experience memorable was the friendly hospitality of the owner or manager, Susie. She was patient, accommodating, and genuinely made us feel welcome. She made everything great with her personal touches on customer interactions.

It's unfortunate that there have been several negative reviews lately, perhaps due to a shortage of qualified staff or an increase in takeout orders. Nonetheless, some of the best dishes we had could only be appreciated when freshly cooked and served straight from the kitchen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgmliG0wkzCCsfYn85x-UYasSgQBkHZy1LkHwG&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2023-3-19"},{"Name":"Mina A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUa3Ot95qqtO1ooc2Pz-iCEqTxvgYh82KnLf13it1wz8uNx1lvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was the second time we ate here. First time was in 2018 or 2019. My partner didn‚Äôt want to come back because he insisted the food wasn‚Äôt great the last time we were here. I convinced him that every place deserves a second chance, especially after so long! Upon arrival, we were told to seat anywhere we wanted outside as we wanted to be out on the patio. We chose a table far from the other couple that were already eating on the patio (this table wasn‚Äôt quite clean and was a bit slanted). A few minutes later the server came with the menus and moved us to another table that was ‚Äúlevel‚Äù. But this table was not clean either and there were no chairs, so I had to grab my own chair to help the server out. She wiped down the table after we were seated, so 2 dirty tables even though the restaurant was not that busy. There was a sour smell in the patio the moment we sat down (my partner thought it could be dog pee?). No soap in the men‚Äôs washroom. Strong urine smell in the women‚Äôs bathroom. We ordered 4 items. The crispy shrimp appetizer with salad and sweet chilli sauce was delicious but would have been better if the sauce was served on the side in case someone doesn‚Äôt love the dressing. Gomae wasn‚Äôt crisp/fresh. Considering the higher prices on the menu compared to other Japanese restaurants in the city, we had higher expectations. For the mains, we got the sizzling scallop and the black cod. The dishes didn‚Äôt arrive together. The sizzling scallops were not really ‚Äúsizzling‚Äù. There were 2 scallops with some mushrooms and vermicelli on a shell over a candle. It tasted good but the portion was small and it wasn‚Äôt that special for me to want to try it again. The black cod was charred in some areas and the portion was also small for the price, didn‚Äôt come with any sides either but at least it tasted good. The sever never came to check on our food or if we needed anything else, only came once to refill the water/tea, and once more, about 5 minutes after we had finished our food to clean the table and bring the bill. She was very nice though. If I only were to rate the food, considering that it was not exceptional and it was pricy, I would conclude that it‚Äôs a 4/5. But considering everything else, I have to deduct a point (I wish I could deduct half points, in which case I would have rated it 3.5/5, but because google maps only does full points, and I just can‚Äôt see this place as a 4, then it gets a 3/5). Overall, we are still not impressed , maybe even disappointed a little, and will not be returning. Thank you for having us though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHe6tz4z7F8SQgqo6zMn7pmnL65n6Rp0VzItOq&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2023-5-21"}]

[{"Name":"Meghan Atkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpn_HJKLz67oWun2TqZ53LpPOuwDcgytLe9I7rJRW9gkR5zUDI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered take out tonight from Dinakis (through skip the dishes). Ordered my regular Greek dish, the chicken souvlaki. I often order from another restaurant but thought I would give Dinakis a try. Upon eating my chicken souvlaki skewer, I noticed the taste and texture of the chicken seemed off. To my surprise the chicken was raw in the middle. The restaurant was immediately called to inform them. They stated that we needed to contact skip for a refund (which is fine!) and said the chicken was raw due to how busy the restaurant was tonight. Unfortunately, I do not see this as a valid reason for serving undercooked meat. They offered to remake the meal and have me come and pick it up. Unfortunately with a baby in bed, leaving the house is not option which is why I ordered in.

I‚Äôll no longer be order from Dinakis. Perhaps if the situation had been dealt with differently on their end I would. However, it‚Äôs all left a bad taste in my mouth - no pun intended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPamzWqtMSJD_2lXqeftQ04VTeQ-qet20_AUo7c&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Queenie Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZJZmSpZQRAFF9t6SoJ29KP7hdKen-l5gR8pgpgRf7-1s6aED9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here for my dad's birthday. Service was excellent! Food was great - the roast lamb, chicken marsala, and moussaka were all amazing, especially the lamb! The only exception was the steak, which was over cooked and full of gristle. To make up for it, they offered us a tiramisu cake which worked out well and was tasty too. Would definitely come back for the lamb and try other items too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUkbQOcVFipathRk-dHPJeXSBTX5g93Ke5HcNA&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Jessica Tite","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDIMc556UvdeCdK2q0SIDelAc_HJzjyapBYqP0A0CPBdyeWUex=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best Mediterranean food I've had! It's no wonder they have so many awards/accolades at the entrance way.
The food is incredible: well priced, fresh and great portions.
The restaurant is neat and clean, including the washrooms. It has a very cozy feel inside.
Service was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2zKnmJCNiyvvJJiFSndVY5qI8Go-Dp0HU1Vdj&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"Al So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLumQHIv-5W9wXPr4ZbA1zWCVnPk2w1Kc3bjsO93-VMG-v7JQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you‚Äôre in the Shaughnessy area in Poco and craving some Mediterranean magic, look no further than Dinakis Mediterranean Grill. Let me just say, the portions here are generously sized, so come prepared to feast!

The tzatziki is a standout‚Äînice and fresh, with a flavor that‚Äôll make your taste buds do a happy dance. It's the perfect companion to their delicious offerings.

Speaking of which, the Souvlaki Combo is a real treat. It comes with beef, chicken, and prawn souvlaki, each one cooked to perfection. The beef is tender, the chicken is juicy, and the prawns are succulent. It's a delightful trio that hits all the right notes.

We also tried the roast lamb, which was cooked to perfection. It wasn't fatty, and the meat just came off the bone. We thoroughly enjoyed it.

For those dining with little ones, you'll be pleased to know they offer kids' portions. These come with one skewer instead of two at a reduced price, making it great value. It‚Äôs the perfect way to keep the kids happy without breaking the bank.

Overall, Dinakis Mediterranean Grill is a great spot for hearty portions, fresh flavors, and good value. Make sure to bring your appetite‚Äîyou won‚Äôt be disappointed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi-Vmmgslvmp-CsAb30_lQnluDK_dEqTU341G1&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Patrick Laplante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEQ6rmzYgqU18BgeUeFbN3j9UzTXOfNOAqOLvy-TwFRIxBth-Q7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Firstly, the service and the staff are absolutely fantastic. Secondly, the food quality is great, it's really great value, huge portions, and always fresh. And thirdly, great drink selection, and I was happy to hear that they can accommodate large parties as well. Whether for a cute date, family dinner, birthday celebration or quick lunch, I'd highly recommend!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGEpDRCp2o6wFFn9ZB0lPz_oE8b1ckSu6JjaQG&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-1-8"},{"Name":"Julian Sara Joseph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWofxVvuCZOl3BWxzMUTJPVosg-yW0WoAuPTsW6aFO5_K2yZycmSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Greek food here was truly authentic and tasty. Souvlaki of all varieties was great. We had come back from a trek and all our tiredness was gone with the kind servers and their affordable but yummy food ‚ù§Ô∏ètheir portion sizes are quite large so it is filing. Loved the presentation too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJvrpsBh0Cgol4Hr9mDBGY6_JEDFnb7KJHbIEJ&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2023-4-4"},{"Name":"Cheryl G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQZ5krFYmB32nSSVZRn_5-zzzmWzMyLr7fQFLOSOH_4NttzFie=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall good experience. We had regular entrees but also ordered happy hour appetizers, portions was a little small. I also found that an automatic 18% gratituity was surprising for 7 people dining. But we enjoyed the food with our dining guests and I would recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thom Slater","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNyquzT0Ty5ga2cGbYXqVQ4Zp1mr8dSG4EejGqH4R5Eqad_PSB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came in for an extended family dinner. Really generous portion sizes, the lamp chops were fantastic.
Other than the great food, what really made this a 5 star experience was the incredible service from Mariah.
She took our 12 person reservation last minute despite being solo, had such great energy the whole night, and really made it an enjoyable time for everyone. We'd come back just for her.","Images":null,"When":""}]
