[{"Name":"Marissa McKinnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBtcJLgdPMQpgMt2XQrlMeQ9B_SDnMecxrkflkfI6-e9ON270=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"sucks that there are such mixed reviews!!! i had the salt and pepper wings with a side of hot sauce and they absolutely hit the spot. the wings were crispy but not too breaded and had lots of meat on them!! tasted so delicious as well as the fries (u might think how can fries be bad) but i have very high fry standards and these were crispy, hot fresh and delicious‚Ä¶not too salty!! They had a delicious garlic dipping sauce that paired perfectly i definitely recommend trying these out!! The space is so gorgeous. It is quite a fancy atmosphere which was a little unexpected for the location, i‚Äôd love to come back for drinks as well!! The server was very kind and accommodating :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3lN4DT_Iycz4TIRz_nUw4Y8sS2jJWKbtd1FJy&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"tru klass","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJULljo2CZpIBgCzW01ZQWqWOBp8nxIDLyMxp6UUoq4toUJ6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My mum and I had lunch there on Saturday and everything was perfect. The drinks were delicious, and so were our meals. I had the prawn power bowl and it was so well balanced and I'd definitely recommend. The service was also great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlyjqXTgBKhX_ls-QU-rYod3bwan86mGUNs6eh&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Grace B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYzRmU5pRggounfGFdNhaCgFB1i2Hk7bErahU4qwNuN7tYIZyf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had read good reviews but this was a disappointing and mediocre experience. Hostess was lovely and the server was trying but had no idea about the food or drink and couldn‚Äôt answer any basic questions and didn‚Äôt really seem to be trained at all. If craft beer is on the menu either have the details on a board or train your servers to know a bit about your beer and wines.

My heritage is Portuguese and I cannot see how this is in any way Portuguese influenced food. Chicken was clearly reheated with sauce poured over it, grilled veggies and mashed potatoes were ok.  Chicken was extremely dry and rubbery. Arrived way too quickly to be fresh.  We only had two mains;a chicken bowl and grilled chicken meal.  Weren‚Äôt compelled to try anything else. Underwhelming. Prices ok but quality not there. Not a good value.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_28xVzDr6ampMPh-VrxFTVBo9NkMFOOXoOsxE&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Andrew J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVmNa6jisgEJLsGMynHFW0Nb2To-ki1W8gv-mWfe16waRH8-6p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not bad! Enjoyed the atmosphere & service here immensely. Food is fine. Wish it was a bit more impressive for thr price. Don't bother with the cesar salad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjAwxz4vmvDkzHTbjJ79xAPH5Hv2gweELvkjqP&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Health food deluxe! I stopped by to grab a quick bite, and I was impressed by its ambience. I had the prawn power bowl, and it was delicious and extremely healthy. The flavour of the fresh vegetables and quinoa is very well balanced by the creamy sauce and shrimp. I'm just not sure how Portuguese it is though. Overall a delightful experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9dwa8kkM4BNbDBwDwSuoJTW9Xh-nRrWgwOaX&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Adam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvBO_gAscD4jQgf7WwLgwSNvcd9hd0WZ5uykstCAcxi1lOdl4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! I was so surprised that the quality and portion size were spot on the for the price. the food was very tasty and I was happy with everything we got.

The restaurant is also extremely well decorated and comfortable.  They do play music but at a volume that is easy to still have a conversation.

The staff were very friendly and helpful. They had a good knowledge of what they were second and what went into it. Also the different courses are well spaced and seem to appear at just the right time.

I will definitely be going back soon and would recommend to friends and family without hesitation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfbzsmuipmh58Tlxh-nSzNEZH3rRQbrO-pzxRa&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2021-7-31"},{"Name":"Adele Watson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLmg9O9eJVdKcgQE9EcLI7KacahS0x1nMw1eZrnJFYsRp_QwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant was dead, only 2 groups of 4 people. The server did not come to greet us. 15 mins goes by and I had to flag her over. After the food was served she didn‚Äôt come by to see how everything was. Again we had to flag her down to get the bill. They did surprise me with a piece of cheese cake saying Happy Mother‚Äôs Day. To which I was surprised. That was nice! I think if the staff was more tentative and had more training it could be a better place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6paIURZCtNemTEJJFNJXiMLROrf43REDF9D_Y&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW45IYuhuQceepraBGwk75o-s6TtuC_5_eWJedl6juhh8_2uy_gyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent value! Good food, big portions, attentive service, good drinks and craft beers. There is what looks like a lounge side that is visible from outside and a restaurant side with huge booths that is hidden, so even though it looks empty there may be people sitting in the restaurant side, they should probably be sitting people in the lounge instead as nobody likes going into an empty restaurant and I think seeing people inside would cause more people to come in. So even if it looks empty go in and try it.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Don‚Äôt come if you can‚Äôt eat spicy at all.
I ordered Beef tartar bibimbap, seafood on rice. Both of them comes with a red sauce, claimed to be non-spicy, but they are actually a little-little spicy.

The beef in Beef tartar bibimbap has some tendon (?) in it, not as soft as I think, so you need to chew a bit more than just swallow it.

Seafood on rice, even added the red sauce, is kinda bland. The rice is a pretty wet/sticky.

Fried oyster & fries only have 5 pieces of oysters.

The server is kind and nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD199c5zDxdMM7Ds_dRLkXLpgJnCeuNirilncm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFSCt_t74XiqlEdz6jDYOHmtwc4pgb3Fve6nsF3wEBwwz9hl0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was my first time dining at this restaurant after a strong recommendation from friends who live in the neighbourhood. The experience and food did not disappoint! We held a birthday party for 13 people, which was tricky for the layout of the tables. However, the staff were beyond accommodating and made it work. They could have used a few more servers on a busy Saturday night, but the staff were very friendly and immediately responsive whenever we asked.

We ordered a variety of dishes, including the seafood hot pot, fishcake soup and fried fish. Amazing flavours and textures, with generous portions that are ample for sharing! The fried items were light & crispy. The steaming umami soups had just the right amount of spicy kick. You won't find traditional bibimbap, japchae or pancakes because their menu heavily features innovative takes on fresh seafood - not for those with shellfish allergies! Plenty of Korean spirits to test out & quench your thirst! At first glance the prices seem high but considering that the plates can be shared, the restaurant offers great value. Will definitely be returning to try the other menu items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7rbCmBk0xQzNEDNpQI0kMl_DuMnV3myDZBA-X&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Hyebin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjDtbZAwmClVNZWe8in7iKPeuWFpJk3xV63n3oUYqAkU_8FufJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had seafood ttukbaegi and clam bibimbap a few weeks ago. It was a good combination with the soup and the bibimbap. Not that spicy and had perfect level of spiciness for both.
The restaurant was cozy with booths and looked good for having meal + drinking.
The service was also good. I enjoyed their tea comes with a tea pot. I will definitely visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAW_pwiNbZD2uo1clqF1wwWNE4bFs3c-7MXZAm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Kwang s Koo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFo3VGQh4dEQHrPSivYNI5XIEy1BykoaCVmEDpxsBAeHTAFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"From entering to getting our food‚Ä¶was about 1 hour‚Ä¶

The small seafood hotpot‚Ä¶was 90% clams and mussels‚Ä¶maybe 3-4 prawns couple of abalone and a few other things‚Ä¶I do wish there was less clams and mussels‚Ä¶and has some kind of fish‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzs80B65n9dqKlhGLZj9jkiEpWUFk5mHNnEtfR&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Toshiyuki Enzo Shirosaki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD_24CqvwnpZ272t1lMbFqdPq5Yicn0-6hmHLPLDbUePqw_ASerw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had dinner at a Korean resto bambad the seafood plate was a huge portion for us four people. I like their beef tartare, very soft and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTthRBMCpezgjbQIAqo9FQZcioh045Rh5XizB7&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came away from the restaurant with a great first impression. The food was solid, especially for the price, and the customer service was decent.

I highly recommend that you get their signature steamed seafood pot. We got a small and it was enough for the family of four. They really pack in a ton of high quality seafood in the small pot. The broth at the end is almost like a bonus and it's absolutely killer if you pair it with a shot of soju.

We also got the Korean beef tartar and they give a lot of extra things to eat with the beef like wasabi, and seaweed.

I will definitely be coming back with a designated driver next time so that I can drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_ntt397jhPBf8nD0ABEKZBcIgPksxdsnfOV5G&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"Estairia Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmDLygqZ3OT1WagVoz_S7MOF1DNcLc8uEquGumaFc59ZLDHz6l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved the whole experience here. Service was great. The food though! I love that they have whole octopus on the menu but small complaint for me is that it wasn‚Äôt cooked long enough for the meat to soften. Even cutting the octopus with the scissors was a bit challenging. But everything we ordered was delish! I def would love to come back here but it‚Äôs far from where I live otherwise I would be a regular here (I think) cuz I loveeeee seafood especially octopus and squid and shell fish! And especially having it cooked with Korean flavours!  Yummmmm!! Oh also the kimchi wasn‚Äôt to my liking it tasted too sour/vinegary almost like they purposely made it to cater more to a western food palette.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqfPJtcPGlVRy_w0dsc2HvQy07vmLEXoiyOdZu&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-5-3"}]

They serve Halal & tasty food freshly made. Pricing is worth the taste although it‚Äôs a little costly. The staff is very friendly, well dressed & professional. For $24, you get just four small pieces of kebab with a piece of bread and a small portion of salad. While the flavor isn‚Äôt really enjoyable, the size doesn‚Äôt seem to justify the high price. It‚Äôs hard to feel like you‚Äôre getting good value here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuEpoHRbRsmSPF6tjM2X1imV1Dd4XPOMwsfFfA&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Lahoucine Zaama","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr0NtHkkklLaFXzATLKk0BHNbNwdaRCjZkySrZiKWfhiMXxk7V=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Aria Afghan Grill, and it was a wonderful experience! From the moment I walked in, the staff welcomed me with warm smiles, and the cozy Afghan-inspired decor made the place feel very inviting.

I ordered the famous "Qabili Palau," and it was absolutely delicious. The basmati rice with raisins and carrots was perfectly cooked, and the meat was tender and full of flavor. I also tried the grilled kebab, which was soft and had a great taste ‚Äì one of the best kebabs I've had!

The service was excellent. The staff made sure I was comfortable throughout my meal and were happy to answer any questions I had about the dishes.

The prices were reasonable, especially for the quality of food and service. Overall, it was a fantastic experience, and I highly recommend Aria Afghan Grill to anyone looking for a cozy place with authentic and tasty Afghan food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdMOTr-0WNYxsRbn7JBt2KMoxhKV64ivr7n9cZ&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Veronica Belle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6pFvHRP0mjMqe62e_f_QKYo-a3lm9h9SR8Vn0pi8n-fCD4bJS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food blew me away üò≠ü´∂üèΩ we had the Mantu to start ‚Äî amazing üò≠.
The chicken kebab and Qabeli rice as a main ‚Äî when I tell you that chicken was melt in your mouth good, I am NOT kidding. It was amazing. üò≠ And last, we had the Sheer Yakh. I cannot say enough good things, the food was amazing. Wait time was great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX4fEVdgLRjoMbDPi5oFFnYDLQy1nRjNbyp9Aw&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"suki kuramoto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjVxKokdh92B4IkfWX1wqB7Z5fz7cqqwhltPqBJs0g8q3DBg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a really great experience at Aria this weekend. We dropped in for an early dinner while we were in the area. We quickly noticed it wasn‚Äôt a very casual dining spot, but even so, the prices were entirely reasonable for the quality and quantity of food.

We shared a plate of mantu -  the best mantu I‚Äôve ever had probably. Deliciously seasoned, and served with chutney and a spicy sauce. Every bite was incredibly satisfying. The entrees were just as good. The lamb fell off the bone, and the ground beef kebobs were succulent and perfectly seasoned. The side of vegetables transformed each bite. Get the fresh lemon juice in their drinks menu - it‚Äôs absolutely refreshing.

Service was friendly and efficient. Overall, great dinner! We would be happy to dine there again if we‚Äôre in the neighbourhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipML56otr3CAj-dfyYUxqu1RAKCZKNxVd8hnsrlw&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Kasra Rayani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdIiPWSpcAx9BqVRsEdkAGO9Cua53EaxS6lGtlui6McfZz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went to Aria for the first time, and it was incredible. We had the Mantu, the Naan and the Chopan & Chicken Kebab. The live music was a nice touch. Couldn‚Äôt recommend any higher. Must try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnuyZJJpyl5U7G007CDTIf1VI9kHnUK2Zq-Ko&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Neena Siddiqui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL2pdLyW6VB_yGefegDLXCVkOee4Wto0dJjoFFQijHYz6Xqwg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a lunch at this wonderful restaurant and ordered a roll, chicken Kebab with Kabuli plao, mutton kebab with Naan , Mantu with minced beef and fresh dough. We had the best mantu and kabuli plao of our lives. Simply delicious. Dough was also very refreshing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-x2oDXqWoxrSS2xUCofBeNvtNT2LbYtmuSNsO&fid=0x0:0x453913a4dd6ab0c8"],"When":"2024-7-6"}]

[{"Name":"Goody Cambay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzukNWpr2_Cfsgh7ImX_QEvrvAvvbQ9OIWPLf3WTSrPOFO6uhX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down for all you can eat restaurant!

So much food to choose from.  The fridge display is full of food on every shelves.

Love the hot pot.

We went here twice in a week.  We are from Toronto and my 1st time at Happy Lamb is in Vancouver Area.  I would say I can recommend to those people love to cook and eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZnkvj-kldovK5udWZxjr3U9A1qLPaeecBBF4p&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All you can eat $31 for adult and $19 for 12 and under or senior.  Enough variety to choose from and soup base is $12.  Must eat: egg roll, chicken wings and black sesame ball.
Seafood: crab, prawns
Good for party and they have a vip room for 10 people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFHtUxWmb4x4zLfWk985sSSGVsZ8-Ixo8TXZVt&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Edgar Ignacio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7oexz4qXoBKr6ujKuYxwMvlf16ckv-ovFMKFmC4nzUqeMSoelFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Happy Lamb Hot Pot offers an incredible dining experience, especially with their lunch specials on weekdays for just $20.99. This price is unbeatable, particularly given the generous offerings that come with it, including free soda drinks and a variety of delightful side dishes like chicken wings, spring rolls, sesame ball treats, and chow mein. The restaurant is well ventilated and fresh air is pump inside the establishment making your experience even better and not smelling like food when youre done dining.

The hot pot itself is a highlight, featuring a wide array of fresh ingredients. Diners can choose from an assortment of meats, seafood, and vegetables to customize their meal. The variety is impressive, allowing you to create a unique flavor profile with every bite.

When it comes to the soups, Happy Lamb Hot Pot excels with their selection. From a rich and savory spicy broth to a soothing herbal option, each soup base adds a distinct character to your meal. The balance of flavors makes every dip in the hot pot a delightful experience, enhancing the taste of the fresh ingredients.

The value for your money is exceptional, considering the quality and quantity of food you receive. With outstanding service‚Äîwhere your drinks are refilled promptly‚Äîand the unique touch of an automated robot server delivering your order, it all contributes to an enjoyable dining atmosphere.

Happy Lamb Hot Pot is renowned for its delicious hot pots and efficient service, making it a must-visit for anyone looking to indulge in a hearty meal. I highly recommend it to everyone, whether you‚Äôre a hot pot novice or a seasoned enthusiast!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtxiQCWygwU-yA4b3UYDg0tzGjNISXjzMUzvUK&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Audrey T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVt7NSeCmrDxjN6eGFiHdOku-giePvd1JuUbLyAEp6odBtHY6vv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing all you can eat hot pot! You choose a soup base and then you can go off and grab all the food you would like. Great assortment of veggies, meat, noodles, fish balls, seafood, etc. The sauce bar is also stocked with peanut sauce, satay sauce, soy sauce, garlic, green onion, cilantro, etc. Unlimited pop is also included. You have to ask the servers for beef and lamb, but the robot is nice and quick. Ice cream at the end of the meal is a must!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmYRn5iZrv9XQsnYw5UBD7gz7eu2xSo-K9GYOB&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Anthony Plaxen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0TosyGAQWTqM_XvTHaXfq2jDGHv6ifKWBgTGcJKYnap3ceipL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great all you can eat menu here at Happy Lamb in Coquitlam. The selection is quite good at this location. Similar to Bigway, there are plenty of options to choose from for the AYCE Hotpot.

Really thoroughly enjoyed the options, including the crab fritters, shrimp roll and the fried section that included chicken wings and spring rolls. Good broth, meat portions are quite large especially the lamb hotpot slices. Excellent price as well, about 30$ per person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNcjZMK2sZPlpyt8pBCl-Uscvj_Ckz6lMrOkZ-&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Sandra Karr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL5AzV3Z5b5TpIqru3lQ2mf2Zz8cTMw8eMxpISWnoQBkQb2Xpg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good AYCE spot (drinks included) unlike their Burnaby location. The servers are friendly (except Kevin, who can be rude) and there‚Äôs also a cute robot that brings food to the table. We chose two spicy soup bases and they were both excellent! I also enjoyed the overall atmosphere of the restaurant. Their service used to be a lot better, but I guess it‚Äôs more crowded now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOB7C1c1B5BUHJB62BX3ApYEmYn1cBPU_DgqjnU&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2023-12-18"},{"Name":"Aimi San Felix","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuaz_nAesiVaBCEvPNDgiT8Hi9tbV_Lq9ORK-eYU4UPo26WalVUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my family had our tummies full. The atmosphere is spacious and welcoming, and even though we had to wait briefly, it was only about 5 minutes, which was very acceptable. The service was excellent, with the staff bringing out kids' utensils right away, which we appreciated.

The highlight of the meal was definitely the noodle soup. The broth was creamy with a distinct bonito fish flavor, making it a unique take on our ramen. We've never experienced a creamy base with shoyu before, so it was quite interesting.

Their Gomae was quite tasty. Instead of using spinach and peanut sauce, they used Choy Sum with sesame paste sauce.

The only minor drawback was the soft-boiled egg, which was slightly overcooked.

Overall, the service was up to par and we had a great experience. We'll definitely be back to try more of their dishes!" the family was delightful! The atmosphere is spacious and welcoming, and even though we had to wait briefly, it was only about 5 minutes, which was very acceptable. The service was excellent, with the staff bringing out kids' utensils right away, which we appreciated.

The highlight of the meal was definitely the noodle soup. The broth was creamy with a distinct bonito fish flavor, making it a unique take on shoyu ramen. We've never experienced a creamy base with shoyu before, so it was quite interesting. The only minor drawback was the soft-boiled egg, which was slightly overcooked.

Overall, the service was up to par and we had a great experience. We'll definitely be back to try more of their dishes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovmOXlxrn71FdseJvAjANGOudb6lv_Ph6vheL&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"melissa choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKPYCcnHjMsXKLjSAR5QRLFI-pwNjpHDAAO3nrNqEuOCcrf9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I came alone. there were maybe 4 tables with people seated and already eating. One other guest came after me. It took forever them to ask for my order. They got the other table before i did. They never checked up on me after placing my food after me. They were not attentive. Food was okay. Wasn‚Äôt amazed by it though. Will not be returning. Overall atmosphere was clean and calming. I personally will not be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzaN_LsU9Kwak7qgzrRh5nUJIoBMK7KF226Z2f&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Chi Hsi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcBbxQUmUDBINWW8gpiVBRZkPGVAvZUVKaxZbYRVQUj9Y0ACg0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came here with our preschooler on a Thursday night at 6pm and was seated immediately. The service was great and quick in response when we raised our hand when we needed anything. They brought the kids utensils, scissors, bowl and cup right away.

I ordered the U. B. B. extra to share with my preschooler. Rich, flavourful, and creamy broth which I found a bit too salty for my liking. I was able to finish the end of the broth with the extra bowl of free rice. My husband doesn't finish the broth whenever we have ramen so it seemed a shame to dump it. We were able to get a to-go container for his remaining broth.

They also have an universal washroom for handicap and any gender so it was easier for my preschooler to reach the sink to wash her hands or go with my husband instead.

We'd recommend this place for families for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMye_HMVe1iRiTuUeVDUU-tRMeahxBkdlzSUbA&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious ramen with splendid, rich and creamy broth. Tried the black tan tan men which came with a bowl of rice and the flavours were great. The black sesame ground pork was both sweet and salty and went very well with the rice. The U.B.B. Extra ramen came with thick noodles that had great texture and the broth was so rich and complex. The service was great and the place was clean. Solid and satisfying ramen place. There are also complimentary sesame seed and chili powder toppings on each table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOZzYuriQu4IYkOTSb_x2nmC5vxcMD9MWz02sD&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"Megan H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIku9KV44jqgA8L-HCiMZoBBhlSnQF2rqxPqsFbb_vW5iUOog=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Thank you for great experience! :D
Vegetarian ramen coconut soup is new to me it was good.
We loved salt and seaweed sause on table for changing it soup own flavor.
Garlic add on was bit over cooked taste was bitter.. more soft is better.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Support local businesses!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKdi8mk0Fh3ap4R69GkSKDttRniyrD0Dyu-lhs&fid=0x0:0x7315c3ddc35be1e7"],"When":"2023-6-18"},{"Name":"Kelly B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkiKuJm4moehDFI36IJphpjRLNWxNWzBlehm-exa9sv2k-Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was my first time here, and I was very impressed by our experience. The service was the best I have had in years. They provide tea and water immediately upon being seated. Recommended dishes and told us there were pictures of food online, refilled water, cleared dirty dishes promptly, and offered extra ginger when they saw I liked it. The food was prompt, fresh, and delicious. The prices are average, keep in mind that every restaurant has raised prices due to covid losses and increased rent. Keep up the good work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeyFz2HjwN9xzz9AnNUP1f9FxIJz9s0PK8fDQoD1g82Jzc6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing experience at this sushi restaurant for lunch. The sashimi was exceptional, fresh, and full of flavor. The service was outstanding; my waitress treated me like I was in a five-star restaurant! I highly recommend this place for both the delicious food and the incredible service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Faezeh Vahdatihassani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2bw-ymcu67hZtIwsDNrPQPJaoPY4lqCRiAu3XCWAdqpV5X3b7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was obsessed with Sushi Koo. When they closed, we checked every day to see if they would reopen. Yesterday, after many months, I finally went there for lunch. I had fish and chips, and it was incredibly fresh. The fish had no unpleasant odor and was crispy without being greasy. The new owners are very friendly and respectful. Although the prices are a bit higher than before, the quality has greatly improved. Pay more and have higher quality and healthier food. Thank you, Sushi Koo team.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christina K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXY44ToPfFNvS5cz96PYOxJzhEcZVC7MRcG4Ip4Xsn3W2MXZgty-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I've been eating at Sushi Koo at least once a week for the past year. I was devastated when they closed down only to find out they were open again the next month. Didn't hesitate and ordered some basic rolls, oshi, dragon roll, the usual.
First, the prices are absolutely insane now. Yes, it's true the portions are a bit bigger, but it was bland and not comparable to the old place. I loved their salmon oshi and dragon roll, but they don't taste the same anymore. And I miss the happy combo :(
At this moment, nearby Shio is the cheaper and also tastier choice, and unless the menu and prices drastically change, I unfortunately don't see myself coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9HnlxvPVjG1v7tlVJ8qV4C-TEaPKCrvUVUw3Q&fid=0x0:0x7315c3ddc35be1e7"],"When":"2024-1-26"}]

I ordered today, after maybe a month hiatus, and the serving size seems smaller, the chicken seemed like leftovers from the day before and the lemon was old. There are way too many options for good Persian food to be lowering your quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuk86eyrKzFCxN3fjC2Gh7WVgfPs4ac8RQel74iDY6fKVzQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"amex accepted.  Decent barg/beef steak with rice and shirazi salad. The food is not particularly flavourful but acceptable.  It's a fast food place, so service is minimum. The decoration/atmostphere is better than most middle eastern fast food joint. The old lady at the counter is very friendly. Might come back and try the ground beef kebob.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs14IYo1pHdekx1j-K9eq221uq_FRoesZnYd7a&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2024-2-13"},{"Name":"Farid Entezari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV35QQyx2JmA30yOGa4kCXMTDZjBP0mMYjKzM0CL9HNh-FF7LAEEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The kebob house restaurant in poco is a small nice Persian restaurant. I tried their mix kebab dish which is one skewer of ground beef (Koobideh) and one skewer of steak( barg). Taste was good, portion size was good. Lots of parking in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONMghztr8XUKJnLI08J656NjDz94WXClWyIBRM&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-6-8"},{"Name":"Jason Shanks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqF_09LHcLQUBwa4sJj1J-2wuuUKxQADdaKcyJX3stv4lfuueH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Go check this place out!!!
What a great little place, we will definitely be back.
1.) Food was great, especially the yogurt for the pitta bread. It was light, fluffy, and had fresh chunks of cucumbers.
2.) Great service, although there was a hockey game on the TV good relaxing music for eating was playing at a conversational level.
3.) Meal for two, we were full upon leaving... just over $35.
3.) Clean kitchen, relatively new renovation making the inside comfortable, happily the renos extended into the washroom... some time these strip mall places can have not so great bathrooms... this was nice.
4.) Strip mall parking = short walk to the restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFxEqNuD7DW3qZGM5hzj53ap4gsScn4pVQDJj2&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Holly Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhQD6BQlcWfE694GJOqlMhXMwIQT-rKw4jcG8DlxP8gg2emzY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favourite persian restaurant to order from on UberEats. I've been ordering since February 2024.

I always order the Vasiri combo with Mast-O-Mooseer (yogurt with shallots), and the Shirazi Salad. The perfect meal! The portions are great, skewers are cooked perfectly and not dry, flavourful. What I appreciate is the consistency, I order quite often from here.

This recent order, the restaurant had contacted me about not having Sprite in stock so I replaced it with Ice tea. When I received my order, they had packaged 2 cans of Ice tea. I really appreciate the complimentary drink. I do want to mention when the lady had picked up the phone, she sounded very pleasant and genuine. One day if I'm in the Port Coco area, I would love to dine-in at this restaurant. Thank you","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK62iJj1ZUFGa-U3A8AjtI1ckQk60_9MMp9OhTpvv0nDBllSzC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here a couple times.

I've always enjoyed the food and experience here.

Fresh, reasonably priced and just plain good.

I live a bit far away from port coquitlum but whenever I come here, I always eat here.

I am a big fan of Persian cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpNJ3rXIwpVXFMcE37cha4yyJ0Xclp5IESBsYC&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2022-3-9"},{"Name":"Magic Eslami","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJo_ometNe5VFxyYN9EFz4qK_PQABq10iwnM8v3Yyyw57cviA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kebab House is a charming Persian family restaurant where I‚Äôve been a regular for several years. The selection of kebabs is impressive, and the food is consistently delicious‚Äîall at a very reasonable price!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Definitely worth every penny.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi-q_1NweNn4z2ThRTUFxzQExHPrQNJtVyh5QC&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"David 04 Make the World a Better Place","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXmkrAyRsAwad4uDl0EKEwpsCVMLq51IOxmbley55h_iwJzGo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"David's Overall Recommendation
‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ

‚óè Taste ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ
‚óè Price ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ
‚óè Kindness ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ

I visited this restaurant around 4:30 pm, which is a bit early for dinner. A female server welcomed me, and she was very friendly.

I ordered the combo with Jajangmyeon (black bean noodles), Jjamppong (spicy seafood noodle soup), and Tangsuyuk (sweet and sour pork). About 10 minutes later, all three dishes arrived together. The Tangsuyuk seemed to be fried in clean oil, and both the meat and the batter were exceptional. (Having worked in the restaurant industry, I could tell the frying oil was fresh.)

The Jajangmyeon and Jjamppong were delicious too, but the Tangsuyuk was the highlight.

The portions were generous, with all the food being flavorful and filling.

There were a couple of minor downsides:

1.	After the food was served, although the restaurant wasn‚Äôt busy, no one came by to check on the food or refill the side dishes. But with food this tasty, it was easy to overlook.
2.	They were playing a Charlie Puth medley, which didn‚Äôt quite match the restaurant‚Äôs vibe. (Just a playful comment!)

‚óèThere‚Äôs parking available, though not a lot.

‚óèThe restrooms are separated for men and women.

I highly, highly recommend this restaurant.
The food is incredibly tasty and clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsoYUAAi-S_HgnQg7DpsMimB6vAJ-ixuB9las&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Y Man","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB62F2-VitrTkpd3TexeBmDt6LJ-Ec6lzQvbbyCIp7HJAIiB3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update:
We went for the second time and we are happy that the food is still great and tasty! Consistency is so important and glad it did not disappoint. We ordered the same dishes plus Jjamppong. The Jjamppong was delicious! The broth was spicy but flavourful.  We will come back and try more dishes.

What a great meal! The food was delicious and the portion is generous. The tangsuyuk coating was light and crispy its sauce in the bowl was sweet and flavourful. The fried chicken's batter was also light and crispy and it was coated with a nice sweet tangy sauce that has a nice kick to it.  The jjajangmyeon was delicious, noodles are nice and chewy, the sauce was good with seafood and waterchestnuts mixed in it. I look forward to try their jjamppong (spicy seafood soup noodles)! We saw another table had it and it looks great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYGfyXK9P4bM98bWmhnS-0JPOB5QwstdK4zmYr&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Paula Mari Calip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDLGLcegymnTs4tKFxCUQkS77Gpb8Bcit9lJfvZ7dcPzKmO_Ci-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Home-y atmosphere, big servings, flavourful meal. My family enjoyed our time here. Will come back for sure!

PS: couldn‚Äôt take proper photos of our other food lol we were hungry and ready to chow down üòÇ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-fmzFjkrXsDSuD70e4LWu0e4GepaXup02B7aI&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a pretty standard Korean-Chinese restaurant that I'm used to. Their black sauce noodle was pretty good, but what really impressed me was the sweet and sour chicken.

The spicy seafood noodle was also quite tasty and would recommend it if you are into spicy food. I recommend that you go with lots of people so that you can order different things to try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVNoe2LTQphTqu1MVyAj3B_wmaTn3z8kg7qon6&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"marieXD21","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-Fu7lpV7ZXo_nlR8y9b6iJvHY1uEHpNZ4ShKlMM_rYkUiQkw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All food are delicious. We eat here once a month but every time we come back, we still can‚Äôt finish the big portions. Undefeated, highly recommend üíØ!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAroCq__K1__QMaOgFHdj2TOTP2iR6IMqfnzCS&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"Fanny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJf8QKhXtO_qInBc0jUDaCE3x1KtIHCwwl5Dp3ugGKzBjub0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We tried the Jjajangmyun and Jjam Bbong, and we're thrilled to have finally found a good Jjajangmyun! The Jjam Bbong was deliciously spicy. The portions were generous, and the service was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFNKr0BhTh7zPnf9l2KU0zrOOR5DhjvZAbQn6k&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Kenny Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPZZirBvo0A4h9mBsQTblhWpjRI5s3b9jzZsDmMvuAnSg24xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We don't often have Korean food but we wanted to try this place since they just opened where Kam Ding used to be. We also didn't know the portion sizes but it turned out to be really big so we ended up with enough leftovers for a second meal! The food was tasty so we enjoyed it. Most of the dishes are spicy but just right for us. A senior couple arrived and sat at the next table. They sounded like they are Italian and were also looking to try Korean food. We helped them choose a non-spicy dish!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhdTuRlDHKuJZqKozH-SA71Wk1X7IfundtlX5N&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2023-12-27"}]

[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious food but service was a letdown. We arrived in time for our reservation but no one was at the front to bring us in so we had to go into the restaurant itself to tell them that there are customers waiting at the entrance. We also got scolded by one of the servers for leaving the teacup lid open as were trying to let out a bit of steam so it wouldn‚Äôt be so hot to drink the tea straight away.

Food wise, we came for the dim sum and everything tasted. My favourite was definitely the shrimp with eggplant. The seafood congee was also flavourful but it was a bit lacking in the seafood. Overall, it came to less than $100 for 4 people before tips for a weekday lunch.

Be sure to make reservations as it was very busy for a regular weekday lunch time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSZfN6QZQKtTQjGvhORwCxQmETX0WOfGF2i1LN&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Sarah Barnes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1ca2s2Ju78fXB3WcTna5eoONK6rtbXd-or7AsBLVFqiGf04UKIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a reservation for 12:00pm and wasn't given a table till 12:30pm. Typical service of what you'd expect from a traditional dim sum restaurant. It's hard to flag someone down after you've ordered if you want drinks or hot sauce. Or anything really.

Food was delicious. Everything came out hot except the Taro birds nest. That seemed like it wasn't as fresh. Service for food was quick. As soon as you order, food starts coming out quickly.

Lots of free parking. Was harder to find the restaurant if you haven't been to the mall before. I would go again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgb2y95oJJvdHYE_HlkSeRes9ZqGxKjmPeF4jg&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered the saut√©ed beef with Chinese broccoli, fried rice with pork and shrimp, and cream corn soup with minced chicken. Our favorite was the deep-fried crab claw with shrimp paste‚Äîit was unbelievably good! The portions were incredibly generous and could last for days. The service was exceptional; our server went above and beyond to ensure we had the best experience and made excellent dish recommendations. The place is very fancy but offers affordable prices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn2GKo_hM5okzMfSZClpBZbu_Dh1Jtjmyl545E&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Allan Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNe78uSaiW7EBdh1XXTEeus_vpGIm93XhcgtH3d0ZMDq17341pmA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not bad; they have all my staples, but most things I found to be a bit blander compared to other dim sum restaurants (notably the Wu Gok). But keeping in mind that this particular location is really convenient for parking or transiting to. If I‚Äôm just looking for low-hassle dim sum and don‚Äôt live in Vancouver, I‚Äôd definitely come back.

I will also add, though the other typical items were on the blander side for my liking, the Egg yolk lava steamed bun was sublime - they did that one dish so so well, I‚Äôd say better than the average restaurant I can go to for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtU_QLUQRPpB3cyiB6qGnOGckTsumilRfNwha9&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Jessy J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHNRFw0Z_JgaU0TxGr1Pv5X-w9V6JzR0bnCuTDlGr_7pfsbx_k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Had dim sum here today.

Food was decent however service was slow.

Had tour regular type of dim sum and portion size is average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPppIrPrzOxtQc8_twj4FXtbZpa_17MutvxfcO2&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Janey Roh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLOMxtxjDNxOF_r0IqfPlGA74SB-KY6cVB7tMqaAybYfIP2Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We booked the private room for my parents anniversary lunch. We had 3 tables with 8 people per table and I think that was the ideal configuration. We had a 10 course banquet menu that included peking duck and king crab. I worked with the manager, Carol for our event and she was extremely helpful. My sister is gluten free and Carol was able to accommodate by creating a 3 course menu for her. On the day of the event, we were able to arrive early to set up some decorations and discuss the flow of the event with the Alex, one of the servers for our event. Each dish was fresh and delicious. The king crab is really something- so sweet and tender. The service during the meal was impeccable. Carol, Alex and another server (sorry! I didn't get his name) were just amazing- so attentive and checked in regularly to ensure everything was going smoothly. Everyone remarked at how great the food and service was. Thank you for making our event so memorable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adrienne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvS1YiBi1kAYmplCTkzo9NqyjbLMViYayHxaEQA-dKyQUyyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We‚Äôve been to Lee Garden several times now, and their food is always consistent. We always make a reservation as we‚Äôve seen people line up outside to wait. Service is quick, and the food is flavorful. We‚Äôre happy with the portions, the food is a bit pricier than other places.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwG2_Az5cq5OI3OpA0WaEUDJNRDggmPhCICaUx&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2023-5-15"},{"Name":"Tammy Hoang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-yEBkQVFHvEWZfuLZqbeoOB7DXxgT7uhpXL_VVia-4TbHCTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Some dishes were tasty, some were just okay. Foods were served quickly shortly after order. Restaurant has very convenient location with lots of parking at the mall. Nice decoration and very clean, we love the atmosphere. It's definitely a great place for family gathering. The restaurant is packed on the weekend, better to make a reservation especially when you come with a big group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY0Wjqe_5Xary3HvT8sMk90xkuTHA31i_L0NU&fid=0x0:0x8cbc8af35596ce72"],"When":"2023-2-8"}]

Basically everything in here is pricey yet quality is not up to par. Not an ordinary Hong Kong style cafe. Stay away!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJAxe1MU5inKBYv7ViYQ-mxrXjCf2k4WieUwed&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"TERRY CHENG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsg-oI6sco7O5Go48_oGM2GdPS9ywAc_QfXDXDKM3uhrlF3VpMxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is delicious. I had the chicken with salted fish fried rice. It was made perfectly with wok hay. You can taste the salted fish. The kitchen forgot my wife's order but unlike other typical Asian restaurant where the server just says it is coming, she apologized and went to follow up immediately. The atmosphere is loud and tables cramped. It is busy so you definitely need to wait. The washroom is 3/5 stars. Difficult to find any slippery floor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcw9bZT9QydmEGTIcGIKCSRHagLaVgqiZt-4Ml&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-3-2"},{"Name":"Kevin S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWW-HoTH05SDyiEsT9u8Wd25Wyn-omXApiCGy1l-mOBxv_wj5xh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A fine Hong Kong style restaurant.

I found the prices a bit on the higher side, but just slightly. The portions were generous, and the baked rice was quite creamy and delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnMqJR3qWP9PZWzBIUrCkSJrm8aqc7e1v_rq0_&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Kanako Sakurada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYybgPjG_d3LYq66Ui47Ocd_2PMrfkKaju5V_L0IyVTR19lQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"HK style cafe with wide variety of food from western to asian to fusion! Great steak combo and 10% off ordering on line even when eating in. Food is more than decent and the portion size is large.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNN16kz7Zh95HdWI--Ik0AAwQ2Z7ETsd_sBB0GP&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious and solid place for classic Hong Kong Cafe food. You can order online from your phone and they give you a 10% off discount if you order this way. There are plenty of combos that come with a drink and the menu is vast with both Western and Asian dishes. Highly recommend the tomato sauce baked ox tongue with a pasta of your choice. The tomato sauce was creamy, sweet, tangy, and savoury reminiscent of Campbell‚Äôs tomato soup. The lobster bisque was filled with lobster shell flavour. The red bean and grass jelly ice tasted delicious and refreshing serving as a dessert and drink at the same time.  Everything tasted delicious.

The portions for the fish and chips and pork and chicken cutlet and steak were good. There are comfy diner booth like seats to sit in and eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOrZgPDR6-6MMRH7dQMHRUTXL89zevjiNTvoji&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best HK style cafe in Coquitlam.

Services and food are fast and efficient. The food is high quality and decently priced.

Breakfast ranges from $12-$14
Lunch ranges from $14-$18
Dinner set menus ranges from $19-$23","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0PCRS9s3F_2r1xDSLsmEsNMEbJdi19UCaeY6C&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-1-29"},{"Name":"ladan ghafouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKWEx_YV_Uj80v-xctgsLSGRY6V78hw5KMb4aNvRdZAaXJWti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My partner and I went there for brunch.We ordered Mexican and vegetarian omelet. We pick the French toast to come with. Also we asked for coffee. The menu was really rich and you will have variety of different opinions. We really loved the omelets. The French toast was perfect.  For the coffee I just prefer to have suger, milk and cream on the table like as every where else( they just asked us how many suger we want and put 4 milk on the table, not even in the plate). Overall I really liked it and we will go back to try lunch and dinner .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHNXWlB85awZcVo4LsFWw7YzcOUxmmYs4aAxUG&fid=0x0:0xb89aa5370ad1307a"],"When":"2024-4-8"}]

Well done !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JD","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVFj7LNOTX4AOFSOmIlvZBDs4m0ZvbzGytwaTX7uYDSavNtj0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best BC roll I've ever had. Crunchy salmon skin with occasional meat, also with a delicious teriyaki sauce (no artificial crab meat, which i hate that a lot of other sushi places do). Then balance the sweetness with a spicy tuna/salmon roll or a spicy agadashi tofu.

Small little restaurant, seems to be family ran, servers are nice and the chefs don't look stressed out. Always a good experience when I eat here. Parking is not bad, there's more parking below towards Save-on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWESBNLIeUqoBdpmKKUHv0eiMBWj8I3hC9PlYx&fid=0x0:0xdf6b68ec77e84579"],"When":"2023-3-16"},{"Name":"Summer Denise","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVLGlEjExYSI9TlDWJA5kTZkeVo9iNkfZ5Fa7s6qADcSesw6sxVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Small and cozy, it‚Äôs nicely located near Mundy Park, one of my favourite places to hang. Unfortunately, my first dining experience here is also my last as ingredients used weren‚Äôt fresh. Rice was so stale that I could barely swallow the second piece of avocado sushi. They didn‚Äôt have enough avocado for the avocado roll and so they added cucumbers to it without first informing me of it. Salad, abundant but browning quickly as I ate along and my lunch lasted less than an hour. Batter on tempura was the right amount but sadly, not fresh, and neither was the spring roll. Terriyaki tofu on bean sprouts and cabbage was okay. Only tasty thing was their miso soup with wee cubes of tofu and no, not returning to the diner just for that or the great service I got from the server.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7L9bWaWCIfdLpLQ5kruWiHQYI3hXPCQWiJkMQ&fid=0x0:0xdf6b68ec77e84579"],"When":"2024-3-8"}]

Food was great, and great quality. Well prepared and still hot/warm after pickup. Fed 25 peple no problem.

I like the small details : provided plates, utensils, napkins, and sauces.

Thank you for supplying food for our block party. Will use again for our next block party.

üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKLa8Ny9hmfpWqaULqFPLIntWwYp7SmXYe8iEd&fid=0x0:0xf88ba7bda27b84c1"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Ghazal Kouhi Kamali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_qIjZ3Oqp_d9BN-AkX25WzsTJtXmDXsKD4pAn_SRunnWNtlM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Firstly do not be fooled by the images of the colorful bowls on Uber. You will receive barely a half chicken breast, for $21. Secondly, I paid $20 two chicken thigh skewer that was dark and tasted like it had been sitting in the warmer for a day or two!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEHkhvOjZFAYmU9nZC-6jHbuUa6QsT3pSFdj6G&fid=0x0:0xf88ba7bda27b84c1"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Lauren W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6_w6rFNmUaFr_S3SqHEkz_5HBIrq9Tf4HaDU8JlvCI9WCSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time ever at Nando‚Äôs and I will definitely be back. In a world of fast ‚Äúfood‚Äù chains it‚Äôs nice to find a chain that actually has some quality. I got the rainbow bowl which had a little bit of everything, the different tastes & textures came together really well. My boyfriend got 5pc wings which were smaller than he remembers & chicken livers which paired well with the garlic bread. The side of sweet potatoes with honey & feta was bomb, and the coleslaw paired well with the spiciness of the meal. The tarts for dessert were delish and not too heavy. We left feeling full & satisfied which overall justified the $60 price tag in a world where everything seems to be increasingly overpriced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFHV9GE6TKin6gZpB5rssiuYpU5EdYnRKtN3AW&fid=0x0:0xf88ba7bda27b84c1"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing grilled chicken, great for a quick lunch. The chicken was served within 5 minutes of ordering and was piping hot. Very flavourful as well. Even the chicken breast portion was well-seasoned, tender, and not dry at all. The fries had a good amount of crunch and paired fantastically with coleslaw and chicken. A great fast meal for me with little hassle.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuU8y_gebvBj-tHQjfL-dK6mPpXUG5VbuRS_Cf&fid=0x0:0xf88ba7bda27b84c1"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Mike Zelt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXCrXMCSIMLlmxYzbG0KU0bWxv4WVzxsnaaHUtaqevbek3bbk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is the second time I have eaten at this restaurant.   I am a big Nando's fan.   Love the food.
BUT, the inside temperature of the restaurant was just too cold to appreciate the food.  It was so cold that I could not take off my coat.   After asking an employee why it was so cold I was told that it was on account of the access door being opened and closed, bringing in the cold air.
To eat in the cold is NOT comfortable and I will not be returning to this particular outlet again which is a shame as it's in a very convenient location.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Omar Al-Sinawi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpEl_g84Seh4qRudRGqX_aaPgLpsARBoRaRxsN_Q8m809Ajxo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Only go there if you enjoy eating your meal in a Freezer! It was literally colder inside the restaurant than it was outside and it was 7 degrees on the day I went. Employees blamed the temperature on the door being constantly opened but I've been to many busy restaurants before and never was it even close to being that cold even if I sat near the door.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ton V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb4h6oZDMjakZ7o0kpJmjp_i41AvhfJ62KCrl6wCnDvytBpv4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love Nando‚Äôs food. One thing I know from experience is that you should eat-in, don‚Äôt ever take out. Straight from the fire or the fryer is so much more delicious. They could play some music and adjust the lights a bit to improve the ambiance. I would also suggest to offer free mayo to dip the fries.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lemon & Herb 1/2 Chicken: Great quality chicken. It‚Äôs flavourful and well-marinated.

Good coleslaw salad.

Nando‚Äôs Kisses: a nice, sweet dessert. It‚Äôs chocolate ice cream with whipped cream on the top.

Service: the manager and the servers are all kind and welcoming. Thank you for serving me, Nando‚Äôs Peri-Peri!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5o4Mf5DomZf2LxCECfC19Ovksg7QY1tcQawmx&fid=0x0:0xf88ba7bda27b84c1"],"When":"2024-2-28"}]

[{"Name":"Hanna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWC8PcJ3VMkwuHFoWwqhZMDiwIhI2-B47BTER2vJc8WkL2eueBj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went here to try their soup in the cold weather by myself.  It was so good!  The staff were so kind and helpful with the menu, and the portion size and side dishes were very large for the regular size, I was unable to finish but it was very delicious.  The atmosphere is cozy; and I left feeling healthy and warm.  The menu items are listed in Korean but English translations are listed beneath each of them!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM89u577pjysd6Ud2W6s8pOofp4JwwhSGoujW8v&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Brandon Hwang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXM8uHkSNQ1f67I6kzgiBGArFLjuzwkTWQKJg_2bHlV9k1h7-rn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you're a fan of hearty, flavorful Korean cuisine, Bukchigo Jangguchigo is a must-visit. Specializing in Sundaegukbap (blood sausage soup), this restaurant delivers rich, savory dishes that capture the essence of traditional Korean comfort food. However, for those unfamiliar with offal or sensitive to distinctive food aromas, it might take some getting used to. That said, once you acquire the taste, it becomes incredibly addictive.

Their spicy stir-fried gopchang (intestines) is another standout dish, offering just the right kick of heat. Pair your meal with traditional Korean makgeolli (rice wine) for an authentic dining experience. This is a true gem for those who appreciate down-to-earth, everyday Korean dishes that tug at the heartstrings of home-cooked nostalgia. Whether you're a long-time fan or new to Korean cuisine, this spot is sure to leave a lasting impression.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmjMSNdMGaNsa1YsVZlsKT7zba-V7Z7hmCXrcu&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Nhi Ho√†ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1QePYF-UVINbDSSmftKYTXlpwLQZXczMrhEF9IMEzva6RJX0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is small, crowded during peak hours but the food quality is still delicious. The fried intestines are soft inside and crispy outside. The pig feet has a chosen level of spiciness, great when eaten with rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGkIWrbmWEO1OdW_NkRIbYdeJZX8MTIZvkpR-K&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Derrick Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAlQdtNkVOB7lzxgMRguauX1p_mYPY6hJnClVyC3T91iV5mPIL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A hidden gem in Korea Town. Always a line up for dinner. Must try their blood sausage soup. If you‚Äôre feeling adventurous‚Ä¶I highly recommend the blood sausage and organs soup.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNht1jFAPS1C1p9_21LN87h7lyTM7NXeh6GrNn9&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Helen D.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyu5Lt8dplX_J1Zs_BtplHu93y_yusuUNzg33OmEALysRDnBlb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic korean restaurant with a diverse menu and my go-to for comfort/soupy food. I have ordered many dished on their menu. My favorites are blood sausage soup, cold buckwheat noodle and seafood pancake. Obviously blood sausage and intestines/organs are not everyone‚Äôs cup of tea. But you can‚Äôt really go wrong with ordering just anything there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH0qE2e5GlsDQjEvEqGpsSmWj0y2wjr9JNweSE&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Alice Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDjZlUFVrVbyNDzA-TlBz2GCFmuAzURRrPGrxlmwdYVifV1EsC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean restaurant. Not super fancy but All their foods are above average. Place to visit if you want to try out authentic Korean foods rather than k-bbq. Expect to wait if you are dining in, but it totally worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT1gy7WK9SJKQkNcwwyZnATpcpIOn4JQOnzFhi&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Y S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTmtWUtCZcs7qDdNKdjVbtcx5f5BcDfDU3YRp4zcFsXHKu1_WS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came on a Sunday for lunch. This place is packed and you have to write your name down for waitlist. But the turnaround time is fast so we only had to wait for 5 minutes.

Don‚Äôt expect fancy decor here. It‚Äôs more like a hole in the wall restaurant but the food is amazing and authentic. Service was fast. The food came 10 minutes after ordering and it was steaming hot. Definitely will come again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPHggVOoDno6Z5zaaKgIt4YzH4EPGOx7DN2eHu&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Iven Tse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWqYBm_0Md_dEh21ObcpKYh8NezukBMGE0J5wxrlAZNMPCyxCi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Finally made it to this place, my wife and I had tried four times and each time they were packed and we could not wait that long and we ended up across North Road in some other Korean restaurant. It was worth the experience - finally - and though we may not come again, it is not because of the food being bad, it was very‚Ä¶..interesting. The blood sausage and organ soup was very tasty, a bit spicy, and full of flavour. The sausage was encased in real intestine, which made for a nice chewy texture. The seafood soup had large pieces of soft egg tofu, lots of different kinds of seafood from octopus to mussels to clams and prawns and was perfectly spiced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPyFB0gsnpW_oMDQUnmmkpYKwvYKZ3u5MAwJSn&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2023-2-12"}]

[{"Name":"Lyndsay Krause","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUw_d91QaVdyXJ_iD_9n4lPuhHR3K42K7S3ljCJwkny1L-l3IuysA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mixed feelings on this one.  We went during happy hour for a friend's birthday as a table of four.  Even at the peak during our visit, the restaurant was at max, half full, but they did have a large reservation table of about twenty.  The food was good, but the service was SLOW.
They were clearly short-staffed, as the manager was working behind the bar while we were there, but we had to ask other servers to find our waitress twice and went up to the bar once to order our drinks because we had been waiting for so long.  That being said, they apologized profusely and comped us free desserts and did explain that they were short staffed. However, if you're offering a happy hour with one dollar oysters in a nice, reputable restaurant, then you should be prepared.
We ordered both off the happy hour menu and the regular menu and there was small tweaks. We would have made to each dish, but overall, a pretty satisfying meal.
We will give them another shot to see if the slow service was a one off.
If you park in the underground and register you license plate at the hotel desk, parking is free.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzq5Fru9vEfYxmcJR5xpopeyv6MziJcBBPsKfk&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Olivia Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIR4XKe445qsIhcDQSa4vWiOM9DrqY3ui4NVU5_YRxUleaadGk6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I celebrated my husband's birthday at this restaurant during happy hour. It was great! I really liked the reservation service and the atmosphere in there. The oysters were especially affordable‚Äîonly $1 each!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdpEVhtW5DRj8LXHSixV5OtUbkSaXNC_r14vrH&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Wonder M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3hGfH7AOg7pRCDa3Bl6Ihva2AjzSpnVzAGWxFqmscwMF13g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our second time visiting Wild Fig and it never changed! Still as good as before. We came back for the $1 oysters during happy hours 4-6pm. Still our favorite.
The server, Gaga, was very accommodating and fun. 5 stars for her excellent service!
We will definitely be back with our family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUKGUqII20gz8cBwmqEzJxiE-UcceFNmhqqtF2&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Darrin Moench","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVTIvDThj7TkTP598AOhul-HvnJ48LyKCbcLeGyiMH4FCfSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbled into the perfect happy hour!  Buck a Shuck Oysters. $4.50 Beers Nuff' said. Fatima was great.  It was very busy with a big birthday party so you could tell they were slammed. But food was great. And waitress went out her way to make rounds and make sure things kept rolling. Food was great üëç","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMYYch2lk-bCunpYV7YUh7ZvVaUV-eGh72LWsx&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Jacky Wan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLB3kh5YHFtu97zOxW9maILk0zgbp2Jc2wc2LfnIwMDfF2vFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of visiting The Wild Fig Restaurant + Bar, and it was an outstanding experience! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for a relaxing evening.

I enjoyed six cocktails over three hours, and each one was fantastic. The bartender, Heyson, truly made the night special. His service was exceptional‚Äîattentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the drink menu. He made great recommendations that enhanced my experience.

If you're looking for a great place to unwind with delicious cocktails and top-notch service, I highly recommend The Wild Fig. I can't wait to return!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9SVtfhGWVywzBeZqt6IVTIHOKpPGQUSE0tYi0&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Simon Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKqDrptZk5K8r7cAAASAK3dUxXTVH7GnPDIaXKpcuAnggfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for happy hour and was pleasantly surprised that the music wasn‚Äôt blaring. Our server was great, kept checking in with us even as the place started to fill. For the prices the food was great. Side note, the security guard at the entrance was probably the nicest and most professional I‚Äôve ever encountered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjdqhF79SAMToD3ZFc3RaKEVz1HLAFAR17piw&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Sarah E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIa_jO-vyQRGGDK2y4e7wiYPff_fxb9XQEgCwprbq-00Y5DNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Sunday Brunch is excellent.  Many choices of food from hot to cold, including an omelette station where you can chose your own ingredients.  Services are great as well,  friendly servers are always around to see if we need a top up on the coffee or take the plates away.  A very enjoyable experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMRayiGdaH9mB7u_Sn0vun5pfSAHE5bERYS9Zf&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Genova ‚ÄúGen‚Äù Pangan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEIdEux0Y6t5oht2jr_SIjM3bcTupGJn9fR2Ts_u19pLcx_Y6eIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend Wild fig , my friends and I had a wonderful experience . Busgirl name ALONA she amazing pretty  , friendly  and accommodating,  The place not  too crowded     , we came in for happy hour the food was great lots of choices. I will surely come back here .
