[{"Name":"ladan ghafouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKWEx_YV_Uj80v-xctgsLSGRY6V78hw5KMb4aNvRdZAaXJWti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The venue itself is simple, elegant, and clean. We visited for lunch, and the food arrived quickly and was absolutely perfect. It was delicious, and I especially appreciated the serving plates. The prices were reasonable as well. We thoroughly enjoyed our experience and will definitely return!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjCsUSBTawbKgXK-huKvzWAvA0uELlp297DnWZ&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Nowell Alcancia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDqmFfelGK9VUjuTkW_fGkawlR7g8hmDyutgBrf42CtjnR7rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Indian food can taste quite ordinary but this bistro‚Äôs modern take is definitely extraordinary!

I tried the New Zealand Lamb Chops and it tasted really good. The meat was tender and it was perfectly seasoned. The chips / fries on the side were crispy and flavorful. And the coleslaw has a refreshing dressing.

I also tried their Prawn Shahi Masala and it was divine! The curry is rich in flavor and has the perfect blend of spices. Pairing it with their Naan bread, surely satisfied my cravings.

On top of that, their staff are super nice and service is reasonably fast. The vibe of the place is modern and is sparkling clean. Their prices are reasonable as well.

Overall, I enjoyed dining here and I‚Äôm looking forward to try their other menu items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMo0tJDOAyH-59WlS---YVwfDX2KkhivrAIiw4C&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Isha Verma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMJciArOeeSjHndxQ0XoXcUzL8SA1GQlEX1BVvRzfvovE8hbdaUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"With the rain I was craving some comfort food today!! We decided to stop by naan club in Coquitlam!
It wasn‚Äôt busy so we were sat immediately. We started off with the vegetable pakoras, which were hot and fresh! There was a great crunch with each bite and I appreciated the variety of veggies in it! (Sometimes it‚Äôs just cauliflower) . This was $6 during happy hour!!

I decided to have the chole Bhature, the chole (chickpeas) was very flavourful. Not overly spicy at all as I requested mild. It came with yogurt, pickled carrots, and some veggies. Overall I‚Äôd give it an 8/10, it definitely satisfied the craving. I appreciated the price point of $13.

My boyfriend had the butter chicken with garlic naan, he said he enjoyed it. He specifically mentioned how he like the creaminess of the dish! The naan was a little too crispy for me but I enjoy the tastes I had.

We also finished off with rasmalai (no picture sorry) and it was a perfect end to the meal. Not overly sweet and the cheese patties were soft üôÇ

We enjoyed our meal and would definitely come by again as we live near by! It‚Äôs nothing super fancy but if you are looking for a more modern setting then this may be the spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQCLBGNcZJsKbodPRENw2s2pzS4GJAdKqIyCXF&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Jason Shanks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqF_09LHcLQUBwa4sJj1J-2wuuUKxQADdaKcyJX3stv4lfuueH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was great.
Some of the best service I've seen in a long time!
Great ambiance, modern interior w/ house music.
One of the oddest things that I've ever made note of in my reviewing history, the takeaway containers have separate compartments so your food doesn't get smushed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQJA2rnvWepgotpwrVniRhZsu-2Petoe271gpO&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Harjeev Sudan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKr3qEpqTajogs2eW7vWKZEyVziveS5niHBWoWFN0KHBqHSJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful ambience, excellent service, and delicious food. Celebrated my parents‚Äô anniversary and they brought out a delicious treat on the house. The owner is welcoming and kind. Great experience, would recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMvYbmh7n6wfDnZE3LjJmX6VyewdMMpj66hETm&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great spot for a quick bite. This was my first time checking out the restaurant. After a long day of errands in the neighborhood it was a fantastic space to take a break.

We tried the Chole Bhature, a classic family favourite. While less fluffy and thicker than other restaurants in the Tri-Cities, the chole (chickpeas) were seasoned well. It satisfied the craving.

The chili chicken was wonderful. Well balanced flavours and texture. The Chicken Kadhai had wonderful sauce but it was so scorching hot, it almost tasted like it was warmed in a microwave.

I'd skip the Roomali Roti. It wasn't as thin as I expected. The Naan was better.

Surprisingly, the Veggie Pakora was a highlight. Tasty, light and not greasy. The accompanying sauces were delicious.

Quick and responsive service. You can tell there's a hardworking team at this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHWyUDQMmK0YVoHaZI6sDWq2llz6oIwRRDm5Bw&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Martin Matahari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAn1gLSlBMeGXZBHUnKkSJRx9LUQmHP9VKEpiPVA6PU8EOwPbl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had lunch at this restaurant on a weekday. It was pretty quiet. The place is nicely decorated and there‚Äôs seating for large groups. They have a selection of alcoholic and non alcoholic drinks. Ordered a starter and few curries. The crispy kebob was very tasty. I like the flavour of coriander that was in the meat and the dipping sauces were flavourful. The palak paneer was nice too, could taste the fresh spinach and it was not too spicy. The chicken dish with creamy sauce was a bit bland. Could have used more salt. Naan was yummy and soft and I loved the texture of the butter naan especially because it‚Äôs so rich and fluffy. The staff was pleasant and attentive enough. My wife enjoyed the experience and overall I would say it‚Äôs one of the better Indian restaurants in the tri cities area. Would visit again, but not sure how it is if it‚Äôs very busy in the evening.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNPa5Z0VI5Dw53lpt3zlwrnLz0WhkvWT7Ls1ez&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Amanda Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX2-QkU6r0X4DLM6-w27hOoQabXaFOXnHBh92gU3KWWKAd6KWGjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very pleasant dine-in experience. It was quiet in the evening and service was warm and attentive. Clean and modern atmosphere. Curries were very flavourful and satisfying, and the naan was, of course, fantastic!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBb5zokjlevGxJEC-fcJbqd4d-2blpdkAkbUDo&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-22"}]

[{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time dining at Oz and it did not disappoint! The overall experience was fantastic. We ordered the dduckochi and cheese balls and they were both delicious. The bibimbap and katsu platter were very good as well and super filling. You definitely get your moneys worth here.

It also has a wonderful atmosphere and feeling inside that is cozy and quiet but still lively. I will definitely be coming back again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaqyr8wzBtJ4GhsosyHHMHgfSOor5SZ1FDiSwc&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Korean food here was a bit unimpressive. Maybe because the restaurant didn‚Äôt specialize in any particular Korean cuisine and they had a bunch of different items so ultimately, nothing really stood out for me. It was quite busy when we went and they do not take reservations after 6 pm. Luckily, we got the last table available when we went at 7 pm and it was quite convenient to sit at even for a wheelchair user. We were given the menu, water, and the small side dishes. We were able to order relatively quickly and dishes came out one by one and temperature was right.

We ordered kimchi pancake, pork bone soup, and two kinds of Korean fried chicken which were just perfect to feed for adults. Prices were reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkn-KfcnXIczMTEP2sbylVcKtdoebbH7O2K1t6&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Alan Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-QmMYfw75kgf5vonVt_7RAAdUJRl5hAF6Ijht6iC6ZE8aPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I use to live in this area and frequented this place often. I remember trying it for the first time 5 years ago and fell in love with their hot pot soups.

Coming back here to have a meal with friends was nostalgic. We enjoyed the food as always and would recommend this to anyone looking for some Korean food in the coquitlam area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtfhd5AfTwF9YtaXD3uJCEFkRn80xV1BvdkYOd&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Warner Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDWKsyLtafyGfK7Q7w1ml3mxeAbc-FKoRYJ5e-a9yHsAmwQ441=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here on a Sunday mid afternoon post hike. Wasn‚Äôt too busy and our party of 3 was able to be seated immediately.

We were able to order off their lunch special menu (forgot to take a picture) which offered a variety of choices from their regular menu at a discounted price or in a ‚Äúcombo‚Äù feature (good value).

Food met my expectations and was decent, however it wasn‚Äôt over the top amazing. Think: homey comfort food, and it delivered on point. They even provided us a complementary seafood pancake (Í∞êÏÇ¨Ìï©ÎãàÎã§!)

Staff were friendly and food came quickly. Atmosphere was as good as a mid afternoon would feel. Would have to come back in the evening to get a better assessment.

Overall, would recommend a stop by if you‚Äôre in the area and craving some Korean comfort food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM10h1t_t07qL6wsIu5gVMXMR7LOB_efmNYcee9&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2023-11-2"},{"Name":"Zaena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0uL5_BX81jM9l56vBhJlVZo9GPHZpZOUMAV-UObxVeXamgoUc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place! Staff was kind, food was DELICIOUS and great quality. Some of the best tasting tofu I‚Äôve ever had - they even threw in some Korean fried pancakes for free, since we asked them to remove meat!
Would 100% reccomend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfok_JVO6TJSOXEdrrWTf-yfX2FNdN4gk1d2K1&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Blessed Love Jamantoc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiJkDfqK1tLHwmtym7NT7sodUjHvZSVRt9FJ_NqcdWkISaxfG4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"i‚Äôm a tough 5 star pleaser and this OZ got me! they had the best soontofu soup I‚Äôve ever tasted.
they served it hot as you can see, NO MSG after taste, and when I asked for no veggie, they just know. I am filled not w preservatives other restaurants does w their food. I am legit stuffed and fully satisfied w the taste and freshness. keep it up you guys!

won‚Äôt be surprised if after this review, they‚Äôll order lots of tofu!

Thanks OZ Sunday (08/25/24) team!‚≠êÔ∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYlkeGSdZKiS0MHeUvlNOykNIPavovUM3fkGYe&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Danna Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF9zEuY7zqRjRIluv60FcQUIH-EGyvSKkPFdpcqCORZX_gMg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a hidden gem by Coquitlam centre. Really cool atmosphere and great food. Only reason I cannot give 5 stars is some foods we ordered were way too spicy like the teokbokki (rice cake) - if you‚Äôre not Korean or you‚Äôre not used to eating super spicy, it can be hard to eat.

I recommend sticking to other dishes like their fried chicken or katsu and japchae (glass noodles) which were super flavourful. Overall,  a great restaurant to hang out at with friends and it‚Äôs opened until midnight.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAk-bHbstZU-CJdI-wvoyKXTIC0WcdxcUcZTIf&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"C.K. [{"Name":"Jason Tribbiani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXpvlAY0NULhaj1b4k1yZZtRXFlzsqxg5gIO8-kzQ1-Qy-iq7d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best Korean restaurant I've visited so far. I've been to many Korean restaurants across Vancouver, Burnaby, Coquitlam, Port Coquitlam, New Westminster, and more, but this one stands out as my favorite. It seems like a hidden gem, as during my visit, I only saw Korean customers. The food is excellent, the service is good, and the prices are fair. A nice touch is the Asian yogurt drink they give you after the meal‚Äîmy kid absolutely loved it. We'll definitely be coming back again soon!"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO23awN-dQ3bi0FKJ5yAWbbs8DflyRWk_O6oFCK&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice food. Good service and big portion. Little highlight is small bottle drink when pay bill ü•∞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpvleOX52Vc9_WylUP3np4rjV6QUxRVLcmYxpU&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Monique","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQcAgOL4v2U_VirmCaadFrb2IzIMWiSeW-tX_pA5B7GcJn2vN8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you‚Äôre craving comfort food and Korean food, this place is amazing!

We went on a cold rainy day, and the food was super filling!

The sogogi soontubu was my personal favourite as it was so flavourful especially when mixed with rice! Highly recommend it if you like beef stews and soups.

When you‚Äôre done with your meal you get a complimentary yogurt drink which pairs perfectly with the dishes and is super cute. ü•∞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEiOwpPj8MDmPUHPnWL3zZrJe9UBD_A4dugiYw&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Visited on a quiet evening, got seated quickly with plenty of available tables.

The menu was straightforward; we ordered soups. Side dishes came first, followed by the flavorful soup and not-too-spicy stew.

We were able to opt out of the side rice for noodles free of charge which was nice. There wasn‚Äôt much meat in mine, but the issue I had was the amount of onions in the soup, it occupied most of the space in the stone bowl so it wasn‚Äôt enjoyable.

Reasonable prices, no rush to leave ‚Äì great for both small and large groups. A delightful surprise was the complimentary yogurt drinks at the end, a nice touch after a satisfying meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMefnWlAUNY_NGLLZAMm4yO6acdkPD-6bSxHwnY&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-2-1"},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"- Very spacious, comfortable seating.
- Friendly and attentive staff
- Delicious BIBIMBAB and seafood pancake
- generous refill of Kimchi and Bean sprouts side dishes

This store is highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVXN7JwN8WX1o98OuOToYl6i_D0JTxQ6G7adEq&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"M Mark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJh32lM4t_7cX4VsExqacG-T8y6qepgXVVz9NQxEaNR5c4_HHo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came for a late lunch. Big restaurant with booths and buttons to call for service. Small parking lot shared with several businesses.

I ordered the gal-bi tang $22.95 - beef back rib and beef brisket in medicine beef broth. It came with free side dishes that were a bit sus tasting. Not the freshest.

Soup came bubbling to the table! Two large bones. It was tender, but lacked that fatty, juicy beef flavour. The beef brisket was dry as per the norm in these soups. Soup was seasoned well. Ended dinner with a free yakult (yogurt drink) which was a nice way to wrap up the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9Qe0JCF6w16VUJbCbv86S78gX2_U55tXLse1T&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Sara Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlSF6ADXHgyatqSj3RdRyjxWuJp2qz8rnQN-QdhLw0IaUlXFq2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We fall in love with this restaurant since the 1st time we visit 2 months ago, my hubby found his long lost flavour of Seol Leong Tong, here, all their soup rice set is very tasty, the environment is clean & neat, quite comfy to dine in, and their service is very sincere too, very friendly and attentive, I introduced this restaurant to my sisters and they love it too, price is very reasonable, feel free to drop by anytime üòÜ

Tried their Gamja Tang yesterday (Nov17, 2024) that was really good, it contained 3 big pork bone stew as u can see in the photo, the spiciness of the soup is just right to go with the rice, yummy  üòã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-23ZXh-8gejMkZpPJXqrpa8RWsEQ6O3sHK_04&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Annie Chu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsXi8Is5QB-hGp8e4gCUiJFiV4Pu0iMPFA2Oi2wm3py-Xxlqfh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quite enjoyed the gamjatang and seafood soondubu (tofu soup)! Side dishes were pretty average. Spacious restaurant and plenty of free parking.

They use the service button which you press to get service. Would return again if I was craving!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOo6twih_bB3X46-45qtZs85Qci7K2gp2cYZIdY&fid=0x0:0x132cccb52a4527c8"],"When":"2024-9-14"}]

We enjoyed two awesome cocktails, the garlic bread was absolutely delicious, and the fish and chips were fantastic. Even my 4-year-old daughter loved her meal, which is always a great sign. We really enjoyed the atmosphere‚Äîit was warm and welcoming, and we had a great time. Special shout-out to our server, Sharon. She was so kind, lovely, and attentive, especially to my daughter. We will definitely be coming back again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"B B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIWXkb7cw_G-9xJo_3-zWM41O-N5FcHl5P5HTGctsYs5K7I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent pizza. The Good ... The crust was perfect and the cheese was gooey.

The bad... The toppings were uneven... Way too many (uncooked) chunks of tomatoes, and not much sausage or peppers.
When I'm paying $32 for one medium pizza, the pizza should be loaded evenly with toppings.

Our server was friendly and attentive.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"O'Neil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlG_qS4RzoXq0jXYAc_venCNNLYuKBdxhX5Bt4JfwcrWcoZULh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to this pizza place other night with some friends. They recommend it. I really enjoyed the service. The toppings were really thick and it was very tasty and well put together. Everything thing was wonderful. Price point was fair and portions were good. We ordered a large and 3 of use could not finish it. Also had appetizers were also delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiDR-RTb1qKIL8QRrBvX1p-oGWlwEhvmurFtru&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2023-2-12"},{"Name":"Candice C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwFBBjzDK0K147Ahvw56fgZp0Wzk8W8u0zo_aJQ425Hu_MYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Mixed review.
Pizza is very good!! I've only ever ordered take out and had no complaints.
The other night I called in and they said I could place a take out order as they were closing in 20min, perfect worked for me. I order the lasagne which I haven't had here before. Well it's literally 90% noodles, 5% cheese and 5% sauce and not good sauce at that, just very bland with little meat and lots of pepper. I won't order it again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOttwakDj7ldqA6GB4WNyu1yGy0wjdN_fIIUjR2&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"John Harris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKAq3ml95jHUMxZNKiBUEM24tdpzJMiqP5RJmX8-A4uSjHfIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want thin crust, go elsewhere (Emilio Finattis is a good option!). San Remo Pizza is THICC. It's kind of like if 1/3 of a lasagna and a 2/3 of regular pizza had a very delicious baby.

They have beer if you eat in, they've been around since at least the 80s apparently, and I've never had a bad pizza from them.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Not to mention the Super Donairs were absolutely stuffed to the seams and tasted delicious!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amit Panwar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUKgPYQo4yYPdQiKuxuluBh25_Mx2ic72A0jr9AoMKieqbFgY0Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today, I ordered the falafel plate from Donair Town via DoorDash. Furthermore, the falafel, typically a standout on their menu, fell short of expectations. The flavors lacked the anticipated vibrancy, contributing to an underwhelming dining experience. Given these issues, I‚Äôve decided not to order from Donair Town again. I hope they consider refining both their packaging and the flavor profile of their dishes in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN5RbaoPNBcEmRvCzqNOu02q-CfZdzyJiX5Ab_&fid=0x0:0x11ba10f0dd4d4475"],"When":"2024-1-28"},{"Name":"Robert Beck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCAGWcbKRzu57s06A_98b26e1MWBkgYfj7YwE4XORrau23931S=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love coming to Donair Town!! Best donairs and plates around and for a good price too. Absolutely delicious","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Okay is the best I can describe it as I don‚Äôt want to be mean. Underwhelming is likely close too. The folks working are kind enough, to the point and straight forward nothing above and beyond which is fine. The Chicken donair left much to be desired though. The chicken rotisserie wasn‚Äôt on and my chicken wasn‚Äôt freshly cut off shawarma style. Rather coming from a container I presume and hope was cut off earlier. It didn‚Äôt taste bad but nothing to write home about either. They have other flavours like Snow Onion, Soy Garlic, Green onion, and etc. So, I‚Äôll definitely be back to try those dishes as well. I'd usually just get the original and make it large to share between 2-3 people.

Keep up with the quality and I'll be a long time regular for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ0jChP4mCoDEU5VdDHk5TJXAr2H9gQSfZP-GL&fid=0x0:0x15802ca10afa6683"],"When":"2023-11-15"}]

[{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A convenient Coquitlam restaurant serving drinks, bubble tea, share plates and delicious mains. More of a grab and go or quick stop kinda restaurant. Good food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdXHVbm4tISC3oVOY17Fw9Rjte3DlkgNSHi7qz&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Eunice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2ALhqjwHhkNkSm6pXiyY4p5qQowzcr6jQE1ebfHzuWw2OswE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went to buy the lunch bargain Bento.
For $14.95 only 3 slices of pork belly  and The box is full of rice.  Not worth it. Do not recommend to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkEr-NhkrIqTLie9Mjy3sjLLJB14S17aoxaFp0&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"John Seong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0htFjeJaWzfoh1Wx3ky51rbanezwWv8SlRvcZ43DjNt3_9Xz8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good Taiwanese food here with ordering available through either the app or in person. Dishes are generally good but a little bit too sweet. We tried the rice dish and their boiled curry. Good pick if you are trying to grab food and boba in the same restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqFaLLwN1pPk88UFMWD_afKpM9HJlFZarycPXZ&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Mark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCap4roQc83_yZ-1MBmfeCbe_pnUK3r9NBKni5HgJlcUtNHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"False advertising, makes this place hard to recommend. Sorry in advance for the long post.
I ordered the $14.95 3 sauce chicken bento box for pick up at around 8 pm. I get to the restaurant and grab my order go home open it and find just 3 sauce chicken, not a bento box.
Put the food back in the bag and go back down to the restaurant. My cell service can be spotty so figured maybe the phone did one of those things where a word is missed.
Get back to the restaurant, yes they didn't hear the bento part so I ask for it to be corrected. This is where it gets frustrating!
First I am told that they do not sell the $14.95 bento box after 5pm so I cannot get it. I point out their advertising doesn't say anything about "time specific" so then I am told they are "sold out". I ask if they sell any bento boxes at night and told no but would I like to order a side of white rice for my chicken?
Those are half the elements of a bento box right there!
So I just left with my chicken.
The food was good but shame on Bubble World for deceptive advertising tactics and for the outright lies.
I would forewarn anyone to be careful when looking at any advertised promotions at this restaurant.
Due to my work I eat at restaurants quite often and this is a first in any of my reviews.
I have attached the promotional poster for others.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbtO_1ImM9lL6q-l4hl_w0y4wwU_3gNltydl-O&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been enjoying their Dairy Free (Almond Milk) Bubble Tea specifically The Oreo Milk Tea!

When I'm lazy and don't want to try something new Bubble World is my best bet.

Mixing shrimp & Egg fried rice with Salt and Peppery Chicken Nuggets equals a happy belly.

Their Bubble tea has been #1 compared to anywhere else, I even prefer it over CoCo

Solid Bets:
Shrimp & Egg fried rice
Salt & Peppery Chicken Nuggets
Deep fried Squid Feet
Salty Peppery Squid roll
5 Spiced Beef in Chinese Pancake
Stirfried Noodles w/Beef & Green Onions","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZ4vQf_AHXm9P8RswB5-4IyXJrdd8YV_rQep4r&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2022-1-16"},{"Name":"Sherry Ahmari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzZjpgnbFzMAdoLwNn-kzRLUMAt8kquABzgD2ac3X12G-Wogw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is hands down the worst restaurant for service. They are not able to accommodate a group of more than four people and are so rigid to accommodate. Honestly our birthday event was made into a horrible experience.
Would not add a table because we were a group of six.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7Zgdu_Vfw2otHQMAyxESPXFh418Zc5HSyT9NP&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"–î–∞—Ä–∏–Ω–∞ –°–Ω—ñ–∂–Ω–∞","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV627FxghGf4TOeVPZpUWXijbu7jcIHN9oro9ByB8LwCxlNoGFJZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I can't say anything bad about the food, but I had to wait a long time for the waiter for the order and the bill. And maybe in general my impression would have remained neutral if the waiter had not put my umbrella in a dirty bucket. I find it disrespectful to have such a place for customers umbrellas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9G1yyg4iEB04yDLUiAVlpMZPiM3W8t8-B-JNX&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ate in at Bubble World and prices and portions were not too bad for this economy. The prices in-store is a bit lower than the one you can find on the website which is the opposite case for more restaurants. The rice dishes came with a good amount of side dishes and it was very filling to finish everything. The beef noodle wasn‚Äôt very Taiwanese but it was decent. The seating were booth formats and everyone had their own privacy. You scan a QR code to order your dish which directly goes into the kitchen. A server comes with the items you ordered on a receipt and checks it off as you get them.

There is a small parking lot where you can park but also a larger lot near the Old Navy / GAP.

Called Bubble World for take out. Food was packaged nicely. The popcorn chicken box didn‚Äôt have ventilation, so there was a lot of moisture collecting at the top of the box which wasn‚Äôt a pretty sight. However, the taste was there with the spices. The squid dish was spicy and chewy. The meal combo with rice had a good amount of variety to the dish. Lots of parking in the plaza. Within very close walking distance to Lincoln Station and Coquitlam Centre.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgxJbP7xrVImriXVuTBYo40slurUQbgQS-eDqk&fid=0x0:0x5c2ed58282bdcee3"],"When":"2022-2-8"}]

[{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got takeout Indian food, so I can't speak to the service/atmosphere/pizza, but the food we got was absolutely delicious! Butter chicken, mango chicken, fish curry, pakoras, etc. Just wish they wouldn't use plastic containers (though rice was in aluminum and roti/naan were in foil).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO012on0RBY9PUx8l_CyBmos2vY1Vt3jRQbOSq_&fid=0x0:0xc49ff3cdbd90f076"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Pranav Chaudhary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7is_lqekWtT1oOJ1IgsVp3m9v6mZREQRsu304Slf5pqYjh8E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As long as the ownera are there you'll be take care of well. Otherwise god forbid.
Chole Bhature are way too good. Paneer tikka masala & malai kofta is top notch aswell. Thin crisp garlic naan
Very genuine prices & excellent portion sizes. Owners are hard working genuine people and make sure your service is upto the mark.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBXZJMt4N7q7BoWuoQ0r5TaDlOAaetCdXjs6bH&fid=0x0:0xc49ff3cdbd90f076"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Affordable all day take out menu at $12.95 with 4 selections of non-vegetarian and vegetarian options to choose from. All of the option come with naan and rice. We ordered the butter chicken and the dal makhani. The butter chicken didn‚Äôt come with a lot of chicken, but the sauce was creamy with a good amount of butter and tomato paste. The dal makhani was smooth and very flavourful. Only downside was that we ordered the vegetarian samosa and they forgot to pack it in the to-go order and we didn‚Äôt find out until we got home. Lots of parking by that street.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMq5Yu8FUUxckXc27FhShf1RBmlAnRVGeUswmYS&fid=0x0:0xc49ff3cdbd90f076"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Sean Colcleugh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFaf1nnb7gwzav3JhIX_9bXSvJUwR3vNP3QK5zCIdEn5kwECMNnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent Service.

Ordered off Uber Eats in a rain storm. Received a call from the restaurant informing me that half the order was left behind by the Driver.

They then offered to drop it off personally as fast as they can. They arrived shortly after the Uber Driver with the complete order and refused tip apologizing even though it was not their error.

Made quite the impression.

Food was also excellent.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rajiv Malik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX31ZLdiw7N503Bd1ScRD6q0to5duo7pt1JVXwwi-UjEfl1T4cscw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our small get together about 20 people last week where both vegetarian and non vegetarian dishes were served from this small little gem of a restaurant. The food was so flavourful and authentic Indian that everyone at the gathering liked it and got surprised that it was not from Surrey..!! (Hahahaha). We enjoyed a lot and our evening became more delightful and would have been possible with all the efforts from the team out there from the Kitchen and yes, the owners made sure everything is perfectly one to deliver the food hot and fresh..! Thank you everyone..! We would definitely be back, keep spreading the joy of serving the best Indian food in town..!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ivy tsui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaTNfE22zKppVepK8QuwPVJfhGTGB2oYsmzZ3iwDLz3Z2C06S7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Indian take out ever, highly recommend the lamb curry and the butter chicken, take out is the best way to have it, there is a sit down area but honestly the soul of this place is the food ! 10/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alisa White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV9LkxCq3711Jv26RfJzr_m51wR4AfYC0Y2hjgj_MRqXSmSklt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Owners are friendly and the food is great. They don't use any cheap bulk precooked ingredients like some of the other Indian places in the area
Very reasonable price for pickup
The only thing that might be a surprise is that their pizza is very salty, but I believe that's a stylistic choice. It makes it quite good with a beer","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Ballantyne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVafdnWTPA396rdDrZ6xQUNbYelyGkRkEN10Mc7RD41RectIZF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was amazing.
Haven't been there for a while and it still has the best of everything to offer.

[{"Name":"Peter Ryu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIA1mPJxqbAq3sA5Yx2oELWcSP1BdJp83hRCQqxHH8j4y2zYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for breakfast on Tuesday.
Service was good.
The food was so good. We had rice noodle w/ minced beef and parsley. Soup was hitting the spot.
Creamy seafood was good. Added some white pepper for seasoning.
The chicken steak sandwich is so good. Their chicken steak is a must try.
Great price, less than $30 for 3 items.
My gf and I left very full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4icTkTUUv9JDkn2JtXGDZMAMx_I3hwCSyteyy&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service‚Äîquick and friendly! We ordered the BBQ pork, shrimp fried rice, noodles, and meat poutine, and the generous servings lasted for days. Loved the ambiance and the extensive menu selection. Will definitely come back to try more items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv9VLbM7Eayn1Tn58vlSESqVHJeByNmFCEMrlt&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Johnny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMH8aFZIGB5a7CFStbNQ6JGT0sYgxOttD7xMtIebcz8N9tnSzq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Typical Hong Kong style cafe.  Sometimes difficult to find parking because lot is share with other businesses.  Food is OK but prices have gone up a bit since the pandemic.  Food and drink arrive quickly.  There are some elbow room between tables unlike other restaurants that‚Äôs elbow to elbow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP9Yp6b7U-wMOA3h89pt4AgqSR2112vjBXwLXE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Copa (cup) of disappointment‚Ä¶

Picking up something in the Poco area and was deciding on some Korean food or this place. In the end, decided on this place since it‚Äôs been decade or longer since I have been to this place.

Upon entering, it seems like the interior went through a bit of change and renovation. The place was pretty empty except for 3 booths seated with customers, maybe it was near closing time (1.5hrs before closing). Everything appeared to be clean throughout the restaurant with a comfortable spacing between the tables and booths.

The service was subpar from the server, maybe she was more focused on cleaning and getting off work. When the owner/ manager took over, it was a lot better and she was more polite.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Sizzling Hot plate combo B+B (chicken steak & sausages) with borscht soup, spaghetti , cold lemon tea. The chicken was a little dry and the soup was a bit off and warm only. And the hot plate didn‚Äôt sizzle at all, maybe a 3 second frisk sound?
2. Sizzling hot place combo A+B (filet mignon & deep fried oysters) with lobster bisque, steamed rice, add lobster tail $23 extra. The filet mignon was horrible, first time ever struggling to chew a filet mignon, it was dry and didn‚Äôt taste fresh. The oysters were little midgets. The steamed rice was more like overnight rice just added a bit of water and a quick heat up by the microwave, it was dry and hard. And lastly the lobster tail was horrible; it had that bad fishy taste to it, one tiny bite from that and had to stop cause not worth food poisoning myself from it. And once again the sizzling plate wasn‚Äôt even warm!! (Facepalm) The only thing okay was the lobster bisque.

Overall, I was quite disappointed with the food. I don‚Äôt remember it being this bad? What happened? Closer to closing time and whoever the cook in the kitchen was didn‚Äôt give 2 cents about the food being served? Is it really that hard to hire a decent cook nowadays after the pandemic? And for crying out loud, it only takes 30 seconds to heat up the iron plates and how can one pawn off such a bad bowl of rice in a Chinese restaurant? I honestly would send this cook packing for retirement if working for me, definitely wouldn‚Äôt tolerate this kind of bs jeopardizing my business.

I guess I retained my good nature and composure by taking into consideration that the owner/manager was very polite and friendly; very poise and elegant with the services. I guess that‚Äôs the only good part of this experience and kept my positivity inlined. Just enjoyed a quick instant noodle when back home lol","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMcEYpyZUuanHEcQL55fa0WprgsuAX0S3V4h87&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-25"},{"Name":"Chang Wun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXinnRETbtdmwq0G3dzHpocXq4c0y1kT8tCLTmXT5-MPrsCx3WH9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went back for the breakfast. There are a lots of people in the breakfast timing, the breakfast set is cost effective! Will revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPglBpXDu8S3-D1K1Vx9zNGj1s7HzGBk70B8aKE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"Angie L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwNm9A8ohrfnu_XFwYhP8N-ACXPuzjT8lHAp_d40ZyvMetcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is Hong Kong style fusion restaurant. The selection is quite good for anything from appetizers, steak and fries, to noodles, rice, soup, combos and beverages.

There's Western style combo that comes with soup, main and drink & Asian style combo comes with Chinese soup, main and rice, no drink. You may think the price is on the high side but you won't disappoint by the portion.

Service is not bad but when is not busy. They are not dial in.

They charge $0.50 per take out container that I have no complaint to support the environmental recycling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDjOVajotJjtkKeh90GhichQoqjYaMOeW4VKP9&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-1-2"},{"Name":"Nathan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6aOctokU9KmE5fwo6-6THfOky0imQyJSKP9b0jCAM3iXNSZtK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Low price, good food. What more can I say? I love Hong Kong food. Copa Cafe has good service, the waiters are attentive, friendly, and efficient.

One time, we came here late at night and they still received us and were patient despite us staying beyond their closing time. I‚Äôll always remember the staff‚Äôs patience and hospitality.

As you can tell, I really like their noodles üòÇüçú","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmD0avsIDuv7S0oR3k1m2RCOwZwtXixWPr-ed3&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-12-15"},{"Name":"Bespoke Happier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_JY_sOUqfgLP_sU_CBSIZzGgEmarbG08tg34uKbeN8ljU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Copa Cafe, a popular Hong Kong-style restaurant in Vancouver, is a hidden gem that I frequent when I'm in the mood for a hearty meal. Although there are only two other Hong Kong-style restaurants in Coquitlam, I prefer Copa Cafe for its extensive menu options and exceptional service compared to its competitors. If you become a member, which costs $15 per year, you can enjoy a 10% discount on all orders, which is a great deal.

One of the highlights of Copa Cafe is their breakfast menu, which boasts generous portions that won't hurt your wallet despite the current high prices. On my recent visit, I opted for the satay beef noodle and shared the cheese, spinach, and bacon omelette with my husband. We also ordered two cups of their famous Hong Kong-style milk tea. After applying the 10% membership discount, our bill was a reasonable $23 with the tip included.

Overall, we were pleased with both the quality and quantity of our breakfast. The flavors were satisfactory, and the portions were generous. Copa Cafe is a must-visit spot for anyone who loves Hong Kong-style cuisine and wants to try something new. The ambiance is cozy, and the service is top-notch, making it an ideal spot for a date or a casual gathering with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSzLi3djIKGAYOhylqv9qdoGJbTHEE6Sfx7hU&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]

[{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff are friendly, but they might not check on you often, so they may miss refilling your water. The quality and taste of the food are okay. However, the gheimeh stew on tahdig was served cold, some parts of the meat were still cold, suggesting it wasn't freshly made or properly warmed up. Kashke bademjon was beautifully designed. The menu offers a good variety of options. Overall, it was an okay experience, with some room for improvement. The portions are big, and there's plenty of space to seat large groups. Plus, there's free parking right in front.The decor is nice, featuring some traditional Persian carpets on the walls.

Totally recommend ordering the dogh. It was so creamy and delicious","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMS8kS3M67NNGNn9x3D7RRXzV_nyU5m94YWXi-w&fid=0x0:0xb534928a10c38264"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Vahid Heydarinia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUm3lYhqP-_BPvMwccMRgnhyMaGZHw9udBZ7-ueoyezFBzXZaWT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good service, decent portions and tasty food. But the service here is not great, our server had hard time understanding what we were asking for & we had to repeat ourselves multiple times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKlg25C6EnRD6b2logAbAhpYWsmn3c638F9vGf&fid=0x0:0xb534928a10c38264"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"Mehrnaz K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoZN7J_sk0wIMGc2sUJff_Htg_dmYOLYdOzdXJizxuarKYwltq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was great, and the portions were large, enough for a very hungry person üòã

Prices are a little on the high side, but with the large portion, you can probably share a meal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"alireza moayer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKO8XW0SORedha2U9XPmnXFan_Fx8L3K2Fs5T76Q1YGNMalQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a lunch meeting there with our team members.
The service is amazing, and the customer service was perfect.
The food was very yummy and nice and clean.
The portions were bigger than normal.
The workers were very friendly.

[{"Name":"Kimia Abtahi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2CE2uN5zYA5-Ne2mDlfB8HQlAxJSeFJKc2I3kIPxW8BoK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We recently visited Red Robin and tried their burgers, onion rings, and dessert. For the main course, we ordered a Red Robin burger, a chicken burger, and onion rings. The burgers were incredibly juicy, and I especially enjoyed the chicken burger. The onion rings were also fresh, crispy, and a great portion size for our group of four.

For dessert, we had a fudge cake with ice cream, which was a delightful way to end the meal.

What truly stood out, however, was the amazing service we received. Our waiter was exceptionally kind and friendly, making us feel very comfortable throughout the meal. Her attentiveness and warm attitude made our dining experience even more enjoyable and efficient.

Overall, a great experience with tasty food and top-notch service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyQ1bSzfAHrgI_7n7PzzGYnOJ5hoJkHYJpvv8&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Never had a burger that looked so depressing, that it probably wished it wasn‚Äôt made.

We had high hopes on trying more of Red Robin‚Äôs finest burgers, but those hopes took a swan dive off the lions gate bridge.

How a burger could be made and look the total opposite of the photo on the menu just boggles my mind. Did the burger master decide to just call it a day with mine? Because the other burgers in our group sure as heck looked a lot better.

I‚Äôd rate my meal a -10 out of 10.

Service was great though. A lot faster than our previous visits.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNULnsGJpOHxYsZjahAn2VSuxoUZ3z-eN5s_p7E&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Allen Beik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF9ADaYp8aM_t6ClRm3K9sF-sNZrKMskbGaiszRmMLDyZbTDv5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently visited Red Robin and had a pleasant experience. The food was tasty, though a bit on the oily side. The atmosphere was warm and welcoming, making it a comfortable spot to enjoy a meal. Overall, I‚Äôd give it four stars!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUkSIzZELbfGV1ee1uwobQvNoLpSzFkBuza5f0&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Sam Goh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKE5mTKD61HIgHQk8dxPyuoRqeGbk2g-M7HwnIwadO5n9CEZ1k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came for lunch and Stephen took care of us.  Really good service with him. We had the Queso Lava burger as well as the blackened chicken burger and both were excellent!  Can‚Äôt beat endless fries with Red Robin‚Äôs own seasoning salt!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwuTv3mieo1ZqGasUlGc3kO1I4ArtVPWR2FPpZ&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"G W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVG1FFo9GTnRGQNpjln74dhjBn3V4nGRQE_Yjur_OV6HYJsv04F_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Well as an Original Red Robin waiter from the 80's.  WOW so bad. I paid $23. for a small piece of salmon and broccoli. Salmon was tiny and the broccoli was cold. Why?!!!! I think the server has so many tables she forgot about us. No refills, quality check on time food came slowly.  I'm so sad all the Great food choices are gone!! My 95 year old father even called after to complain and all they had to say for his $200. bill was "sorry"
Did I mention the discussing bathroom, piss all over and the place stinks! He didn't clean and check washrooms!  I will not be back, sadly.
COQUITLAM GRILL, 10X THE FOOD AND SERVICE.  Bye RED.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsb6TiqSmI_znsP3--Zw_yiYWZLDvk85CbbgI_&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Shuja Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEBorCT1xB53Ohf-r3sasYNY3f1aLK2cvkUGn0blmUthajlwZj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went in to this place because my friend had an account and they give a free burger on your birthday. Burgers were nice and juicy, the fries both yam and regular tasted very good, the seasoning on the fries was standout. What‚Äôs amazing is that they offer bottomless sides so you can keep enjoying. I asked for our fries to be served first so we can get going while we wait for our burgers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCVPc3NX_1XU5BPKtEwntyVWkLc6dTpo_OtlNx&fid=0x0:0x15816451600c2b52"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Hillbillytc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV833YeKMKJfxtYeKhRHVRSrikZoFOcCapKBwyEFBOnxiCMeXAZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The server was amazing. Normally, I'm not a big fan of tempura due to its greasiness, but theirs was a game-changer. It was so fresh and perfectly crispy, leaving me thoroughly satisfied.

I can't recommend this place highly enough. It isn't awful but it's the tiniest most expensive donair I've ever had
Not worth it will not return","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpUDbM_OYMzPBiiBOt-5z-hhVIEyoMqIh70Znm&fid=0x0:0x73cbd87c93d2aa0d"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Al So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLumQHIv-5W9wXPr4ZbA1zWCVnPk2w1Kc3bjsO93-VMG-v7JQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been going to Shawarma House now for quite a while. It is a Lebanese Style shawarma shop and has lots of flavours. The owner is really nice and the staff were are great to deal with. Since this owner took over from Krispy Falafel they introduced many different types of flavours of middle Eastern cuisine. When ordering the plate I like to have the mixed plate with üêë lamb and üêîüçó chicken mixed. It $18 so not the cheapest, but it's allot of food and can feed 2 average sized people or 2 meals for me at least. What I like about this place the best is that the food is reliable each time I've ordered I've come to expect the same quality quantity and service. Not in the pic but there fries are really good, they sprinkle their spices on them and it's good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkC-7SCh6o4JYQVF4UTGIsP7uHVTC_E8H4RRjv&fid=0x0:0x73cbd87c93d2aa0d"],"When":"2023-5-13"},{"Name":"John M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWItgijJKwgA0f52g38y2veJk-Ddfx32Y6n5pRa8jqM3m7RR0lStA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Got the chicken plate which came with chicken, rice, hummus, pita bread and a salad of your choosing. I really liked the hummus and salad! They both tasted freshly prepared and the hummus was smooth. I found the chicken quite dry and couldn't finish it though.

Didn't find anything wrong with the service and nothing spectacular either. Just an average experience.

In terms of atmosphere, they had tables and chairs that you could use to dine in. Again nothing really special but it's nice that you have the option if you wanted to dine in.

I found the price point on the expensive side for what you get compared with other similar shops.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhlSSfnoBNJZ42v6b-XJH1VYzd6eEfy8VtMHom&fid=0x0:0x73cbd87c93d2aa0d"],"When":"2023-9-6"},{"Name":"Scott Phillips","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTiIcwbuuh4QkXoj1cJb_o58UJZ7vG1oxrCvOCaizEwz_9KyGNzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It's been a while since I have ordered a Donair but my mixed chicken/beef came in at $14 and was gone in a literal 14 bites! The kobide and kashke bademjan were absolutely delicious‚Äîthe kobide was juicy, perfectly seasoned, and made with fresh, high-quality meat, while the kashke bademjan had a rich, creamy texture and a perfect balance of flavors.

Beyond the incredible food, the customer service was top-notch, with friendly and attentive staff who made the entire experience even more enjoyable. This spot truly stands out as one of the best in the area for Afghan-Persian dishes. I can confidently say I‚Äôll be coming back for more.

The food was excellent! I ordered the Vaziri, which came with rice, salad, 1 skewer of boneless chicken kebab, and 1 skewer of beef kebab. It was delicious, freshly made, tender, and juicy. Service was a bit slow but understandable, and pricing seems very reasonable.

The decor is casual, with only a few tables, making it a cozy spot rather than a fancy dining experience. However, the focus is clearly on the food quality and taste, which deserves a solid 5 stars.

There's plenty of parking available, and the restaurant is conveniently located behind the "Day 2 Day Halal Grocery" store.

Overall, it's a great option for a satisfying and flavorful halal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs-CtF-t8p6d__qbtNWKvWHOGFoIGHiSzG-wTQ&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"Adam Cartwright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsKnCsOP-0T-zwsfA634EBIBcODT2U7_gjSIBsfbKoL7ngRw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Buddy took me here for a bite to eat. Here‚Äôs a glowing review for Day to Day Restaurant in Port Coquitlam:

‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Day to Day Restaurant in Port Coquitlam, and I must say, it was a truly delightful experience from start to finish! From the moment I walked in, the warm and inviting ambiance set the tone for a wonderful meal.

All staffs really nice and friendly,Specially Sonia and Hamed üåπ,thank you so much

The food at Day to Day is nothing short of spectacular. Every dish we tried was bursting with flavor and prepared to perfection. It's clear that the chefs use high-quality ingredients, and their passion for creating delicious food shines through in every bite. The menu offers a fantastic variety, ensuring there's something to satisfy every palate.

In addition to the delectable food, the service was outstanding. The staff were incredibly friendly, attentive, and eager to make our dining experience enjoyable. They were knowledgeable about the menu and provided excellent recommendations.

Day to Day Restaurant has quickly become a favorite spot for me in Port Coquitlam, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience. Whether you're there for a casual lunch or a special dinner, you can expect top-notch food and service. I can't wait to return and explore more of their amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObswPg8l3CZK5x4spVMzuhtyJXbbQV3iGZNT4I&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-6-6"}]

I love this spot. I've been going here for the last 15 years or so. I was introduced to Pizza Factory by a friend telling me about their Monday pizza special a Large 2-Topping pizza for $11.98 (,pick up only) The toppings are premium, the crust is on point, and it's not over cooked. They offer various specials everyday of the week
They also offer Indian dishes, pastas, and wings. I would have given 5 stars but the wings aren't really anything special or memorable but when those improve they will get that 5th star.
The staff are friendly, welcoming and really appreciate their customers.  Give them a try you won't be disappointed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItsk8TaWY-bgEdARRPgnrRBpwZ2F6MpE5TS8rdDn2mvHmHlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today, in the afternoon, I ordered a pizza and was pleasantly surprised to learn that the person ahead of me had already paid for my order. He had left before I entered the restaurant. I am deeply grateful for their generosity; their act of kindness truly brightened my day, making the pizza even more special.

I would also like to extend my gratitude to Gina for her excellent service and for facilitating this unexpected gift.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKZxRrfm7QrUJXQp_a3iGr51Xh3gdqjtk2JsO9&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-3-26"},{"Name":"Gary S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbwfFqaCkOn1VbU76HFhDcbA_7j2OWGRTuW1QlH9kSO3wvLsk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has become our favourite pizza joint around this neighborhood. We first came here because we had to wait for our food next door then we saw the 9.99 medium 2 toppings walk in special, so we gave it a try.. since then, we had been back almost every week. Pizza is delicious. Perfect crust. Sauce is super tasty. Right amount of cheese and toppings. Jst amazing. We also tried the Indian food one time and they were good. Service is also top-notch. Kudos guys :D","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Evelyn Nie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnnZak8L0h58i8GPwlEL93KsUuO9alR-EbBWfg-W2mWudr8yE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Your pizza is delicious, your service is amazing and it's worth buying back many times","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-uHPORZ7a7LefDunKZ34cUy1Re8QQwWNy-WDO&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Emmanuel Mor√∫a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVgDDr7Bq5maIJYTC_on0x6OlVE8ViM6rt1o7JGzQMU2HdiVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super cheap, very delicious, extra hot and super cheesy pizza. I paid no more than $18 and got a whole large pizza, jarritos pop and a dipping sauce, honestly you don‚Äôt see prices like these anymore. My pizza was ham and pepperoni, ham was set up in one big piece under the first layer of cheese, never had it like that before, it was odd to me but definitely loved it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWy2bIHrcbbq4vp96vJR_PS1FVhsLzufPuMyqU&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Brendon Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwVwAOeHIXcmr9314sP51Aq_8-OvMrjaGARJ6YSAF1fH5wVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went in to order our pizza and butter chicken.

Butter chicken was alright but the pizza was overly salted. Called in and spoke with Anmol, she mentioned that they are closed now. So there goes our dinner. Had to order late night food so we spent more on dinner.

Anmol doesn't have the best customer service either. She said to call back and talk to the manager. Basically brushing my concerns off and not giving proper reassurance of what's next.

Probably won't buy from here again. The taste of the pizza really does reflect on there cheap price.

Also pizza places need to stay open longer. Not close at 11pm. Another downside.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Deb PS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JrjvxBJWPrjHCwBxV9NiRybb9V5GJpynDBuSW5sd6snYZiMa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is a very unassuming place. I would have never guessed it looked like this inside based on the exterior. It was very clean and the staff was super friendly with a great sense of humour.  The food was also very flavourful.  We all enjoyed our meal very much for not being a high end restaurant. Prices were very reasonable as well. Will be back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCVOc1V1GanW0vAfXOMHxUlD7OXgwln2QuHrH_&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Ton V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb4h6oZDMjakZ7o0kpJmjp_i41AvhfJ62KCrl6wCnDvytBpv4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hadn‚Äôt been for a while. Food was really good and service super friendly. Good size portions. I would prefer a menu with pictures though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxcvuP86fZtjp3Yr1fSFBnF1sXV3XGZII_RYI&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Ricardo Amanda Paliotti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1-tWR3oImGXb1bh0eJaBkqqB4lKa--eRLaWv99DtP2gOoadI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellently executed every time we visit. Flavors are on point. Always fun times there ! ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ / Dec. 15th Sun 2024","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFnUCp9_Bgr50_ywSBFmDWPht7MdMv6uwMz8wv&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place has been here since I was a kid. Glad to see it's still here and I'm visiting again after 20+ years. All I remember was that I liked their hot and sour soup.

Not really an authentic Szechuan restaurant. 30 years ago, most chinese cuisines were cooked by hong kongers or south chinese people. So, most of these dishes are going to be a southern take on it.

Hot and sour soup - price is awesome. $11 enough for at least 6 bowls. Souo base is missing a bit of flavor but it is jam packed with ingredients.

Drunken chicken - it was ok. Little on the salty side.

Shanghainese pan fried pork buns - these were probably the worst I've had. Not made in house and not properly pan fried. No juice, super dry, no fried bottom crust.

Bean curd wrapped pork dim sum - surprisingly this came out last. At least 20 min has passed. This is a steamed dish but it came out with dried edges like it was sitting on a dry heater. Taste was ok.

Mapo tofu - asked for extra spicy and extra numbing. Numbing was there but nowhere near real szechuan numbing. Was not spicy at all. Sauce was more oily than saucey.

The price point reflects the quality. Things are either mediocre or a complete miss. Would come again to try only the better stuff. Staff was friendly. Came to try to refill the tea way more times than normal. The iron goddess tea tastes much better than a lot of dim sum places elsewhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsyXtmZVjFTpSM7j5XHpsMqasJjiN51hrkn9sk&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Sarah Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P_FT3n0HZdmLMDEJ6UcRFNPyHbE7QJ8GW3gOL-SGGTFh-sFdQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good Chinese food, some of the best we‚Äôve tried! Brought my family of 18 there and everyone had a very positive review to leave. The restaurant is clean, nicely decorated and the service is phenomenal, on top of amazing Chinese food. 100% recommend. Accommodated us no problem and efficiently being a large group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Zm-hsHEcTAf_11Ju8D7ypxHDl4umZ6xffmp0&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I have been craving for a good Chinese food. We have done take out here many times before,  it's our first time dining in actually.   I am so amazed on how good the service is at this restaurant. Food came out fast and it was delicious.  Did not disappoint üôå.  Thank you wahwing, we will definitely dine in again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVB0fCOEp8ge2kh842Ux2XpFXVwgqLutUtBbEG&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUamHxgbXpYwrJI1uE5cJUYfe1wmxOQk5ygeSabzKwSDEQZmU3C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my first time to dine in at this restaurant. The service is good but the food need some improvement. I ordered a noodle but the soup base taste salty . Chef should put less salt or no salt since the veggie already taste salty and the Chinese broccoli taste not much flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCpErihv2HeGr4hQralU6fnwyOSS6XRaqyldOu&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"Julio Cipriano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdiL69VWk_HhrY9vvXJcaFkLa2z0igCrSjghxutPFMYl05ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going or ordering from here for 20+ years. Can‚Äôt remember a less than great meal!  Same applies today for lunch ginger beef, pork buns, even something simple like spring rolls all 5 *.  Tried the fried banana balls  and mango ice cream.  So so good!  Staff went out of their way to make sure my mother (little older) was taken care of. [{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There was only one staff in the early morning but he was extremely efficient. The cranberry turkey sandwich was surprisingly delicious. Cream inside pistachio bun was on the sweeter side but would be a good choice as dessert. Wish price can be lower, so that I can come back regularly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxEsqgdYQlHDlZlCYuy0cl7Drwho52YwlHjKCh&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Danilo Teodoro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rV4_xok36vIezJ6uAhpzSfyECA8ogmjA4ehyXVTr4dBqIAFv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time I tried their bun with pistachio and the turkey bagel, and they were good! The cappuccino was good as well. I tried the Turkish coffee just because it's been years since the last one, and it was very strong, as usual. I'm glad I knew how this type of coffee is made and didn't stir the liquid.
The toilets needed some love..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHVVDDLtjxI1rM7Dy_3mg1tubzrGtmjT7wNGaz&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Alecia Hack","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0y1s7Bm_wrj5Zk4QFomT2h-qOh3c4CJw37lBhykQlV1HXtuw4ww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve come here a couple of times and I‚Äôm completely obsessed with this place! I had the pistachio coffee bun and a salted caramel latte last time I was in, and while I wasn‚Äôt expecting the size, it was such an incredible treat. Cant wait to go back soon, thanks for a great experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyHEfOUN4bSSLdn0q7eE6t88Gu1R7qdGPR22CG&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Mavis Gevido","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVC-AP02ZE-ah41YCH68XbacnGEFbWfIc3R3T9FQiOBp_VcLYiP_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of coffee buns and the ones we tried were all so good! Relaxing atmosphere, good space. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUNszxgua9dx1DrmJ42Rm939D2PVomTSIp69Fc&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the concept of their buns. They have a lot of different flavors, and I tried the pistachio one. The bun is better than what I expected-- I expected a flavorless, chewy/tough bun but it had a great fried flavor and chew to it, made indulgent by the toppings of cream and pistachios.
I also had a toasted salmon lox bagel which had a generous amount of cream cheese, I loved every bit of it.
Very friendly and welcoming service!
It was quite busy.
I would definitely come back if I were in the area üòÜ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMEcOHD1pKqbcUepyj1ihb-fvVuAsZ3n-9iqr_&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Zaayer Nasib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkh0fpj6mvCROx8j1Ux0TdNtszR1GgFfGTRvlt6JMDCheOJwvK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ratings Scale 0 - 10
Variety: 8
Service or Product: 8
Customer Service: 8
Environment: 8
Cleaning: 8
Washroom: 7
Cost: 7

Tried a few of the buns, all of which were served fresh and hot! The ice cream bun was a delightful experience of warm bun and cold ice cream, but you have to be a little quick otherwise it starts melting really fast. The drinks were equally yummy. I had the hot chocolate which was perfect!
They have plenty of tables which was pretty good since there were quite a few people. There's only paid parking nearby though which was the only negative I see.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0IOQFvGUF-_OZnnytcmsz4gQreANuw04M0Tk6&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2021-5-16"},{"Name":"La Mc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3bmuxSiXCjm1iot5JpVUU_Lxxw4iPTmDpAUVL9Q9e-760ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute place with fresh buns!

Very bright location with a few tables outside.

Need to come back and try other flavours!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQryY1DW2BwXBGxMAb_y7tat0BDpJD4G0vlOCs&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Rochelle Barrett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfUfMrQqNwSQLSz_oSIsTrz93OXwAr4KrdgHWS4xUKxTxBh4cgIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first visit, despite living at the opposite end of the block!

I was there just after open and it was very quiet. I was able to stare at the menu without pressure, which I appreciated.

I got their Spanish latte. I'm not sure I have ever loved a coffee more. It was so dark and rich coffee flavours. I considered proposing to the barista, it was that good.

I hear their Turkey sandwich on cranberry sourdough, absolutely drool worthy!!! Creamy, savoury and sweet, perfect balance and the sour of the sourdough came through just enough.

Lastly, I had the gluten ginger cookie they out sourced from Wendell's. I did not love it. It was grainy but not their fault and I really appreciate they bring in options for multiple dietary requirements.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvTAeW_Ad9YU9AOS6XyvZZ8C-blZKGBy516Jo6&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2021-6-13"}]
