[{"Name":"SylverscreenArts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXulb8lBMEyh77llMzSuNBPq0Y3PJ79kx2d0ad9bIm1D3BdKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing view, great place for meeting, weddings and parties. The outdoor is perfect for that destination wedding, a great bond for nature lovers, a Golfers nest. The staff are warm and friendly, very supportive, positive vibes. Great attention to details. And a great place to relax or hold short meetings outside office. It's indeed a great place to visit. The mountain view and the green vegetation is like a mini paradise.  I will recommend this place any time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFF7RYptgXdxXmn36_au-zsmp0QBonoGIjljs&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"T.J. Hatten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVOLMVb24vyK1YFvD0fD9FRFgcvInujAC77z1dMK_hF2UlhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a great course to golf. Both fun and challenging with some great elevations. The clubhouse is well run, staff are knowledgeable and friendly. Highly recommended this course if you‚Äôre looking to have some fun experiencing a new course and challenging yourself and if you have a morning Tee time make sure to get their breakfast sandwich, it‚Äôs a great way to start your round.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX252unc4TTVkrFHvTKjhe9MulxwyzzHFfV11L&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"William Weissig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrNXc3fo0JyuPHUboE7J5f28BCwV75YBHCPbj2rWiKGZWsN4oi=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sylvia and Jayden helped set things up and coordinated for our wedding. They did a fantasic job and we have remarkable memories for the rest of our lives, thanks to their services.

We would definately recommend them as top workers who are great at wedding planning! Thanks a lot!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMe90ZvOc6zd1SpgYI62qfzfaWEnUaFiTtOqxrB&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Jalen Sekhon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq1XiBH92zFuiFtCb_QVoX4RoDeUFm_uYKWZgjITl7PxOn110=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The ‚Äúmarshall‚Äù said ‚Äúyou played a slow round‚Äù to me as I finished a sandy golfing experience. He verified that our round was 2 hours to play the 9 hole exec course. We had 4 walkers and we were up against the group in front of us the whole round. The round was fun despite the sandy covering the greens.. but I am shocked that a ‚Äúmarshall‚Äù would say that to me when he clearly saw the group in front of us just walk off. I think he would have gotten more data on the pace of play areas of concern by giving feed back to people mid round. I would have wanted a more warm and friendly guest experience than that, and certainly feedback from the ‚Äúmarshall‚Äô about our pace of play that actually made logical sense.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEEAL9Sl0nR7Hzve6jlrEl6K3yW4ubHTjxZfrW&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Ralph McLennan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrZ02oyygmsqSGGsqmF1szgrz-yPF3IvDkZC4IW16vCFUxAq9t=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We played on Monday morning June 24 2024, pro shop staff and starter were welcoming and informative (warned us we may come across a bear and made sure we had no food in the cart). We did come across the bear on the picturesque 3rd hole ! Course was in great shape, played in less than 4 hours. Had a great time with the twosome we were paired with (Dave & Julie) !! Will definitely be back this summer !! Thanks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOH7o8PuNHvguzLKrjPNp5HKbR0LFBgo2IonpH3&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"D√´min Photography (Wedding Photographer)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAzZoBizu3g6fBece5zJLjGQxh8xQ2ZfhWDhSKPwt7Zp1Qwkmpow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of photographing weddings at this stunning venue. The high ceilings in all of the halls and ballrooms create an elegant and spacious atmosphere, and the huge windows allow for natural light to pour in, making for exceptional photo opportunities. The outdoor ceremony options and bride and groom session areas are also fantastic, providing an abundance of picturesque settings.
The staff at this venue are very helpful, going above and beyond to ensure that everything runs smoothly and efficiently. The quality and variety of the food is also outstanding.
Overall, I would highly recommend this venue to anyone looking for a memorable and exquisite wedding experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuQWHeTjvNDzEbE84r3SjQwMjFNWRMyH6ML_7G&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2023-3-17"},{"Name":"Rob Boyle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULkY7_3AudI1Xn76AMW8uXeaTp75rSDuuXFRwd84yupHS7bF7_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I played Westwood Plateau (the full length course) for the first time ever. It was great. Westwood Plateau is literally in the mountains of Coquitlam and the views are amazing. The holes are challenging too. The neat thing is one can choose from a variety of tees. A top pro can choose the back tees at about 6800 yards whereas a newbie can choose the forward tees at about 5000 yards. I went with the middle tees. The conditioning of the course was pretty good for April. A little wet but we played the ‚Äúpreferred lies rule.‚Äù They have a super amount of sand bunkers. Unfortunately there were a lot of stones in those bunkers which have to be dealt with. Actually, do you know what the solution is? Don‚Äôt hit into them ü§£. There is a hitting cage to warm up but if you want to practice, you‚Äôll have to do that at Westwood‚Äôs driving range and Executive course a mile or two away. By the way, the clubhouse is awesome and they have super food.  Overall, it was a very nice experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeCfz7lBeO0gWdTweXR0qihre3PFlnxgA-qvo_&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2023-4-30"},{"Name":"Philip Bentham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvCsZHcboVwOKcvYf3W188SQ0Qr6C6tSw3blyb-BqxpJMhnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered drinks and one came out after 20 minutes. The second didn't come for another 5-10 minutes. Very strange. We ordered the roasted red pepper queso and 75% of the chips were obliterated to the point where you couldn't even pick them up.

The servers were all lovely.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Ca Media","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrWY3NtfDMrrfIyiF99Bkud8n1enS71zA5IqjAZySXq1LlIpY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I am deeply disgusted and upset by my experience at this restaurant, both due to what I found in my food and the owner's rude response. While we were halfway through our fries, waiting for the main course, we discovered a chicken bone among them‚Äîsomething that appeared to be part of someone‚Äôs leftovers.

When I brought this to the owner's attention, rather than apologizing, she attempted to justify the contamination. She argued that the chicken bone might have ended up in our fries because the same deep-fry basket and oil were used for both chicken and fries. Even if this explanation were accurate, it is entirely unacceptable and unhygienic.

We left the restaurant without receiving a proper apology, feeling unheard and disrespected. This experience was not only unpleasant but also concerning from a food safety perspective.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6dC70QDNbKSMRKLJ3G9IecJr0_mOmJ0pXMDMB&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"peyman alamesh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIh14BLAkO2Ok8oQuCYa5ZqPQcRZqabouP1Xpr0AFYX6chAaA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"‚ÄúAn Unforgettable Culinary Experience!‚Äù
I recently had the pleasure of dining at [restaurant name], and it was truly a memorable experience. From the moment we walked in, the warm and welcoming ambiance set the tone for a perfect evening.

The food was absolutely incredible‚Äîevery dish was a celebration of authentic Iranian flavors. The kebabs were perfectly grilled, tender, and flavorful, while the saffron rice and tahdig were cooked to perfection. The appetizers, especially the kashk-e bademjan and mast-o khiar, were a delightful start to the meal.

The service was exceptional, with friendly and attentive staff who went above and beyond to make sure everything was perfect. The attention to detail in both the food presentation and hospitality was impressive.

If you‚Äôre looking to enjoy a taste of Persian culture and cuisine, this restaurant is a must-visit. I can‚Äôt wait to come back and try more dishes!

Feel free to personalize it based on your specific experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRC2TAD0zbwIAOV3v0qY2ELBDr7kKstsL-psxY&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Limping Ninja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEnsg6wB_b4XFmIHZf5Dk-Fs3hq6WGzzbCBHgVgDVv5FAQ28Bfqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lovely atmosphere, very nice tasting lamb and well cooked rice, with a smile and attentive staff - what more can you ask for!

The food took longer to come out, but it was freshly made and the portions are fantastic. Thank you TiTi!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPicqUikH6VXF3GIAu3yXi5zt6IDGwGQyrDIY5U&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"Negin Rahimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4DUUoCWRf2VeIHKqwIhVGBDp6aPH06WL8KyLGIL_eC6FWBXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had an intense craving for Persian-style pizza, and my taste buds were blown away when a friend suggested I try Titi Restaurant. This is not only offers a diverse range of delectable dishes, including pizza and chicken kebab, but their cooking is simply divine. The quality, portion size, and flavors of the dishes were absolutely fantastic. Everything exceeded my expectations in terms of taste and presentation. On a late-night pickup, I was pleasantly surprised by the warm hospitality of the owners and the kind-hearted staff, who despite their exhaustion, treated me with the utmost kindness. While waiting for my order, I engaged in a delightful conversation with them. I cannot emphasize enough how highly I recommend this restaurant. You simply have to try their entire menu. Congrats to the team at Titi Restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZsaf4OS_S22DuA5YJPzW5ZXnDbZvrVOomD8v2&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Brian Krause","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdP7woIjNOL63V37wHT09kxdTUjnvdRus14yp9YD6p7IyLBnc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Big portion and pizza was tasty. Bathrooms very clean. Ambience a bit slow/laid back but enjoyed experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipON0WnxfAezTu8bYRSgHFC7uG10zBcIDAE_unuC&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Nazanin Eskandari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTrW5zYZ1EYPClt_zOeVHFz8Qz1spDq65vXAskRtnqhRxUqSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this Iranian restaurant in Canada multiple times, and I have to say, their "Fesenjan" stew and kebabs are amazing! Each dish is packed with authentic flavors and beautifully presented. Highly recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjFexRAsQK7DJsb-rw9XpWJ3eeYhPLAbh7z9gQ&fid=0x0:0xae7b86714c63c62f"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"zey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQZkkgMj8lJ8cQAPaQLN0nMqKvKWJRbFjom0wk11K44rygyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The quality, quantity and price of food was excellent, fair and competitive. But when u order by Skip the Dishes expect delay more than half an hour. It takes more than an hour when it should be less than 30 minutes. I know this is not Titi fault but this impacts on restaurant reputation and they have to follow up the reason and fix the issue.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Shirazi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzf4KVzISXZ9WpQa0kDI1joNREQjKZOjIp2Zn0BKoJ3Gs3_hvq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I visited TiTi  a few months ago with my non-Persian colleagues and unfortunately, our experience was not as positive as expected. Despite the restaurant's good reputation, we encountered several issues during our visit.
1.	Pricing Confusion: The price for a specific dish was different for takeout compared to dining in, which wasn‚Äôt clearly indicated in the advertisement outside. This led to some confusion and disappointment considering the service fee and expected tips.
2.	Service Issues: The waitress was not as friendly as we had hoped, and her attitude was noticeably different when serving non-Persian guests. Additionally, she insisted that I speak in Persian with her, which felt inappropriate.
3.	Order Mistake: One of our orders was initially incorrect. Although the correct dish was eventually brought to us, the delay was inconvenient.
4.	Tea and Dessert: When ordering tea and dessert, we were told the tea pot was only enough for two people, despite it being sufficient for our group of five. Also, when we asked for extra candy, the waitress‚Äôs attitude seemed unwelcoming, even though the candy was a minor request.
5.	Billing Process: The process of splitting the bill for tea and dessert was not accommodated. We were told that one person must pay the entire bill, and we would need to settle among ourselves later. This was quite odd and embarrassing, especially since splitting bills is a common practice.
6. The quality of food was fair.
While we appreciate the restaurant's efforts to provide a unique dining experience, these issues made our visit less enjoyable. We hope these points can be taken into consideration to improve the overall service and ensure a better experience for future guests.
Thank you.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Our favorite one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0py2qMlde_FO_Z7LlpoyZ4Td2EYjbA6EA3nx3\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We absolutely love the brunch options here! The Eggs Benedict, specifically the Yorkie Bennys, are absolutely delicious! We also enjoyed playing skier-ball while sipping our drinks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdVWNFzIMlOntd15pJqyDW99DKYpC3tuLXKK2_\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Moe Tahir","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9iDu-e6jGh4v-LimNB4J6hLIMigr5EdCcxZwrTlr9-nZtYuSxcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very, very disappointed.  Seems like they don't take initiative on any of their mistakes. Warm beer in cold glass. Eyes rolled back when I pointed it out. Wings that had all drumsticks. When ask for about that order. I was questioned.  Clearly it should have been mixed wings. And also I was told that I would have to pay for that first mistaken order. If I was going keep this order. I had better service at Samz neighbourhood pub and at Earls. I was going to spend a lot more time here. Not going to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYkoPz6yXRZzy703JQdfKUzSDVtyF0eKPI5_ap\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Clint Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxh6VsX6hLeU_9_m0ZG1nvLQ2h4LvbdxIxIz9rHEU9MwIOCByM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff here are the best I've seen in over 20 years. Every waitress that walked by our table, always looked over to see if something needed attending to. Whether it be an empty plate or a drink that may need to be refilled. Even if it wasn't their table or section. They work as a team. I was very impressed and I'll be back. Food was really good and the restaurant itself was very nice and clean.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cecilia Torres","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNEEaaadExpk4TXS6qqCV0FmYUxFhqMOus525fmHWN2GQT7vM68g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Bellini Bliss, Dress Code Bummer\nThe Taphouse is my go-to spot for a delicious Bellini, but their dress code is a total buzzkill. I was so excited to go back with my boyfriend, but we were both wearing shorts (on a summer night), and he was told he had to leave after 10 PM. Can you believe it? I'm hoping they loosen up their rules so I can enjoy their amazing drinks without worrying about my outfit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAX2kSioalJrmcBKuNSvagnO2mZyPWLdTENjm1\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Sabrina Dean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsuNoq0NjIZsw7Q0s08xv-ogcv0ajmV0Oo0HaZ5E_raW8Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Happy hour options and prices are great. We only had the sweet potato fries this time - too salty and not hot! Server was friendly, quick and checked on us multiple times. Washrooms had 5 out of 8 stalls Out of Service - not sure what's happening there.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Madrid Rachel (C)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvf-PcqiVpvwr8lRb4KDHKMwX0b5MC1Fr-oiihQzWaQrrLLEqr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At first, they seated us inside, but I requested if we could be outside, and they told us that it could be arranged. The women working are so nice and accomdating to our needs. They will go at the back and keep checking here and there. We had the whole patio to ourselves, and the weather was perfect for that day! My partner and I would definitely  come back again one day to try the cold noodles. The food proportions and the money we paid for it is worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYWOocxVgzgo0EvR-trYO8V3TgKrbAIvJksmW5&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Tatiana Kamakura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWK7ZmVLiCrm06mIZ8nEoydM1aHmV1jz4_Pf0vfjLhNGl4wZBRSUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We arrived by 6pm and sat in the outside part, which was lovely. The dishes came quickly, even with the restaurant close to full. The staff was super friendly, and the menus had the ingredients in english, making it easier to choose what to order. Everything we ordered tasted amazing. Spicy rice and fish cake was delicious, but really spicy for those not used to spicy food. Trying rice wine for the first time was a nice experience. Would definitely come back to try other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMa7zy5e2C6GKhrfer3Np3-WiL0StLVOmO6sQtn&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2023-5-22"},{"Name":"Patrick Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9837XYJatBhh8uygAXZ5cFqnhdVU7CsJgBMh-TzrJtW8lVns=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is good... we order seafood pancake, spicy pork bone soup, mixed chicken. Portions were humongous, as we cannot finish it... and this is with  big eaters thats hungry.
Pricepoint is also excellent.
Highly recommended!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYTx31cP3f85St1FgN0aCUeEb41tC5D8yA5oIf&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2023-10-28"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Splendid Korean restaurant.  A new hot place in town for general Korean food.  I have heard some of the menus were quite good and I wasnt disappointed as I tried aggucim.  Portion was very generous too and ingredient were also great.  I would definitively return and try other menus.  Friendly staff as well.

We tried more dishes in later visits and all dishes were above average.  This is one of better Korean food experience in lower mainland.  Most of dishes are impressive and my companions want to come back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEGX3dYsN5YxJPJJZn8Jhmzf9LLHHVUo4xNFNX&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2022-8-11"},{"Name":"Mary Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTR6oY9lWiiFzO0IMhpp4V_CX15n1cYRzi6LeGXsGPhqIE6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was quite disappointed with our visit today, especially as a regular customer of two years. I ordered the spicy stir-fried squid and pork with rice for the first time, but the vegetable portion overwhelmed the pork and squid, and I could hardly find any squid in the dish. The pork consisted of only a few small pieces. Additionally, the stone bowl for the bibimbap was not hot enough, which was quite surprising given the usual consistency.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TIM C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsL9NSrG8jjAVNG-x9rN6XSoaFI_Viwwt29jo0hKnGaLtx37Tb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time trying, we ordered the fried squid and beef bone soup w ox knee

Taste 0.5/1*
Fried squid was over cooked, quite dark with a bitter taste
Bone soup was creamy and watery at the same time, lack of depth, wife liked the fact that they don‚Äôt season it, but instead gives you side of S&P

Value 0.5/1*
For $19.95 was expecting a larger bowl of soup not gonna lie

Speed 1/1*
Order was prep‚Äôs & received on time

Presentation 1/1*
Delivered well, presentation on point, always appreciate being able to eat with eyes first

Overall/Revisit 0/1*
Personally think there‚Äôs many better choices of Korean food at this price, even just in the same area

Above and beyond? 0/+1*
A side note: we originally wanted some spicy stir fry pork, but there‚Äôs no option to order that as a dish, only on top of rice‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPickoA8wJ9bWiggT5M5spTQboUX0nkdKLU_qhr&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2024-1-29"},{"Name":"Ariana Abedini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKNjWemH3JT4c-lZV9IuSCGGzTuGZDPVm9u6xasU8uvx3gj15E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic Korean food, very very delicious! It was my first time there yesterday and I have to admit that, when I walked in, I became kinda sceptical with my choice, as the interior looks old and not very well taken care of. I‚Äôm glad I nevertheless decided to have dinner there, because the food was ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS! And very good prices too, considering their generous portions. Definitely recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOP5F7y2D0tgvW4XgukYKMK6MVZhovx29fE6HH5&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2023-12-17"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was a pet decent Korean restaurant. The staff were very friendly and accommodating and would visit again! We only had 2 dishes shared between 3 people - we got the pork katsu and the intestine soup.

It‚Äôs an authentic Korean restaurant so they will have dishes that might be a bit too adventurous for a typical diner but I think that you should venture out of your comfort zone because you‚Äôll never know what you like!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4s1reJqggGcJ8xhRwjOyuJ9l5GhK5RspyRH8e&fid=0x0:0x794e2821ebc80351"],"When":"2022-11-11"}]

[{"Name":"Julia Tallentire","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn_PwbzuLg5S_bvw5WHe4l0QZc_at0pWbVdGfDZVABBRc3U2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food! And friendly staff
We've had and really enjoyed so far: ginger beef, Sichuan string bean, spicy tangy dumplings, and Xiao long bao (not pictured)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeSIwUywSsyDEQI1Pq27rykd23xsm7ar3ppLqg&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Christopher Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVexNzsO8991iK-9EWX-70Xc57sEkVGaaf84klilDJ3qadcoigBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Shanghai food! This place has signature beef rolls and dumplings. But don‚Äôt be afraid to try their other dishes. This time I ordered beef noodle soup and deep fried squid. Soup was perfectly flavoured (spicy) and noodles were just the right texture. Fried squid was also spot on, seasoned well and nice and crispy. There are lots of items on the menu I still want to try so I‚Äôll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgA2PeHLvPPlkRNTVYhK4DL8hjIT3xoB0l1vFA&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2023-8-8"},{"Name":"M Carol W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrApweCZ_o2cDt96mptjdkKLzhWxJGrqd2c_QO9FLaF9_6WY6Yig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had read my local Peaceful Restaurant (Poco) had very good Szechuan food and I was craving decent soup dumplings. I also ordered Dan Dan noodles, which I‚Äôd never had before, but seemed like a good bet. I was very happy with my selections.

The soup dumplings were delicious. The skins were not super thin so you had something to chew, but not thick either that it would be heavy. Each dumpling held a lot of soup which was clear and tasty, not greasy at all like some other places.

My Dan Dan noodles were such a surprise. So delicious - the flavours were well balanced. I would definitely return for another good meal there.

I gave atmosphere a 4 only because some of the seats need repair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSTDqMuxZj7V8h9zTazE-awoO9lc6V7tJgHCtX&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Janessa Irene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpSbGDk4PCkkLcrRU_e1Ak4moHQg_aEB533erdgDtSMnKW0one=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been coming to Peaceful restaurant for years. Being from Edmonton, we only get here when we are visiting the Greater Vancouver area and the food is ALWAYS good and consistent. The noodles are so perfectly fresh and chewy, the beef rolls are crisp and the beef is cooked to perfection, the XLB are the best anywhere and the Dan Dan tastes like an airport hug. Often I find service can make or break a restaurant and the service at this location was phenomenal. Our server was attentive without being too much, friendly and super engaging. It was our first time at the Port Coquitlam location and it definitely will not be our last. Thank you again for the amazing service and food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIbJhJMOR9aBntLk6tLpaANizaTnPokA81-W-u&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2023-4-25"},{"Name":"Clara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJWIwshLULE3B_RdNi9aKWLWw8jS-s52J_rdUUXlZsGL8nMFDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At the old Deer Garden location, so same humble Chinese restaurant vibes, which is something I personally like (not even any music). I'm guessing due to the pandemic, it was pretty empty, but our food came really quick and service was polite.

They're known for their Xiao Long Bao (soup dumplings) and those didn't disappoint. We got other standard fare in this category of cuisine to test on this first visit (rice cakes, garlic string beans, Taiwanese beef rolls, Northern pork dumplings), and it was all very flavourful. I could eat the rice cakes all day.

Not a fan of using disposable plates, though. Feels a bit irresponsible, especially with so few customers during the pandemic.

Will definitely return for the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOV8JXRtTwa8nwu5YuczgGlaoLSjK0H7mGNHMmJ&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2021-9-15"},{"Name":"Shar E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSTTeWSwBUCCTyXplz3ZdtlER3HBP0xmei1e1PbBmts9nKzEHujg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went to the Vancouver branch some years ago. I remember it being really good, so I visited the Coquitlam branch.  It did not disappoint.

We ordered the beef rolls, pan fried pork, sweet and sour chicken, young chow fried rice, vegetarian noodles, hot and sour dumplings, a s Xiao long bao.  Everything's really good.

The only thing I didn't like about is how cold it is inside the restaurant.  They had portable heaters on but it wasn't enough to make the whole restaurant warm.  Probably their heater wasn't working that day.

But other than that, we enjoyed eating in Peaceful restaurant in Coquitlam.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fred Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlT70QWwV2DY9EdRG6qQQBK_x9FK_vcq8MKjgCHFTXA_U_2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is new, but they are good! Fresh ingredients, great menu options, and friendly staff make this a go to!  they are always friendly, easy smiling and helpful explaining everything. There is a friendly & lively atmosphere with great tasting food, quality of the meal was excellent and fully loaded.This place is neat and great, I like it very much. I also feel that their response to Covid-19 is very good I have seen in restaurants setting. I highly recommend you try them out, and you'll keep returning.‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjyp9fVbVXFemLZMfLxEZ-DcRgBBL39O9_k3Cm&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2020-10-31"},{"Name":"Jennifer H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEzU9INF1_sZTYVftrDSnlryIgHLw3kMLOe1cm6D0xxwHTb8jqsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Having been to the other Peaceful Restaurants in Vancouver I was excited to hear that a location opened up so close to home. They seemingly opened quietly during COVID so I wasn't too sure what to expect and I'm sure a lot of people also don't realize that this location is here. So that's why I really wanted to try it out and leave a review, because I think there's great potential here and I hope they get more business!

I've been here twice now, as of this review, and I think this is the type of spot where they do some dishes well, and others not as much. I often find that to be the case for restaurants with larger menus, not every place can do every dish well, and I think that's understandable! So your experience here could definitely vary depending on what you choose to order. The first time we came we ordered the Kung Pao chicken because another review said they enjoyed it, but we found it to be pretty "meh" and just okay. So the next time we came we ordered a different chicken dish, the General Tsao's Chicken, and we like that one much better! Much better flavour!

Other dishes that we enjoyed were the Xiao Long Bao (a dish Peaceful Restaurant is known for), the Beef Rolls (another dish they're known for), the Spicy Gingered Beef, the Vegetable & Tofu Stir-fried Noodles, and the Sichuan Stir-fried Noodles. The broth in the Xiao Long Bao (Shanghai soup-filled dumplings) was delicious and went well with the vinegar they serve it with, the vinegar really helps to cut the richness of the broth and pork filling.

The noodles also had a great texture to them, a nice bounce and chewiness that was satisfying. The Sichuan Stir-fried Noodles were my favourite as they also had a nice light heat to them. I will say that the "Spicy" Gingered Beef isn't very spicy but that may be a good or bad thing depending on who you ask. It's still very tasty regardless of if you're a spice fan or not!

I had family members who visited on a separate occasion from me and they said they wouldn't recommend the fried rice (a category I didn't try on my visits) and that the squid had good flavour but was not crispy enough! So maybe keep those notes in mind when you're deciding what to order!

Now, the ambiance at the restaurant is where I think there could definitely be improvement. It's very clean and quiet in the restaurant, but a little too quiet as there's no music at all! So if you go on a quiet night it's a bit strange having it be so silent. I'd recommend they put some light background music of some kind on and it would be much better.

Also in terms of ambiance, they don't provide regular eating utensils, but plastic cutlery and styrofoam plates and cups. Yes this does upset me as someone who hates single use waste, but I do understand that they opened during covid and it seems to be very quiet for dine in (at least when we've gone). I suspect that they may also be short staffed, so this might be a way for them to keep costs low and keep workloads manageable with only a few staff members.

I definitely hope in future that they will move toward regular cutlery and plates, but if this would be a deal breaker for your dine-in experience, then I recommend trying take out! I did see quite a few take out orders get picked up so that's definitely an option some customers are choosing, and it makes sense.

Aside from the music and dinnerware, the waitress was very friendly and attentive, which we appreciated. Parking is also plentiful so there's no issues there. The price is not bad at all  either, we always get at least another meal or two as leftovers so it's good value! My hope for this place is that it can work toward building a better ambiance and that people will still give it a try as they work toward that transition. I think there's room for improvement but I also think there's definitely some things they're doing well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0DwGVQ0f-1evWkGfS9MOh0jP9iL_22siWwZpO&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2021-9-23"}]

[{"Name":"Monica Nguyen Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZBeMwSkt7l1K2HVfyeAFOoXFwnBn78IKEly42V3HGsujhC8gu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time coming to this location but not my first time coming to Chicko Chicken üôà.

I got half buldak and half snow chicken with shake shake fries. Buldak is definitely spicy and very yummy. I forgot the pickled radish this time but they are always good. Great combo with the chicken!

I ordered in person so I had to wait 30min for my order not bad since it was made fresh and there was only 3 workers (1 was even taking calls and packing orders for pickup and delivery). It was worth the wait though the food was amazingggg ü§§

I was also craving it for over a week too, pretty satisfied. If you do want to order, just make sure to order for pickup/delivery to skip the wait. I will definitely order for pickup next time ü§£","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObb3li8YJmp4jeRZ5J8ZjVfUmsfrT_A0LuGQaC&fid=0x0:0x464057daf042c093"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Chris Wolfe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu8fbcvAdoID9Egy1yMAxykKuWztsrQaE5XfcgR9nw0KWwqKaZ1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôm giving this restaurant 5 Stars because their chicken is out of this world.

Chicko‚Äôs Chicken has officially ruined all other food for me. The moment that crispy, juicy masterpiece hit my taste buds, I heard angels singing‚Ä¶and I don‚Äôt even go to church-es

The chicken is so good it made me reconsider every life choice that led me to NOT eat here sooner. The fries? Perfectly golden little sticks of joy. The sauces? Probably illegal in some countries because no one should be this happy.

Sure, I walked out of there with sauce on my shirt, grease on my fingers, and zero dignity left, but you know what? Worth it. Chicko‚Äôs, you‚Äôve got me hooked harder than my uncle‚Äôs addictions.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an excellent lunch to taste some Korean style fried chicken.
So tasty that makes you bite your finger!!!
Good pricing which half a size is enough for one person.
Tasty side pickles and drinks.
No dine in only take out. Lots of parking for free.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDqJRewPdtulpaYON0iar_3OEapzYo0PsXRMxW&fid=0x0:0x464057daf042c093"],"When":"2021-2-23"},{"Name":"Pauline Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRNG7TpX7rUc6XCTzrQAMxwHXV7kNiIeWY2TA0eCmZOWTgow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Doesn't follow regulations and conditions of operations permit.  Doesn't allow customers to use washroom facilities which is a violation of BC Food Premises Regulation.  Received Permit to Operate from Fraser Health only for Take-Out but has obvious front of restaurant dining area for 18 diners. Makes me wonder what other short cuts they are taking in the kitchen?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Priya Badhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUWrpdymoiG3drKefuP1fHuEVUxK_kqe7u0-JFka_xzidrhRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place their chicken is always fresh & flavourful cooked at the perfect temperatures.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOi0KavoK86_rgCSwcB4Znv2HSlDPQ2LXH6Jpj&fid=0x0:0x464057daf042c093"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place, the chicken is always fresh and tasty. The app for ordering is precise, fast and easy to use. No complaints from any of the flavours and or dishes I‚Äôve tried. My go to delight! My favourites would be the Yangyeom and Buldak ones, The recent addition of Haek is also nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlsAYVBIwCMqkmQuWxhDb1nEo9wughmhSw-dyB&fid=0x0:0x464057daf042c093"],"When":"2021-1-21"},{"Name":"Ellen Sea","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgyvw39gUnCgl6xsGC3h38EgAvDpICnxUdU619L8I4-wyV0VMy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"**PLEASE DISREGARD THE DUMPLINGS, NOT PART OF THE ORDER**
I ordered the soy garlic bone-in chicken and it was very delicious. I didn't eat it right away because I wanted to get home first and watch a movie with my meal but even after the 45 minute transit, the chicken was still crispy. Of course the bottom was a bit soggy but that's not for them to blame. Knowing that my chicken was still relatively crispy after nearly an hour, I imagine it would've tasted spectacular straight out of the fryer. I made dumplings alongside (should've taken a photo before putting the dumplings in, but oh well!). The chicken came with a small side order of pickled radish. I personally LOVE pickled radish so next time I will order a bigger side pickled radish. All in all, definitely some of the best korean fried chicken I've had in Vancouver- highly recommend. Even the boneless chicken tastes amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONCk_af9v-W-pPAZRamFWWFPIvbpz4lV3BeWwM&fid=0x0:0x464057daf042c093"],"When":"2021-8-12"},{"Name":"Nathan Ozee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX082A1x_wj7AxxsD2GKy5bR5t4BkjbO2P7RKrD-PyQx-wdvkD1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Radish and drink no longer complimentary with an insane price for half order‚Ä¶.
Every Korean place had complimentary dishes but greed took over these guys.

It was previously a complete package.
no longer complete. Next non greedy place.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Milad Firouzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzrgrIGNGbel6o9MR69Ok-V4had6hrv3OGfRkMbkDP6QkTT80y2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This Korean restaurant offered an exceptional dining experience! The presentation of the dishes was inviting, as seen in the sizzling hot plates surrounded by cheese, corn, and egg, which added interactive elements to the meal. The flavor of the grilled meats was perfectly balanced, complemented by fresh vegetables. The cheese melted to perfection and paired wonderfully with the savory main course.

The servers were attentive and ensured the food was cooked correctly at the table, enhancing the overall experience. The sides, including sweet corn and creamy egg, rounded off the meal beautifully. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, making it a perfect spot for a fun and satisfying meal. I highly recommend this place to anyone craving authentic Korean flavors with a modern twist!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXWThLQdXqvFPeTGvwdYt2rhjQ90OeIDfCGpyI&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Y S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTmtWUtCZcs7qDdNKdjVbtcx5f5BcDfDU3YRp4zcFsXHKu1_WS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came on a Friday night for dinner. Like many people have said, parking is limited to the few spots at the front or else you would need to find parking on the back streets. The back street is residential area with no street lights so it can be scary to walk by yourself.

The food was very tasty and good portion. But I found the soup a bit heavy on MSG. Food came out really fast. The side dishes is unlimited refill.

The service was excellent and attentive. The server checked on us every 10 minutes or so. She knew it was our first time trying the hot plate so she helped us quite a bit. She explained how to eat the food quite well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0tYqFcFaR2HAYAxHucZYUMCbz6cXcwHpSrJWJ&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"X Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXF-fh-XeTsj_eALyZoNQufIdpcqdopw9XVl72CTpZbYMgCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the cheese grills here. Makes any kind of food more fun when it‚Äôs surrounded by cheese.

To top it off, the service is also great. We were seated promptly in a cozy ambient environment surrounded by extra cushions ‚Äî a hospital touch I personally really appreciate especially on a tired and chilly day.

Great dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHt6kUcIXPux82BDRgZiwo4h1hYcEHpKGo9g&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Jenevie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVce3HruZ31gaGncYHwX95oKzLpg_0g7BO_KicbohIHjs3w6eDj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been a few years since I've visited but used to come here all the time when I resided closer to Coquitlam‚Äî always been my preferred location! The new renovations are lovely and still has a cozy atmosphere. Food is as good as I remember and I always recommend the spicy octopus hot plate. ‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfsLUOyIbfJI6dWWFL7DkzijmKDsxiWo-5dlEn&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Kun Ho Yoon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7a_TkQUEpAcdGGNy9qU2vuDm2_Ypkj7DPW3ASPBDUd0z4TSse=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all, my dining experience was absolutely fantastic. Im a big fan of Korean food and have tried every single one and I have to say Tabom‚Äôs Dak Galbi and Japchae is one of my favorite of all.

The grill is creative in its way that it comes with egg, corn and cheese (extra). It‚Äôs a must-try and Im definitely willing to come again for its food and service. Not to mention that the atmosphere was relaxing and cozy, warm vibe with good service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5IWzar2KaZKDx-sht0D8ClCBkSd2pRuZKa2XR&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had a great dinner at Ta Bom. It was good that they offer live BBQ grill. Servers were friendly and prompt. Restaurant is quite small, but it was clean and doesn‚Äôt reek of strong BBQ smoke smell.

I find the dishes to be fairly priced. It was tasty and fresh.

Will definitely dine here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKhQouTyWguciGJfX0oQCiZREEdlsjkdVqAHm3&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"Jessica Aranas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG8N5f3Wd4GKt8zT_qaGsKHP4OREkobtyE2Xefb2cmdEv-KSHu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst korean restaurant we‚Äôve been too. We went there around 4pm and I think they only have 1 server so it took her a long time to get our order (but it is not that busy). Anyway, after we order we‚Äôre expecting for some side dishes because every time we eat at a korean restaurant the servers automatically brings you side dishes after you make your order but sadly they don‚Äôt do that here and the free side dishes is not enough for two person (3 types and a very small portion, you can refill it max 3x). The corn is too dry, the egg and cheese is so small, there‚Äôs even no rice together with our order, everywhere we go there‚Äôs always rice that comes with this. The price is not worth it. Not coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPz4caRGfDFkaPclS8CZ24ZB97CGURSa8GHWqX&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ta Bom was one of the original dak-galbi restaurants way back when Nolbu in Downtown was the only other place to get it.

It‚Äôs still one of the standouts for its hot plate shared mains in the area. They also have a number of other Korean classics as well as fried dishes.

Prices are bit on the high side which is what I think keeps it from being more popular.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR4CCGgkm1CNjYYz-4BuHmgCsq1DCxZP-SPAFC&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-19"}]

We had the large pork bone soup, tofu soup, half and half fried chicken,  pork knuckles, pancake and blood sausage. Also shared a kettle of draft rice wine.  All so tasty and perfect. Asked for the soups to be as mild as possible due to kids at the table but they were still a bit too spicy for one child,  the other pulled through because it was just too tasty to pass up.  Great service too. I highly recommend this place. 5 adults and 4 kids it was $300.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMehQNl7c5eE4rKCr6KzoRu9WDSE4BoSDANMgIU&fid=0x0:0xeedfc463fb2ffa17"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"Jun Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGM0sPDngIBUuKXJ98Z4EgCqnGHniV_swcpvtNFopsfWMJuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got the spicy pork hocks and pork bone soup. They were ready when I went in for pick up. Meat: soft and had good flavour. Soup was tasty. Did not dine in so have nothing to say about the atmosphere but you must try their food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Florence Wong (Flo)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5uzANVYaEyXcMzOyEyAPF_tqRXx52FZ4susMFD2pCokdMQhcO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I came here with a friend for dinner and we were seated around 5:15pm.  The restaurant is cozy and clean, with an iconic  Korean happy hour vibe.  They had quite a selection on their menu and we shared the house special GamJatang and Reobbokki (Teobbokki with Ramen) üòã!!
Since we were seated so early the food also came quite quickly after we ordered.

The GamJatang came in the signature bubbling stone pot, with a bowl of rice on the side.  The flavor is relatively mild.  I personally like the strong peppercorn and perilla seed flavors and this one was lacking.  Also, they didn't have potatoes in the soup! I thought it was part of the recipe!! Needless to say I was a little disappointed.

Then came the Reobbokki! Both the rice cakes and ramen were chewy, which was nice.  The sauce was very flavorful and on the sweet side.  I would order this again the next time.

The server was very friendly but she was pretty much on her own so at times our calls were not answered or delayed.

By the time we were leaving the restaurant was full and the vibe was great! I'll definitely come back to try the other dishes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0nsdLFwQciAZAblFBlUtHZVCK5gQYX1LgW7si&fid=0x0:0xeedfc463fb2ffa17"],"When":"2023-12-2"},{"Name":"Julie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6iqNbgJ99pEVigrdmqTpMQQRCYbL7zrrvCytBAxs45Tk47A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My FAVOURITE PORK BONE SOUP RESTAURANT OF ALLLLL TIME!!! My friend showed me this place 2 month ago and I have been back every week at least twice a week. This is my go to spot now for hangover or just soup craving. Every time I come here, it hits the spot for me! The price for value is insane. They always give around 5-6 pieces of meat. Most soup places give 2-3 for the regular size. All the meat is sooo tender and juicy. Falls right off the bone. Soup is always super flavourful. It‚Äôs literally LIQUID HEAVEN in my books. Only thing for me was I wish I found this sooner!!

PRO TIP:
Ask for a side of sweet soy sauce with wasabi. And dip the meat from pork bone soup in the sauce and eat it with a bit of rice and chase it with a spoonful of soup for the most perfect bite on this planet!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_o8xtz_da_rSAvIVjHS_vY3HQRaOAGfm7yfsh&fid=0x0:0xeedfc463fb2ffa17"],"When":"2023-3-29"},{"Name":"MAY Îß§Ïù¥ Elford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxJVIiA7BVVmzUGqT6sRzP7-hCdYJttIOnYMeIvWOWZPmq7cr7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a Friday fun with friends. They got a table for 4 ppl close to 7pm. We ordered some dishes and shared them. Service was great and friendly. Food was yummy.. pork hock and fried chicken were recommended by many.
This wasn‚Äôt the 1st time I came.. last time I had a good experience too. You gotta go and try it! üòä ÎßéÏù¥ ÎìúÏÑ∏Ïöî ^^","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFRZu1Q8wdZzZBf8AMO3qtbLM1k7bcEELwVV0a&fid=0x0:0xeedfc463fb2ffa17"],"When":"2023-3-7"}]

Finally, really good prices but the service is no good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi1YBxhAcQdMw7_Xi5ontWRu5FmdjkKadhBNXe&fid=0x0:0xc29909442b15211c"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decided to grab some dinner. Donair looked good and this place had rather good ratings.

Food:
We ordered the chicken platter. I got the upsize (+$2), which meant, more meat üòç I had all the vegetables and sauces on the platter. The chicken was marinated and roasted well, a little dry, but given that I went a little late, it was expected. Rice was delicious, savoury and filling, wasn't too sure what stock they cooked it in, but it was amazing. Two options of salads, Caesar and Greek. I had the Caesar, it was alright. Nothing special.

Service:
Friendly young dude. A little quiet. Quick prompt service.

Location:
Pretty empty at 9pm. Rather warm given that it's summer and there wasn't much ventilation/AC.

Price:
Approx ~$9/pax

Would I recommend?
Yes. Meat portions are generous (refer to pics for clarity), food is relatively filling. Get the set meal(+drink) for better value.

Go with friends. Share your meals :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNMpewhO9MetLpVjbM3nkmWdXS8MjGNJ9CHxN4&fid=0x0:0xc29909442b15211c"],"When":"2017-8-3"}]

[{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute little Thai spot with very attentive service. They actually take the time to pack your food. Delicious and good portions.
- Spring rolls were jam packed with ingredients and incredibly crispy.
- Chicken wings had such a unique lemon/spicy and lemongrass taste
- Seadoo red Thai curry - sweet and spicy with coconut flavour. Served with rice.
- Pad Thai - large portion, well made.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhf4jj_ordOfTlpBgCG1HHhBJm9h8cccQ4XSUU&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Swapnil Kambli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdhhWN0KCMgQl8JxSlRxuwT7oQItuYRCMRTco9Mv-DKvRQLHe2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We‚Äôve dined here twice, and have found the dishes to be excellent, in terms of taste, quality and portions.
I‚Äôd easily highly recommend this Thai place, over many, cause of their authenticity and flavours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPee8MUlEDDmW6qpcpri4m-4XLuD0d4IJYlg0Er&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Liz Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIuViSUslkGybLwzF5hJuKnwuKDgGhdfdvpLRCkLln5KJ6Gw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We discovered this hidden gem of a restaurant today and it was a hit!! We ordered veggie red curry, and rice and basil, and regular and coconut thai iced tea, and coconut shrimps. As you can see, their portion was more than enough and our tastebuds were satisfied! Our belly was satisfied, and we look forward to tasting more food from the menu in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgNn7gSB3UeOhmTbslc6I5LlGvGVY3roArCks2&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Tara Elizabeth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWafp5-DbmdXd42lrIMIaPpUa4TG8IACFTFef3W9rqO44JjPcQgRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first visit to this charming spot. The Thai food was exceptional. In particular, we loved the pineapple fried rice (chicken in there, too). We also really enjoyed the veggie spring rolls, and though it was very mild, we found the red curry tasty, too. Our only disappointment was there was no yellow curry. Our server was lovely and attentive without being too  intrusive. The decor was delightfully retro (see pic of 70s phone).  All in all, though it is tucked out of the way down Westwood Street, it is well worth a visit. The two of us ate for $50, including tip. It is hard to beat those prices. The restaurant closes daily at 8:30 so lots of time for a little later dinner hour(we like that)!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3MkAuBqkfQID1HZL5cIqkSx2hcvXrZgyPvGE_&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-5-22"},{"Name":"Jade Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJWSVoZW1CCY-_xhdgdeWOnL28P_e39FAE_t38PKZ_hYo17g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered take out: chicken pad Thai and green curry with chicken. Personally, I'm not a fan of Thai food, but my husband chose tonight's dinner plan. Of all Thai places, this place did an outstanding job. The pad Thai was not too sweet, not too sour, not too salty, and smelt incredible. Good amount of chicken, big portion of noodles, good amount of tofu with bean sprout and the crushed peanuts on top was perfect. The curry was spicy despite mild, but manageable. Again, very tasty. Chicken was excellent, not dry and it was just right.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Dhaliwal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOeC5VCbc6g3HH3dxXpDS9bE993HEKMDVI3SjHX2aNdHbQOJHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would say Thai Coco is the biggest highlight of Coquitlam. The decor was so nice and it was cozy and the food was so great while dining in and even better as leftovers. Also this was the first time I ever experienced pasta or noodles that stay surprisingly nice and HOT because they were served on a hot plate! Loved the interesting menu too","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhBe8YpmOUQfEqReIlDxMZtW7WFTShOKLL4Fgy&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Shweta Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtnc5g-DhlNFKBuVm-Ri3EJhNR7eysyJfm0HrPZFoOOsluh9pj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A cute thai restaurant with great food, prices, and customer service! I read a couple reviews about the portions being a bit smaller, so my husband and I order 3 dishes. But we we're surprised by the quantity and the quality!! We had plenty. The portions were great. Our waitress was kind and quick to help. We were famished at arrival but left super full and with leftovers. We will definitely be coming back and be recommending to others.
We had the drunken chicken noodles, chilli chicken, and pineapple fried rice. All of them hot, fresh, and yummy. Try this place out if you're hesitant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmH3fPnITUAyOsmQwjgPlxztjt0Yy5IV34PKKy&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Jhk 727","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRlpzpCG0lmTiswrjxl92nKs9mapw2VnKHEXcy00upiXVnodNCJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Amazing Tom Gha! Deep rich flavours that opens up your appetite perfectly. Red curry was flavourful while being not heavy - I could have had another bowl on its own.  Friendly staff with cozy modern atmosphere was a plus. Only knock I have was the portions - all dishes ordered were medium to small portioned. I would increase the portions by 10~15% and perhaps raise cost slightly to compensate - but that‚Äôs up to the owner‚Äôs business strategy:)
Overall, I‚Äôm glad to have found this place. Will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSunyzuHZ8vtGGAmGtgFvTcTEv07fpipni41Kq&fid=0x0:0xa680fed803c187a1"],"When":"2023-12-10"}]

[{"Name":"Andy Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWooGSzw1FKhky_mrftz_qLp6fsBzAqJ7JcjT2pde1tUMh4Y9hx8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Shrinkflation and inflation.

Dishes taste fine but the prices are going up and the portion seems shrinking as well.
I ordered to pick up some dishes. $6.25 for 6 pieces of small spicy salmon roles.
Maybe I‚Äôm out of touch these days. $32.25 for takeouts does not go very far these days I guess.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHN74PVQXn88pZBDO_WRQkASFUILQKLltLDqPH&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Mohammad Tabesh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjokXICqa-0DdrHKHh0Wt3GGaHTAC4RDuOqk22M3flRzjmqoKo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good quality food for the price with a nice variety, really quick service and convenient location inside the mall. It's a budget place with disposable plates and chopsticks. Miso soup was plain but tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPL_iRBW2adsUvuZctF90SuqpluYd65jND4m7dv&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My partner works in the mall and grabs lunch here three times a week, especially loving the teriyaki. I had the chance to try the unagi oshi sushi, and it was delicious! The creamy prawn tempura was a fantastic bonus, making the meal even more delightful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6on5Y08KZ9VAGnb-Q10oavACH62ly3bxzrkNn&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good Sushi for being in the mall! Lots of options to pick and you can order online so you don't have to wait!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5ux3twBDePDGec0k-4hwPkab1Rd92kFjUs18y&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"I D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJePVcTLvMpAzx-nv1Jiy6G3BSAT8AXC96M8bp3iDt95AnsQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I wish Coquitlam Centre has better eateries. I ordered the Beef Bento. Price was okay, but the portions were not big. For $15, I only got 4 pieces of California roll instead the standard 6 pieces. I was surprised by the quantity of the beef. It was more than I expected but the beef quality was quite poor. There was also not a lot of rice. Salad was fresh. Service was quick and friendly. It's a small place, and I couldn't find a place to sit, so I had the food to go. I forgot to ask for napkins :(","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4lll3FSw4DuoAXTTSQfNVd2BMOvLsNf0gg2O5LBY3etPVgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the prawn tempura and miso soup. For mall sushi, this place is consistently great! I enjoy eating here and will always return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEOr8Ou4QsT2tC4bIAmYmBwtpMCrNDvv-oKLq1&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"K S H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUpfuZFJ8RwqNTmsEi_Ve_L99RruCBycZdik5Nf-7YZZhK-hRF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the Best Sushi places in Coquitlam and very conveniently located in the mall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtjlH9F0FcLxhh45QyYB26pLJ8aF_QRpWZxyIU&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Johnny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvkqlZ5wz-o7qQiMAPvxq4Uq26umX4_opBke6CDrVfkbGhCeuLaA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first time at Togo Sushi was excellent. With exceptional service by the lady employee, I ordered the teriyaki bento box, and I opted for chicken rather than beef. The teriyaki bento box comes with California rolls, salad, gyoza, and miso soup. The teriyaki chicken was, to be honest, disappointing, which I was not expecting. I also ordered yam rolls, which I loved since I love sweet potatoes. Would I go back? Likely not.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Sarah Okut","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTH-O9yHrUXXSzwuweULzXw1pBbME2AVL3wPUzYMdoLT_dRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Pizza Pietra and really enjoyed their pizza and San Sebastian cheesecake. The pizza had a crispy crust with fresh, tasty toppings. It was delicious! The San Sebastian cheesecake was the best part‚Äîit was rich, smooth, and creamy, with a slightly caramelized top that gave it extra flavor. If you love desserts, you should definitely try this cheesecake!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3wU0_wer5w028bhetbEqdDgTlTPAd9mr8aiH5&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really loved this small and cozy Turkish caf√© run by two Turkish women. The staff is very warm and friendly. Although the menu is a bit limited, the breakfast options are quite delicious. I loved everything, from the sucuk (Turkish sausage) to the eggs and meat-filled pastries. For four people (we ordered a bit too much), the total was $105.
I definitely recommend it‚Äîa lovely caf√©!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZkVllSrfsqQVnk7-eaCEQy80caDFl6QFecd6N&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Î∞©ÏÉàÎã®Jp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPRFl5X_2oRYVKyp5YOzyZvBiFq4LXRAXvUH4K1gSFuhrTkvIu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the poached eggs with avocado.
They took a while to get the plate ready, but it was much better than what I had hoped for. Ingredients were fresh, tasty and I would definitely come back again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW5MCUo0Kn75oa42Blt_gR0Ah7EI2gXYUVdZhL&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Mahesh Vanga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_R99DIUm3YNCVBnH6ipuMklk--v4TSFTsQ7Tybr4ECj_qR-ZP9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is by far the best pizza place I have ever been to in the Mainland area. We explored this place as part of checking regular pizza places around, to our surprise this has been the best random pizza place ever been in fact the best pizza I ever had in the mainland area. Any food/pizza lover cannot miss this place, they got a wide variety of pizzas to offer as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO263l3lNZQ04gOHPrnihMubx8QyholXqUTO6DE&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Graham Sutton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8UeAA1nmB6Ej3WgCR3VioNDAdhDivzoWDT4UCyjNTsgC4MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Breakfast was awesome!  Traditional Turkish meals with lovely fresh bread and Turkish tea.  We'll definitely be back on a regular basis.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODmWArQZDzyV5LCBa5m3uJi_01rXQ5LyF0EMno&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Onur Kaan KO√á","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl3-LHlkDHqQOafBmwY6xCPBlOCHVa2JkVR6DeNJcaxq3QYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Clean, Happy and delicious Pizza Pietra, siezed my day üòã

At first I was hesitant because of the mixed reviews but I really wanted to give it a try, especially because of the praised stone oven and authentic dough.

I've been to most regions of Italy, ate a lot of very good pizza and I must say this pizza restaurant reminded me the times I was in Mediterranean.

You must use good quality ingredients and have precise dough craftsmanship, and have the right oven with the correct temperature to make a delicious pizza. But every body knows, in our modern times, this equation is quite impossible in big cities because of the cost and profit concerns.

But in this pizza shop they nearly got the perfect combination.

They have a real stove oven at the right temperature, good quality ingredients and handmade authentic dough.

Both pizza and Foccacia are nicely crusty and juicy. The Tomato sauce is not bitter nor too sweet, just yummy and fresh¬† ;-).

Toppings and mozzarella have a very good price to quality ratio.

All the ingredients are really really fresh üëç

A suggestion for them, I think you should make a pizza with different ingredients which are hard to find in PoCo

And for me the most important thing , people in this pizza shop are really happy, hospitable, positive and energetic. They really smile to you because they just want to. The total vibe is just like the warm and welcoming family owned pizza shops in Italy too üòçüòç.

Ps: I asked the owner to tour the kitchen because of my cleanliness obsession. And yes he let me to quickly tour the kitchen and I'm amazed, this is a really really clean kitchen for BC standarts üòâ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODw8DnBQZ_EDJZzRNN9UlLF96GZOid--UDy1PJ&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-3-28"},{"Name":"Aamir Sheergar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTKU4wfuc0kwoyEwJxy3N-nmGgBy-VjbHs41hImisM4pU2gpbxyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great pizza, loved the thin crust. Friendly service from the ladies in the kitchen. One of my new favorite pizza places.

Also tried the cheesecake, it was not too dense and had just the right amount of sweetness, a great balance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M. Murat Kucuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQxmakxls5MdK3S6o9QjUak841XsiEQ7PpJlT7cOAjNN9ECiE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Prepare to be amazed by this extraordinary pizza haven nestled within town. Without hesitation, I wholeheartedly recommend this remarkable establishment to all pizza enthusiasts. During our recent visit, we indulged in their custom 2-in-1 pizza, an exquisite combination that left our taste buds in a state of pure bliss.

The staff at Pizza Pietra were not only kind, but also exceptionally helpful, ensuring that our dining experience was nothing short of perfection. Their attentiveness added an extra touch of delight to an already exceptional culinary adventure.

Do not, under any circumstances, allow yourself to miss out on the opportunity to visit this exceptional pizza establishment. [{"Name":"K‚Äôs coffee lover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-385uQOflrqOxsV0QWsdIyhv-rxdZ7rLwLnLPmzpfPGzr9P6Z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After not visiting Denny‚Äôs for over a year, we were happy to find that they still offer a free birthday treat. So, we headed there on a Saturday morning. Judging by the packed parking lot, it‚Äôs clear Denny‚Äôs remains a popular spot, bustling with customers all enjoying their meals.

Our server was lovely and attentive, adding to the warm atmosphere. Although there was a bit of confusion when we arrived, with some customers who arrived after us being seated first, it didn‚Äôt affect our mood. According to the official website, the birthday treat includes a Build Your Own Grand Slam, but we overheard from the next table that Denny‚Äôs will deduct the equivalent cost if you choose something else from the menu. That‚Äôs a thoughtful way to offer flexibility for customers with dietary needs.

Our breakfast arrived hot and well-presented, and the buttermilk pancakes were soft and buttery‚Äîjust the thing to kick off a great birthday morning!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORkvKT7-OLSChxlnmYvfSbHoRXFcgK_vhOiG7Y&fid=0x0:0xce11d22c64824992"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Mahsa Safari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUchvWzR219vkKaIpFisPaWM7tup-Txwsp5Pxmxgha5rfxN9fROgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went to Denny‚Äôs for brunch, and the service was excellent‚Äîvery attentive and friendly. our server was the best. he was asian with great english. didn‚Äôt get his name sadly. he always had a smile, he gave us water while we were just browsing. he helped the other family with their teetering table which usually be over seen by any other person. he took my husbands order when he knew the order was wrong and was smiling about it the whole time. i even asked about an old 55+ fish that was not on the menu AND HE KNEW ABOUT IT! waw! he talked to the kids when he said the liked wolverine, said sorry to the mom when he mentioned deadpool cz he didn‚Äôt know if it was appropriate for these set of kids to know. mom said they loved deadpool. he was the best AND I HOPE HE GETS A RAISE !!  you hear that!!??? Usually packed at dinner time and need to wait for a seat. Korean owned so you know service if fast and efficient. The food the pretty much the staple Japanese styled you will get in all Vancouver restaurants. The same goes with the price üòé","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYm_soM8QFBubs1_cCZC4JSLe7NDLvI4zva7_J&fid=0x0:0x8d300ae9fd6e087"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Muh Ruri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkStAcVhSLoWZluIOVQ74c2fLDnRh9SyZ_LHSDWUY1b4U3yJnx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you're in Coquitlam and craving an exceptional sushi experience, look no further than Sushi California. This restaurant offers an impressive variety of menu items that cater to diverse tastes, including some delightful surprises like Korean-style stone rice and creamy mentaiko udon.

The first thing you'll notice is the extensive menu. Whether you're a sushi purist or someone who enjoys exploring different Asian cuisines, there's something here for everyone. The Korean-style stone rice is a must-try, served sizzling hot with a delightful mix of flavors and textures. The creamy mentaiko udon is another standout dish, with perfectly cooked noodles bathed in a rich, creamy sauce that balances umami and spice beautifully.

Every dish is cooked to perfection, showcasing the kitchen's skill and attention to detail. The portions are generous, ensuring you get great value for your money. Despite the high quality, the prices are remarkably reasonable, making it a great spot for both casual lunches and special dinners.

The ambiance is inviting and comfortable, perfect for enjoying a meal with friends or family. The staff are friendly and attentive, adding to the overall pleasant dining experience.

In summary, Sushi California in Coquitlam is a gem that offers delicious, well-prepared dishes at great prices. With its wide-ranging menu and generous portions, it's a place you'll want to visit again and again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrKCslRF8whiyuWjlmYeIaXsehuvKXjRM9ulzC&fid=0x0:0x8d300ae9fd6e087"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Mohammed Yahya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLT1QQjsQL0cVBO4YH4tgQfBRBthb4gM79UjFdzAIKyKZVPkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried there spicy tuna and it‚Äôs a spicy ü•µ for me. [{"Name":"April","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKU_JwwXfd502_5uPpJ0cg8bzuPOCD-lU_roxsnKQpWzN9H4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my second time ordering. Ordered premade seafood bowl last time and the amount of salmon and shrimp in the bowl was so small but thought maybe it‚Äôs just one time issue.

Ordered large BYOB today, and added extra salmon based on my experience last time. But the amount of total protein I got is equivalent of one or two scoop i get in different poke store. I tried digging through the salad to see if there are more underneath but what you see in the picture is all I got .. :(

I really hate to leave a bad review but for 25 dollars (doordash did offer 25% off happy hour deal so total was 21 dollars) this is not what I would expect to get :( The ingredients were fresh and loved the umami sauce! Would love yo try out pokerrito but I don‚Äôt think I will be going back for poke bowl.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlWJ7KIrPCdNv1eNvir5VYUxtG4PF0LUe4yGjP&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmvRXPt1uR-h9wzBQ7gvu3Mw7LXVhjVVQ6HaLxs-H4Cg1YdGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious poke bowl - great size and copious amounts of toppings! the presentation is perfect","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFEtS1Z3Jolp9wA8YFZG9JVLryd5Q2r5zPEsrE&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"M Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHG8GdHq5I6-mOUqVi4cC2yNBk1XXSYpaOlZE02ebzKaRnMg8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a delicious quick meal here with very fresh ingredients and really great service! I‚Äôd recommend the roasted chicken bowl üòç so good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It‚Äôs a great poke place especially if you‚Äôre going to get them delivered. They are quite filling for the price and they allow you to customize your poke to your liking.

I had the aburi bowl and I recommend it to anyone who likes smoky flavours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWwAve_yVl1bv6rZiO9kRP66NuJdNdAaXK-NGu&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2023-1-24"},{"Name":"Y.
