I can tell they might not be¬†as busy in Burquitlam as at some other locations, but I hope they stick around as this area is about to get a massive influx of new residents with all the construction around.
I have only good things to say about their food. Great choice of ingredients that are always fresh, a solid lineup of sauces and interesting signature bowls. It took me a while to try, but pokerrito wrap has all rights to be a form of serving poke. After trying out different poke joints, I mostly eat at two chains, and Pokerrito is one of them ‚Äì a staple of the Vancouver poke scene.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmx_R7NaCGwb58h-UKB8sNColpip-IDURMEbJK&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2022-11-5"},{"Name":"Fernanda Nauata","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9GQdgcgq5IMDtuJ2e1vR0Cjj0qtSmZsKJjBhEGJUsOJDDWOBr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve been coming here for the past two years, and every visit has been fantastic. The poke bowls and pokerritos are consistently fresh and delicious, with high-quality ingredients. Always a great experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"michele mateus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgFSf1yUGq2xdkVhBjzgbP2Wi4fm50mcfX5yAdtq7l6CG-y9wd5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love this place so much. The staff have always been so lovely and the food always taste so fresh! Has quickly become a family favorite.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeeah Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqgJmPrySY_RgHzxjMFLcdtBqI7sy94lCU5W9nkMpV7ohYK2I9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love & and recommend this poke place much better than the poke & co at the Coquitlam Centre Mall Food Court. Especially their mala jjamppong is sooo good The smoky flavour makes it even spicier and more delicious The seafood pancake is amazing too and the prices are super reasonable compared to other Korean spots Honestly it‚Äôs the best Korean restaurant in Vancouver","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOimlhJoewRKTb_QPpVNJ2FhOJevn30QUbWiW_Q&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Hyejin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxmpr7FWXMJqHRsBv5DODkOQBS3knAjvplMlXBCEswBGZElLIF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I‚Äôve been to BBONG three times now, and the experience has been inconsistent, to say the least. Every time I visit, the taste of the jjajangmyeon seems to change. On my most recent visit, the sauce was far too watery, which was really disappointing.

The rice was overly mushy, though I understand that might come down to personal preference, so I can overlook that.

The service, however, has been consistently poor. Whether it‚Äôs a male or female server, they are unfriendly and simply take orders and bring the food. If you need something during your meal, good luck getting their attention ‚Äì I‚Äôve had to get up and ask myself. There‚Äôs no mid-meal check-in, and you have to go to the counter to pay.

After being let down on multiple occasions, I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTGzIaHO75rEKRmtXMVQzIjM0x7SwyIofJqR7Y&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"iPhone reviewer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmGIoE2HgBiExZ87gC-H42hJO4cRpKNlIwK3By628OIt4LWoi2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Consistency matters, without it there is no success! I have visited this restaurant couple of times and noticed that their customer service isn‚Äôt that great, however, the food is decent. I can clearly remember my last visit and which is the reason why I have decided to write this review. Gentlemen‚Äôs and ladies, what is the definition of tips? You leave a generous tip depending on your satisfactory towards service or quality of the food. Tips should be well given according to those manners. Expecting such a high tip for poor service should not be normalized. I am not judging, this is literal facts. Please control your emotions.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mia Duong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPAUy0Htbh5FTHA7CrcyalmfPE1fNra4l4o1y3j6EQjpz6Sdhn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went for lunch and I love the prices for the lunch specials, $11.99 for jiajiang mian. They have 6 mini side dishes and that Sat‚Äôs pretty cool!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmlw3UAa9VAmiGL8ogwg6erEy6Nyj5qZJyKkFd&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Joce Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGrFjNBgSTeUkB5TUuTFijs7_U6G7FKJaRg-dNPU8w7lk_6hJf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here! Trying to try all the restaurants in this plaza. Was craving for clams in noodle soup! Clams in noodle soup is absolutely delicious! Clean broth no sand in the clams. Ordered seafood pancake as well, crispy and loaded with seafood goodness. Tofu soup wasn't too spicy super tastey as well as the seafood and rice combo. Taste of wok flavour! Ordered enough food for 4 ppl and had to take the rest of the food home!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBRDse9fLHIds8ny6GNaKVkkzC4jIF23cNBEeG&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"Youjeong Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtzJGpSrpmPRXDdKNXTKSZoTCOByK8-BhMGahndBI58CKzRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had Jajangmyeon and Tangsuyuk, and it was absolutely delicious. The black bean sauce was perfectly rich and savory, coating the noodles beautifully. Every bite of the Jajangmyeon was full of flavor, with just the right balance of sweetness and saltiness. The noodles were cooked to perfection, neither too soft nor too firm, and had a wonderful texture.

As for the Tangsuyuk, it was fantastic‚Äîcrispy on the outside and tender on the inside. The sweet and sour sauce had a delightful tang that complemented the fried pork so well. I loved how it wasn‚Äôt overly sweet, just the right mix to enhance the flavor of the meat.

The portions were also very generous, making it great for sharing. Both dishes brought me a lot of comfort, and I was genuinely impressed with the quality. I highly recommend this place to anyone craving some great Korean-Chinese food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAWWz16C1RXtxLo50X81UJOyY-1sgtf_q3NZWp&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Michelle M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeetN-W20mnzvtvgZG8vAeDlWwG6zd354oPCvc1I4B_3Cjy_PI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Portions are massive!! The sweet and sour pork was good, it wasn‚Äôt too sweet or sour. The spicy fried chicken was really crunchy and didn‚Äôt have much tender juicy meat in it. The black bean noodle was ok, it was flavourful but only had a few shrimps and cuttlefish in it.

It was hard to call the server because we were in one of the booths and the walls are quite high. This is a great place for value not really quality but I didn‚Äôt mind it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgWgrtfS5bP-GGjDY9nXAwpQMzTc8ZXmnNNaSK&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2022-2-13"},{"Name":"Vic Yung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjSUFpvFSwHsCrywPzGZzN7WDhV8Ljlj3YECw07iwjqMR_leW5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went on a weekday evening for a group dinner. Made a reservation beforehand but the place was not busy upon arrival, so reservation may have been unnecessary. The staff gave plenty of time to look at the menu and we ordered four dishes in total to share.

The food arrived relatively quickly and they were all in large portions. It was just enough food for 8 people.

Our group was sat behind a divider, so it may have been difficult to see if we needed anything, so staff were a little less attentive than they could have been.

Overall, it was a good experience and the food, considering the price, was well worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtmmhnj1Cj3EcIKjkw7daNcT10GwLPPbW-c98J&fid=0x0:0xf6f1c00a0e0f8389"],"When":"2023-7-4"}]

The flavors were bursting, and the presentation was top-notch. We will definitely come back again and again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMc-dp_ndyykYeZm-5FAlUAEAGob55LyQfy3vVI&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"V C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLk2wwFONQqAunDwsj4VVYlkGmIB9ggQgBx879H-91jhcYS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"There is a robot for delivering dishes which made my kids excited. Food is good. Less than $20 per person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-woEeQXqncYdhne092bvglRUfsgfGeIgO2f4&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"kwokyin lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDy1zFu9C8XXSdRNlEu20ovp7aSg7gDRBv_ulSBxkJzRweDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently dined at a fantastic Shanghai restaurant and was thoroughly impressed. The Shanghai soup dumplings were a standout‚Äîdelicate yet bursting with flavorful broth, the perfect balance of savory and satisfying. The Dan-Dan noodles were equally delicious, with a rich, spicy sauce that complemented the noodles perfectly. The dish had just the right amount of heat and depth. The service was attentive and friendly, making the experience even more enjoyable. The ambiance was cozy, adding to the overall charm of the place. It's definitely a spot I‚Äôd recommend for anyone craving authentic Shanghai cuisine.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cori Keating","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnmeI3fd9na4O4qGDfgGzQuDnkeLouJovnhnGUIoneMCOCl_M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Omgoodness!! Northern Dim Sum like we‚Äôve never had before. Hearty, made in house wraps and sooo delicious, had the pork buns, hot chili wontons, soup dumplings and chive pockets! Added garlic green beans which were excellent. Generous portions, left overs were enough for dinner. Can‚Äôt wait to go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM06S7U0dpMNukUyoeon59lCcchmsNKIyZwfnlQ&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great value lunch deal with a dish, rice, and a drink for only $12.95 everyday. There are 7 dish options to choose from and their combo meals are also discounted during lunch hour too. Sometimes the food can fill you up for both lunch and dinner due to the quantity. When we went, there was only one person juggling the takeout orders, the dine in customers, and any phone calls so service may be a bit slow. Once we ordered though, the food was out within 10 minutes. Some of the dishes are spicy so make sure to note that you don‚Äôt want spice if you can‚Äôt handle it. On street parking is limited but you can park at Coquitlam Centre near the Walmart and walk over.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPg1hoqKmZT1WRdHvOjV_CFw-0A6oS0ltpj0uUW&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2023-4-15"},{"Name":"Eva Tong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbdn1JwTeGwTMz4zaH_aM0s2MjqUg4f-ith9g4COdwAGXFieA4Ow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family came to visit, so I brought them to a Chinese restaurant. Their food is delicious and the portion is enough. My parents love the seafood and tofu soup and the fried fish fillet with sweet corn sauce. The fried fish is well fried and the corn sauce is a thick sauce instead of watery, so the sauce can stick to the fish. We have also ordered  green onion beef and sweet soy glazed spare ribs.

The only thing about the restaurant is that they don‚Äôt have round tables which my family is used to in a Chinese restaurant. As most of the seats were taken we have to sit very close to the area where they are standing all the time and tray of dirty dishes. Even though they do have something to block off the sight but it‚Äôs still very close.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4VpNKHWo7un0-FiiC_r_FtsJtmC8ljFKvDI-7&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2023-4-11"},{"Name":"Regine A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJu3rFf3mgxBA4mBu9iInDniuxdzfgKO1oQ5uTfVErzQD3BBe4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a fantastic experience at Legend House Restaurant! The Chinese dish we ordered was absolutely delicious‚Äîflavorful and perfectly cooked. Highly recommend this place, and we will definitely be coming back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Katherine Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ_fbiyyufWMqoCFysCuKDQEuZRz-jR8Hk5G3BPhWwM2YISMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came for dinner on Sunday 6pm. Was seated immediately without waiting. Server did not provide printed menus but there was a sign at the table with a QR code for an online menu.

Ordered pork soup dumplings (XLB), dry fried spicy green beans, Legend fried rice, and scallion pancake beef shank roll. The XLB were exquisitely wrapped with a thin wrapper, lots of well seasoned pork filling, but only a bit of soup. Dry fried green beans were delicious but quite salty - would be good paired with white rice. Scallion pancake beef roll was crispy, flaky, flavourful, and delicious. The Legend fried rice was loaded with toppings like shrimp, Chinese sausage, corn; a bit oily (you can see it on the spoon in the pic) but very tasty. Overall, all of the food tasted good and was great value for price.

Service was amazingly fast. Bathrooms and tables were clean.

I can see this being a go-to spot for Coquitlam locals to catch a quick casual meal of Sichuan Chinese food. I'm looking forward to coming back to try their dry spicy hot pot and chili boiled fish!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqip9WwvMx664_JHQLBQnmzF2qxDwFx6NYuSgS&fid=0x0:0x578fb8e94ebe9c76"],"When":"2023-6-12"}]

Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I usually enjoy my visits to Mariner Brewery in Coquitlam. Free parking lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZOep9PY3X_UZZI0gHiWKfkD3_Rwg7S6IlxOXy&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"shotavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMh1hfEFIJYaCTSLthIdHQ3TANUnSyqWujpD58h8MinLMJyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a casual place to grab a drink and found this spot on Google Maps.

The atmosphere was really nice and relaxing, and I thought it would be great to come here on a sunny day.

This time, I only ordered a drink without food, but next time I want to come back for some food and beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8MebbW-WnQTRvvxKA_I0ZvOyBNH4FxfomcuPu&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"jasonbenj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXesObwVr-MYoNivn747YIQhYO4b8Vn-9xP5t36MuM6wxR0MRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time back since the renovation. Sadly, it looks like a lot of re-branding of the same old product is 90% of it. Also, they took all the good items off the menu. RIP beer cheese dip, you will be missed. Sorry to say but it's not for me anymore. Also, $13 25 flight before tax !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOql9qRevUlia8U9C-dRW3PT6r5a5AmKlZ5qwHk&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great beers and great food for a brewery as well. We got the fries with mango chipotle and it was delicious! There‚Äôs also a great atmosphere inside - not too loud, good lighting and very clean. Would go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7VsLepap0KHEDl1zc5eEsDCQ9ndL4l7M2shto&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Christina Faminoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX12CPz5calL7TtQ0KnMyeMWTusgq3nB56xjWsl60LKS9agnIFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had the burger of the month, the Fall Forage smash with the falafel patty, and a stout. Both were awesome. Falafel was super fresh and tasty. I've tried most of their beers, and kombucha, and I appreciate that they are all really different, and don't all just taste like hops. Love that they added a food menu! Nice to be able to get good hot food instead of just snacks, like a lot of breweries. This is one of my favourite places. Would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9KQYgc3UAPTrvyVhcEulEHKDPEevANrCc4rQ&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came to this brewery with a meetup group and it was an on experience. There were limited non-alcoholic drinks on the menu, but they had four different craft sodas. I tried the cherry cola craft soda, the taste was interesting, but it wasn‚Äôt great, a bit flat. I also tried the pretzel and they were very generous with the mustard, but it was overall still very bland and got too cold too quickly. It‚Äôs a nice space to hang out and it can get busy even on weekday evenings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5hAZODlvyOhf9B5lJi8jBxhRFGkFm5uo_rePD&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-12-21"},{"Name":"Lauren St John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi3pWsd_jh8y8V1Pl7XbMiNRgCVHq-YYCdAOx_KkkOFRnXREk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pass on this one. Unless you're a beer and ale aficionado, keep going. Sorely disappointed in the food. We heard it had improved with new owners but it's obvious that more changes are needed. They charge $17 (plus tax and tip) for 8 chicken wings. That's outrageous. We tried the Jamaican patties and they were ok. The venue is cozy with more outside seating than inside. The service is "meh." The beer was average. There's not a lot for non-alcoholic beverages. The whole experience left us nonplussed. We will not go back or recommend it.  We spent $65 for 2 beers, 8 wings, a can of ginger ale and 2 Jamaican patties. It‚Äôs a good sign when all the servers and patrons are Korean. Soup was very bland, but the galbi was delicious. Service call by pressing a button at your booth. Menu isn‚Äôt large and very little banchan (barely enough for two people)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVPDxJmtYBMa6TYpMwheidrWeuU-tbsG66oSra&fid=0x0:0x8bc17fa85fb1b6ec"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Sandy Y. (CameraGourmet)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQ9J8ig1HwUQBJbXRdKDIwR0OrTw3YtQtyHDEaRuCN8XnUDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wang Ga Ma ÏôïÍ∞ÄÎßà delivers authentic Korean cuisine right here in Vancouver.  They don't serve a ton of side dishes (banchan Î∞òÏ∞¨), but their radish kimchi (kkakdugi ÍπçÎëêÍ∏∞) is a standout.  They even provide tools for cutting meat, seafood, veggies, and noodles!

Walking into Wang Ga Ma feels like stepping into Korea.  Most of the diners are Korean, which is an excellent sign that this spot captures Korea's true flavours and vibe.

Their soups and rice are amazing in hot stone bowls (ttukbaegi ÎöùÎ∞∞Í∏∞).  The bone soups are super delicious.  We've tried several dishes from their menu and always left satisfied.  Don't miss the burnt rice tea in the stone pot after your meal ‚Äî it really completes the experience!

Wang Ga Ma is located in Hanin Village.  While waiting for a table, we love grocery shopping at H-Mart nearby.

This place might be well-known to Koreans, but it could be a hidden gem for others.  There's nothing fancy about their menu or entrance, and they don't even have a social media account, but they've been in business for years.  That says something.

Highly recommend checking Wang Ga Ma out!

They get super busy and there‚Äôs a line up that can get pretty long if you don‚Äôt get there before 6 for dinner.

Food wise, if you‚Äôre looking for a soup/stew, this is an absolutely solid option.

The service is a little bit on the slower side, we got our order and food, but no one else ever came back, so if we wanted more tea or water, we had to go up and ask. This could be because there‚Äôs only one or two people on the floor, and it does get busy.

Overall, if you can overlook the small flaws, the food is tasty and worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQ0CoaNkluIKlMekyGqeRew28qB74zV6HmQq_A&fid=0x0:0x8bc17fa85fb1b6ec"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The dishes arrived piping hot, opt for the stone rice ‚Äì its hot stone bowl yields a satisfyingly crispy layer at the bottom.

While the restaurant's interior is pretty small in size, the quick turnaround and efficient service make for a seamless dining experience. They also renovated recently so it looks more clean and fresh.

In my opinion, it stands out as one of the better Korean restaurants for soups. Don't miss the complimentary whole kimchi (it‚Äôs amazing).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-7YsI33WuxbI2rSNmd4sDD5DOz96nM3-FADvt&fid=0x0:0x8bc17fa85fb1b6ec"],"When":"2024-1-31"},{"Name":"Eva Tong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbdn1JwTeGwTMz4zaH_aM0s2MjqUg4f-ith9g4COdwAGXFieA4Ow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Hanging out with my husband‚Äôs friends. We found this place is quite cozy and family-like restaurant. However it is quite full during dinner time, the server asked us to order while we are waiting outside in the cold already. We were standing outside for 15-20 mins before seated. They seem to be too busy serving other tables and since we don‚Äôt speak Korean so they don‚Äôt come around unless we need them. The restaurant has a few flies flying around while we are eating. They have a bottle of water for us to fill by ourselves. Their front page menu is 1-2 people food size, and the back of the menu some are for groups, 3-5 people food size. (The prices are different comparing front and back of the menu, which we don‚Äôt know at first until we asked) Their food is delicious and size is good, the beef is soft and tender. Seafood pancake is crispy and soft in the inside, a good size for our group to enjoy. We ordered two rice stone bowls and each come with a soup. The pork in stone bowl is more flavourful as it is spicy, while for the beef stone bowl tastes pretty plain so everyone needs to add some spicy sauce into it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYJKAg-YC4295iNWc5ZDs1A8N6OR3csGfzL27b&fid=0x0:0x8bc17fa85fb1b6ec"],"When":"2023-10-14"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Korean food cravings brought us to Hanin Village in Coquitlam. So tasty they didn't even need ketchup!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOupzXR9Znz2moILexerkTwqsTjirx2aPiO1shv&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Roozegar Mohammadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrQru4VExe7pdnc_LNPc1yA4v-RaJaPJWbL5u-B9MOm7dojm-4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"1- Thank you and a quick question  regarding your meat shop,  Is there any Halal certification accredited by Halal Canada?
2- Your answer: "Response from the owner
Thank you for your inquiry! We‚Äôre proud to share that our supplier is one of the best Halal meat providers in the entire country, ensuring the highest quality and adherence to Halal standards.
Regarding your question, yes, our supplier is accredited by Halal Canada, so you can shop with confidence.
By the way, if you‚Äôve enjoyed our services, would you consider giving us a 5-star review instead of 3? Your support means a lot to us, and we‚Äôd love to hear what more we can do to earn that extra star from you!"

3- my reply to your reply:"Thank you for your reply. Unfortunately, i have to change the mark to 1 star because of the following objective evidences:
"Although you mentioned that your supplier has an accredited halal certificate, based on my observations during everyday shopping and watching your Deli and Meatshop employees, it seems that you are not adhering to halal provider rules. Specifically, you are selling halal and non-halal meat together and using the same knives and surfaces to cut them. The regulations in this regard are similar to those for allergen and non-allergen items, where cross-contamination is strictly prohibited. Rather than this, open packages of halal and non-halal meat inside the freezer or fridge should be completely separated. I recommend that you read the Halal International Standard requirements for retail stores. Until you are able to meet these standards, please remove all halal signage from your store, as it is misleading to Muslim customers in this regard"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Fasihizadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeEgxRiuCQGGcgBhaC0R0-E7HN9SKaiGfOrL8NTnYlp6WMk2xa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered a birthday cake to Suzan at the bakery and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with the result! We had a server named Sareh who is very friendly and attentive. She‚Äôs also recommended and offered sampling authentic food we‚Äôve never tried before and they taste really good and we all love it! It‚Äôsone of the best places to have really good quality food and customer service. In addition the atmosphere is very comfortable and inviting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fuzzley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuQBLG7TksG6wDxiaXxGD7Hm142h_aQxwM9_mE25IYjf3jo0BguA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As a long-term customer I was very disappointed with my recent experience at Urban Gate. I brought to the attention of the cashier that I had purchased some barbari bread a few days ago, and that I was told these were baked the night before.
Unfortunately when I took the bread home and opened it on the same day, I found both to be rotten and stale. I did not want to drive all the way back for a little refund that. The following week while shopping at the store, I informed the cashier. All I sought was a simple acknowledgment of my concern and an apology for the inconvenience. Instead, what followed was a lengthy justification about how fresh bread can spoil overnight due to moisture. Additionally, the cashier explained their return policy, stating that I should have brought back the receipt and the rotten bread for a refund.
I felt that the response lacked empathy and a proper understanding of customer service. The interaction came off as arrogant, and it left me feeling undervalued as a customer. It is disappointing to know that, as a loyal customer, my concerns were not taken seriously. I hope Urban Gate can improve its customer service training to better handle situations like this in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marjan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJi5kZ8SK7DmiaOMIRuV-4Ttne1NBXp-Dh_P2EIrXoD-QM7Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This store has a good selection of products from my home country , especially in the meat department, where the staff are polite and helpful.
However, the customer service at checkout is very disappointing and rude, especially from the cashier ladies. They rarely greet  and often have a negative attitude. For example, one cashier today threw the receipt on the counter, slammed her hand on it, and walked away without saying anything. I even said hello and thank you, but she didn‚Äôt respond. When I asked the others if they had the same experience, they said they did.
These interactions make shopping feel unwelcoming. I hope the staff realizes that everyone deserves respect and that good service is important.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Now, let‚Äôs talk about the food‚Äîabsolutely outstanding! Their nostalgic Pizza and the Tah Dig with Gheymeh took me straight back to the beautiful memories of Iran. The flavors were authentic, rich, and reminded me of the comfort of home-cooked meals from back in our beloved country. It was like taking a delicious trip to Iran without ever leaving Vancouver!

For all my fellow Persians in the area, I 100% recommend that you come and try this place for yourself. Ron‚Äôs Kitchen has truly captured the essence of Iranian cuisine, and I can‚Äôt wait to return!

Thank you, Ron‚Äôs Kitchen, for a perfect meal and for bringing a slice of Iran to Vancouver!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiXbAVwcP3z55Fs-Xct5p7ayC1xWdYz0NWIKh0&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Hamid Hadilou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ12isydAXwM3ARp62zO3XO3aAlRt1Lz7EzJoHZ_jp5xJJpCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have a new Chef in PoCo Town! The attention to detail in both the food and the service was evident, making it clear that Ron‚Äôs Kitchen is dedicated to excellence. [{"Name":"Jonny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJShSgCHbmme6GLETHZczdb6MWGsJKCwpKUqZlkj3SXYWukfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Been to Sol Lee's Korean Restaurant for several meals. They're in the Hanin Village plaza. Clientele is mainly Koreans.

- Banchan
- Hot stone bowl bibimbap ($17.95) - rice crisped up in the dolsot. Solid
- Soft tofu stew ($17.95) - homey
- Pork back-bone stew ($18.95) - gamjatang was excellent. Broth had depth, complexity
- Pork with rice and mixed veg in hot stone pot ($17.95) - rice wasn‚Äôt crispy, tender pork
- Spicy cold noodles with yulmu kimchi ($15.95) - decent but standard fare
- Deep-fried rex sole ($18.95) - every table orders this. Sole was perfectly cooked; light, crispy, not oily. Two good sized portions
- Steamed monkfish ($47.95 medium) - agujjim was a mountain of bean sprouts, sadly bland and flavourless. My least favourite dish
- Skate soup ($17.95) - broth had a touch of smokiness. Skate was cartilagey

Some interesting, unique dishes at SL.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOPV26g_4xH_g0o0lVXsLW9zVk9SuB5pDvdQbi&fid=0x0:0x7a7465984d59684f"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Fuzzy Nemo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhjGNDhI-RZYgIiVRXnRDEQCiyyP-dsVjb7EhBkcymNr9MvYi0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was pretty authentic,  in my mind. I would love to come back for other food on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNA9aHHzTUDF_eKvITm2xR_9coXhb12wOsxU7H5&fid=0x0:0x7a7465984d59684f"],"When":"2024-4-17"},{"Name":"Kabooles P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpcl-z1Upr3dHvkNkgTrEuLquBclgtoXN23rfj7Nc5hb-0tMyfXg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I usually avoid deep-fried food, but I decided to try the recommended fish dish at this restaurant, and I was surprised! user_reviews: [{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A noodles/rice dish ($14.95), an iced hk milk tea ($1.25), and bubble waffles ($2.25) is a pretty good deal for a meal considering how expensive eating out might be. I like to come here once in a while, a favourite of mine. Comforting customizable soup noodles. Waffle cake is not as tasty as the ones I've had in Hong Kong but it's not bad (can be improved by adding more sauce, peanut butter, condensed milk etc. inside). Staff speaks Cantonese. They close their dining room after ~8pm but you can still order for takeout (which I did and took home to eat); they pack the soup separately so it won't get soggy. There's also a few tables outside that you can eat on instead.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQ_NUIebPeUa28qRGQr-zRNXTokSJZdFRRtpnV\u0026fid=0x0:0x9cc78848dcf357cb"],"When":"2023-12-16"},{"Name":"Jessica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw-LXo5xhG4SA6zCFCGB3BxfH-AfeUaeOC4Ca76Q_iufHH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible service, so many issues with the service at the cashier. I online ordered and when I arrived to pay they told me unless I paid using debit there is no discount. There was no mention of this on the website and I have not encountered this at their other locations. Also when I asked if it was possible to eat in the restaurant they told me no because it was an online order and must be take out. The restaurant was empty minus one booth that had one man drinking a single bubble tea. I understand if they were busy but seriously the restaurant was super empty. Overall the food was mediocre and there was absolutely no incentive to order online as I received no discount and wasn‚Äôt even able to eat inside afterwards. Will be avoiding this location at all costs in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Ao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkBvZ6ce_zHnWsLqA5ojfX0nMQ_CDE0WIX5k8yhZ46T8a1BLiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Noodles were decent but the bubble waffle was delicious. The customer service was outstanding‚Äîfriendly, attentive, and made me feel truly valued as a customer. On top of that, the quality of the pizza was exceptional. Fresh ingredients, perfectly cooked crust, and delicious toppings made every bite unforgettable. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back and highly recommend to anyone looking for great pizza and fantastic service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nima Samadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZYjK7LkbimZZ9ef6fheipzK9U8WYlT_FCafhCohZ1aIX39A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fresh Slice (Coquitlam Centre) has quickly become one of my favourite lunch spots over the last few months. I find myself going there at least a few times a week now.

I'll let you in a secret. Although they specialize in pizza by the slice for a quick bite and take home pizzas, they've got one of the best deals for a personal size pizza to eat on your own for lunches or available whenever really. $12 for a medium with unlimited toppings. And I mean unlimited. Choose from 8 different sauces, 7 different cheeses, 30 different toppings. Think of it as the Subway of pizza's. Honestly a deal so good I doubt it'll stay at the price it is for long. Definitely the best value in the area. And filling too.

To top it off. I love how you can order through the app/site. And you get a text alert when it's ready for pickup. No waiting in line or ordering in-store. They're also open until 5AM in the morning if you get the late night eats. And the store is impeccable clean and the staff and store manager are extremely pleasant to chat with while you wait.

Highly recommend if you're looking for great pizza in and around the Coquitlam area that's always open and the staff is always pleasant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSDVQdeIogUM5pcMwRkgSnHSlP9lvySED-OLLk&fid=0x0:0xc6bc18ecc74aef53"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Kirpal Johal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmLzsgZLQ-AcVDJ3-c59fr_fqCNVMoIQGsn_hzjb-jHFChUA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a chance to drop by FreshSlice Pizza in Coquitlam and what a pleasant entry into the shop with a wonderful greeting by Jasmeen and with a smile which definitely makes a day better. She was very helpful and detailed with the making of my pizza, i must say this is one of the best & pleasant staff i‚Äôve ever dealt with. The pizza she made me was tasty and was exactly what i wanted. We left feeling that they were more interested in taking our money than providing a welcoming atmosphere.
First and last time here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amir Beheshtian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJ6C_Bum8v5F39RUuKIpjJ_TP5q278YpYCRflkkdsQCBi_EyZ9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was soooo delicious one of the best noodle places I have ever experienced, highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQJeR7Nx9Ku2O1_5IaWYLDRXhNyfjDz9ppaDw8&fid=0x0:0x2b766e3b9b7bf89b"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Derek Hansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaBRm-VY_m99UwZ6UwdvGjzB7nw1EejvhcMIUbGB5N2HHxrZpHjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Have been in a couple times before not bad but there are better options around for Vietnamese food. [{"Name":"Gustavo Torres Lauria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgB5NGic5lsyx494iU5NEDDDei2vBk5Dik0XtIwHIOdAsln9HE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sushi California is such a bad sushi place that you will regret it. I feel so upset I got to pay for this awful food: the Dynamite Roll was very weird tasting. Tons of lettuce (in a dynamite Roll!!? Like, really? Unheard of!) and on top of it, the lettuce was off, too mushy and well tasted rotten.. Long story short, terrible! We also got a Mr Prawn roll, soaked, but like really soaked in mayonnaise and a sweet sauce. Too rich, too fatty‚Ä¶too disgusting. Make yourself a favour and chose another sushi shop. Any other, it will be better hands down.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwZl0kJgh9FrRr6Xxfk7XxyoCFpDyk1ocgNMz0&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Mohammad_s Zare","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0zvPgAwUepTiYIAUBS1yK_ACR_lBIpMWJx1RjPIgsoDnibPMz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing Sushi and Generous Portions!
I recently visited Sushi California in Coquitlam with my wife, and it was an incredible experience. The food was absolutely perfect‚Äîfresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. On top of that, the portions were huge, making it an excellent value for the price.

The restaurant had a great atmosphere, and the service was friendly and efficient. Whether you‚Äôre a sushi lover or just looking to try something new, this place is a must-visit. We‚Äôll definitely be coming back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeI3Cs79Mlaxc-wMUOtW1bpURpme_tGfArB8bW&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"mackenzie jackson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgC9tzVS7yRJwpcQ5nDzCNUvslbCgrhdSrEMgtr15St-UUo4Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place! They have the best Nigiri and Sashimi in town, their portions are big and fresh unlike other restaurants and the servers are kind and pretty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvl_iEnVk_yp3zyXO4YFzKFSGNuJAZjnaQnPXr&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update: Went in for dine-in at 5pm, true service was a little slow as they seemed understaffed, but it was still a decent dine-in (4/5 for Dine-in)

So happy they opened a Sushi Cali here! Not sure if it's because they just opened but the portion and flavor is 10x better than the other locations. I will most likely order here, minimum, once a week!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUBxlTq8joKbn9Tatg_7Xlvx_uzxndzjI198rx&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2021-12-12"},{"Name":"Cora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9YQmsmKhqCSvMVPAZKT18eImIWQ2QjEOLJi24FjTkNMSIg53C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally a Sushi California has opened up here! I've always liked the one on North Road but the parking is atrocious so I never went. Tonight we tried out this new location and the service and food were great! The food came out quickly and the service was excellent! If you needed anything they were happy to help and refilled our tea often. The food was fresh and very large portioned. I'm glad a new location has been opened here in Coquitlam.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtxlzQ69e1MqOiCqoDn76iexZBOuyDRl393O5v&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2021-12-19"},{"Name":"VanGogh013","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxFt4JIPmZ64ezhA6PUPFbMs3FhoBo_XeES_VgIT5n9E34NQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Normal sushi . Nothing special
Today Aug 31. We went again but wasn‚Äôt that good at all specially dark horse roll. It‚Äôs awful and other rolls are really bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHTngwVVWmmWSmCHoaNmT3g-a8-Q9UYN1WKJVD&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not busy at all when we went to Sushi California on Saturday night. Got enough food for 2 for both the meal and breakfast next day for $45. Prices were reasonable especially for the individual sushi. Vegas Roll was pretty good and had a small kick to the usual California Roll. The veggie sunomono came in a small bowl but the base was very flavourful and refreshing. The tuna from the BC Roll combo tasted fresh and not so fishy. The restaurant was playing mukbang videos which was an interesting choice. Small parking lot out front. Would come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgPtL7fSgaGRiA6El5vY7FT51CBmNCzE-5cgrH&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2023-4-29"},{"Name":"J Q","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWLFaR2htiLNLIQAXB2-FbuNystyoB794RiAm0Uo82lJgg8OdK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update:

Visited again recently, food were even better then last time and the customer service got much improved!! Loved there Ton Katsu, it was crispy outside and soft & moist inside.
Never disappointed :):)

They have just right amount of rice on the nigiris, you will get LARGE portion of food than what you are paying. Great customer service and very clean :) I would come back for sure","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyL9OzF-uKdBpBEJNlsr8Yx19y7hRVeKM13avr&fid=0x0:0xeb1c795ce885c7de"],"When":"2022-3-29"}]

[{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A true hidden gem in Coquitlam. My partner can't get enough of their extra spicy chicken, and I thoroughly enjoyed their fries too. Highly recommend checking this place out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNt9f88ndaRd036qoohrw_t3ZPHje_k5haQCOSq&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"argh c","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2c34N4-KZC9sfBqKbqJSYJcFxkP3ce_vYTvsj7Y6T7ga6urdW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food was generally fine. Things were still crisp when they arrived. The soy garlic chicken was sweeter than I prefer and the original recipe chicken a little bland, but that‚Äôs just nitpicky personal preference.

Watched the Door Dash driver, on the app, circle the neighborhood a few times before finding our house, so we know why the food was cool-ish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVDNEQpXxKKZfsQLkRk4icrTxRH467vpVhg0gJ&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"Belinda Jin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQN2pGhoNzK76Clox_ElaIbflMT40WxZHUMqKpCiI5FtnukLZ6Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The biggest advantages living in the Coquitlam is that you can have authentic Korean food. GOGO Chicken & BBQ is one of my favorite Korean Chicken Restaurant. I'm highly recommend everyone to give this place a try.

GoGo Chicken & BBQ is a small Korean Restaurant, located on 105-2973 Glen Dr, Coquitlam. Since it's small and on the street, it's very easy to pass by if you are driving. Inside the restaurant, only few tables are there.  This place is better for grab food to go.

My husband and I have ordered food from this place so many times. The Chicken here are good, crispy, flavourful, juicy and succulent inside. The most important is fresh fried chicken! The portions are huge.  Normally, we ordered 1/2 Original KFC and 1/2 Soy Garlic  Chicken boneless as well as the Go Go Fries. It will take us more than three meals to finish all these food. So, when you are ordering the food, please be careful. It will be a lot of food.

Highly Recommend this place !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUn21xEnFKANZEbRy7Qq97dAtQw7Cbc9L1rx-D&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2021-5-23"},{"Name":"Elnaz Etminan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmz21sbX2OgbPxtYDJY17TDDX2tdEpJRPILPXCRlOuUkYQWC0X=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good location and 2 tables outside for use. Ordered Chicken Bao and Chiken BBQ bowl.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNe8yi7a9udBBcI1HqFYM29iKsRbiOR5od9uQdi&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Dasha Melnik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXL2jlFLZHs9ZwNN5ssey6RDI1bggc2Q8OBg2ZHd1-2oyzkn1XB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Half size box of deep fried chicken. I should admit it is tasty, but the box wasn't fully packed for $16+taxes. I will be back when it gets warmer to eat outside. The place is nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYqRgQeWDTdQiANZJjZ7-V8QoXhl4pq6v76nfm&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2024-2-29"},{"Name":"Teeka Nedilenka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2T28buTAQlAhyk_WUlnanatMQSqwCz9P8Q45ikEbQ9lxEJf50=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You can't even comprehend how amazing this food is, seriously juicy amazing chicken with the most crispy crust on the outside. The staffer are always so friendly, one mistake I should have gotten the cilantro spicy sauce to dip this in because I had it last time and it was absolutely mind blowingly delicious!!! ü§§ü§§ The prices are unbelievably reasonable for how amazing their food/chicken is. I'm sad that they're not open on Wednesdays/ chicken wing Wednesdays here would be my all-time favorite go-to!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcLj2UIW_Ii0cHrEJPz9DyyrI7-lTeup7pvAl8&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2023-9-21"},{"Name":"Jiwon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIsZg-pNG4lb9PqK7xCUlXSaQxpd3Jdf6ktNLgUMoYNFrnzim8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am SO stoked about this one! LOCAL, CRISPY, DELICIOUS & JUICY!

Although we had dinner ready to be eaten at home, we couldn't help trying out a couple items. We decided on 2 pieces of regular fried chicken ($5.99) and pork belly bao bun ($3.50).

As we was waiting, the owner was talking to us and let us know that they make their own special brine for their chicken to make it more juicy and flavourful. He also said that it's mainly a take out restaurant but people can eat in if there are spots. He was a very lovely guy and you can tell that he really cares about his business and his customers.

It did take a while to get our food but they make everything to order. I hate when you go to a fried chicken place and they give you fried chicken that has been siting there for who knows how long. So I didn't mind waiting.

The fried chicken was extremely crispy, juicy and flavourful! It wasn't too greasy and didn't make me feel sick afterwards either. The bao bun was just okay, I wouldn't order it again.

I am a huge fan of Church's but Go Go possibly has taken over to the #1 spot. I will most definitely be returning to try out everything else on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwr_oYJunwJKKPjS5cIBewFtCO3gdOcftXIE4C&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2019-11-10"},{"Name":"Iris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuI2UF9tE3ZrxOyUZSh_nizM_Sr9TFUm8fPaLEBlASv1eRDOW2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the Skirt Steak Bowl and I was really impressed. The steak was very flavourful and tender. I loved how the sides were roasted brussel sprouts and kale, very different from regular rice bowls that you see. I will be back next time to try their chicken!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdYbiAVLNG0w44siPkTs4GPKpuk1ci7o1W9Uj3&fid=0x0:0x37a99b2a94c8acc5"],"When":"2019-11-8"}]

She said what she can only do is to take the veggie dish back to the kitchen get rinsed and stir fry it again for us.  This is just ridiculous. My family and friends have supported this restaurant since they opened. Today we went and had a dish that tasted so awful we sent it back Immediately and were told we still had to pay for it because it‚Äôs our fault we didn‚Äôt like it‚Ä¶..then the manger had to argue with the ‚Äúboss‚Äù and sent the male ‚Äúboss‚Äù out to Yell at us two women in the restaurant which was the most disgusting and disrespectful experience ever. I will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzEragvZzg_Yg2jdetGbUQJR-8weKnZSkpR4Sw&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"There's nothing bad to say nor is there anything amazing or special to mention about this place. We all left still feeling hungry and how we preferred other Japanese restaurants.

Not much service was offered at all besides waiting with our hand up for a while for someone to finally notice we were ready to order. The tables are close together and the group of people seated behind us were incredibly loud and talking about uncomfortable topics, contributing to an overall "meh"  experience that almost leaned towards negative if it wasn't for the nice presentation of the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdFohvFV-ToVUZA8IyMBzgz1CZ0GG8KH-KPkmR&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-3-4"}]

[{"Name":"Dominic Faria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXja4ouwjZsqs66nHtVuLS2IUwKRavf12dJTVD_z_WIl8IDQw17_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant has a wonderful atmosphere and great service, our server was very on top of clearing empty plates and when I asked for more tea she got it right away. The food was absolutely delicious, so fresh and so beautifully presented. We ordered hells chicken to start, then I ordered the Dragon roll, Tiger roll, BC roll and California roll, while my date ordered one of the lunch specials. The prices are very reasonable and comparable to other venues, so there aren't really any pricing surprises if you order sushi regularly. You can tell it's a busy venue as there were several customers in the restaurant and a steady flow of customers picking up orders and this was a visit from 12-1pm to give reference, when the restaurant opens at 11:30am. Would definitely recommend going to Sushi On and will definitely come back 10/10.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEQhCMrEAVKv0Jdspa-kYtJngVNFTr3N9gFQ-D&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Aaron MacEwen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Ky6ximZkKg4l7lYD2oaitNzrrzF59AoquM1M8Z4is8xtKGnG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like rice rolled up and stuffed with things then this is the place for you!  Also if you know how to use chopsticks is a plus but not mandatory.  We had a basic sushi roll layout.  Cali, teriyaki chicken and the classic dynamite.  Standard decent rolls.  Then came the Wild Wild West!! Hot Diggity Dog it was phenomenal.  Presented really nice and clean. The torched salmon and avocado topping with sauce reminded me of the BBQ salmon my uncle used to make.  Awesome Roll one of the best I have had.  Definitely worth the trip.  Restaurant super clean and staff were excellent.  Cool vibe and modern decor completes the look.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvxydOxrJa0wlxtQmDjfD-KBgu4c55a1ZcOQsR&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Chris Bennett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiyRctkUdXqKsV-iEZq3A4JF3vUq2QZcrQQUBG84a49C195QUzuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi On is a hidden gem among the thousands of sushi spots across the lower mainland!

I was introduced to this place on a date night 6 years ago, and we're now happily married‚Äîthis sushi spot has become a staple in our lives.

We order from them once a month, and I've brought many family members to experience their incredible menu.

The atmosphere is beautifully ambient, filled with positive energy that makes every visit special.

My go-to rolls are The PoCo Lady roll and The Halloween roll‚Äîtwo flavors I‚Äôll be ordering for the rest of my life.

Sushi On is more than just a restaurant; it‚Äôs a place that holds cherished memories and continues to deliver excellence every time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONjlyIzpQcUnXnOizAOFkSHrJq9w9ofIqeMIrz&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Rosa Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgxwKwGYZa5ZolcnIrIix77qAMZ1zxGI9KVT5k_Mku76RimgEn_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden gem in Port Coquitlam! We tried one of the lunch set menu as well as the fresh sashimi and aburi nigiri. Everything was flavourful!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMX22X_X29Kg2VjgxyQmEw8f06f7dD_-OCKgIDl&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Lizzie S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5qIG1VmBASZQRSYXsIMifm6rtLhZA6xcKTGDs0bvXyJT2pXkmsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a decent sushi place. Food was very fresh and good seasonings. Services were ok even if they made a wrong order this time. I liked the bright and tidy environment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcExQvJoB8Mi9z9h6f3yZB9N23EDnofTUZCtAt&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"Dominic Kohler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr_Rds6INzk8uBD6vTiDGl0q4vd8v53cFPe8-iHXMsWrqpx1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here for the first time for dinner. Was recommended this sushi place so had to give it a try. Really nice atmosphere, super modern and clean. I appreciate receiving complimentary tea upon sitting down. Menu is large, something for everyone, easy to navigate also. I ended up starting with an appetizer. The deep fried spicy tofu, it was delicious. Then went for a few rolls. The spicy California roll, and an inari roll. Prices were fairly reasonable. Very fast service, food came in minutes. Everything tasted fresh and was well made. Would come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNiG7bVibVUdk062rY7zS_KwCTJXHqfzgWOdV0&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Staff were friendly and attentive. The decoration is new and modern. Food wise, presentation, taste and freshness are all pretty good. Nothing surprised/impressed me though. The price is on the higher end. Lunch combo can be ordered at dinner time with $3 extra.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYshSH1Dq0FeX15xOidTXDCGLtho34VKC7cE9X&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"John M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWItgijJKwgA0f52g38y2veJk-Ddfx32Y6n5pRa8jqM3m7RR0lStA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall food was fresh and tasty for the reasonable price point. Bento and wakame salad portions were a lot larger than I thought they would be which was a plus. Tempura was crispy, Cali rolls were good, miso was hot and fresh. Torched salmon was okay.

One server came to check on us every once in a while and was quite pleasant and smiled a lot. The restaurant was pretty quiet and clean (smelled of cleaner when I walked in).

Would recommend and would go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODlFmUmJqhZGgihF3UmUr1SL7NNEZSV8OTpv91&fid=0x0:0x2c6dfc723189a0c1"],"When":"2023-3-18"}]

The standout chef makes this branch exceptional. I highly recommend dining here. We ordered the spicy chicken bites, chicken karaage, and beef teriyaki, and each dish was fantastic. Just a heads-up: if you visit late, sushi might not be available as they switch to a late-night menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN49Ks3ddRv49CewTMfgD6DHa7mpOe76H01K6c&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Nelson Mah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMvSq7-l8Kje4bUGcJFo_gjx31JEZujbDf7RAmASmnqxtIa8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came on a Saturday with my cousins. Very much enjoyed. Great location by Coquitlam centre.

Awesome roll was actually awesome. Glad we tried it. Mango roll is also a favorite. Sometimes the computer i-pad system to order food needs to be charged and thus have to order by server sometimes. Can be confusing for new customers. Maybe charge all the iPad's at night to help improve efficiency.

Was great experience. Server was kind to refill hot water and tea regularly. I recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF9N9bDYccydaW7nM5ZX_3HWUgfoXb19TgbmXV&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"argh c","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2c34N4-KZC9sfBqKbqJSYJcFxkP3ce_vYTvsj7Y6T7ga6urdW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very crowded on a Sunday evening, fortunately we had a reservation. That said, we were competing with a bustling take out business in addition to the other patrons in the restaurant for kitchen time.  It took quite a while to get our order taken and although food started to arrive almost immediately we started to wonder if some things had missed being recorded (they hadn‚Äôt, it was just a long time start to finish). Noteworthy is that hot food arrived first, strangely the salad was delivered last.  Timing issues aside, the quality of food was very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPR71aAmtNVdYdVWNqI5KToT7ZnsFk1gt_-3Pm_&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2023-7-8"},{"Name":"rob donnelly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbVA4p6yG-H9CQp-_Eh3D0lvIffky01DTDsh0aIk6h_fTFkc3t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Long time Sushi Town customer, it‚Äôs always been very good, no complaints. However on this visit, all the portions are noticeably smaller. Awesome Roll definitely not awesome this visit. Definitely less fish on top, and at $14.95 we feel ripped off. Salmon nigiri, noticeably less salmon, and some of the rice not cooked properly. After many years and dollars spent in this restaurant, we won‚Äôt be coming back. Very disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emmanuel Carino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ9g6OsewbE5PvEJQG0W2MrejjY87xqZcS0O_-lbnLLATuQeGq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Town in Coquitlam is a fantastic spot for delicious Japanese food at great prices. The menu has a wide selection of sushi, sashimi, and creative rolls, all served in generous portions. The quality of the food is excellent, with fresh ingredients and beautifully presented dishes that make each visit a treat. The atmosphere is casual and welcoming, perfect for both small gatherings and family meals. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring you have a pleasant dining experience. Whether you're a sushi lover or just looking to try something new, Sushi Town is a must-visit for a satisfying meal!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Aanei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5r3ZjSCmXMog20pYsE9fANH214snHKhL7fPna0KCOa7Y9FQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going to sushi town for years and love it! Wheelchair accessible washroom and parking.  Plenty of parking available.  Prices are reasonable.  They are a must check out place!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOopCAGmjqnOdOpyxFpVeAkYLMHD2EV5q8vmwEX&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2023-1-5"}]

[{"Name":"Nicky Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdbrHfH4GFsTTqgK1b8FKEyHjbYNyqA15i6JBcGlTzjesmGsA3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Doppio Zero Pizza truly lives up to its name when it comes to their pizza! The crust was perfectly thin and crispy, with just the right amount of chew, and the toppings were fresh, flavorful, and generously portioned.

As for the pasta, it was just okay. While it wasn‚Äôt bad by any means, it didn‚Äôt quite stand out the way their pizza did. It could use a little more flair to match the high standard set by their pizzas. I also didn‚Äôt like how the pasta noodle was too over done? üò¨

The tiramisu was delicious as well.

One thing to have in mind as well is the parking.. if you go during a busy time.. you might need to park in the residential area up the street and walk..

Overall, Doppio Zero Pizza is a must-visit if you‚Äôre craving top-tier pizza. I‚Äôll definitely be back for another round of their incredible pies!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWz1qkXa_dRoPp1tDige938yd0NVrn7CaniteR&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Youngsoo Song","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KF6xNrz8Ca-06zFTT1f92qb4UuXywvQbI5TeswgCgRYyBqNnHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was good and the server was friendly. I had the pizza and the burrata-- both were good and reasonably priced. I gave the food 4 because while the taste was good, the dough near the center of the pizza was so thin, the toppings kind of tore through it. Perhaps my toppings had too much moisture(?) but either way, I wish the middle had not torn.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4lvZij57sk_m_zZG-bu8SmTU-NubQmz8Gv00S&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Cheestravels (Cheestravels)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUu90KHK59eES_iLdA-5e4hTpzDDtNybwcTzvnfRLjdEkfHdQ5Xbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A tad overpriced for what they give you. Pizza is great and gnocchi is amazing. Tried a few dishes and pasta was decent but not incredible for price. Desserts were underwhelming with canned whipped cream on the sides. Was disappointed that they charge an automatic 20% gratuity charge for groups or 8 or more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVfMFJNbu9g2OV8HWFRcI2fA01-Ha4oSxuV8kV&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Conor Finding Realtor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWt3-qD1dIuKKhCigfciL6_hrPkCXppeVegMsaV8xEZkwNnNrs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down best Pizza in tri-cities. Love this place and such great Atmosphere!

I ordered the Margarita and this pizza was made to perfection. The staff had such a welcoming vibe as soon as I came through the door.

I met the owners Giulia and Daniel who are outstanding people that clearly have put there all into this restaurant. There story moving here from Italy is the icing on the cake.

If you want truly authentic Italian food come to Doppio Zero!

Thank you so much for the great service and amazing food!

I will be coming here a lot more!

Conor Finding","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNECU47lUiUaAQU5C8wuyEQ1na0QMa0t_F1iu5J&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Swimming Lion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoNuKoBPU8hDsJrOBlEDRPQawlWHi3C9rUvrLYtz7paaZM0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place !
Stone oven pizza so delicious the crust is thin, chewy and crispy
Love the carbonara  too the pork is very special hefty meat taste , fatty but not too fatty
Coffee was creamy and rich with dreamy aroma
affogato - rich and robust flavor with a pronounced coffee taste.
Servers are very friendly and attentive
Free parking lot
We went on Sunday evening around 8 pm the parking lot was pretty empty
We have party of 13 and when we pay server told us we don‚Äôt need to tip extra as for party over 8 they will automatically add 20% on top for gratuities","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLr6M3r84e3yCErwyvFutgs65ZD7_DzQAmlugN&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"N√¥MƒÅR √Ölt√Ø√ß≈Ç√∂≈õ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKVyqW_kOlfqb-yGJ_Ks--LFkl55GXHpZ6S3YNX2dqaycCck_x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice, quaint Italian restaurant at Como Lake Ave., in Coquitlam. Open kitchen well depicts their cleanness and pizza craftsmanship.This is my new go-to.üçï","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzpZBxs-lPZeno12i-7kpMiuuoOoeBWV2WbyXP&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Joshua Fang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVYKjZadI3GLvYlhP8JzW1RAWYF0hYt7IB342AdEQBC7hNDQVNQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretty crazy that this spot is in Coquitlam. [{"Name":"Ricardo Esteves","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhLIO2qt-2RQR0_aQCihSuDY8549ydYAIf_Ebc863j0CC6irdH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow!ü§© Best pizza I ever ate, hands down. This place takes the cake! Not sure how they cram all those toppings on and still manage to keep such a light, airy crispy crust. I‚Äôm visiting from Ontario and I saw the flyer in my Mom‚Äôs mail. She never orders pizza any more because it always sucks. Mom had never ordered from here before, but I decided to try it any ways. We were both so pleasantly surprised at how beautiful and delicious the pizza was. I may not live here, but my mom does and she will definitely order from this place again. Try it. You won‚Äôt be disappointed! ü§§ (we had the Juliet üòã)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfcmZDOkXuXHHfApnVXrXSE03TOb8qP-MbB4q0&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were in a time crunch and asked if we could get our pizza in a rush - they said yes and they delivered on their promise! Our pizza was tasty, hot and fresh, and we had plenty of time to make it to our next appointment. Our server was friendly and prompt. We‚Äôve been here a few times and will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLly5sdKZqb1_imp4OGBRs4Dhktp9UI7we_mRH&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's been awhile since I've had Me N Ed's Pizza, and it certainly didn't disappoint at all. It's still fantastic after all these years.

We decided to order a few pies for the NFL US Thanksgiving games on Thursday for delivery. And they arrived at a decent time, and still fairly hot still.

It's a little pricey, BUT you definitely get what you pay for. ( They definitely don't "SKIMP" on the toppings ) as you can see from the pictures provided.

We made up our own Pies two of which were the personal ones with their Gluten Free Crust. Which friends said were excellent. I myself made one up of original crust and Tomato sauce with Capicollo, Salami, Pepperoni, and Bacon. And it was outstanding and loaded with toppings. And the Capicollo was some of the best I've definitely had in a long time.

Great Pies and I/We will be definitely ordering more often from Me N Ed's Pizza Parlor...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZ8c0Q2gaomnnrh8SVY4SW_UCMu_Uc0GDiZvLh&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"J wico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFLTpvMyLxVfHKit3ZJqPccY65Bl-YeNGA1wEu8pZSIRWpww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pros:
- Family and team friendly. Great family atmosphere, which is always a plus for me when dining with our toddler.
- Considering how busy it was, the food came out quick.
- Staff are friendly.

Cons:
- There are 6 other pizza places within walking distance and I'd put it towards the bottom. This doesn't mean the pizza is bad, there's just too much decent competition.
- Price. 2 smalls were $36 before tax and tip and it was today's special...

Would I go again? Maybe for a team party or a kid's bday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1MNiIwxPsTfI_D1Gyey22Wh_Gy-8bxTa2Weij&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Lord Stanley (Lifepilot)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzQPaJP0C4QgYze9YWfcg4vOQGSlA7Fi1WI2IqpyzPqwuzcItLsg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We popped in for a quick pizza üçï before hockey ü•Ö üèí game as we really felt like pizza. Saw a few pizza shops and then came across Me-n-Ed‚Äôs which we knew from Burnaby.  We got a table right away. Staff were friendly and restaurant was clean. We saw the Salmon & Roasted Garlic pizza with goat cheese. Seemed interesting, so we ordered it. It was absolutely delicious üòã couldn‚Äôt fault a single thing about it. Crust was perfect and very flavorful! Yum! Pricing is also fair!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXkyEI6QptUTCf1-w_s5__bZl3WIuNYKdP0VLm&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-12-16"},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great location, very nice place with lots of room. Waitresses were welcoming and polite. The food was ok but had better Me & Ed's pizza. Chicken had a little bit of weird taste on BBQ chicken. Overall, it was ok. Place has a lot of free parking and good location. They have kids menu which comes with ice cream.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIEpEpFb1gDy7vAh00FHxcrupgV651s-LKiH6S&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"Victoria M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4EhJg4Rc2VuzKf5_JHxexyjVp-afUrXeUpfgefDqByTw_eqXIfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing meal here on Remembrance Day. The food here is always great. We tried their Mighty Caesar pizza for the first time‚Ä¶definitely will recommend. So many toppings which all pair ridiculously good together. Only critique I have is that I would expect quite a bit more beef to be on the nachos for the $4.50 price tag.

BUT enough about the food, I just want to point out Izzy for being the best server I‚Äôve seen in a long while. She was beyond swamped, legit had the entire room to herself. She needed bills paid, food cleared, food delivered and to make the drinks on top of that‚Ä¶.and she did it all. If she wasn‚Äôt doing all that she was answering multiple phone calls in between. Heck I‚Äôm surprised she wasn‚Äôt in the back cooking the pizzas herself at the rate she was going. Plus she was personable and extremely kind within all the chaos. Total superstar. 10/10 will come again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSa86tUfJWBd2NRD4nRR1FBYS_U1NiczNltakJ&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-11-12"},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10.
Such a fun place for a father's day adventure.  The restaurant is large; nicely decorated; and very clean. Service was outstanding!
The pizza was so yummy!!  Not your regular pizza "dough"; more like a thin crust flakey cracker - so tasty.  The toppings were super generous and fresh. The  Nachos were HUGE; served on a large platter so there were toppings on every chip.
Really fantastic food.  We will definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrwCYhvy5QqYykCBedXwx96v2e64SasZCSs-eB&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]
