[{"Name":"Dana Sliman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLCGVuOanB5fZdK4mDXVlNu1FRWwlivE-0dO5Jtxe0XvekGJ21jg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Service was fast and efficient, the place was very clean. Since it‚Äôs our first time there, We shared but the tomato beef brisket soup, it tasted a lot like canned soup with no deep beef flavor and very few meat pieces. It wasn‚Äôt bad, but have been to other better places nearby‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaTBTLQf2FreJIFFH4ImcBvwILoTpIPzyGDLYw&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Elaine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3sByrBumaUTi4SsjcCOqzuNL-H25OBzqdKkk5bQB9PSzxRg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Some of the best rice noodles I've ever had.

Pictured is my favourite Tomato broth with beef brisket rice noodle soup.
The meat is soft and tender, with a rich broth. I recommend asking them to add a bit of spice as well.

Service is great too, it might get busy during dinner hours, but is quite empty when I went late afternoons, so you can just chill and eat!

I also recommend their cucumber salad appetizer, it is refreshing and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkHFx1k1gMRMUOu0YXCfIFVdwKNMZ7jr_TRjBk&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty variety of dishes and great service. The noodles were so soft and unique. I loved the quiet atmosphere and the self serve counter in the centre that allowed people to get chili sauce, garlic, and such by themselves. Will be coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNg3vtJEdf60AyLtLjeBg8UDQD1HN0YanOnN8ax&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Jenny A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJRvpNIDvr6_vjm-fMJFybg-lbSH8oM7mSKCGMGU6FC8cVuKGk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I liked this place before, I came here many times and recommended this place to a lot of my friends. A year later-last night , I went there because I missed their soup so much. OMG, the soup is different taste, something off. It's not tasty at all. My husband and I were looking at each other and tasted the same thing..something off. The bowls and wooden spoons looked old, dirty and sorry to say " disq...". So we didn't use the spoons at all.  We won't go there again. We are still talking about it now.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been coming here with my friends and family for a while now - and I have to say these noodles have basically become the staple hang out. Decent price, decent food, and very fast service too.

There is a little cupboard where you can get garnish like green onions, garlic, chili pepper oil, as well as cilantro.

They put most of their stone bowls in stone pots, which keeps the noodle farm (this unfortunately also keeps it hot for a while for those sensitive to heat).

Definitely give it a go :)

5/5 Food
5/5 Service
5/5 Location","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7uMnBpK-fAlIo111nc222zMkle2-kVZGDgzbs&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-4-19"},{"Name":"Jo Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1TqwVe-O5n1d06B2UdI-0JvwJ-TmiUkh94kPgCXIRbaD0Dlbo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"- expect a small wait, when it is busy there is no greeter, just look for the clipboard and write down your name
- there is not a lot of parking in front, but there is also a covered lot in the back
- washrooms are quite small and not the cleanest

I would recommend this place for a relatively budget friendly spot for a quick and filling meal.

Food was good, we had the lamb cross bridge noodle and the noodle pot for 3. It was a lot of food. The broths were flavourful and came out piping hot.

We enjoyed the sauce station in the middle of the restaurant for guests to add extra condiments and garnishes.

Service was mediocre. But it was to be expected I suppose, since the restaurant is newly opened and they are adjusting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPocHZiM_wZnOiV_xs25BbP60_lO-Hd9PkD-J7Y&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2018-6-28"},{"Name":"J Yeung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNJ92b9j3lqmRqAgTBh-3qy3x8VVuxDUGF6GquG2EpmZTw61k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem! We recently heard out about this place and decided to check it out and have come back 3 more times.

It's always quiet (during the weekday at least), great for kids and there's lots of variety of soup options. I also find that their prices are very reasonable in relation to their portion sizes.

The first couple times we came, the server was very attentive and we had a very pleasant experience. However the last couple times a different server sat us at a table that hadn't been cleaned, slapped a menu on the table and told us to order online through the QR code. If we were a first-time customer, this definitely would have turned us off so beware if this is your first time.

There is a self-serve station for hot sauce and other condiments at the center of the restaurant

The parking lot looks busy but there is free designated parking in their underground lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpMdatJkx8IgU1QxY185jbm7t1ihq4dHz7TJN1&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-7-27"},{"Name":"Nick Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9cUtJY153nRWD4hzNcIo_gDDe44hWUa0zRGkneCYmPYO49A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We‚Äôve been to this restaurant many times throughout the years.  The noodle soup is amazing.  They‚Äôre served in a clay pot that keep it hot throughout the meal.  The portion is pretty good too.  What I like the most about this place that differs from other noodle houses is that they provide a self serve condiment section that customers can add green onion, parsley, chopped garlic, chili oil and peppercorn oil.  So customers can adjust the flavor and spiciness for their noodle.  I like garlic, so I would always add a fairly good portion so the smell would last for a few days in my breath ü§£.  Their bubble tea is surprisingly good too for a non-bubble tea place.  The pearl is chewy.  They also have a flavor we enjoy so much and haven‚Äôt been able to find it elsewhere (long yan and dates milk tea).  As there is only one server that also acts as a cashier and the bubble tea maker, don‚Äôt expect too much service.  I guess the restaurant made it clear of that when they made a QR code menu for you to order from yourself.  What they should do next is, buy a robot to deliver the food so they don‚Äôt even need a server.  Overall we enjoy the place for our noodle fix.  But the one thing they should really fix is their washrooms.  Let‚Äôs just say if you use it before your meal, you might lose your appetite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPlFVdvlsgmcnXJ_jDxBVi2k4eyh215XvLBhN5&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-7-12"}]

It‚Äôs not too busy around this joint, so service is pretty quick. Root beer is cold and the best as always. Only thing I‚Äôd want them to add are the root beer lollipops. Great for breakfast and lunch or a late night eat. I love the teen burger and the all Canadian special, they are delicious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ll L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsQWelEytIqASazSt0BFxqlsz8TCl3Y1zj2xC28NBy31fYTA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Halloween day 2024 they had free kids meals. We waited 30 minutes in drive through which is acceptable for such an event.  What is not acceptable is the quality control.  When I received the meal I placed it on my front seat and only gave it to my child when we got home.  As soon as he received it he complained of 2 big bite marks.  Took pics of what we discovered.  Ridiculous. Don't have time to go back and line up again and now have to make a meal.  Pic attached.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOPGdPk6jbz8CDzoLIHmjLWU3bsr32G3SzZBEQ\u0026fid=0x0:0x845a3b8e02de3411"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"alex drzewiecka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwMOkjqv9LqNy1Jd6-oGHkkZnGbmEyCRwpJrT4niBUNMe0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Took my sister out for lunch told her the chicken cruncher is good when it‚Äôs fresh. We dined in and asked front cashier to make fresh chicken patties: he said okay. Saw him punch FRESH onto screen. We told him we are willing to wait extra knowing it takes more time. We sat down and half a minute later he brings out our food. We both knew it wasn‚Äôt fresh as it was handed very quickly but we wanted to trust his words. I‚Äôve had the burger steaming before. Anyways Pattie‚Äôs were dry and tasted like they sat out for 2-3 hours. Not enjoyable at all and the fact they lied made us unhappy that they aren‚Äôt willing to provide good customer service. Made it seem like we wouldn't notice and did what‚Äôs easiest for them. Just disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYNzNY3pJZ1U5zM4jgpck2OVTOMXE-kgECSu0\u0026fid=0x0:0x845a3b8e02de3411"],"When":"2024-1-31"},{"Name":"Reetinder Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXL6v7l8uTriY6YAPrdi3hwqvGY1zxq_2G2avL5AdtY-KgoU4s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had a horrible experience with the chicken burger at this branch. The burger was clearly spoiled, with an unpleasant odor and bad taste. It was completely inedible, and I‚Äôm really disappointed with the food quality. I will definitely not be visiting this location again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPklpbx_HIm2xuHnwHAH6jHhziBwcQe8UEPxlW\u0026fid=0x0:0x845a3b8e02de3411"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"JaeMoon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDkuNJvMivUKiBT7DilWG8D-rHi32C042BV682xb8KEFAkrRxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very kind staffs and nice foods. This A\u0026W branch has gotten pretty good reviews comparing to other franchise fast food restaurants. And I found out why today. Before it was more meat portion now they replaced it with more vegetable portion","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXN5fqS1pznqVGYu72lK_U7h4Izlohc2zLcHa6&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Lanie Zulueta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIjacOZZNFIlv1T1yr25Te9nNNi1G78MhV6gOT7cCRO1Lr8sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Hefty serving portions are good for two. They have lots of menu options to choose from so you can build your perfect combo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFBMHNaxyGX85r9O7F_ThNP7Ed2H3WdaYQ9AqL&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried the three item combo with sesame chicken, green beans, and bbq pork and it was surprisingly delicious. The meat was saucy and full of flavour. Could have had more green beans in terms of portions. The chow mein was average. The 3 item combo was $15.99.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDhY_q7wNn6C60wSOQhG35fTA5YIo2NBLgR04l&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Happy Sidhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyyMaIgDuAnw55L_QkRaEGKi8IpWnP5jyUOt9IbH6p6YbQSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food used to be better portions here but still better then the Metrotown, meat used to be towered on-top .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsNEaD-n-LgO7C86qrVfasxBiOr0mqRIMlmQG7&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good place to go if you are looking for large portion sizes. I had the noodles, green beans, mango chicken and BBQ bourbon chicken. The BBQ bourbon chicken had too much sauce and was a bit on the salty side. I wouldn't order it again. The Mango chicken is always good if you want something a little sweet. Noodles were not bad. Green beans are cooked in butter and were quite good. One of the staff was friendly and offered me to sample the mango chicken. Overall, minus the BBQ chicken it was not bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0KKYLmXhPkMNCc40tZ80L5Y_j9gvcDCFyBLG1&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"J V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXubf4BA64V16YiH2FLbFkz0cA-ymFySyrMyQMYlXsSONYar4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food really delicious.  The food was tender and fresh.  I ordered the Honey Garlic Spareribs, Honey Mustard Chicken, and Red Bean Rice with Broccoli.

Service was good.  The people were friendly and nice.

Atmosphere:  the food court was super busy on Black Friday.  The restaurant was clean and organized.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8Wx8YFvhXPNaaZVmAEiVEMkBiBwRmzoed2Ku0&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2023-11-26"},{"Name":"Ny Richard NY","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlDNPF-DrbmHT47LTOB7oRHGB09r77OmyZnT1Fbb4vmnk5SD7h=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"What is going on with this place? Is it new ownership, bad training or cheap managers? Have they ever had Bourbon Street Grill before working there? The bourbon chicken used to be saucy and amazing. Now it‚Äôs dry with very little sauce. Having rice with it makes it a very dry lunch/dinner. If I don‚Äôt have a huge cup of water with this, I‚Äôll get constipated. Why is it in Metro town they give you sauce on the side? The quality of this location in Coquitlam Center dropped and desperately need to do better. Got to keep it real.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1sveXqEWdh29_NAn_8-ohw_8YiULF9dXzVG3X&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-3-15"},{"Name":"Jason James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjOeectPZC-yl54vwhkEIEWC7kDb-OthFjAg7Xn6ChCoZ-ooFG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My wife and I have been going to Bourbon St. Grill for years. It used to be a real treat for us. Yesterday, we picked up a Combo 3 and took it home. We were so excited to dig in‚Ä¶ but the excitement soon faded.

The bourbon chicken no longer tastes like it used to. Weak flavour and barely any sauce. They used to have to spoon the chicken out of the broth, but it was pretty dry and the server almost seemed to be upset at having to drizzle the sauce over our rice. There was so much cartilage in the meat that it was actually becoming annoying and nauseating to eat, knowing you‚Äôd bite down into something semi-crunchy. We also got the mango chicken, which didn‚Äôt taste like mango and was essentially candied meat. The crunch wasn‚Äôt from the breading but from crystallized sugars. And the rice? Where did the veggies go? It used to be loaded with an assortment of veggies and now it‚Äôs basically rice with a few veggies peppered in for colour.

It‚Äôs sad that something that used to be a fun experience has now become such a disappointment. We won‚Äôt be back. üòî","Images":null,"When":""}]

We already ordered the same food, such as Peking Duck 2 courses, sweet sour pork with pineapple, eggplant with spicy garlic sauce hotpot, beef shank in house special sauce hot pot and  spicy pork floss and string beans. The ambience is really dated despite the fancy light fixtures. Order the 1/2 bbq duck and that was delicious!

Would I come back?  No, I would try other places. I called to discuss with the restaurant and they refused to refund despite my offer to return the food myself. Extremely poor service. And they were just as bad.  Overall,  not acceptable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUfomZ_fKV6HWf2_v1CBZVbfGyLLB6QrC-XJ4l&fid=0x0:0x777d23cd7e4cba1d"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Ari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVZFr2lOsm-1DRRKbAML3xGYmN4IFUhEIuuxxMwCh-Sc_HMlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the veggie roll dip and the tomato tofu. They were also great about double-checking if I wanted fish sauce, since I got a vegetarian option. Super filling, hearty, and healthy as well! And it only cost me $15. Definitely coming back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maya T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLd2oFHq1BetvTY4OmSsoWnEb0yiYC1ATEeiwtKakGalwPgQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Vina Vietnamese at the Coquitlam Centre food court is a scam!! She didn‚Äôt apologize but did refund the money via e-transfer from her personal account, as I could see her name a the sender.  The manager is not working at that time. She claimed it was a ‚Äúcomputer error,‚Äù but from her tone and how she handled it, it seems like this happens often. The next day, I called to speak with the manager. I will never go here again and will definitely let the community know to watch out for their charges!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Prabhat S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJU26Mv7wrF_kHRTI1pZUcReR7O4NpknuGlRvECZ5U9FquW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"basil chicken with Rice- its nice hot, delicious and potions are large for 1 person, the lady in the corner of that pic is very courteous and friendly, is the only person show speaks decent english, the other one is just business minded attitude. not a great customer service, but definitely a economics place to dine, buy more for less. very few staffs are friendly there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2E62RxbjQMLoFNOOARozzH6syjKxiDR4OACg&fid=0x0:0x777d23cd7e4cba1d"],"When":"2022-3-9"},{"Name":"James & Gie Ann De Vera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYQ8yacZbfhxhPY4zdrqJRI9m4F7TWGxPxVJ2K7LFSqoKhU3A5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I found the woman so rude. I gave up and just asked to make me a falafel rice platter (no idea what it included and was never told). Anyways, she starts to microwave three falafels for me and only after being chastized by an older lady including the fourth one.

Two small spoons of tabouleh salad turned out to be an extra which was not mentioned anywhere.

Final charge was more than expected at par or above meat rice platters, and was told to pick my package up from her end of counter. Is this what hospitality industry has come down to. üëé

Would like to come back for the Lamb for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFbO8dINaF7fyw5zsN28ayrEBCLYYIP4W66wDo&fid=0x0:0xd8e604a6cfae6336"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Rob Mckenzie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKYMc54aGeQ2e0cqU4irUfWRI9HTjwHqMkkeRPSw0YLWi54uo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I give 5 stars down the line because if you want a legit, classic style Donair this is the spot. Food:
Ordered the House Special Pho, large. Was pleasantly surprised to see a bowl that wasn't as big as Pho 99's large. Pho was good, soup was just right, neither too salty or too rich. Noodles came in a good amount. Meats in the House Special Pho left a lot to be desired though. Not as much as I'd expect, half a beef ball, about 2 slices of beef steak, 3 slices of beef flank, tiny bits of beef tendon (which was really soft and delicious to my surprise), and a few bits of tripe here and there. Kinda disappointed with the amount of meat but as it was still pretty delicious,  I'll overlook it.
It comes with tea, beansprouts, basil leaves and lime on the side.
Refer to pictures for more information!

Price:
$10.24++/person

Service:
Nothing special. The lady sounded angry but I guess it's just the way she speaks.

Would I recommend?
Yes, go with family/small groups of friends as the place is rather small. I have not tried the other dishes, but will do so in the future :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQm5L8nR0xCYWH_i_xK2j7rwq5AZRQ2MMi8XQj&fid=0x0:0x136fcd8e7d93f071"],"When":"2017-1-8"},{"Name":"Stan S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJDG5_awNL6dSqZYIF4Ack_45eiH9so1tVgUCK8vlfNcXo0LDN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not my First time here, busy place seems to be lots on the go even though there's only a few of us sitting down there's plenty of takeout or to go orders and the people are quite friendly and the price is reasonable. I want to try something new so I check the menu as well as the reviews. After reading the reviews i don‚Äôt want to order But still my brother, order three pizzas‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶. Pizzas was soooo sooooo good, i never ever eat pizza like this one. I tried Super Hawaiian, pepperoni and one more‚Ä¶. And their food, service, and atmosphere are unbeatable.
I think someone put fake reviews from fake ids to misguide other people, may be jealo*** factor ü§£ü§£ü§£ü§£.
I will definitely recommend you and 100% sure you will not regret..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqBWqbDlfL29K3j-AfpwiPIpYFEk_zSfUkMPLB&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Varun V Uppalapati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0hR2k5UhurSCZ0f1b3vsC5kzt4eLzD-FXYy6uD0N-RZwQC-SL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Walked in to get a pick up special. The place looks absolutely clean.  Since it was our first time, I wasn't sure what to order and was helped by Ritika. She accommodated our request and also gave suggestions. Excellent customer service from her.
The pizza tastes good.

There is also plenty of free parking.

Overall, I will definitely be going back to try their other pizzas.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zachary Morritt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRKH7SdPojmEckRqAYwgOckuobhtGVtbG5dmrr8IcoZmzDXDrU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New place from the Pizza 1 that used to be here. The guy who runs the place was on his own, but the pizza was great. It‚Äôs good to have someplace close :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMgdnpUZI9HwdU8D66Qnhq_cI39gXUw3czU8Qy&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Nd Nd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9aAIyoQdMUZKpjAinmtBfvwVxIudCnPnmTIDeiBcffl9essqt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It's OK, not as good as the previous Pizza One that used to be in that location. Also they don't have multiple pizza combo specials which is too bad. Very average pizza not very tasty or good quality just very basically will do if your go too place isn't available. Too bad :(","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhGlLP_VJpl3qW9qoyQpsesE5pvucyY6kZX0X5h01hxsrvPnlBbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A Disappointing replacement for Pizza1.

I‚Äôm genuinely disappointed with New West Pizza, the change in owner and menu is not for the better.

First, the pizza itself is a huge downgrade. The ingredient portions are noticeably smaller, not fresh, and the flavor is nonexistent. Instead of the rich, big taste that I expect, what you get is an overly greasy and oily mess. Long wait times for pick-up, even on weeknights.

As a vegetarian, I was particularly disheartened by the lack of freshness and variety in the vegetarian options. The few offerings they have seem like an afterthought, and none of them come close to what Pizza1 used to serve.

On top of that, the customer service is was very bad, I‚Äôve noticed this on several visits when placing an order by phone and picking up my order,

I can‚Äôt recommend this place in its current state. It‚Äôs truly disheartening to see such a decline in what used to be a local favorite for Coquitlam and Port Moody. I had been a regular customer of Pizza1 since 2009.

However, I‚Äôd be more than happy to update this review if things improve on a future visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ABHIR GUPTA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLg7qltToC35uub3-sdU4FB5qano4DzGiAQsY3A2I6SE3DPlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried shahi paneer pizza & loved it .
Will visit again for sure","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOO7lhNainD2S4b1m_nKfsjCl7PtSidUmo93rpI&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Kalpana Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHQPp8UeHV5Wsmr-yzP8HkKMjoFTIDIs2DmT9itjN2CFex-Ogx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza in town. We are glad that we hosted by Ritika , I ordered their Shahi paneer pizza and it was so flavourful and authentic taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOw7hIXBzGylQ7AZMkkKaG2OF2aapvnCnf3GVaW&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-7-4"}]

I highly recommend this restaurant for family dine-in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP61jdct5gPQytDMdHPfQhPfCjuShmJpan19VB_&fid=0x0:0x76c34e41dc3dd317"],"When":"2021-3-24"},{"Name":"Francis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgfmbUHLwmxF3ATfQGv1RD5eZck6TDnyYt1IZAHB6YDFw4kfEYkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is great. We quickly ordered a combo. It came with sweet and sour pork, black bean noodles and a spicy seafood noodle. The sweet and sour pork came first and I must say that it was crispy, juicy and flavorful. We had the sauce on the side so we dipped instead of drenched.

[{"Name":"Dante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJJBsnDt-Jyx-wWvCneLo2yoEFwzv6R1zGdLk7DybFf-Xv7HBL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I love Thai Express, but this branch is just stingy. Unlike every other branch I‚Äôve visited, they only serve half a plate. This means you get less food, and makes it difficult to eat without spilling.

Peanuts have to be requested. They‚Äôre not available as self serve nor in containers you can take.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPkaMtYTq26d4kb7ThXuAs54DjK5a7m_oEpCQo&fid=0x0:0xf25c2b56dbf214d9"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"S. Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl5qhDUZCdateg0WcgkvmZprfnKo9oMSCLmabYKumv4hl1DQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Had I known the serving size was half a shallow plate, I wouldn't have paid $15.  Mind blown.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpQqZiqPWz0DF_M6dZzFaLUWWYpT8piQpUvWtN&fid=0x0:0xf25c2b56dbf214d9"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Henry Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIkmralb63UHDHcUq51u8dg864_lKWN-I_JUgA2SkNx2-T9Uc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very disappointed!! I thought with the renovations and appeared that there was a change of ownership at this Coquitlam location, that there would be some improvements.
I was very wrong.
I've ordered the daily special and I recieved almost half the amount.
When I was at another location a week ago, I've ordered the same thing and the portion was a regular size, a good size.
I asked why the portion was so small and the owner stepped in and sounded like she was getting pissed, that I had asked that.
The cook said different locations run differently.
This location here in Coquitlam better smarten up or they're going to be out of business very fast.
Stay away from this location.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sandra Niven she-her","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXG28vnwnpOipZoVvGlfdbQ3fI92AEWggdngjPJ9YQ4oMaiBFW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Such a simple request and so rude. I asked for extra lime. Happy to pay for it. It was added to my receipt (no charge). One scrappy little corner of a corner. I requested the extra lime and was rudely told no. Ummm... I wasn't informed this was not an option and since when?!! I used to love Thai Express. For $15.52 a little bit of customer service would have gone a long way.
Bye!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashley Melecio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn7b3YsltOZczvp34LlGl71lMMhrOd9WThH168eGU8CC-Ly1O6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The workers here are super kind :) I didn‚Äôt get his name yet, but the cook with the yellow hat makes the BEST pad sew! So yummy, and great customer service!! I would highly recommend, and I always order the beef pad sew","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Grimsdick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVNAwbGbAg7iHFZCH2ZcRPNQCqhdrLGjma3MI6N7NMRmpkI8DArQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You get a lot of variation of quality with Thai express at different locations.  But the main guy who does the cooking here always does a great job and is super friendly.  I eat lunch in the mall a lot and often look around randomly not knowing where to go.  When I see this guy there I always end up eating here.  He's always wearing a yellow Nike hat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Hall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDVZIqSwQU4-t3Xl8NkkBY2wRf7fllHkKMKqkZV7FIl6QtJqS_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I‚Äôm so frustrated! I am literally in labour and been going through inductions. My husband was so kind to drive to get something that tastes good to me. Just look at what we paid for! Supposed to be a yellow curry, the most measly amount of beef, no flavour, like they decided not to add the right amount of curry sauce. I asked for noodles instead of rice and it tastes like Mr noodles curry flavour!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMch3uzy52oExo7Rv-mCj8leNliZ1MDZfAglTF4&fid=0x0:0xf25c2b56dbf214d9"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"Luca Morris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJigR1Eg1lPuEJo9rF1p-7DRmWmkt1n8D1xM4tJit_Hkg7ZEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5/5 stars for Chris and Sev. Always friendly service here and they make amazing dishes - my fav is the Thai basil fried rice with a little extra ginger and broccoli. Very spicy. Thank you!!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Susi Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfeehOX1TY5zbmvSyfkDaNxrPebRDamgwxks_pqPIh2ep-MItQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I often order spicy chicken wings from this restaurant. Today I ordered spicy chicken wings to go. When I opened the box at home , I found that the colour of chicken wings is much darker than normal. And the skin tasted very hard. They absolutely were leftover, and over fried again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIopja01aA4Q7WTNRdtwFsTvSYjgGMUD83jW3Y&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A solid Church‚Äôs fried chicken location. Tried their 3 piece special which comes with fries that you can also substitute for gravy or any side of your choice as well as a soft drink. The chicken was crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. Delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNG9ca7jeDEb1yvdafu9V8nc0Lz47jgZ8jFW1Zk&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Hazel Agonia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0_1GJHuKbORRDhqVZsEO-1iWfM-vThx8b406L9roVGa4xuw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Chicken is very dark look like using old oil
And it was burnt.
Every time I bought chicken here I am expecting this time will be good.
Very dissappointed not worth the money.
Piece of drumstick is small.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS5JxwsZ0Re8VAxX6HqMJ-L7C6EzYDrOTzinOA&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2024-6-7"},{"Name":"Ohr Thgil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLN2i4qCmXPoC9W5_zouVHNlKbN4SGyK6orGgQY-tDPsxtYPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"To the ladies who worked on Sunday, October 20, 2024 between 12:30pm and 1:30pm: You need to learn basic math. I'm an idiot for not checking whether there were in fact 4 pieces, but you're also dumb af for missing a piece (see photo).
If I ordered 8 pieces and you put 7, MAYBE I can see how you might get confused.
But frankly, whether you have 3 or 4 is plain to see. Please COUNT next time you bag chicken. $16 for 3 pieces? BS.
At least you managed to count properly the 25 wings (which is quite flabbergasting ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYinMPWTOxnna66iN0z5cdzoPk-BnFwuxPyX_A&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Hailey Babb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmftm4oM1j8_9wGQR4O-gX3PTZ_QhAphv0kGZ6VakKZ3xlW8n-JA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Me and my friend were last served yet we ordered our food 10 -15 minutes before everyone else who was in the store and we were the only ones who didn't get asked if we wanted spicy or not. It was so spicy we had to force ourselves to eat it. We said we wanted it for here and our meals were bagged up after waiting there for 30 minutes watching people come and go while we were waiting almost seemed intentional..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Small fast food joint with most people doing take out orders. Ordered the four piece chicken combo which came with four piece dark meat chicken, one drink, one side, and one biscuit for $17+. I ordered the regular, instead of the spicy. The food was just ok, but nothing outstanding. The two additional wings for $1 each was small but a good addition as it came with a sauce that can be used for the rest of the chicken. Interior of the store didn‚Äôt feel very welcoming. Small parking lot in front of store but it shares parking with the rest of the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkDjP_HZw_HGBI1qcx3dcCUUqM96QiM_Odu26Y&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2023-10-12"},{"Name":"Harrison Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjMtINmNs4A8X0-NaOGuqkp3rSAktfHw1GyYexwkm7fKi72g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have ordered three times here, frankly speaking, the food flavor is good, better than KFC. However, the waiter always seemed to act impatiently, as if unwilling to take the time to attend to the customers properly. Indeed, modifying the order can sometimes be tedious, but isn't that exactly what your job entails? I may be not visiting this place again, there is a Korean fried chicken resturant nearby, the waiter is always kind and handsome.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was close 11pm in the evening - just about when my chronic craving for chicken wings was kicking in.
I hurried drove and arrived at this Church's branch about 7 minutes before its closing hour.

I ordered 5 regular and 5 spicy wings with 'buck a wing' promotion. The male employee promptly took my order and handled it professionally - the whole process didn't take 5 minutes since I stepped in.

- Wings were not super juicy/tender: but still delicious
- $1 a wing is hard to beat
- Regular wings had rock hard batter which were meh
- Spicy wings had better texture for me
- 1~2 of them were extra greasy, 1~2 of them were extra dry; others were fine
- Wings were lukewarm, probably have been sitting on the shelf for a while
- An alternative option would be one of the Korean Fried chicken places: but I didn't want to spend at least $25+.

All in all, an affordable option when you have a craving for fried wings in the late night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4wcJgMS4c0mirmU6LrkhLGUWjIDUMl5m6siQ9&fid=0x0:0x201a26182f23506d"],"When":"2023-12-30"}]

[{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The beers and chicken wings were very good; I would have liked the wings even more if they were crispy, but they weren‚Äôt. The ambiance is nice, and there was no music in the restaurant, which I liked. There were also two pool tables available for everyone to use, which is great for entertainment.

The waitstaff's attention was a bit lacking; they were very attentive, but they barely spoke.

Other than that, there were no issues with parking. The road is spacious, so you can park your car easily.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6mPnTXiOVAIyLPVjnLRdzoBzQQToaph574RRr&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Kyle Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMtJJe2qhOrA2XlnNzIHU-2PKFecjgd4Zhh5leir5YT5OkF-4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would like to thank Whitney and Gina. Our party originally booked for 20 ppl. Found it later it was going to be closer to 40. Well it ended up being almost 50+ppl. So thank you very much Gina for booking us and accommodating us!

Would like to give a huge shout out to Whitney! She took on our whole party herself with a bit of hit throughout the night but pretty much all on her own. She kept up with us throughout the night and was very on top of what we ordered and our bills. Service was very fast and she never got annoyed with us at all as I‚Äôm sure we were pretty drunk.

She mad us laugh as well as making a funny joke to one of our pitchers of beer.

Again thanks Whitney from all of us for your wonderful service and taking care of us throughout the night! Happy holidays!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0R3FCWivkDnuYcJ95kowd_YrwAnNeeX-k2ycn&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Cheryl A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocId3JTMrjtqtdmj_0XOBMchbLGhcrTAO0uBPM1jzlHcNAjL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We sat outside and had to move because we could smell like maybe a dog peed in the area? They do allow pets on the patio . The waitress never told us any drink specials or anything related to happy hour . She was very vague. The chicken burgers looks good but the taste was nothing special - the chicken tenders were very dry / horrible-   The positive? - nice big patio","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsVgrRofMXLWxsm-_F-Pt1Zp7eK8T2JgzSLs0&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Lavinia Kate D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUULjpaarpF4E4hyNszixvzThLgNY-_uK_5m05JhvQ6h30xmymY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were here today to celebrate my daughter in law‚Äôs birthday. The girl at the front door was very welcoming, and so was Kevan, our waitress. She made sure we got what we wanted, and she recommended us a very good sparkling wine to celebrate. Wings were great, as all of the food. Thank you for making this day special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9o8BD8MNIIXOsn6WSgtWmIUOKGLikbPU91CTd&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Eva Tong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbdn1JwTeGwTMz4zaH_aM0s2MjqUg4f-ith9g4COdwAGXFieA4Ow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our friends and I went to this place near where we live, they have plenty of parking, we went around lunch time on a Saturday. No booking was required, also plenty of seats inside.

As a big group of 8 people, we order quite number of dishes. We have ordered 2 lbs of chicken wings - honey garlic and lemon pepper. It is quite impressive that hey have quite many sauce and seasonings to choose from. If you do choose seasonings, it might not be season evenly. Spicy waffle fries was pretty crispy but it is not spicy at all, which is a little disappointing for my friends. Chipotle ranch steak salad is in good portion and the sauce is spicer than the spicy waffle fries. We have also ordered pizza-When pigs fly, the size of pizza was a little smaller than I expected but the crust is good. The last item was ordered is baked lasagna as main dish, the dish is in good size and flavour. As general in bar, the lighting is quite dim.

It was enough for everyone, probably because we have 6 ladies and 2 boys. They did not put surcharges for more than 6 people, which is appreciated, which we did choose to give higher tips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlhidH17Pq533TJHOqnJd1l3TP6zmOhaz4KoeZ&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Allen Beik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF9ADaYp8aM_t6ClRm3K9sF-sNZrKMskbGaiszRmMLDyZbTDv5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently visited Cat and Fiddle with some friends, and it‚Äôs definitely a great spot to enjoy with friends, family, or coworkers. The atmosphere is inviting, with options for both indoor and outdoor seating. They have a nice bar, and the food is solid. I especially enjoyed the chicken wings with the salty pepper seasoning, and we also got a pizza, which was casual but hit the spot. Drinks were great too! The only downside was the wait time, which was a bit longer than expected. Overall, it was a fun experience, and I‚Äôd recommend it if you‚Äôre looking for a lively place to hang out and enjoy good food and drinks.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Helena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiYVJyd2ntFwLRumbYS9Kznuj6jXHoPn0UkQ_zdJDM29rWiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Three families, six people gathered at the traditional and amazing club on one Friday afternoon. We ordered beers, French fries and the world most famous chicken wings with different dressing, such as dry garlic, hot & blue cheese, BBQ, and buffalo hot etc.. All of them had great taste. Every one enjoyed the happy hours, delicious food and drinks. The service was amazing. Parking lots were ample.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ7_A-OlL9iAHhEpbBv4ZX8mj2AhOqUVxg2NRR&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Antje S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLt-LBIe3b3nKdqJNrzC8mzrltLY4gghwveDzasU9yAkF9Fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good place to chill, relax, and enjoy. They have a minor allowed zone. Wings night is always packed. I love the loaded nachos. Pizza is also quite good. The burgers are kind of disappointing. Staff is always friendly. When they have music, it is often Iranian, which is not for everyone's taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9PhFBNAOnqmd-Z52QgnhzFJFAbSwuorscKS0f&fid=0x0:0x9f47a4ae62bc88ab"],"When":"2022-2-27"}]

[{"Name":"Kevin N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP-ZslnJG-cFBsTow4YlDjdGLQF1WwIx66rdKNelzsaPrx3qOv2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We have been a supporter of Ninja for 4 years now. Unfortunately had an unpleasant experience here yesterday. We ordered our drinks and noticed taxes were still added despite the new GST tax break being active. When I brought it up the worker said, that‚Äôs how our machine is, do you want the drinks? Although a small amount, it‚Äôs not a legal charge and no resolution offered whatsoever. Very sad to have this experience. The Surrey Ninja location has great service and the drinks and food was much better. We will be going there from now on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPjTax1j_N_sgQWh_V_EdpC2btspXnDzIdOS1H&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Tony Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCf0Goqhisa7q0sS3Ll5w5xspVuL46bLhGdKhCbN8pg1Qh6xso=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is just crazy! The rewards card gives you great perks like free bubble/jelly add-ons, and special bonuses when you load the card. But their poke and 50% bubble tea deal is the best in town. Not to mention the Mac & Cheese. My go-to spot when I need a fix!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGwc07JsZmcdIG-9ZVVAdfVUHzfO7L_m1-vyeM&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The large bubble tea is really big for $8, so value for money wasn‚Äôt too bad compared to bubble tea places nearby. The pearls are firm and not as chewy. You can customize sugar and ice levels. The packaging for the bubble tea leaves a lot to be desired as the tea become warm quickly even at regular ice levels. Music was playing too loudly in-store. A few seating available on the inside. Street parking only. They have $1 off drinks after 9 pm for their happy hour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9Y4k3xNdb9K48O9yODFACQPCSsiXDV288taMQ&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"I D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJePVcTLvMpAzx-nv1Jiy6G3BSAT8AXC96M8bp3iDt95AnsQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a nice store. I ordered the mango slushy to go with my lunch. The 1L drink was a good gimmick but I won't drink it all by myself. I had a mango slushy at a different store last week and I could tell this one didn't have a lot of real mangoes in the drink. What I was most impressed with was the friendly service and the welcoming environment of the store.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josho Kamoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ4n3iaFjoQyR1zucz1_1m7k51NtiBqRfCJcIPe2noft0FdsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome service ,awesome art decor and vibe .reasonable price for a lot of food ,really good price on the bubble tea drinks that will keep me coming back .i love how big the large size is which is the largest I have ever seen especially in shrinkflation times . Wide array of items on the menu and a diverse selection of bubble tea ! I would recommend and will be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdKY74nV69D7LV14R9G2n7QM5QYqmaiYoeB0U-&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dear @ninjabbt .. Please please please open a branch in Burnaby & Metro Van and I promise I will consume LOTS of your Matcha Slush! Love from your biggest fan, Ads.
I love Ninja BBT, you rock!! This joint is rad and has cemented itself as my favorite Bubble Tea go-to for numerous reasons.
I got the almighty yummy Matcha Slush with Lychee Jelly which is the perfect one-two punch combo of bitter, bold & rich matcha flavor with a good old sweet tooth injection from the jello. Their matcha is an excellent grade and contains no added sugar or premix. An awesome drink, super tasty with fresh wholesome natural ingredients and served with a friendly five-star service. One of the reasons Ninja is so kickass, is their quality of drinks is better than everywhere else but also provides incredible value for money whilst also offering litre size options which are HUGE! They also have a very vast and customizable menu for lots of different types and flavors to curb your tastebuds cravings, whilst also offering us great plant-based milk options (Silk refrigerated) on top of dairy or milk powder based.. I'm always such in such a happy space after visiting this place and cannot wait to go again. I really hope their business can grow and expand across Greater Vancouver area as they are so much more superior than all other places or chains.
Support local businesses!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRPVJ-rpDZjTzG6cq84qpXDMW-lA6N4HsDQcPp&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2021-9-19"},{"Name":"Sarir Parvizi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsJ0mUsWH0K1pkhc8A3UJ8PyvF-Mdp8a5M9PA7Pc9jwDQA-AM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We just went here today and the barista who made our mango banana smoothie and milk tea really made our night :)  Amazing service and the mango smoothie was super delicious too!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josephine Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ctBP8R2rm9S8Aa5NyuULMapTvyTQYakS6AvI9Cd025oSy86H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My daughter and I were out with a friend in Coquitlam and we all felt like having a drink so we went to Ninja Bubble Tea. It's a cute shop with a lot of greenery adorning the walls on one side of the shop, and comic book covers on the other side of the shop. Slushy drinks are my daughter's favorite, so she ordered a Peach slushie. I was in the mood for something hot and when I caught sight of the words "Honeydew Latte" on the menu, I decided to give that a try.

Peach slushie: So good, she ordered the same drink again, about one week later!

Honeydew Latte: Awesome! I've seen Honeydew drinks in Bubble tea shops many times, but always as a cold drink. This was the first time I'd seen and tasted a hot Honeydew drink. The Honeydew flavor was very pronounced. Such a unique flavor for a hot beverage and it was simply fantastic!

Service: Good
Parking: Street parking
Location: It's a very short walk from Coquitlam Centre so very convenient if you want to do some shopping!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqlGFah1ZjCTN1x1dw7CF-4uUyslR9Ybpx-0vn&fid=0x0:0x747490f0faaede74"],"When":"2022-9-23"}]

[{"Name":"Monica Nguyen Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZBeMwSkt7l1K2HVfyeAFOoXFwnBn78IKEly42V3HGsujhC8gu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have ordered here a few times now and the lady at the front now remembers me. She is so sweet and kind. The food here is amazing and the portions are great, four dishes for a group of four was wonderful. The spicy squid is one of my favourites and the sweet and sour pork tastes amazing. If I ever want Chinese food, I will always come here first.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNitwmRV6rfwJDN7EpwKsiCIe7pTNGZKwGGU2OS&fid=0x0:0x5089b53d0100262c"],"When":"2023-11-17"},{"Name":"The JOKER","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQuiHl5446ZqSIBmhoQY8q4NuTHDo0F4Qr2KVa1APrDHGiVv22=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Excellent tasting food. The Calamari could have been deep fried a little longer with more salt added. The fried rice is very tasty.
Everything else is excellent. The price is right, and the lady owner is very courteous.
Poor cashier girl was saying sorry to everyone as the restaurant was backlogged with orders. Skip the dishes driver picked up 10 dishes before I got my 5. All in all, the food was fresh n tasty. I had to give the 10% off to cash sales as a tip to the cashier.  She was very courteous and apologetic to all the customers waiting for their food.
The Richmond market squid was excellent !!!!!!!!
I ordered more food 2day. The dishes were fresh, hot, and tasty.
Bought 6 dishes today.  The food did not taste fresh as there was an overnight fridge taste to the food. The Gen. Tso's spicy chicken was not good. It was not spicy at all n even worse it was made with sweet n sour sauce,  ( I hate sweet n sour sauce). The fried rice was abit hard meaning it was left over many days rice. The beef n broccoli was below average as the beef was cut into small pieces to make it look like there were many slices of beef when actually there was not. When you are very hungry, most foods will taste good. Unfortunately,  the food this day was not good at all. The cook must've had a bad day as his heart was not in it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjZRUrWqMbNGNm1P4lhsUFKCdLr2ugTFenLboD&fid=0x0:0x5089b53d0100262c"],"When":"2022-4-21"},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX98PrUHxEgks1p_UHXz6OQ_Vovq-hbr6NA6018tymH019sjnz4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Depending on what you get from here is good, but small portions for what you pay for... especially for the meat dishes. Sweet and sour chicken is good, but sweet and sour pork... not at all, can't even chew it, literally. Soft chow mein is good. Beef and broccoli is good. Rice is good. I'd eat here more if the portions were better. Pay so much for so little, especially the meat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eggo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA2E4qPkriaAPlXZWiV1U68JcCrwz32VLQy_R-OB4nVbIK4G0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love ordering from Happy Chinese! The kindest people working and the best food. The egg fried rice and Honey Garlic Pork are my fave. The potions are massive of course, and everything is cooked so well. We‚Äôve ordered about 10 times now and so far not a single miss. Everything has always been awesome!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjAFyC4uzW51_W5CulBHcEUtWIE8X82cV7J9Mu&fid=0x0:0x5089b53d0100262c"],"When":"2023-9-25"},{"Name":"Winston Ow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4VK8olZKHHa7aoNtjL4Gd6F-ndnpQx6mPR5PLsRYshInbvp001w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Small family owned Chinese restaurant. Decent menu and reasonable price. Food were fresh and made to order. Lunch special is a good deal. Food was ok for that price. Friendly staff. Overall good experience. Will come back again fro take out üëç #supportlocalbusiness","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgXvhYBW9msBCP21WMj6WRpSiVzy0IVyc9Mrfs&fid=0x0:0x5089b53d0100262c"],"When":"2020-10-12"},{"Name":"Tara Dixon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLEYEcN6JSaRY9BfoEh1ynICuaE3-8A7bT3FkKuYmWm8pjZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was going to give these guys another try, after our last experience left us with a bad taste in our mouths, like literally!! My favorite Chinese Restaurant is temporarily closed and I didn't feel like cooking. So I looked at their menu. With the menu prices through the roof now, it would be cheaper to go buy a few ingredients and make my own, or hit the food court @ Coquitlam Center.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"karen boyd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLM-Czk3Y6iA2F4PseH1s0lKxESbFkRLdhCd6Rll_VRSCYx7g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Just picked up dinner for 2.. spent $45 noodles.. ok but bland and sweet and sour pork so hard .. not edible.. and so much batter..
when I called to say it‚Äôs not fresh.. they say we will remind kitchen.. no customer service.. go elsewhere","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Keith Eastcott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk5BCUEJh42hOpsF-_OoCCbmyygcrHIJcijMiuq6slKML49qmN0g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is very good and the 1 person combo is a lot of food. I definitely will be eating here more frequently.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jay Ram","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZkA1ehrIA4VnNy0PIxLOt0BXpiMfZdoXQo11n2kz7ZZx0ww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I used to go to this place all the time when I lived in the area. I stopped by the other day for the first time in a year and the first thing I noticed was the sky high prices. $20 for a large bowl of pho is unacceptable with the amount of meat that was supplied is completely unacceptable. The overall portions have gotten smaller as well. I ended up spending $51 one large house special, one small meatball pho, and one order of spring rolls. I get that inflation is a real thing, but there are other pho options out there with the same, if not better quality, at a more affordable price. I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll ever come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTI8GwxOHdZLbG3qDKV924E_r5hll7-dApLXG0\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"70s Guy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLpFEkMFgbYDe4BGpd7FdUKJSZCGFJjct_f3_FcWBpZ1Qx4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little Vietnamese restaurant across from the courthouse in Port Coquitlam.  Owners and staff are very friendly and attentive.  Food was tasty and prepared quickly.  I enjoyed a vermicelli bowl with grilled chicken and spring roll.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-GSLwny-1Nf4ZhT2KPb5F0ahiLUwRtavL1tDm\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Rayant Yeo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaSGd8rGguK-MzK7O72I-ocdHyBHvKJG59MOmI710XLPYz1DeB_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly \u0026 Excellence service; served us with drinks immediately once we gotten a seat. The dishes were delicious especially the Pho; simply authentic.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHKqK78B6cDzzuiNC10G-fo8KdwReZ3wOrBlom\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"Autumn_Kiko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1zcZdU411-b8f5Fcx7HImynMifJ7qg-_yzjSJzTLgmhJaggW_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little inconspicuous Vietnamese Pho diner that has some Parisian vibes and your basic necessities for soup and vermicelli and rice dishes.  I tried the small sized No. 27 Pho with a side of extra jalape√±os since they didn‚Äôt have the little red chili peppers.  It was a rainy day and we were hungry after our drive out to Tartan Town nearby and found this place in Google Maps.  For me rainy days and soup make the best pairing.  Especially when it‚Äôs a wee bit chilly outside.  I found the soup broth had slightly sweet notes and for a small size I had plenty of meats to go with the sprouts and chili peppers.  Perfectly sized for me and the price was affordable.  Also ordered up some spring rolls that came out hot and fresh and tasty.  No wonder this place is popular with the locals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzpbGk7esuvzRZC5gD3wjkp6AnnQHUenGP-f9x\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Adrian W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkC00uJkJsFbk_OdOD9rrYTPpj8QZN9D-8L5mx-4-sXG1BIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was perfect and the service was as good as it could be. My only reason for 4 stars is because it was pretty busy and the restaurant was definitely understaffed which resulted in a big bottleneck of service. Management, please hire more staff during busy dinner timeframes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfglg0dhmsWeP2dhUZn-lsNEIIblpWun2WWJQx\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2022-6-14"},{"Name":"Discovering V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIw0nwNgIa5O9CwW_XBE-aYX1t3_wGZTSaPfaYP36jNTmtocw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hello, i am vegetarian and the Veg Pho was just awesome :P The broth was flavour full and full of veggies and Tofu with a very good presentation. My BF took the beef pho and we both loved it. We also ordered the spring rolls - which were to die for. The chilli oil was the highlight of it all with a lemon grass flavour. We would definitely go again. The service was top-notch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCPn6z0JFTIZPgh1pE-4V1VNSKncUjzbuIqQfQ-OA3rQoJavMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delicious!! Great portion and perfect flavor. Everything was spot on.\nDefinitely recommend this place. üíØ","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob Mckenzie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKYMc54aGeQ2e0cqU4irUfWRI9HTjwHqMkkeRPSw0YLWi54uo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like a spicy broth this is your spot. Always fast and super friendly service. POCO has a couple great spots for Pho and this team is the top of that list! I am here almost weekly.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Joey Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIncJBLfbVzRO24PRdfxE4-hovZn6C_s4RV_vqsGslULP8YEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Originally we wanted to go to Cactus Club but the line was crazily long. We came to the weekend when there was a festival at the mall.

So we searched for the highest-rating restaurant nearby and found this place. The food was so good, it blew our mind.

We had a spicy shredded potato appetizer. It was spicy but still manageable for us.

Their noodles were very different from what we normally saw at other noodle places, so we just kind of picked two very different ones. One was glassy and in chili oil soup, the other one was thin pull noodles in a relatively clear booth. Both were very flavourful and we were so glad that we found this place. Even though this is far from where we live but we will definitely come back to try other types of noodles.

We were given free dessert in the end! The dessert was some sort of jelly - it was transparent, chill and not too sweet. Lovely! A perfect ending to a delicious meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOx7_m78rUA4KWGk0lGb8Ceuohpz_2UmkZrSyss&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"charles bai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVivIWOvTOamsgiucoqI5EKukhiOsZqTk7nog1iV-Y1Xav6PIczow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really flavorful, really bouncy, chewy noodles! Honestly can‚Äôt go wrong with any noodle dish, and they all have a unique flavor! Just don‚Äôt expect a lot of toppings - the star of the show is the noodles with the sauce!

I really enjoyed the cold noodle dish, Â§ßÊãâÁöÆ, the sauce was the perfect salty sour spicy combination","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIQ-D3nMLqaxvfeRc-ihmVJMl9FVF33g1PYhY1&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"A. L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5TiPH35l6b0Yp0-BDY7r9mxPb2PWCWLOWYg3E7uIKxSRcy84P=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best hidden gem in Coquitlam!! Highly recommend the garlic dumplings (their most popular dish for a reason) and the dry noodle with beef brisket (pay the extra 1$ for the hand made noodles) as well as the red bean pancake. Food was perfectly seasoned and so so delicious !!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFdK1xNLIAQFO20WtiU_cJl86OvWu0Wb4_XpSh&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Ryan Blight","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbpH73lI2xtK9WJxadw5s8Ist4ItI3NEBYZImc9aopB1Hhs9lf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered homemade garlic dumpling, Dan Dan noodle and handmade noodle with beef brisket - all dishes with medium heat and it was absolutely delicious! The sauce on those dumplings was incredible! Will recommend to others ü§©","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjB1-v-OnwdXhOzu-73B0SjDMd1KJI52-XJJYn&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Emily Sanchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMrCl__83PRc54jDLOKOkfjwZwBODeNVlQZ-bPXLZAKUk3EboR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are looking for some authentic Chinese spicy food, especially noodle, this is the place to go! Reasonable price, good portions and great service! Summer is super nice and helpful! We would totally go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOO8qMMgo39RmJ-76A6WtKE1-T8c_Y8nInZxtR&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have not a single bad thing to say about this restaurant. The owner is the nicest lady ever, she kept giving me samples of sweet jelly and milk tea even after I was stuffed by the delicious food here. The food here is absolutely delicious, super authentic and has massive portions. The chitterlings were clean and seriously flavourful in the spicy sauce it came with. The cold shredded chicken salad was also wonderful. The Szechuan hot chili wonton is listed under appetizers, but it is actually a full meal by itself. I couldn't even start it after wolfing down the previous two plates with rice. This place is insane value if you are into spicy food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGfS9sHXFHX-GIUqaFjaBE0peRj7TE-q4oLmfp&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Andrew Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPIxXxmEDjGJcYO362T99oS-5qWMFJgvMbwHh0mGwwfhau82E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The duck feet, noodles, and glutinous rice cakes were absolutely delicious. The duck feet were tender and flavorful, perfectly seasoned with a hint of spice. The noodles were cooked to perfection, with a wonderful texture that absorbed the rich, savory sauce beautifully. The glutinous rice cakes were a delightful finish, with a chewy consistency and just the right amount of sweetness. Overall, each dish offered a unique and memorable taste experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzMRBsszdMd9y_Ruutiww3mSpWiPcytluwVi5S&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Sy Y.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlvv5Hw7BczrB2EJa0tUi7oVzXQrKcexe_QyluaWJfb22gz7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cozy spot might be small with just a few tables for various group sizes, but it adds to the charm of the dining experience. I can't emphasize enough how incredible the food was, particularly the garlic dumplings and spicy wontons. The ability to customize the spiciness level for most dishes is a standout feature. The cold dishes like cucumber and potato were refreshing and tasty. Even though there was a short 10-minute wait, the overall experience was definitely worth it. The complimentary desserts provided to combat the heat were a thoughtful touch. This place is a definite must-visit for its mouthwatering food and attentive service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTGmEiqiIDhpLZSa5uu6VZhUyjR999Na0YSTOG&fid=0x0:0xba62bb428697b557"],"When":"2023-8-13"}]

[{"Name":"Soren Oakley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXYOgTeV2_ww6s9tqNXmDRJczT1aljcVqEtrRtUoOfjdBo_zI_bg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This all started with an unexpected encounter. A friend recommended this restaurant, and at first, we thought it was just an ordinary Korean eatery. Little did we know that the dishes here would be so diverse and delightful. From our very first visit, we completely fell in love with this place. Over the next six months, we came back multiple times, mainly to enjoy their udon and creamy udon dishes.

Although there‚Äôs quite a distance from where I live to here, I‚Äôm more than willing to take the trip just to visit again! Wishing your business continued success, and thank you so much for providing such amazing Korean cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi77AO_2BLOY6EeE011HSVXP_TclX9nfsLjD4-&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Ellen Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzoh866OovBfVlMHdFGLQnEdLyB97Utya-3yzGLsM4EYweL6y3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious korean food. Can‚Äôt even count how many times we‚Äôve come back now!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9p1vKrQTNJUY8mnBHspHSs3XqMG8w74KLRKZo&fid=0x0:0x2ab3aeb548bc78f7"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the lunch combo beef ssam bob for $62

It came with a soup of your choice (we got seafood), marinated raw crab, steamed egg, stone rice, cheese corn, 2 salads, and a selection of beef meats.

Of course you get all the banchans as well.

Soup was very flavourful and the meat was so tender.

It was my friends first time having marinated raw crab and it was a very good experience. It would be better if it was a spicy flavor instead of just soy.

Service was very good, she was very attentive.

Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHjlsvMS8DFN8cJel4S05z6iwrwUs1W46b4iMV&fid=0x0:0x2ab3aeb548bc78f7"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Nancy Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJy5Qf1QbM0_c1L-F7OulUL2yIwJwQ1TDUbUpgT-AhPSJuxhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this Korean BBQ restaurant.The quality of the meat was outstanding, everything was incredibly fresh and well-marinated. They had a wide selection, including beef, pork, chicken, and even seafood. As the meat sizzled on the grill, the aroma was irresistible, and every bite was tender, juicy, and flavorful. The side dishes were equally impressive, with unlimited refills of classic Korean banchan like kimchi, pickled veggies, and potato salad.

The service was exceptional! The staff were so friendly and attentive, greeting us warmly as we arrived. They explained how to use the grill, adjusted the heat when needed.This Korean BBQ spot is definitely worth visiting!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danielle Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmVYhJdAokXRNv0OeadwE83uAo9bdT8RA0Z1YdZz0bhl9Lbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place so much, they have an iPad on the table for you to order what you want and you can call the staff from it and ask for the bill. Also ordered the seafood pancake and thought it was also okay. I wasn‚Äôt a huge fan of how it fell apart really easily.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoQI5xqma306X3Xj-tyh3h7T8B0a6EB3d-8ggy&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Leanna Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-SXyk3Kx1735OiIr1tgjifqKKjDGVUvlOKwRxhFYCtDjEz6O6zQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was good but nothing special. The premium set was tasty and enough food for 4 people. The meats were good quality and delicious. Everything was too spicy for our groups taste unfortunately and there's no option to adjust the spice level. Even the soup was spicy. Seafood pancake was very large and filling  but lacked ingredients. Marinated crab has nice flavour but was too mushy for my taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPajHsix8dfb9OGSgYQ-sXLBMZ5j72d8V7mWYRU&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Dongjun Yan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzkf4xL8CHsYSdrMooQZRL1NM56MIZidM-scMuAvdhuaJcHD0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This barbecue restaurant is truly an exceptional dining experience! From the freshness and tenderness of the meat to the unique seasoning, everything left a deep impression on me. The meat is incredibly fresh and of top-notch quality, with every piece grilled to perfection and exuding a tempting aroma. The service is outstanding as well‚Äîattentive and thoughtful, with staff always ready to assist at just the right moment. Combined with a clean and comfortable environment, it‚Äôs the perfect place for a gathering with friends or family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3Lf8xMOWJg9muKBfkhJblYwGw_im1uBzkTakn&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"R C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0eD31csNo04JzXmFiGxOw6om-U7XoOcrwih3LN1YIW10DJFxa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the Best Korean BBQ Spots in the Lower Mainland!

If you‚Äôre looking for fresh, quality meats, this is the place. The beef and pork were outstanding, and we loved the clams bibimbap and corn cheese as well. The portions were generous‚Äîfour of us were completely satisfied for around $60 per person, including some beers, which felt very reasonable.

A heads-up: reservations are strict! We were about 7 minutes late, and they do only allow a 5-minute grace period, so be sure to arrive on time. I‚Äôd definitely recommend booking a table 1-2 weeks in advance to be safe.

Highly recommend if you‚Äôre in the mood for authentic Korean BBQ!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6x4IJpXMApkWRzoIXtRrpxgUvJMrp7QZKsgNi&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Aileen J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuWvzbfzO_jncgaSim3qZy7MJd3uK4aw634-6jwwEqoRXiGA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited 'Toedam' after for a while. When I said, "I was starving...üòÇ", the server kindly handed us a tablet and mentioned that we could order right away so our food would be ready sooner. Such amazing service‚ÄîKorean BBQ Restaurant at its best! To top it off, they even gave us drinks on the house as a thank-you for waiting patiently. I was so touched! And the food? Absolutely delicious!

I WILL VISIT AGAIN THIS RESTAURANT!!!üëç‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMewMIOzZ36BKgF3xgwFR4vyqwomB3xrtylUXCH&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Xiao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIS_o-8XQcfu3J4J73uohpXess7RNYg9bt22TmDVZmInFoeZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Toe Dam, and I must say, the experience was fantastic!
