The staff was incredibly kind and attentive, making our dining experience all the more enjoyable. If you're looking for a place with generous portions and delicious food, I highly recommend Toe Dam. I can‚Äôt wait to return and try more from their menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp0sgha2dFdxnH68-Xu6_xipdi0tZkR85NbgAx&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Hangout CAN (Âá∫Ëµ∞Âä†ÊãøÂ§ß)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLsataZBHdbXdf5fvvtSixzA7_P_SmPgA4k4U2s2VVx5uk12E8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is very fresh and delicious üòã
Love this BBQ restaurant!
And we tried soy sauce crab & shrimp, seafood pancake too, Surprisingly tasty! Love it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNm1gvEQamVqWFkt6AN3o_ul0E7T-sgRTJHsWXK&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently visited this restaurant with my friends, and the experience was terrible due to the poor service. I wouldn‚Äôt be fooled by the other good reviews this restaurant has. Our server was inattentive, failing to refill our water jug or check if we needed napkins. We also asked for gloves with the raw crab, but they never arrived. To top it off, at 10:20 pm, the server abruptly rushed us for the bill, even though the restaurant was supposed to close at 11:30 pm. When my friend chose not to leave a tip and selected the no-tip option on the payment machine, the server rudely informed us that tip was not included and repeatedly canceled the transaction and tried to force us to leave her a tip. As for the food, we ordered the raw crab, beef tartar bowl, bulgogi bowl, and clam bowl. The only dish worth noting was the beef tartar bowl; the rest of the items were disappointing. The raw crab lacked a strong soy sauce flavor, and the other bowls were not enjoyable. I will not be returning to this restaurant and strongly recommend looking elsewhere for a better dining experience!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoJCNgvYB_ywjz6R0cZ75YKeGLpBPtBO3cKwnA&fid=0x0:0x1091031f4479bc0b"],"When":"2024-8-17"}]

[{"Name":"Gab Wiessmann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCJTnBjHmNVcf6NPJ-Hd6gf8lWFoXmsloOeyZIsL5GoTQ3qtCc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the tonkotsu ramen with extra noodles and it was one of the best ramen I‚Äôve had in the Coquitlam area. The noodles were perfectly cooked, not too hard, not too soft. The broth was really good too, not too salty like most tonkotsu ramen I‚Äôve had. I also loved the amount of customization you could do when ordering through the kiosk. I will definitely return here next time I‚Äôm visiting the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVw6_k1kxlVmZKBASUISFP5WwoODLH2Xsb0ijW&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today we revisited my favorite spot with the family. Unfortunately, the food quality has declined significantly. The 2 shoyu ramen priced at $17 each and the karage Don at $18 were disappointing in terms of portion size and taste. Was hoping for the great experience we remember, but left unsatisfied. ‚≠ê"  ps. The salad was so dry, gross!
The person with a good review before me, must be a friend or work at this place or he or she doesn't know what real good food supposed to taste like.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-JioxapoTk3ckQS1ZHI4fDu4tlWI3ZLL_WaYk&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-4-6"},{"Name":"Viona Halim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5PMLEtvgkAwv2IjmL8XXm0-Ly_XpBo5Kd0Hv2pxoQ26_Hfy4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Passed by this stall when we were at the mall and we decided to give it a try. If you've never been here before, the way to order is by self-service touchscreen stations they have on the left side of the counter. We're so used to just ordering to the staff and completely missed the touchscreen stations üòÜ.

One thing this ramen place has it going is the noodle. They're perfectly cooked with a nice bite and chew to them. You can choose between pork-based or chicken-based broth. We both chose pork-based since we like to base things on traditional first when trying new places. The pork-based is very thick and  creamy. If you're a fan of those really thick and creamy ramen, this place is for you. For us, while we like rich broth, this one is more on the too thick and too rich side of things. I also find for the TanTan ramen, that the broth is too much on the salty side of things. My husband got the chashu ramen and the salt level is much better, just right. Maybe we should've gone with the chicken-based broth instead...

Avg price is somewhere between $13-14/ bowl. You can make it a combo and pick 1 small side dish like gyoza, karaage or donburi, etc. Drinks not included in combo. So for 2 people, if you order 2 combos, expect to pay somewhere along the line of $40 or so. Price-wise, I feel like you can have a better ramen at a sit-down restaurant. You might be paying a little more, but not THAT much more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOScIYJALBSiF24q2-KcOHh_ChTNlQ-S70oyD2K&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2022-7-29"},{"Name":"Alex Barros","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbGQfDFyWBFf-SHj8dHqz7fJQ6yDYj9me5-vlKbsRH7vrJMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The noodles in the Ramen has a strange chemical  smell.  I'm disappointed  with  the food.  The service needs  improvement. Price is reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMu4DPFM0ceUOEV358GE-Www877YZsbj2xHvYVL&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Ivan Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAnyoYYXXFP9snQgaU7KUgox1Ss1DMCPvpD-7cL-ggizeHFLh87A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The noodles tasted very good, with a good amount of toppings. Though the price point is a bit on the more expensive side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNfayJ7TEep5u_6KWqksKK8Ej6UXvgY-opNj3I&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Sally Zeng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyvG25e-9g8jG0ZfEMdub-S4p2HgxJMLK-NlH0Jp5V2gdVjPNsjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My son enjoyed very much! I like it too. It‚Äôs butter than some  Downtown famous ramen üçú. I like the Shio, and the chicken base soup tasted not too great. The actual use fire to burn the Chasu meat makes it so delicious. I always go to enjoy it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlJSGXtQTPWpT_r0LF5x7JXOhuEIKq2fLCXAka&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"In the gastronomical tapestry that is the food court, Menbow Ramen stands not as the gourmet stitch but as the humble, durable thread that holds it all together. Though its ramen won't be ascending to any culinary Mount Olympus, its reliably decent servings manage to stir envy in its broth-boiling brotherhood. Plus, with their takeout packages more secure than a bank vault, others could definitely learn a thing or two about food to-go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP26cs1Lk5fkGR9pw9_NT-qSYbA_hURSlVx_xXD&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2023-6-22"},{"Name":"Joe B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgMmsnd7ebO17Gbmka7I7uLdXQJEThrmwrdC1eUggf2HzY-KVbLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved it at the first mouthful. Broth is superb. Noodles chewy.. Pork tender and well charred. In PoCo it's hard to find a good Ramen shop and this one definitely did the trick. Loved it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwalkgiLrTb2Thx4NXPhDWrFshx7vUoqJLneZm&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-2-8"}]

[{"Name":"Neda G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcXBADLi2CMhn5hf9f-JdbOlYYM_LHhdjb9JmX03VjxzMph4k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The reviews are legit! This place is a hidden gem. We had a lovely breakfast with my kids, mom and husband. The service was good despite only one person working, she did awesome and they were very respectful of my daughter's allergies.

More importantly, the FOOD was AMAZING!!! Crispy gorgeous potatoes, really yummy pancake and waffles and great coffee. Will absolutely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZm2JrIJBpWvMNrTgyP1KWz2ol7OXkf14yCZLp&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Cherilyn Morris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFSsTxkRHOvnhVnL21RRcRzjanEDvQ_-BctHEQEFo9i_I6jA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered via a delivery service and were very pleased with the food from PK's Diner. We gave a 5 for atmosphere as we have read reviews stating how comfortable the diner is and therefore had to give a 5 for that reason. We had the Bacon Cheeseburger and Clubhouse sandwich. Both were delicious. My husband said that the burger is one of the best that he has had. The burger was loaded with tomatoes, bacon and onions and he really liked the burger sauce that came with it as well. The bacon was thick and my husband said that the caramelized onions made the burger. I also found my Clubhouse to have been very good also with thick bacon, ham, and a generous amount of grilled chicken. The fries were crispy and the picture with the Clubhouse did not have all the fries that came with the order. We both have left overs for tomorrow. We are always cautiously optimistic when ordering home delivery due to the food not being fresh out of the kitchen. Well, we were so pleased with our meals and will definitely be ordering again. We are looking forward to trying out more items on the menu. Thank you so much PK's.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLTqRnbF0525X_IBQ69XBMilRq6EUKYroOWi1f&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Kim Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIR3fyXypuJm8ILEdOCVPODC97_SULpf89BUpmEUxYYnr0uBA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Breakfast tasted great. I had the smoked duck benedict - delicious, tender duck meat. Fluffy pancakes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQQTCyuOJoSGd_q3QxCrjr06WtsiKzh8wWmmkI&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Khwanravee Phajum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6GF6hlgxdCI-il-sbuGK3OWdGWyHB-PRNuj8HpNLtL-GTcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love PK Cafe‚Äô!!! The service is excellent, super friendly staff. Their breakfast menu is almost like desserts, especially waffles and French toasts are unbelievable delicious, moist and crispy at the same time! I love my chicken lemongrass, so tender and flavourful. We can‚Äôt wait to try all of their dishes. To add to how wonderful this place is‚Ä¶the price is so affordable!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfrFZiCKbIhIzaUyEMRXaImFdwP6Ap1U7eiGgh&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2024-4-8"},{"Name":"Deborah H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsXwwC3s9WyQKJ7Zs95PXuhLbAGHn9sk0S1KGXgVkYpWzFwg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a nice surprise to find this great brunch place! Situated in an unassuming small neighbourhood plaza, PKs Cafe is a very clean cafe with a perfect selection of choices on the menu. We have been here a few times and it is always topnotch and tasty whether its breakfast or burgers. Their breakfast potatoes wedges and fries are just the right crispiness. Coming back to try their sandwiches next! Service is always friendly and love the attentive coffee refills.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP30Phpcy40cKMXuRkCo3k4xseN5ZBjAvd2aWS7&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"Dariia Druzkina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1HtrODnJhuv0fWVXjF7xNuGcR7qBMJc7wC52gLfs1dI0JGA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a very cute cafe with big portions and amazing staff. The food was delicious and the menu has great options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3kHOFd3zoIPRpic-fVDR1pTnhEO9xOU7hJ5GR&fid=0x0:0xde5d02ec9b39e76b"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Nick Tang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQkP22OPLsbOln7vAD-ae1LRI9zUvNKoMyd5lAIDRgo7JO2KRe=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"HOLY!!! The Banana Almond French toast was soooo soft, light and not overly sweet. [{"Name":"Lenny Pottier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxzZl5gT-cauJ3WfvWzNtU6dLIejZJz4545gK9rOohGI8c0kc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Bbq is my go too fro kfc, i love their cheeseling fries... i usually order from the port moody location and never been disapointed. Today i order from this location and received weird shaped fries mushy and barely edible. Yes it was free with my purchase but for the quality i will have prefer paid and get rhe real deal.... (see picture attached). Chicken was good but not as crispy as usually get in port moody. Will probably not order from this location again even though it is closer .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwJ1OtTgs7S3n5mfI5LJ9h1H_DuFFGlqgoLD9G&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Jennelle Stam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIWYGUfyG2dESbyA1fBLy08rntV4nEfvkAAwXniWbZmYxCYIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got the chance to dine here, after months of my friend recommending it (and sending lots of bragging pics). It did NOT DISSAPOINT. Not only am I planning on coming back here to make my way through the menu, I'll join my friend in singing it's praises. Food was awesome, and service was wholesome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK1D7wMftVr2zQ-SnWrQzZ8xwrydvMFLAIxHYB&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Blampin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUe_Zl-7bsR_k4aPN0CDrFm3JxQQaY2wgkXgNPVdZQs9NDoFTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This spot was kind of easy to miss entering the plaza where H mart and Pomme are. The KFC Korean Fried üçó Chicken was absolutely amazing! Tou have no idea so many flavors ever Gangnam Style !!
Rhw server was super nice even though the kids were making a rawkus!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMljFLHZqn4SXfgxAlv9n7VzRvIazMUCtesYhyP&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Ellen Sea","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgyvw39gUnCgl6xsGC3h38EgAvDpICnxUdU619L8I4-wyV0VMy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the galbi q chicken and the assorted cheese balls with a pitcher.
The chicken was actually quite good and moist but it wasn't crispy at all, so I can imagine that the takeout orders wouldn't be crispy either. The assorted cheese balls were also really good but just know that they're filled with cream cheese and not the stretchy mozzarella!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVhOBmL1dXlMrjKdvXJeEweA36IPC25MDmn-qE&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious hot chicken straight from the deep fryer. Fast service and it only took less than 10 minutes from ordering to when we got our first dish. Lots of fried chicken options to choose from but we chose the golden fried which is this place‚Äôs signature dish. It was so flavourful despite looking very normal. The restaurant also has $5 happy hour 3-5 pm and 9-close every day. Lots of parking at the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdBNPkj9lUhkiYlFXOCn5CmJyKztu4wSvXxjsz&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2023-4-15"},{"Name":"Lindsey Williamson Christy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUm0fBNIzlRgvO6bgjVqXgXmvR5p2HzkxHc09XqHLqCh77AS_a1fA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Awesome little Mom & Pop Korean Chicken place. We tried a few things and everything was great. It‚Äôs good little spot for a quick tasty meal","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVDSwHj5NdWzjBydxx3Bp83sC3EjikOB47Bkxh&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"P H (p p)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJKZy9bt4M6XUHig_6VLAGdw5hO6Ek6ULZkNZOMB3D3bFiKF4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Service is good cause I just picked up not for here.
The secret source flavor is not good as Metrotown. I still remember that metrotown‚Äôs is more spicy and the amount of chicken is larger.

I could remember wrong for the amount but the taste must be right. Hope it will improve next time. Well I still love it anyway.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNifXAAchMK9-BVRuriRjlpbA5Rzsa8LWflCELG&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Fremy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqXXZ5rKarOZyZdNvNUw-YcnDQL3N2JVFQewPrpwmHEPRYalMs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The honey garlic chicken was really succulent and crispy. The flavour of the garlic and honey harmonizes really well and its flavour was bursting the moment you take a bite into it. On the other hand, the mala hot chicken tasted more peppery rather than the signature flavour profile of mala. It has a really strong kick for people who are not accustomed to hot spices, such as myself. Overall, for less than $20/pax, their portion is just right.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiPdaZa_WzdSiRuZctc9_11e4iWL0ills8MITc&fid=0x0:0x616e899f573a2426"],"When":"2023-2-12"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love the food here and definitely will be back but most likely grabbing take out over dine in if coming on the weekend. Came here for the first time on Sat, Oct 20th for brunch at 11:15 AM, it was packed and we (2) put our name on the waiting list, it took about 45 mins to get a seat which was the only negative but we figured it must be good considering how busy it was so we waited. The seating is a bit too close for my preference to the point there is no privacy to have a conversation while you eat but I get they are likely trying to maximize the seating, it's also a pay up front before you order type of establishment so just keep that in mind. Not my favourite since I like to tip well but based off the service so in these pre pay scenarios I unfortunately just have to go 15% because I'm hoping it's going to be good, but I don't blame them with all the shady people these days doing dine and dash and etc.

That's where the complaints end, the food was absolutely amazing and the staff are very friendly and welcoming. I will definitely be coming back and seeing if they're a bit less busy perhaps for a later brunch around 1:30-2 PM next time and if not I'll stick to take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4miz5R1JAfwId5oUPDkbUvfO1VKqG9oN3FhiG&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV44fpfaEhe-NUZmd0KxbQW5h4ZO24PneHP0Sgtc4_visySni_S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I can't say enough good things about the food. The bowls are huge and though they seem pricy at first, the amount of food you get is well worth it.

Our first visit came highly recommended by a friend and we were also suggested to try the bowls. We went with the Plant Based bowl and the Brisket Bowl.

The brisket was extremely tasty and delicious. Broke apart with barely a sight of the fork. The combinations were great.

The plant based bowl was equally tasty with the chorizo style no-meat.

The server was very kind and was excited to help us out of provide information.

The problem however, is their pay-at-window system. They require you to pay prior to being served and their system pops up for a tip of 15% or more, prior to having had any service. I voiced my frustration to the server and although she was understanding, this seems to be a growing trend among many small restaurants.

I don't feel comfortable tipping without service first, and especially when ordering food first, you feel compelled to tip so the restaurant gives you good service. This "good tip first = good service" needs to stop.

If not for their tip system, I would easily rate this place above and beyond. It is STILL a must try in Coquitlam.

Don't feel compelled to tip first, tell them right at the window you'll tip after the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN-yo_rdnY4iXeMEJun1d0qpS8UBc72wb_7x32&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-2-24"},{"Name":"Amy W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXW2kFPUz2ZEuA7b5L3P1pRYoMNSxOcfMvE3AI7nWAbheGCBAE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food and service if you need catering for office lunch or family gatherings. The owner is easy to work with, understands your requests and accommodates well. I‚Äôd recommend providing a budget and let them create a fun surprise menu for your event. (Hint: You can order food that is off their regular restaurant menu!) Generous portion size and packaged well for take out. Best to order a few weeks in advance and pick up if you can as it is a busy restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwxxVmyjv9uN1f9MMaxfxZM1_hfx8PLZ62oczi&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"Neil Westlake","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkJv3AzW4tBOSLrqh2jethB1xgQxQAL7dV6GEGf7O6ziwbP2c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is phenomenally good. The pan fries are perfection,  scumbled until they are floury on the outside, then cooked to a perfect golden brown.

I had the Longanisa patty inside a brioche bun. My wife had the brisket bowl.

The interior is clean and very well designed with live-edge wood accents.
Service is attentive.

Well worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBdQidu9-LBp2UYGcCi5vlNKrzu1asCqFnSHqw&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2022-6-23"},{"Name":"Jasmine C (Jasmine)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl_wTRZRv85CvyyDAN1cvtTS3H_ie2czWqnkRltr5-8JeM_xhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I understand why they have such high rating now. Their breakfast bowls have a super big portion and honestly taste really good. Very yummy and filling. Good value. Good food.

This was one of the restaurants attached to the bowling place so washrooms are outside to the left and close by.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUD6OSE3IfIK4WRh44X3OqHrYzMiEXZHC-znyR&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2023-10-31"},{"Name":"Marley Mckenzie cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5n4XAwgV26WrtDQFOwKexjEHrP8ok0rq2RztGWysEOnM29r4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time trying this place, food was decent but that‚Äôs not what I find wrong with this place. It is a busy place and I understand they don‚Äôt have much seating but to have customers sit in the back where people are constantly walking past you to go to the washroom or take their kids to the bathroom is unpleasant. The back seating is a joke, they have pest control traps on the floor and it‚Äôs where  all the recycling is. I find this pretty disgusting and shouldn‚Äôt have customers sitting in the back recycling/ trash area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNg2EmY09HpYOYp0h_X9SgkEoIzE6F1a6apmlk&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I really wish I could give this place more stars, but the experience me and my friends had here was a hectic one. First, we came on a Sunday around noon for brunch. Sundays are a very busy day, so we expected a waitlist which is totally fine. We waited about an hour for our table. There was so many people leaving, after an hour of not receiving a call we came in again to check how it was going, they apologized said that it was so hectic they were behind with calling the customers. When we finally ordered and sat down, it took quite a while to get our food. I ordered the chicken sandwich, and I was really disappointed when they put pickled peppers and onions on it when it never stated on the menu that it was on the burger. I didn‚Äôt bother saying anything because you could see the staff were already really struggling to keep up with all the orders. Second my two friends ordered the acai bowl, and one was completely forgotten all together. We had to go remind them that we never received an order. I do not blame the workers that day, if anything we really felt bad for how stressful everything was. From my understanding aswell is a lot of them were very new, and being new while working a Sunday ,plus understaffed is understandably very overwhelming. We even noticed they were accidently overcharging guests, and not being able to refund them due to the new machine system. One worker really stood out though; I believe her name was Lea. She was so kind and was going above and beyond to try and fix all the problems and issues that the restaurant was having. She was really trying her best and it was lovely interacting with her. She alone made our experience a lot better. The food we received itself was really well made and very delicious. ( Besides having the pickles peppers/onions on my sandwich ) But Like I said before, I had such high hopes for this place, unfortunately due to our experience and the stress it caused us , this place would not be our first choice to come back to. Overall, they need more staff on a Sunday, and better organization","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmqPqRoJVr9_gx0TGti-1enX-R7IWzO0rr5NXI&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2023-9-13"},{"Name":"Janet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJLdrp4_-PzGWs8I7cbVIruptxWktGjE-_19gAKtYsnjV7T8DB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lovely little brunch place in Coquitlam, the staff is friendly and the place is clean, it is on the small side and at rush hour expect line ups. Food was delicious! Be prepared that while they do seat you, you order at the counter so you pay upfront.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS52NqhoATiiFpOsVT8tFxwp_yGdQbsREFjSfm&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-3-16"}]

[{"Name":"alex son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHu7LRFyxDEmIiDicGOX9Xw2wJytUGtyrAHnY87q_4pR8Nvw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of Doni‚Äôs standout features is its dedication to quality ingredients. Each dish is freshly prepared, and it shows. The portions are generous, and the presentation is impressive, especially for a food court setting. It‚Äôs clear that thought and care go into every meal, making it feel like you‚Äôre dining at a standalone restaurant rather than a quick stop in the mall.

Doni has successfully elevated the mall food court dining experience. With its diverse menu, commitment to quality, and friendly service, it‚Äôs a standout option that‚Äôs well worth a visit. Whether you‚Äôre a regular mall-goer or just passing through, Doni offers a delicious escape from the usual fast food fare. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMs9cNGsHAmSchoBQxjUsrv8agGYTMoI2S--hcg&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update: Half & Half Dumplings are spot on, and the Seafood fried rice was delicious with a generous portion! Restaurant quality

Past: The place is pretty solid. I tried it a few days ago for the first time.
Counter service was good, clean space and of course the food tasted great!
Surprised the Seafood Jajangmeon was a little spicy! (Was a good kick just unexpected)
The fried dumplings were awesome!
Great addition to Henderson","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-zI0R3T-jkGs0KmDo9pLx5dNk7T-q5Ld3D4_I&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food with value.  Can‚Äôt expect more.  Spicy noodle is very hot. Can ask for mild if can‚Äôt handle but taste good with spicy especially in cold weather","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNILjIKJkBv16vwWr_GhP6CrP8ogBR_A7AP0_ey&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I discovered Doni through a Korean community, learning that it had recently relocated from Surrey to Henderson Mall in Coquitlam Centre. Intrigued by the positive reviews, I decided to visit during a weekday at off-peak hours, shortly after 3 PM.

I ordered the spicy pork cutlet, and it did not disappoint. The batter and pork thickness were excellent, and the dish was well-executed. Although the sauce was flavorful and creamy, it wasn't the typical accompaniment for Korean pork cutlets and was spicier than I expected. I didn't quite like the sauce tbh.

However, I loved the texture and the flavour of the rice, and the sliced cabbage was fresh. Next time, I would opt for the non-spicy version, though I couldn't find it on the menu this time.

Located on the 2nd floor of Henderson Mall's food court, the area was clean and well-maintained. Like many Korean restaurants, Doni uses a small remote that rings and buzzes when your order is ready. The employee was kind, and the ordering process was smooth.

Some have complained about long wait times for their orders. Despite there being few customers, my order took about 10-15 minutes, which suggests they fry the cutlet fresh upon ordering. Otherwise, the wait time wouldn't make sense.

Considering the inflated food prices elsewhere, Doni is very affordable. I'm definitely returning to try their Korean-Chinese menu items and dumplings. Keep up the good work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFkwX60yoagt8J6S7gtGwralkkMEjZF_TbKQwP&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Price point and taste wise, this is a very good Korean restaurant.  Interior design leaves little to desire but quality of food should make up for it.  We loved the taste of the fried dumplings especially.  Also the noodle soup was excellent.  Soup was rich while the soaked dumplings were awesome.  Stone pot mixed rice tasted great too.  It could be little spicy for some people but sauce was too good.  Squid can be little chewy but they were generous with portion size of squid.  Parking‚Äôs plenty in the plaza though it can be busy at times.  Overall, we will definitely return for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFa8mzPd2sVHz-3vms-QQixtWW5Gio1n2t9Yh3&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2023-7-14"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I usually don‚Äôt post my pic but I have to because it‚Äôs first post :)

After the sudden shutdown of DONI King George left everyone in a tizzy, I am so happy to say that THEY ARE BACK!!

Same great flavour and similar menu as their old location. Same amazing service albeit it‚Äôs now in Henderson Mall Foodcourt and served in foodcourt containers. But it‚Äôs no less delicious. It tastes the same, people!

They‚Äôre running a promotion for their grand opening so come one, come all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiKOJv-I9kfzc8hCyxCwU-I90s0w8lkAGjgpQ9&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-1-7"},{"Name":"Kane Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEgxeO4rzWbqbMjwUBC8AaFegiYqCe3sPvwn2pXruIC8Du9piLVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A lovely little corner of the world. It's been a while since I've visited Surrey, and at a friend's recommendation, I came to this little gem of a dumpling and noodle shop.

This is one of those unfussy spots where the owners take great care to provide. Prices are very reasonable, the decor homely and well used, and the food -- it embraces you from the inside.

It's nothing over the top, but the dumplings, noodles and soup (Combo A provides you with a front and centre taste of what this place provides) are hand made, of carefully considered ingredients, and delicious. Grandma made this for you, and happily. Eat up!

Crispy deep fried dumplings with a lacy crust are filled with pork, vegetables and tofu. Light, guilt free, these were my first and last bite of the meal. The soup was light and some of the best I've had, and the soup dumplings were plump and well filled.

Noodles were a little softer than I would have liked, though -- but this dish might call for softer noodles, so I'm not a good judge! They are made of a similar body and texture as the dumpling wrappers, which totally makes sense, but seasoned with spinach.

Seriously considering bringing back some frozen dumps home, but I'll revisit that idea after a walk.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdh8e7Sdn5N1FK7Hk3SHQTRQ2Ump4r383CRvNV&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2021-3-21"},{"Name":"Michael Xie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuofARxYvhwxxfylcnz8mBM0K5uLGN7Ke55RRoKhlEZOs358vlwA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The king is dead. Long live the king!

There used to be a Korean restaurant where DONi is now, and that place used to have great Korean food at a great price, and my go to place at this food court. I was sad to see it gone and replaced with DONi, but I still ordered from them anyway. The shrimp fried rice quality was excellent and I think the pricing is not too bad as well!

Will definitely be taking advantage of their grand opening sale and try a few more items! I think this place is my new go to place at the food Court!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1f7eqHzIreSNqR6TuidZ2UGoJDLTE06qvYI6Z&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-1-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Thushan Dodanwala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWS_aDjXUy-U3JADt5BUTq5yyJMYhOkFN2Mlsu2VrgDFcuEVsMe=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic lunch at Gordon Ramsay Burger with my wife. The food was delicious, and the service was outstanding. Our server, Kiyomi, was attentive, friendly, and made sure we had a wonderful dining experience. We ordered the Nashville burger with onion rings, Hell's Kitchen Burger, Hellfire Chicken Wings, and for drinks a Watermelon Lemonade and Mojito. For dessert, we really enjoyed the Sticky Toffee Pudding and also they accommodated my request made at Reservation to bring out an Ice Cream Sunday with a candle as it was my wife's birthday. Everything was perfect and the flavors were incredible. I highly recommend visiting this place for great food and excellent service. We'll definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjZVjP-ljjBQc-9i8VcY2WRaDYrE6tr8bBYxYL&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Earl Malvar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIKiqglVXoT9nPmI192J6J7r6928JA2bFrsB4MMWVRLWvGQBQp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you very much to our dinner-date host, Mark, who was very personable and eager to assist for us to enjoy our Gordon Ramsay dining experience. All the staff members were happy to oblige and acknowledging during our dine-in and that kept the vibe fresh and cozy.

We had a 24-Hour Burger and a Hell‚Äôs Kitchen Burger. Both were distinct-tasting gourmet burgers with their merits. I must admit that I‚Äôm partial to In-N-Out burgers, but these belong to a different category of food. Gordon Ramsay‚Äôs burgers are good in their own way. The 24-Hour burger‚Äôs Bbq sauce kept this dish interesting imo, while the Hell‚Äôs Kitchen burger was not so-in-your-face, as its subtle flavors from its ingredients kept this a pleasant dish to enjoy through a chat. For our drinks, the Espresso Martini tasted like a chocolatey dessert and the Earl and the Empress was like an iced tea punch. Both were good enough drinks to pair with our burgers.

All in all, it‚Äôs at least worth a visit to try out the menu, but the price points may not be as appealing if you‚Äôre looking for heft or more generous serving sizes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOq1McavZOXafsAfIX0lQP4i5lEYxGu3gUPU0jm&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"George Watson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDDOfxretD35ARsdREF1AzgD2ndrlNCvaeJvYRp_CvcKbsfn0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôd come here just for the onion rings! SO good! I had the ‚ÄúBrunch Burger‚Äù and it was crazy good! The bacon is candied and cooked perfectly. The house side salad was a flavour explosion in my mouth with the raspberries and feta. Damn son!!! What can I say? I‚Äôm gonna come back and try every single thing on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfj82P-z-gt5xKUZw2ZFNCZsRk3OUTHtDCOfJ3&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Triple Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpOUu3KPS1-er6yleoWeyiUKtsRw4U7A4457Dg5vEpOaOkhJ5E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our waiter at the Gordon Ramsay restaurant, Vanessa, made our experience fantastic. She was friendly, sociable, and genuinely kind. I‚Äôll definitely be returning‚Äîthe hamburger tasted just like the one I had in Las Vegas earlier this year! They also surprised us with a complimentary birthday dessert, which was a lovely touch. The atmosphere was great, featuring many pictures of Gordon Ramsay, all in a classy yet simple setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCPCiCYfHm4yURTL7vTdma4Z4y0Ou7xwa7WP2N&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Leah-Ann Maybee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMulsRVvripmeyJ0yWPz1sCxHKRTmTLYktUy8Q7KQNujw4624=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The host was wonderful and our server was friendly, prompt and informative! Today was a special day that my friend and I that haven‚Äôt seen each other in close to 20 years got to see each other in person. Drinks and food, including dessert were incredible. I‚Äôm happy I have leftovers. I honestly can‚Äôt say anything but good things about the visit (first ever to a Gordon Ramsay restaurant). I will definitely come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOl_eQns2ny4lprfMujqIK5dJkVLFsHmBWXgCSW&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Jennifer Ramirez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAFq69iTIcaZDekD27us44d8ngDu8WdKsqDyyYnNu7GaC-OA8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place was alright. It‚Äôs unfortunate that the ketchup doesn‚Äôt taste good, nor the sauce that comes with the sweet potato fries. My burger was dry‚Ä¶ the one thing I did enjoy was the truffle fries and my glass of wine. My boyfriend enjoyed his unlimited Pepsi üòÖ ‚Ä¶ no Coke sadly. The waitress was super friendly tho!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNahmbfQmQ3sMJbXpf9gArja5QUgUuUbbHFXfm3&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a fantastic time at Gordon Ramsay Burger. The food was delicious, and the service was welcoming and prompt.

I wish we made a reservation. The restaurant was busier than expected, and I can understand why.

I'd highly recommend the Kettle Chip Nachos. The braised beef with the kettle chips are delicious.

The Blue Cheeseburger was also fantastic. So glad we didn't skip it! The Backyard Burger was also fantastic.

We also tried a Straight Up Dawg for kicks. But it was just ok.

Looking forward to our next visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdaSsKuwS7YzJhGIeD9Q6x0zCdBtDdSRcDTWlj&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Kirsten Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVY2Ec4gYGj3899LMmpRLOZW0Bf3u8nXrFYPnjknNaI8LNqqssEgA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best onion rings I've ever had!
Reason enough to go back. Our table of 7 had a wide variety of burgers and they were all delicious. Fries were just right. Wings were good too, however overpriced for the qty. Service (Michael) was 5 stars. Attentive, warm, and professional. Milkshakes were a better value than the $15 cocktails. Appreciated the birthday treat with a candle.
The waiting area between the restaurant and casino has more decor/atmosphere than the actual restaurant. I'm not sure what it needs but "something" to make it feel less "generic".
Went in with trepidation and left with expectations exceeded.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYcLrehLGCWt3TxtSMNnZDKTyQVLR3yz8zYCcw&fid=0x0:0x949c4608707b7a90"],"When":"2024-8-20"}]

[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered takeout and the pizza was delicious and real tasting. Our favourite was the fungi de Alfredo pizza. The manager‚Äôs choice is good too if you like meat and lots going on as toppings for your pizza. The Hawaiian pizza tasted standard. The only thing in my opinion that would make the pizza taste even better is if they applied a little more tomato sauce on the pizzas as the Hawaiian and Manager‚Äôs Choice pizza were a little light on the tomato sauce (as seen in the photos) and the tomato flavour was very light and not too prominent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDanaQg5OogPQ81J4SQ9fw9ApD-2ZO_W4nlOgX&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Upon recommendation from a friend we ordered a pizza. We chose the Italian delight but switched the olive oil base for pesto instead. It was delicious and quite affordable. Large (6big slices) for $22. Love the light thin base and great toppings. Easy walking distance from our place. Will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7PNveFE7yJk1kR3lFheirfPwsbjs0YO3AvaFT&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""Just tried their pizza for the first time, and I highly recommend it! üçï Best pizza I've ever had with amazing customer service. Definitely worth a visit!"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOk6JBQ77EXh9lNodBouxDx5ck25ioObiX2nxxi&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Karen R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDV_xh-2FRTt60Dk8cmOVYbJK862izxJKbtP4b4MrmUNx8NdUF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôm Impressed!

This place came up on a google search and I was rushed and just went for it, so I didn‚Äôt know what to expect. I didn‚Äôt even read the other reviews. I went in blind.

The crust was nice and crunchy on the bottom and soft on the top. It is somewhere between the Neapolitan thin-ness and like a ‚Äústandard pizza‚Äù. Best of both worlds.

Toppings were not too heavy but I think there is pizza science out there with a toppings to crust ratio. If you want a stack of toppings add more.

Cheese was light but again I think this is purposeful and it works with the rest of it, but if you need to live the cheezy life, just add more of it.

I was very annoying by accident and I made a few special requests while it was busy on a Friday not knowing this place is actually quite popular and busy. They accommodated my requests anyway.

Online ordering was easy and the timeline was reliable. I waited maybe 2 extra minutes (probably while the accommodated my annoying peak hour requests)

The staff were nice.

It is August and it was hot. I would not recommend sitting inside on a 31 degree August evening to eat your pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHPjN224PO1yD1vEICW09TRi7_Ob8BC9EHiWeE&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Jessica Dhaliwal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOeC5VCbc6g3HH3dxXpDS9bE993HEKMDVI3SjHX2aNdHbQOJHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice flat pizza with great toppings and aftertaste. Really grateful they have slices available even late","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdju3xRR9csby2HRwLCeCGjQ8wAdbmHMC6jUyr&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Vegan Cheese option! My friends & I ordered takeout this past Saturday for UFC. Their delivery timing was on point and the pizza tasted really good. I got the Bulgogi Pizza, flavor was spot on with a little kick of heat, crust was so good.
The only thing is the base dough was so thin that when I lifted the pizza.. All the toppings fell off. Otherwise it was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzoCgWjE1mKqA-AcqireE5BW9YSqEN4e9L_wWq&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Nathan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULis9x-C7u8jouJ6bmV-m7Mb2r-esn5uJaOqGwjwAA9z2MADUV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great lil place, food was fresh and tastes great for the price and quality. Only problem is that the place is small inside so dine in can be a bit difficult. Other than that good pizza with soft crust!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfKGlU00XGevawFJe4aofL74KKYSwEHBqbTgIw&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Eric Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaP-Cv8mkM8LXkeKN8VsQ-1rg-847adCVZNi52fJh1oGiXYu83=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My daughters and I ordered three different flavors of pizza and baked chicken wings. They were all very delicious. This must be the best pizza I've ever had. Highly recommended! The pizzas were thin and the edges were baked to a perfect crisp. The two lovely waitstaff were also very friendly. I will be a frequent visitor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkQZGxMHjWxiw5ZUeIbcIZTQKH4JB1YG_XJSBI&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-1-3"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Alex Borrisovski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKscHxIUcTePI3B0hf5AcOoUDC6DPl_UJyjo0agQXSvGbdsCw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The new management have changed things. The food was great, the service was fantastic. It's too bad the hours are limited, but having come here for hockey for many years, this is the best this place has been in a long time. Worth a trip upstairs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kiara Pelletier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw5wFIRt-58eUJT28bMXW-_A1xWl5sIe2bSiREMFXtx_acLSIt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This establishment has recently come under new management, and unfortunately, the change has not been a positive one. While I had no issues with the food or our server, the on-site manager, who I later learned is named Patricia, displayed a visibly hostile demeanor toward her staff. This kind of behavior not only creates an unpleasant work environment but also inevitably affects the guest experience. Once I became aware of the tension, it made the atmosphere uncomfortable. The manager appeared neither happy nor adequately trained for the role. As someone with experience in customer service, I strongly hope the management takes steps to address this issue, as such behaviour is both unprofessional and detrimental to the business.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Douglas Dykens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpykpVkqtjv0MqJuItxb6Lo4JCIsRiaf3W1yzgFWMMebHVJmY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to watch your Childs hockey practice or game. The staff is always extremely friendly and eager to provide good service! Wide selection of drinks and good bar food!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jackson Marsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3mkw9Aq2Mni14yKQWSLZoYdzU3NK2eNe4GZLZ7D_9erjD-MUg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It took over 30 mins to get a beer at the self serve station.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josh Shelley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-u2KR2ltM-k7o6fpr9UQ45PGDaM7oO18o6KV1D86b1nU8Hg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always the nicest, fastest, best service! All the staff is super friendly and my glass is always full. The food is always excellent! Come and have a drink and watch a game at a great place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shawn Nixon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIumHKDqc_JzC62C4yB5i8Sr2Bo2is2gBUEKUkyQoFqg-7irw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered food and waited and hour and a half before finding out they never put the order in. So I ordered nachos instead thinking it may be quick, the place was empty and they messed up my order and they took an hour before finally getting my nachos. They showed up cold, I‚Äôm not one to complain or write reviews but this was really bad. Definitely don‚Äôt recommend but the hockey game was good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly\u0026Lana Coueslan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_VEbyssnQ_Dp5CEkmVByMHdrZsP1DBL_DBSksKGYY1gvUHw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Being a hockey mom I get to visit most of the bars attached to rinks in the lower mainland.  Boomers by far is my favourite.  Love the varied menu, the \"Boomer\" burger being my latest favourite. More importantly, a decent wine menu for a sports bar! Staff super friendly and the manager always ready with a smile and suggestion off the menu!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kim T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuNnN2AN1A4S0bJdZTcCwOg5iTyoan1x5VhxaYJqSv4T5hQykItA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love Boomers. We make sure to come up here anytime our son is playing hockey here. The staff is so friendly and they make you feel welcome. The food is amazing and the drinks are even better!!! Thanks for everything!!!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Trina Whitsitt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzPXgI6R8ydiXU8rLTfBo8AtaNVUjLUFgDXd1vE_leiLYPO6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I was there on a Monday night, and it was not busy at all. The server was super nice but really slow. It took a long time to get our drinks and put a food order in. The food was okay. The chicken sandwich was over deep fried, it was a bit dry. The place itself had a cool vibe and it was playing football.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This pub is outside the residential area but is conveniently located near highway with plenty of parking spots.  Our server was very pleasant and nice.  She makes your experience better.  Food are quite alright, very reasonably priced too even to consider this inflation era.  Taco Tuesday was neat and tasty and we also tried their golden Brussels sprouts which were also pretty good.  There are many kinds of wings to choose from, and special deal on Wednesday.  This now is one of our go to pubs as children are also allowed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN87lH3GXT1p4K4IxHWDfUQl7qY9BczmGifIZII&fid=0x0:0x463038a64e1c3b06"],"When":"2023-6-21"},{"Name":"Kelvin Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUK7ZMdBlhvlFPiSySdxIgCJsO71IZXbDpx391sCwTkzkHaCpIv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10 out of 10.  Went there without any expectation and it was better than many popular restaurants.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf6lbWLIzN9KUR-RyKssqq9_fs3Wk7_g9MJxZK&fid=0x0:0x463038a64e1c3b06"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Jordan Hsieh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbyRrh7UlWzOsyT41qQtxTb1m2bLd_4-Pusobxgdazm1EeUfU04g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to checkout Golden Parrots with a buddy during their happy hour to catch the basketball game and we had a fun time. Guinness tastes great as well as their Fat Tug IPA which didn't taste that bitter so I loved it.

We got their deep fried pickles which came with a bit of fries. They were so good so we decided to get the poutine as well.

The owners came around to check on everybody and they were super friendly. We had a chat with them and they are absolutely awesome people.

Would definitely come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxUYzcPv1Z4heht31dXjvvjvPPInzWeM1C03GF&fid=0x0:0x463038a64e1c3b06"],"When":"2023-5-17"},{"Name":"Sabrina Dean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsuNoq0NjIZsw7Q0s08xv-ogcv0ajmV0Oo0HaZ5E_raW8Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here a few times and always enjoyed the food. They allow children in the "restaurant" part of the pub, which we appreciate since we bring our 6 yr old. Tonight, we had exceptional service by Iona - friendly and fast. There was all day HH drinks (Thurs) and a $18.50 steak special that my child devoured. We also ordered the chicken pesto penne which was tasty. Only downside was the cigarette smoke that comes in, every time the doors open.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJErGKqO7BCzy2XzklkyTf07vqCBU_uYCQXwxZNuIKr42BWbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Consistent food with lots of menu items, daily food and drink specials and friendly staff. Hit and miss on timely service. Sometimes really quick and attentive and sometimes not but not really tied to business. Noticed a fair amount of take out on this weeknight dinner hour which maybe made the kitchen slow.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fred Rivers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgSCi2q2xQIo8etBfYKiAM7XcBCTUa-DDDdV9iPxCRjF4O86trZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were greeted quickly and friendly.  Found a seat and the server had a menu for us right away. Took our drink order and was quick to return with our frosty beverages and took our food order. Chicken burger was tasty and wings were moist. Servers were all attentive and friendly.  Would highly recommend this place and will definitely be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Doug P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLx6YpxAAaIZ7Cj9PSMphfRQfkkw46YLaNdEeYIQOo495lpxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Unfortunately we must have visited on an off day. We used to come here quite regularly about 30 years ago. At that time the food was always good. This time the fries were delicious, but both our entrees were sub standard. The prime rib sandwich was bland. The meat was overcooked. The cod was soggy.
Service was fine. We were greeted immediately at the entrance. There is renovations in the dining area, but that didn't affect the pub section. Multiple TV's had a ballgame on and others had CBC French news??? Very entertaining üôÑ
The prime rib sandwich order was related to their Saturday prime rib special, starting at 4pm. I was hoping to revisited soon, but that won't be happening now.
Other diners seemed to be enjoying themselves.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Kevan Bonn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvNnHmBNFG_G3ySw9mP3BZPzSJjPIurU1Hy79afN_SrMR1Zg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered online a Cajun chicken sandwich with no Cajun, upgrade the side to yam fries, tofu lettuce wraps and an eggnog cheese cake for dessert. I got a notification that the food was ready for pick up 40 minutes later, my boyfriend went inside to pick up the food but was told it wasn‚Äôt ready yet‚Ä¶ when he finally got home with our much excited take out date night dinner, we started to dig in. The first couple of bites were yummy, nothing out of the ordinary, but it didn‚Äôt take long before my boyfriend noticed that his chicken was not fully cooked through and still very pink. He refused to eat anymore and then we had to make dinner, which negated us buying take out and waiting for it. We wanted to treat ourselves to dinner that we did not have to make or clean up after. Over all we were very disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_E3fTpJJdLK0kMeulnj-eqylf46yXWbc1CBWM&fid=0x0:0x5a740195b1b5f06d"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Mur L'Amour Beauty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLWRTv6Ucl2AQriy5TjtYYVHeEv9CMDUYjKrDpm4hOiOHfpNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was pleasantly surprised by the carpaccio at your cafe Very fresh and thinly sliced pieces, perfectly balanced with sauce and spices. The presentation was also impressive everything looked very appetizing. I‚Äôll definitely be back for this dish again! Gluten free, vegan and vegetarian options available. The crispy tofu was so delicious.

5 stars for the food & service. Our team will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyRhebp-rXmnYbmBl2L3bBgxAdFwumqf3-XiKh&fid=0x0:0x5a740195b1b5f06d"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Naz Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRq8l2FAHrB_BVK6IQu7kkBhuqAvVszlJ_x3nATjhjB42KboI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first server was great, super sweet and kind.  She made sure to make us feel comfortable and helped us decide what to order.  After her shift ended, the new server introduced herself and took over in the same friendly and helpful manner.  The best part was, the manager came over to check on us and was an absolute delight!  She chatted with us for a bit and made us feel so welcome and appreciated. Overall, my best experience at CC which is almost always wonderful.  Kudos to management for hiring great staff and training so well.  I felt almost like I was at a small, family owned restaurant!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"dawn lopez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVN4Fd7SxUXBbHiu42-5cl9bOQZMv8_jHLVnj32nQgkACFpiRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went mid day on a Monday

I chose steak while my husband got the Creole chicken, both were great, but my husband thought the asparagus was a bit overcooked. There were only 2 options for dessert so we ordered both, cream cheese and chocolate bar, well, we didn't like either of them. In general, the quality met the expectation at the pricing. The kids at another table were too noisy but well, what can they do about it? I wish the light was brighter, it was too dark in the restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2pjoMgbvtOo7ShfHUVzqISv7Mmrfu3zzrkBJf&fid=0x0:0x5a740195b1b5f06d"],"When":"2024-1-23"}]

[{"Name":"Sinyo ganteng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK6DhObLW3StVcJ_e9Ph42mdmAq5cSoW-d536hao-jSu7WAn8I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"small cafe in the office and industrial area. try their soup, corn chowder, overly taste, too creamy. price is decent, for $5+. seems like a family owned restaurant. pretty clean, not bad for a quick lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiQo4DqXLR9V04yjZDEQzIs-Ff2PVIpJ7mvO_u&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Patrick Wilkinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYakHcvOGD9AcOA-_R-KQPKBzO69i7w3xLbLsb1CP3UOPDU9LogQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cozy cafe has the best food in the whole area. At prices lower than you would expect for the quality! I absolutely love Kim‚Äôs cafe and stop in whenever I can. Sandwiches, lunch specials, burgers.. you name it. Extremely friendly staff, fast service.

Seriously this place is the definition of hidden gem. Incredible, fresh amazing food. I love it!

10/10.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6wGK7i3z5zi2jm9yssKB-dMnQry9x8AnulkHo&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Daehyun Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIHxxz0drxXNhxABHkARE53of9eUDqUYMpgMl7k7eCkK24jniG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited this restaurant 2 times in a month.
We had Hawaiian burger combo(burger, fries, coffee), bacon cheese burger, everything omelette.
Their burger bun was so perfect. It wasn't greesy, wasn't over cooked dry. And also the meat was perfectly cooked with very juicy and fresh tomato and lettuce.
The everything omelette was another perpect food. The vegetables( bell peppers) were grilled so that you can taste the fire with own flavours. The egg was perfect medium firmess. I said to my wife that the chef must have worked in a 5 star hotel before.
I will visit here soon again.
But you clean up after yourself. But also you are asked tip them. The tip is totally up to you. I was very happy with the food so i tipped them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_tIQvAXNYbojJ6nM_n35MYU2n4-dpaAlQcDCJ&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Ronald Neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3-UYUNJrMpFog9fj3pIFLK5tmoK0-LgL_hzRpH2SFmt6tHLqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mainly come here for their chicken curry katsu special on Tuesday. Great flavor and I usually order a bit extra sauce. Value is nice and service is quick.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcamyhkXmfRnmHFdRfV9lg3R51sPMe9vznZKP7&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2023-10-18"},{"Name":"Kay Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmxcCu0a7Tl2EIwVjP2qrHq3Yql4NE9ewxjMr7ovKkKB3Rew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very bad experience here.  No one could even say hello or acknowledge we were there .  Took forever to order.  Dirty tables. No thank yous or anything.  Ok if you like mediocre food from a dirty facility with no customer service.  Avoid this, there has to be something better in the area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marta Szmilko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5cxLIqYW9CEaeY8Pk-Tk56SV38TRlVi8sTLyufepImTtZw98=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The hamburger is very tasty, the fries are divine. The staff is fast and friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPghJKRjiO6K2T7y9oPUjjwK9lyf2fz1jk3PCUQ&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2023-3-8"},{"Name":"Grace Xu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAmY3gC_74HFyTtrGM9YMgQR3nvqGbAUqTOig9dL6vWfDc5Mfy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little dinner style restaurant serves breakfast and lunch, Korean fusion food, Western comfort food like chicken soup, hamburgers, etc.

I only come here for lunch because it‚Äôs close to work, and I like it here, friendly service, tasty food, nice and clean restaurant, no complaints!

They have also recently upgraded their menu and up their game in the social media network, yes they have an instagram account now! You can follow them and see what‚Äôs new on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3FolAgK4QCMQSWbFotC-N17ICNKu3mjix_mfj&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2019-11-28"},{"Name":"Kevin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLL8WdmmeXgGd14-pwts9OY5wJqKS1a-qMe0A4PK7ODpCo5wH4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It‚Äôs rare to come across a non-chain food place that sells sandwiches and wraps. I was pleasantly surprised by how great everything tasted. The quality of the food served here is easy to tell based on the freshness of the ingredients, and it‚Äôs quite clear that they put in the effort to make sure that everything is fresh and delicious. Their bread is what I think makes their sandwiches taste so great (I‚Äôm a sourdough fan myself). It‚Äôs not your typical grocery-store bought bread, and it plays a huge role in the flavor factor.
I was inclined to get the soup since a lot of the other customers at the time were getting them, and I can see why. It tastes homemade and fresh, which makes me consider trying all their soups.
They also serve daily specials like chicken teriyaki with rice which I also enjoyed. The portion was generous for the price, and the chicken was crispy which made it much more enjoyable than the typical soft/mushy chicken teriyaki from other places.
This caf√© is in a secluded area and it‚Äôs one of the healthier available options for breakfast/lunch. It‚Äôs also nice to see how the staffs here know their regulars‚Äô names and usual orders. This to me means that they are tasty enough to come back! I would recommend this place to anyone who is passing by and need a quick bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwCsSIUWY4XzdvVSlTnZEnJ0Ubabs22REdsSGB&fid=0x0:0x2a2857896adc1231"],"When":"2019-2-4"}]

I ordered via skip the dishes and the packaging and overall quality was exceptional. To start they sent two bags, one for the cold drink and one for the hot food, where they easily couldn‚Äôt packed it in 1, this kept everything at optimal temperature. My order was the new Kung Pao Chicken burger with the Cajun fries and an iced coffee. Everything tasted delicious down too the details of their usual good quality napkins. May sound insignificant but I hate when places use cheap napkins that break apart when you wipe your mouth with them. Overall the food tasted great even though the Kung Pao burger was a bit too salty to my taste but that‚Äôs just my palette. No complaints overall and for salt lovers I think it was great. Great experience and 5 stars for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaP-ZGL9izkICNG5pZulXTcLjofpcVHZofepOC&fid=0x0:0x10aeeac89f964abd"],"When":"2021-5-18"},{"Name":"B A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9IKjY9jl-kq9zdB-dcoMbL_HP572D_A4DEYF6-9WM7slplX0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Avoid this location. No I will not reach out to you.  Figure it out.  Pretty simple.  This location also changed their cut of their sweet potatoe fries.  Now they try and get away by charging the same price for skinny ass fries. Chicken burger use to have fresh leafy greens and not they serve shredded lettuce slop.   Not sure if it is a franchise thing or not.  This location is going down the crapper.  Terrible service and food is always over cooked and dried out.  Will no longer be going here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The store to my eye wasn't to standard. Few parking spots in front were so dirty with food and bags.
Prices were ok but I think they have lots to improve.
As a Canadian restuarant they should have more pride and attention to their operation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFi02TVOGnLk_p7OfU7-rOjBFrpnSiAh-6lZii&fid=0x0:0x10aeeac89f964abd"],"When":"2020-12-20"},{"Name":"Susan Flow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9JHoi5w1AvN5k_T8qBCpxA7cd1F7_Ub8b-9iN5llghf4f8A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ladies working there are  very pleasant.
