[{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Average Vietnamese beef noodles.

We ordered their special beef noodles, signature short rib soup noodles, deep fried shrimp spring rolls and Vietnamese coffees.

The noodles are good but the taste is just like any average Vietnamese restaurants.

The seats are small and not very comfortable.
It's also not easy to find parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPe5wuB2rkUOyZJne_65HKkXt1YDZUhQVmEqcyy&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Aleah Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOfmiP6ZZLzOHDPNcx4PgZrUTDT2IUnYpu9vyaqTf1SFX-yNf6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never disappoints. I'm hesitant about trying new places but I work close by and was craving pho one day so I ordered from here. Since that day I have eaten here multiple times and get pickup for lunch at least 1-2 times per month (possibly more). Great broth flavor and hits the spot every time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray Dubs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWv4pQtKu2wy66jann-Dj8Exe3FIdSioz5JunQZJxz8XSK1GHcjzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Review from guy eating his way through the Vietnamese restaurants in the Lower Mainland.

This restaurant is in my neighbourhood and it‚Äôs my first time eating here and I‚Äôm glad I took a trip to Pho Holiday. It doesn‚Äôt look like much from the outside or inside but that‚Äôs not usually what you‚Äôre looking for anyways at a pho joint.

They‚Äôve got a lot of menu options and some special types of pho. After some debating I settled on the Spicy Peanut Pho. This was really enjoyable to eat as the broth was very flavourful with just enough hints of peanut but not overly spicy (at least to my standards - I eat spicy). The assortment and cuts of beef were great as you get rare slices of beef, brisket and some fatty flank(?) pieces as well. This will be on my ‚Äúeat again‚Äù list.

Other special bowls are the beef rib pho and the smoky beef pho which I will have to come and try on my next Pho Holiday.

Rays Tips:
There‚Äôs a few parking spots in front of restaurant.
Parking is available in the back but you‚Äôll have to walk around to the front.
Credit card is accepted here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMd-1VTsEF15quKBk1eyMZRymQdZ900qgP2LLRa&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2023-8-28"},{"Name":"Alexi Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtyDIWOs-lCvlSbaSncyGpUjQXa0VAI5wpYfXSxXEeur1bqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food here is very low quality.  Our noodles were served cold.  No fresh herbs and very little flavour.  Some of the worst Vietnamese food we have ever had.  The service was very poor.  They didn't check on us once nor did they offer to refill our tea.  Servers were on their phones the whole time we were there, and never smiled once.  The atmosphere is awful; the seating looks like it was repurposed from a tear-down.  Muzak was playing...just dull and lame.  The only time the servers smiled was when we paid, obviously looking for a nice tip.  I will never go here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joe B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDpi_rGpZjUyMPy1allklXwcA7eocPaTgiwR-3r8sEtq5q0A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After enjoying the Rare Beef Pho and famous Spicy Creamy Peanut Pho here for years, I recently tried the Spicy Coconut Curry Pho with rare beef and I absolutely love it! They told me it's been on the menu for a while so I'm surprised I never tried it before. My only regret is that I didn't take a picture of it before I polished off the bowl. I'll definitely do that next time! Pho Holiday has always been my go-to place in Austin Heights for great food and friendly prompt service everytime. :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVFhY732bD9lfdS5xRbM8v--TtM-9arBdJ7DQT&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"chau tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdcSjef95Ja-t2NY1EpbZAYMMQl0yANsuKnHISuTj9NgmlLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yummy food, cozy place! Curry Veggie noodle soup is recommended üòã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNa8032K33WTDm7QlKCCRT3AG61uMsQ2QOsUBhu&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Jenni Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfoMGgCjxjNl5-oajeOMf3off2y6SlHFRXa9nWrixIvJpM9ho=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Picked up a vermicelli bowl with grilled chicken and spring rolls and the meat was very dry and bland. The staff wasn't very friendly either. Seems like they had a little bit of attitude when I asked for a small container of chilli oil. Overall, just very underwhelming compared to other Vietnamese restaurants.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alana Cotton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0BjBagguJl5UqSuBOUicH5WMmdzZe1BphC3SP1FpVGMEXTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everytime I've come here, I get exactly what I came for. The staff is super friendly and the food is very tasty and consistent. The fried spring rolls are one of my favorites and I cant find any other place that matches it. I come back here again and again :)","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Mina K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqkiz0bzpa-16Pndf1kiK6M5DS6vr61upv2ilmD1PLQdXAb-I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good chicken, crispy and juicy. I ordered 3 flavours. The yangyeom and soy garlic are cover in sauce, it‚Äôs so tasty. The creamy onion comes with a small sauce on the side, just wish it has more sauce for that amount of chicken. It‚Äôs the best chicken in town so far.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC3bXMUb8Wgdoo4_FkMUAtaamWzdnoEgX6IE85&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX98PrUHxEgks1p_UHXz6OQ_Vovq-hbr6NA6018tymH019sjnz4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to finally try this place out. I tried the "Big Bang" (sweet and sour chicken with pineapple) their photos and description are a bit misleading. This dish is mildly spicy even though it says "sweet" on the menu, and they use smaller pieces of pineapple instead of the bigger pieces they have in their photos, it still tasted good but I didn't expect for it to be a little spicy. So, I would ask for extra pineapple in the future myself. I would go back to try more of their menu. I wish there was a smaller option for the Big Bang or a combo for one option. Good chicken here","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHN632jLVNxQQVGLcrL1nnVcwd10rxTsA_P2ur&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food, made fresh to order. Clerk gave a bottle of water on the house on a hot day too. Very charming and funny man.

Cant wait to come back to try new flavours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMI6ShFxLapYajTPoq2MC_sArGIkrzCbzLmve4a&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Jag Dhillon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtpdplh3A6xm-KZ7Hgdk0TvEmNi0MAclqn7NsyIPBJuuFEonw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best fried chicken I have ever had. Nice white tender meat, crispy and non- greasy on the outside. There‚Äôs no drenched oil taste or smell. Super tasty seasoning and sauce flavours. I highly recommend and will be back. I wish there were more locations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kaveesh Kukreja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyGM5Wur1OIcPaIKHk8y8hADl72LlmzqOApRwMvp0cKEQAxid2PA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our Boys at Hens Up Chicken serving up some Delicious Korean Fried Chicken without so much as an Instagram page even.
Honestly, those pieces were FIRE. The sauces could have been better but whatever they lost on the sauce they made up for on the crispiness and tenderness of the chicken.
We ordered the Trips Threat for $32 in which we got the Spicy Yangneom (Not Spicy at all), The Honey Garlic (Your Basic Honey Garlic) and the Pepper ( My favourite)

I also got a Mexi Ranch sauce on the side to dip which was like a mixture of Korean Sauce with Sriracha so added a bit of spice to the mix and it came with coleslaw and what I can only describe as Coleslaw Sauce.
Extra $2 for Pickles if u a radish is a must have guy otherwise I'd skip it.

Clean Place, Quick Service and Good food. If I'm in the area I'd re visit for sure!!

Rating - 8.1","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXTQwYZvk6mT8chLPPpC85KpFRL3-ws8kYVK9F&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Half & Half Chicken (Honey Garlic & Cheesling): I liked the honey garlic, and would recommend having either soy garlic or honey garlic for your chicken. They featured two new sauces for me to try - one is soy-wasabi sauce and one is like a sweet white garlic sauce. I loved it! Thank you Chicken Hens up!

Upon my third visit, I ordered rice and soy garlic chicken. The server was very kind and gave me a side of coleslaw too. I appreciate them!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRxTpMaPrF8s8qnSdSI3J873ZVw9YhgET7sDGN&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-4-14"},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing chicken, along with its sister branch in the coquitlam center.

Fried perfectly, and it does deliver the flavour!

The owner is super friendly and goes above and beyond. He recommended the onion sauce to go with the original chicken, gave me a small portion of sample and it was perfect.

I've already ordered twice from here and I'm definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1K094qyuSjiOqQpK8FYP3M8v-Wi3DZDWMVsfT&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Called to ask whether it was open Boxing Day and luckily it was open. I ordered three whole soy garlic fried chicken and the snow cheese fries. All the food was delicious; however, I wished the soy garlic chicken wasn‚Äôt spicy. I also hoped that there was air holes to keep the chicken crispy during transit back if there is take-out involved. Prices are good for the portion size. It is located in a plaza with parking spaces. Negative was I stood waiting for a while for an employee to check up on me at the counter when I first entered the store.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-S3RgkD6lOgogRVV5ZsDeUSvena19R34XWog2&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-1-8"}]

[{"Name":"Cheryl A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocId3JTMrjtqtdmj_0XOBMchbLGhcrTAO0uBPM1jzlHcNAjL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved my potato Marsala Dosa. The coconut chutney was super delicious. It came with a soup ( spicy) very generous portions . The servers were very friendly & kind . Reasonable prices for what you get . Fresh and not much of a wait .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQcIzZnZe-I0wMCOjUfijOQEx2ad0NLGuE3ig&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"PC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnLR6JbppM6GM5nol1xpc9XuPLJD0bzW-RWDiP6CpTO8u6ksE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Desi Dosa Madras is such a great find!  I ordered the lamb shank curry and the spinach chicken dosa, and both were incredible.  The lamb was super tender and juicy, and the curry it came with was full of flavor.  The spinach chicken dosa was so fresh and tasty‚Äîit hit the spot perfectly.

The portions were huge, which is always a bonus, and everything tasted fresh and homemade.  The owner and staff were really friendly too, which made the whole experience even better.

If you‚Äôre looking for delicious food, big portions, and great service, definitely check this place out.  Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such friendly service :)
My first Dosa experience!!
Got a Lamb Dosa, infused with so many flavors, and boy was it spicy but I enjoyed every bite! Also, it was incredibly filling.
Definitely planning to try other dishes","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDXHxroDT1KqlQCFEHsYQgPbuYbcZHrChRbnRe&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2023-2-9"},{"Name":"Dora Eng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhBtDPoDG5jAGseu0DWPAqVq_MQfyz59Il4JHwDJMLbh2lmpSv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I recently visited Desi Dosa at the Henderson food court, and I‚Äôm so impressed with their customer service! My husband ordered a plain dosa for our son, but I forgot to mention that he doesn‚Äôt like cilantro. When we went back, hoping the dosa hadn‚Äôt been made yet, we asked if they could leave out the cilantro. Even though it was already cooking with cilantro, the chef went above and beyond by carefully removing most of it to accommodate our request. Such a thoughtful gesture! This kind of service, paired with their delicious food, makes them truly stand out. Highly recommend!"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"GRoo3Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnyXegPToN37SksvZIxBb7lUyVf07LGjT7LQNGsVWronjLoc58Jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered a lamb Dosa,  First time trying it and it was very delicious.  The staff were very kind and attentive on top of that the kitchen was is probably the cleanest of the food court, something to be very proud of in this restaurant business! Will come back to try other items on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-wVJO1_3TV0Tv3jtEGK81kp3EofARuLrvSV4r&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2024-2-29"},{"Name":"Delwin Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIyLIbxl3BJt2gOJQPp7WrSxwN1pDT08k_u0WCg3VLt8LjxjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I usually hit up this food court for something else, but I‚Äôve always been curious about this stall since I‚Äôm a big fan of dosai.

Super glad I finally gave it a try today. Ordered the onion potato dosa and was kinda worried it wouldn‚Äôt fill me up since I usually need a good-sized portion. Happy to report that the portion was spot on, and they didn‚Äôt skimp on the onion and potato, which really made the dish. I‚Äôm hoping they keep the portions and fillings generous even as they get more popular, ‚Äòcause it‚Äôs part of what made it so good.

The chutneys they served‚Äî one coconut and the other tomato ginger‚Äîwere both killer, and I didn‚Äôt leave a drop. Plus, it came with this sambar lentil and veggie soup on the side that was the perfect cap to the meal.

They even threw in 2 napkins, which I really appreciated since I ended up using both! Definitely coming back and telling my friends about this place üíØ.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMe-LFG7h3bXAKEr9xgvfWsb79gIMwLvNn9CWHj&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"CHHAVI VERMA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdw4FcCl6_OEFKvnlOn3MBE1LOnnJfyRu1VkXzfRzzlZXglg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden Gem - Dosa place in Coquitlam!!
Hands down the best dosa I had in Vancouver. Amazing service and greetings at the counter.
Delicious food & a must try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUvWApnNPy4CpzSLB1S_QpSssRjMbElbB_oP4a&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Prabhat S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJU26Mv7wrF_kHRTI1pZUcReR7O4NpknuGlRvECZ5U9FquW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is the first visit I had. I would say this is a good place to have a biryani experience for those who like a different flavor. They serve Papad and boiled egg which is an exceptional service. Neat and clean, quick service, the portion was just enough for 2. spice level, salt level are good !, OIL is not good quality, need to improve the oil type and reduce the quantity of oil being used for such small portions. price is higher, it's not a reasonable price I would guess 13 $ is reasonable rate for that. For occasional dinners the price and place shouldn't be hitch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN06dLvVO7tpIP2nl3Kl5ihXNOl_FGjLqHnKcc&fid=0x0:0xa294bdbddd105db6"],"When":"2023-5-10"}]

title: The Big Flat Pancake Co.

[{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very popular local breakfast and brunch spot. Be ready for a wait, but it's worth it if you're looking for generous portions and sweet rewards.

We ordered a few dishes to try:

Apples and Cinnamon were exactly that. Sweet and delicious with just enough tartness.

The Mexicasa Omelet was savoury and spicy. Wonderfully satisfying, and a huge portion.

We had a hard time deciding between The King Kong and Bowser. But the toasted coconut won, and we went with Bowser. Believe it or not, it wasn't too sweet. The flavour and texture of the pancake helped to balance the dish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtawtl5BET-xx7jUpEtFONFxkBUI9Bfsvlqihi&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Juan Jos√© Salaya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1Ln__1lVc-JSwJxu3Sudj7VGGpDHTTaI6ATzhk7kkdUk_WRTN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Amazing service from Shauna, fast en friendly.
I had the chocolate waffle, insane! And huge portions.
But the savory pancake not the best, hipster hash. The pancake was good but the side of hash and vegetables were not very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmaviqW2sU_R_MfMRdvFHaU01XhNLfVwSVCcOH&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Mar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWTdC3Cu0qquRYQVKhOdWcOmJsma73tOEyPAbRghfK5B9Xyfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quiet and cozy place on weekdays. My favorite dish of all time is Veggie I Love You, which comes with a pancake. The veggies are always fresh and neatly sliced. The only drawback is the high price","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoiGISJgSmJLSHz_XDKv3UeFGIR2oQ23GqinXJ&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-10-9"},{"Name":"Jeff Downer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl3HQ-1C4N-_a7ykvhIi5aM883AB-cDQVYb1xeenCY7zekayvZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had high hopes for this place. The hash just didn‚Äôt deliver. Pretty average Sysco quality potato hash with premade tasting hollandaise that resembled cheese. One slice and a half of avocado : ( I just wish it tasted more homemade and less store-bought. The pancake was good! Sweet and caramelized. Not worth the price of the dish (Hipster Hash)
My partner‚Äôs chocolate banana waffles were a hit though. Very good and nice portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtalSDrAz-3j5GtPKct2PF6onzeKeFu4j88AIk&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"danakhatib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkw_MS-bFFQL-DqU_kCatDuVYGKImx-f2Z5AnYQHBCy9-uZ6_t=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Service was fantastic! They split our foods onto seperate plates (without us asking) because we wanted to share some dishes, which was very kind! Food was great, we got the chocolate waffle, which was delicious and the smoked salmon benny. I‚Äôve had better hollandaise sauce but overall everything was awesome!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcXsNe5b-w07YgnnqAfyFuObJiLP2t5VicwA1B&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Kiah Rose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTVXBfiLNTJ8gFd9zcQjhLGEsYxsifqJuzzyh3SEwJwRrMplme=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you‚Äôre looking for incredible food and an amazing atmosphere, The Big Flat Pancake is the place to be! The quality of the food is absolutely top-notch ‚Äî everything is fresh, flavorful, and made with care. The pancakes are delicious, and the portions are generous!

What really sets this place apart, though, is the staff. They‚Äôre full of positive energy and always make you feel like part of the family. We shared lots of laughs, and their warm hospitality truly gave us a fantastic start to our Saturday!

I love supporting local, family-owned businesses, and The Big Flat Pancake is exactly the kind of place that deserves your attention. I highly recommend giving it a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMy6zOwu4HHfJ_gTbG6krgQtrhQd5D-xVfx0wsj&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Davina Johnsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOWfxjdUo4u1LYvAiA8xMOSJlaFjaSMXKmyFbVlITAYWYoqbeaXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our second day in a row here because it was sooo delicious yesterday. I liked our server from yesterday better (purple haired girl- I think her name was Tasha?) she was great. The food here is out of this world. It‚Äôs a cozy little hipster place, great music. Clean washrooms. If you show up and there is a line up, please stay, because I promise it‚Äôs worth the wait!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk5YdsWzVNzwwA_kkRWs6GwvBXaSg7LV_7oKIg&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2023-10-21"},{"Name":"Adam M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBezQ5u52QUPfNCS-XISW7oETfNlf5RvdoikJTFUzauPV7HEINiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big Flat Pancake has been one of our favorite restaurants since the day they opened. Whether with my family or just the two of us, we‚Äôve enjoyed countless breakfasts here, including many Mother‚Äôs Day and Father‚Äôs Day celebrations. The restaurant's modern design and simplicity create an upscale breakfast experience, even though it maintains a casual and welcoming vibe.

Seating is limited, and I still recall waiting outside with social distancing protocols in place during the early post-COVID days. Last week, we visited again, and as always, I ordered my favorite: chicken waffles with whipped cream and strawberry topping on the side. My wife, on the other hand, loves trying something different every time we visit. The food arrived quickly, and as usual, it was very tasty.

However, (our visit on Nov 30th)  I do want to share one piece of feedback from this visit. My wife and I were enjoying our coffee after finishing our meal when the server brought the check‚Äîcompletely understandable, especially when tables need to turn over for waiting guests. But this time, there were four empty tables, and no one was waiting. Moments later, while we were still sipping our coffee, the server returned with the cordless payment unit and stood by our table. We were both caught off guard, thinking, ‚ÄúWhat‚Ä¶?‚Äù We paid because the payment unit was already there, and the server was waiting, but the interaction felt rushed.

Having owned a restaurant in downtown Vancouver, I understand the need to turn tables efficiently. That said, there‚Äôs an unspoken etiquette between servers and guests, and this instance felt a bit abrupt‚Äîparticularly since the restaurant wasn‚Äôt busy.  It‚Äôs a small issue, and I‚Äôm sure it wasn‚Äôt intentional, but I wanted to share this experience in the hopes it‚Äôs not repeated for other guests.

Of course, we will continue visiting Big Flat Pancake because we love the food, atmosphere, and overall experience. This is just some constructive feedback for management or ownership to consider.

Thank you, and see you again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3DgZTp8jMRgeo2EOBKceMPW-1SSt0lYSYOwaO&fid=0x0:0xaaebff47a4a99ef2"],"When":"2024-12-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"N Bala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIn-ixFNj17bJSobYLeT7X0RAI7NKEGNiwAY1UO4Utugg8qdljqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome place! Limited hours of superb breakfast everyday - 9:30 am to 11:00 am - 7 days a week. Limited menu but very healthy and hearty. The basic breakfast is quite enough and comes with one portion of scrambled eggs, cube-diced hash browns, with either 2 pieces of sausage or few ribbons of bacon for just $3.79. Compare this to outside one for a minimum of $15 at the current inflation. Totally subsidized by IKEA for the customers. A great bottomless coffee comes at $1.50. There are few more items during the breakfast time - vegetarian medallion $1.50, garlic bread slice $0.99, samosa $0.99, vegetarian soup $4.39. Large Cinnamon bun $1.50. Muffin $1.50. My bill came to $9.72 for 2 persons. For other after-breakfast items, please check their menu with their transparent prices. Ample parking space. Excellent view! Fantastic bright and clean ambiance. Simply a heaven!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXlHRpIbGEQcxCQ39xskWaWmh2Mo9KnnRQLh0b&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our group had their Swedish Meatballs Meal, Plant Balls Meal and the Vegan Chocolate Torte. The meals are nothing fancy for $8.99 and $7.99, but as diners who visit IKEA once a year, the food has a nostalgic and comforting feel. The mashed potatoes were creamy, and the different balls had good flavour. I was a big fan of their vegan chocolate torte, which was rich and decadent without the use of eggs and gluten! I'd definitely order this again, and appreciate the vegan dessert option! Water is self-serve by the other beverages and is complimentary.

We unknowingly went on Swe-dish Thursdays, so it was packed for the lunch hour with many families in line for food. There was a bit of a wait, but the line moves quickly (finding seating is another question, but we were fortunate to find a table soon after paying). I was looking forward to having their Veggie Balls, but had to settle for the Plant Balls as they weren't serving the Veggie Balls on their menu.

The only minor issue we had was when we were paying full price (because we weren't IKEA Family Members). We were happy to pay full price because we were unaware of the Thursday special and were not signed up for membership, but the cashier had insisted we keep the receipt as they said we'd be able to get a partial refund on that food bill if we became IKEA Family Members at a later date. While we were eating, we signed up for membership, but another staffer in the restaurant area said we could only use it for future meal savings and couldn't get the refund. It wasn't a big issue for us, but we were left questioning why the cashier was insistent about a refund as we hadn't asked for one in the first place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKuqoOjwtD_cF8WJfhhDxkulxgeMyJ_DngE1Xd&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"eddy wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Fjpj3y8teHQ4LqbC4PHR8whbU4-XOrTXEwklI9bGRqZLRD20=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friday Friday Friday only this Black Friday! Haha! I was in the area with family and we overheard that there was a special pricing on their breakfast.

99 cents for breakfast. That‚Äôs right! Definitely brings back nostalgic times. How can you go wrong with breakfast. Normal price is $3.79 but you‚Äôre getting your grub on for 99 cents. It comes with scrambled eggs, chopped fried potatoes, your choice of bacon or sausages.
You have to scan your ikea family membership for a free cup of coffee or tea.

It‚Äôs not a glamorous meal don‚Äôt be expecting something fancy but where else can you get a traditional breakfast in your tummy for 99 cents? Perfect for all you young bloods that are hung over LOL üòÇ. Cheers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNERpfUDm3RduHXYePa14HNCdN3zgNkRpBdXflC&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Fox hmp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQDamDUP5o_LpyAHYzMLSTM2wh8oeibxwZqA9_fJNfLvrII5o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very weak management and organization for customer service! After waiting 30 minutes in the line, we found out that half of the menu is sold out or they dont want to make the fresh one! The line organizer stuff was on the right sode of the salon and the employees were trying to move hundreds of people to the other side! But the food still tastes good and fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO04pmEIy6LsLnKRnrJj8xzvQ4M5g8syAr0jzOL&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Tried the haddock and chips and it was extremely mediocre and not the best tasting. The fries were good standard fries but the actual fried fish was super dry, and as seen in the pictures, even had burnt crust that was very hard and abrasive to the mouth. The quality was poor.

The NY cheesecake was barely edible and didn‚Äôt taste like real cheesecake at all. It was quite acidic and tasted very processed and not freshly made and had a very preservative heavy taste. Would not recommend the cheesecake.

The wait is insane and they appear extremely understaffed as there was one person serving food in each of the two food lines and one cashier for a giant crowd of people. The workers seem to be doing their best and appear overworked for what they have to do and getting your food is a bit of a chaotic process.

Thankfully there is a lot of seating and the self serve drinks are nice but when we went lots of the syrups for the drinks ran out and weren‚Äôt working and many of the drinks were watered down.

The IKEA food box outside is way better if you want food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHu0GnBDezHfCHc_KDB0jv3jW_IuYzxKY62JXs&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlresWC5ihFwmlqPDXUUvDy7NYECPjcTq6PKBfdWyBeF2JHw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The epidemic of mis-advertising has reached to IKEA too.
They show you the picture of their traditional breakfast in a relatively proper portion, but they give you close to half of the amount. I guess they want to make you buy two of them to get a decent portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUcPZCwt8yvpqf3kWazzlcJ9C4F4sZuzLybu7y&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It‚Äôs cafeteria food, and it‚Äôs great for what it is. Cheap and cheerful. Lots of seating available on the Friday afternoon I visited. I appreciate the vegetarian options and I opted for the plant balls with mashed potatoes and peas. I can‚Äôt remember the name of the dessert but it was tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAf0J7Q0nNqGngCf_PXziXAdg4I8QU8TlEHW2Z&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Bala888","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwpXKXLnWVbmRWE49mxf-yYsdsA4jpYsnTuSzc7_Jf6iiW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time tried the food here, actually it was not bad with this kind of price tag.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdxX8oTSR1wNbJqcpwC1NZZd-27jNRyM_08M0&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-12-7"}]

Real crab rolls
Assorted tempura rolls
Chicken teriyaki with rice for kids","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5pBoUJjJAjwMpZT-brTBlVOHTGgCjq13QxMIb&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"bahar n","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmfGtscBDa09dk7b-7RvVKIZH6hneZ4y0b-VObedbjnl-MZvE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely fell in love with this sushi restaurant! The sushi tonight was incredible, and the staff were exceptionally friendly and welcoming.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfw_RBvIS5VtgBMxeCT4ydcAEtFK8Y1uv-rjcE&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Jack Pajak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7kRSq5QM1wGXm36_dbE9YR6CpcUs9VUAhu1SxvpJkrQ-nGO0N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The reviews are right, Kai Japanese Restaurant is some of the best sushi I've ever had. Super flavorfull, perfect portions and a great variety of choices. I would return to try more for sure. The service was great, restaurant had a great vibe to it. Highly recommend trying them out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgdwW24fDqJiAj279Q1v5WoTLNvDPRJXBFBbhK&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Dung Dang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAXjHAV2t4x36Ir5lWIrz-sX4qzKSQvReu75jDU63zwMhoO5PE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best sushi place in town üòã all the plates they make are beautiful and high quality. We always enjoy dinner here with our family, it's a great bonding time together at a nice restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUlKrtDkDNKVshWFLOAZ2kLfpEITBZtUQYTbYv&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-4-8"},{"Name":"Chi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcP2Hqb8y0uQXQVGiRb0Rhd8unHZXF5ccgIFUUDph7myO2Fj88=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food at this restaurant was delicious. However, the portion sizes were a bit on the smaller side, and I found myself still hungry afterward. It would be great if they included a bowl of rice on the side to make the meal more satisfying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORVR9mzSxQMc651YKUWETjp--R-S_F76ieESdO&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Patricia Sarroca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3gn9k0ww-YG-IL2ET6t-Te-Van1nsgwgpJXzLXGZEiwGGfW4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow what a gem! The sushi here is fresh and taste delicious. My partner and I got the lunch set b which came with a variety of different dishes that paired so well at an affordable price. It was fairly busy for lunch time so I was expecting service to be slower but I was completely wrong! The staff there know what they are doing and are very nice as well. Definitely going back and recommending this place to everyone!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bruce Luu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRaf1m45VYyCGlp50uH-2rHvYNM9RdGoAjp3PIAgLWyz7pPnyN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great flavorful food, the spicy chirashi sashimi bowl was MASSIVE btw. Blue fin was excellent fresh and rich in flavor. Fois Gras was also a very nice bold and tasteful option that was a rare treat to see. Resturant is rather busy and packed. Bur for good reason.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGSnA4lOBbl9_OITOUk-uDm3EmclsgwsnOvFrF&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update:
Came back to try more food. Quality was still very good!

So good! I came here on a Friday night around 7:40pm and there was no wait. We didn't have to wait long for our food to be served either. We ordered the Sashimi sample set and it was so fresh! This place has gomae with okra and tuna. The sauce was soo... good. More pricey than regular gomae with spinach but it was so much better! I enjoyed the Scallop roll and the special roll with Mango salsa on top. There was plenty of seating for small and large groups. It was clean, modern and had a fun vibe to it. I will definitely come back to try more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPEJ5JLS8UmtGSSi9dnvc3fmV8eMmEQLkIDCRE&fid=0x0:0xc045733293aaced8"],"When":"2023-7-30"}]

[{"Name":"Chris White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzRlBtbLn_MTw22MPSJNZY56aO7efn0TxSkabP8h45RyA7WQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is your quintessential and nostalgic mom and pop Chinese restaurant! I love these people, I walked in last night and it was empty because they were just closing up. The woman asked me if I had been working and I answered yes. She asked me if I was OK with takeout And then asked me what I wanted. I told her I wanted something custom black bean sauce, chow mein, and lots of vegetables as I sat down they were already cutting the vegetables. Such a nice people such great service and the food waswas fantastic. This is a gem,  a little hole in the wall restaurant with great food run by a wonderful and kind family. It‚Äôs not brand new, and that‚Äôs why it‚Äôs so excellent! It‚Äôs got character and love. ‚ù§Ô∏è
Plus the always make me custom veggie dishes!! I will continue to Support this awesome family restaurant ! üôè","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSqHLcNQw7FURU6GQgzSziJNsyTBan_mmRNMtj&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"D S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-PeUVNeu41R0OvIiWLD9zV4iyAZGwVHh3yeozO_e8MkArmt11tg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been eating here for years. Love the cozy cafe atmosphere. Don‚Äôt expect a fancy restaurant, just a simple small neighborhood cafe that serves up good food. The owner always remembers our name and what we love to eat. Makes you feel at home. Excellent prices. Good food. Family owned and operated. Highly recommended for take-out too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lam Swiss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKcrpABvkrMV2liUkHTaQXa4k5H2O8MO19I-XneWFRvSSbj_h-o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious Chinese Hong Kong food
The boss is friendly and nice
They offer delivery service to nearby places
Will come back often","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMshkQv7wsbETvaoVLrWav_SNIzhktOt20eGGZ5&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered a Malaysian fried rice and a chicken chow mein to take away. They only accept cash or debit cards. Place was not busy by the time we went (between 7pm and 8pm). They took only 12mins to prepare the order and portion sizes are good. It could serve 3 people easily. Both te dishes were good and I  would reccomned to eat it with some chili paste and a sauce to have a full flavor. In addiction to that we added some cucumber and onion salad to the dinner. Both dishes were okay for the dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_XGtomfPWw1JRWm-yyhp7eet446272UZPmOQo&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2023-6-16"},{"Name":"Sam Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSeVO8E3yvku7uop8tLoVEGM_NaXzKBAia20QDNEQRDvXqDThPZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Beef was a bit tough compared to the same dish served in other restaurants. The quantity and prices are better than most restaurants I have been to though. So it's a good deal!
There was only one waitress doubling for cashier too and probably is the chef's wife or daughter or is the owner.
Cash only or debit card. So bring enough with you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"L Mk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA11Vll-dqFbuF7cgumBdvAFntLV_6upoinWS5aQlM6PFl-MMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered $70 worth of food on Wednesday lunchtime.  A combination for one, egg foo young and wonton soup.

Took it back to my office (in the same plaza) and we ate some. Everything was ok, not particularly good but not particularly bad either.

We got quite busy and didn‚Äôt have time for more than a few bites each, the leftovers went straight into the fridge. I tell you this because the next day we were planning to have the rest for lunch but when we opened the container with the combination (broccoli, chicken chow mein and bbq pot fried rice) it smelled really bad. My coworker decided that was due to the garlic broccoli and ate anyway.  He got really sick to his stomach a few hours later.  I tried the egg foo young leftovers but immediately it tasted sour.

The majority of the entire order was leftover from Wednesday and had been thrown out Thursday.

Obviously they did not use fresh ingredients.

Usually leftover restaurant food is good at least a few days.

The woman working there was really friendly and sweet so I feel bad writing this but people need to know that the quality isn‚Äôt good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"james corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXORPNpjn99AmypwXC5L8gqaCK1buk43veXhtLSzHUK1ZItjmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the outside, it does not look like much and a place to walk past. This would be a mistake as the food is amazing for both takeout as well as dine in.
I've been doing takeout for years and finally ate in with a friend. Both of us enjoyed the meal and destroyed the house special chowmein. Beef and broccoli were some of the best I have ever had.
This is a great place to try and you won't regret","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phebe Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-Z1C27OOwYGEF9JwCtvaCRwmMrnupov1bImceSNjwHKI4NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I like this place, the lady working you can tell shes been in this industry for years. The food portions are pretty decent with the price, and tastewise its pretty good. I ordered the beef black pepper, the cod fish tofu(?) And chicken chow mein. Its enough to feed 4 people I would say.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food was decent, and the experience was enjoyable, but I‚Äôm unsure if it‚Äôs worth a return visit. The service also took a bit longer than anticipated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4ROFsnf93KhJeqBR3yZh_LOKAdmCTo8PR3XU0&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"james findlay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLt84_RgdMpRogmDX-lDIyrbCZ45814V53LA5wsiIYzjATJeQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This restaurant will never challenge for anything more than authentic clutter of trays of dirty dishes stacked by the bar and a very ordinary seating area that makes no illusions about being decent and nice. The ladies who are both front and back are not English speaking but we are okay with the idea that they don't cater to a Caucasion crowd that much (but they should try to). We have gone there 4 times now and the first two the food justified the sparse interior.  But the last visit about 9 months ago for take out dinner not so much. We live a 30 minute drive away so we expect a special feast when we go there and the prices are not cheap. They charge as if they are top drawer and they have been in the past in my opinion. Their take out this time was skimpy!!!  The deep fried won ton is now some store bought cheap and frugal version and the portion we received was unsatisfying for us three. It was not the robust and plentiful won ton we received on our first visit. And for twenty bucks we get a meagre portion. Sweet and sour really not great either and again for the price why go so cheap! Lastly our fish dish was bland and boring and served in a medium takeaway plastic bowl that could have been a good meal for one, but was rationed out by the spoonful to be fair.
So what is your attraction Deer Garden? Friendly welcoming service from your ladies? No thank yous and we didn't feel like our business was appreciated. Good food in portions that justified our 60 bucks?  Nope.  Or maybe I should exercise your tip option....what a joke!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Did takeout, fried rice tasted great just not sure if it was worth $20 but I still enjoyed it.
Place was busy and service was normal standards.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5lWG8kBGGZq2ozzxm8mJdeCEN8z-hUL73EFSA&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Anna Zhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ02jEC0GbE8rA7lyoVVPGxTbOAvDoh1bAmNxeRbS-LbgtI4w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had takeout order of one of their speciality sweet and sour pork, which had thin batter and good quality of pork. Also beef fried rice was unexpectedly delicious. Both were outstanding. Surely will return and order again.

And very friendly customer service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMepgu3BLhdoIeLn80Zj61C3rF69WMzkgHlml3Q&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"CASEY LU","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgeCpn0LhtSJ0EVTEqBJLUv8bYrl0aK4SzX8G4nXXW8dcHtA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We rushed in for a late lunch almost 3pm  The owner recommended us to try their Four meat balls noodle which was absolutely delicious. The thin noodle just tasted like Hong Kong‚Äôs.  The curry beef brisket also just the right taste.  Next time we will definitely go back try their sweet and sour pork.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alvin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpasldH6X4K8TtkMbIbac-orAN0Eb0jJ-m74oWvWE0xRNC-us=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All servers are very friendly! Glad to taste the best handmade noodle in Metro Vancouver so far! Tripe is soft and very tasty, not to mention the wonton, beef balls and HK-styled milk tea. Prices are very reasonable given the quality and generous portion of dishes! Will come back for sure!üòãüòã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcVzaxAPM2faZ5kI0H2ZsmesWqEHnxZo6snzg1&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2021-9-19"},{"Name":"J C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRid-486EHf3vFFlqzxc7hc71kbL9n1FDLFiUelrs10b7uY4If=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Interesting resto that seems to be doing well from take out business.  Big space but they only use maybe a quarter of it with two waitresses.  We tried their curry beef and it seems off compared to when they were at their old location outside of the mall.  Still good but just off and the pieces are higher.  I didn‚Äôt expect to pay almost $60 for two simple dishes.  Will come back if I‚Äôm craving curry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaP67dvqo2sdyYwP142fhxisNr-DWWBZECcjiV&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2023-4-14"},{"Name":"v l","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdZvJxBhGRMKAh6ZoV-1pNG0RsqEMX0Q7xeTmMWZiQ1-rLiRu7Rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really friendly service. The food is typical HK/Chinese cafe -- noodles, congee, milk tea...etc.  Lobster and crab special meals available but must order in advance.  Love the steam milk dessert!

Update... been back several times and the food, service are consistently excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYf29Z5mZxMwxqKILN1Kol-IYrxi33V6oBbcRo&fid=0x0:0x44571a2bfa63ef77"],"When":"2021-6-7"}]

[{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quiet restaurant with plenty of seating. Within walking distance from Coquitlam Centre, the Coquitlam Aquatic Centre and LaFarge, it's a great spot to regroup with fresh sushi.

I tried the Salmon & Spicy Scallop Roll ($9.95), Avocado Roll ($3.25) and a Miso Soup ($1.50). Sushi rolls were prepared fresh, and the flavour was satisfying.

Very reasonable prices. Surprisingly beautiful tableware.

Perfect local cheap and cheerful spot. Next time, I'll try the Korean Chirashi Don.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaPAinBXUUu3ilSaGH9s6s84yk_foIZfB7F_7O&fid=0x0:0x8fbdacf2df47aa40"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Inari (bean curd) nigiri sushi: good inari sushi, I liked it.
Chopped scallop with masago nigiri sushi: first time trying this and it‚Äôs quite delicious.

Miso soup: the server was very kind and offered me a second bowl of miso soup. It was decent.

Chicken teriyaki donburi: awesome dish! The portion was very generous and it tastes pretty good. Would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTtGnweFoM8BOXJe_TVo9-7V78JMoAJTYoaNkf&fid=0x0:0x8fbdacf2df47aa40"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Maya Ushikubo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJxE78gPCdJOshqUdmDjplgd5sCYNs7KC5rpdfRolyT7BeGidS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I usually order from Uber Eats. Every time I am increasingly more disappointed with the aesthetic & quality. Never ordering from here again. Seaweed is horrible quality, stale, damp, and hard to chew. When you order the party tray sushi in the middle is squished & barely have anything in there! This time was the WORST! And the sushi never stay together, it always falls apart! Ugh. [{"Name":"Tyler Hazelman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaOeOfMrKb93Y_IutfdRfQ5RnvS47tYfW1M-2iSLOIvO-Sl_d1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cozy spot in Coquitlam is perfect for a steaming bowl of ramen, offering plenty of options and add-ons. My go-to is the Double Double Chashu Tonkotsu with added Kakuni (pork belly)‚Äîan absolute home run! Do yourself a favor and stop by for lunch; you won‚Äôt be disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi4M9zFpvrTZRL3MwFQwZTu2FtK3Bu5LwX6OJa&fid=0x0:0xedb6807f8baab6cd"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Pe√±a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Been searching for the best ramen spots in the area, but this one didn‚Äôt quite live up to my flavor expectations. While it wasn‚Äôt for me, I still appreciate the experience and hope to find a better match next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm4QHh43LMJEbyVIMPwt6RtPbDWVTv99tk8C22&fid=0x0:0xedb6807f8baab6cd"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Mikayla Cortan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUSbVNbWxTmKX3pyqaMjVhNP6W7orlcHjVcPPcVICoFkwdwTLO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely adore Shobu!! Ramen is always my favourite and is constantly my craving so I‚Äôve tried a fair few of ramen places around metro Van and Shobu has always been the best!! My favourite is the Kakuni ramen, it‚Äôs absolutely to die for! Their prices are very comparable or even slightly less than most ramen places, the best broth and pork flavours too. I‚Äôve even gotten my dad hooked on it and he was originally not a fan of pork broth. Absolutely recommend this time and time again to all my friends!
P.S. my girlfriend and I came so often one of the waitresses would always recognize us and remember our order and it was so sweet!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS4hjkAdxyZfwmksDC-f9uJa1GOOnTlYc5ZnyJ&fid=0x0:0xedb6807f8baab6cd"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Thor Campbell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh1pnkJmsn1D8awag9xC4L5eddyHFQgwiWuJifBf1DVM9IvsHo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sho Bu came up as a random spot for Ramen, I tried it, and it was so good!
The portions are actually fair, and the amount of protein and toppings in the ramen are loaded, too. Followed by fair prices and convenient location by Coquitlam Centre

The service was great, food came super fast and it brings me back to a legit ramen shop in Japan. Small little shop for something quick and easy just as it should be.
I would certainly return to support this small business around the Tri-Cities area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOa6qib1zyeQB8go2Zru8Z45a8GzcbJVXuPGndc&fid=0x0:0xedb6807f8baab6cd"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Noah MacLeod","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnGOTt69QkP-Odwlqd-UzHafm6Dj1VvbHDQiYOi-yrHDWH31aixQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really great spot, I will come back next time in town. The food was out impressively quickly, and I was very happy with the combo I got! Tasty, well portioned, and interesting balanced flavours.

I've been told that I don't know what good ramen is because I haven't lived in the city, which I do argue against... but my amateur taste buds, and wallet, give Sho Bu fivvveee stars!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM95x6j6OVVCQ8SMjraWVu8XB_N5pHCUbaoNr16&fid=0x0:0xedb6807f8baab6cd"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Evangeline Reymundo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI1Nlu3hdQyr4eln6VfUWQFA-CRztL9qvZigMJlicalVY3cw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food is good and affordable. [{"Name":"Vivek Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYp1C5l327sjxI5T5cxPgV6Pmx3XlTZGysaP2xspHDo4iWuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best sushi spot people don't know about. The deep fried food is so amazing, warm, crispy, but so fluffy and soft. Its truly an amazing experience. Great prices too. And what a friendly staff. Love to come for a special time whenever I can! Its worth the drive from anywhere to coquitlam! Trust me!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3OYgYXrygxVSs17ig4YkYFkVdPi4ToboRZEX7&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Rusty Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4ymAI0f0o2WU902QSrg48zXGqcHFwOV2z_Z9nq6__IKEsHA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portions, great prices, good service, great food. I'll be back. Haven't been since it changed over from the original Mr. O. My dinner box had Iike everything you would ever want. Kids sushi came with glowing flashlights.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpWEVDOsEU-_mvrBnWt8WpZNME6uLyTJgjQJJw&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Lana Han","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWcXKPjpw8dJryG_tvzIMFSLPamG9klKTAGOKeFJikbZZWgu3S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I had a fabulous time at O Sushi.
I ordered Sashimi and Sushi Dinner Set; these days everything is pricier so I didn‚Äôt expect a lot but I was pleasantly surprised to see that there still is a restaurant that does not compromise either the portion or the quality (or the price) to provide an awesome dining experience for their customers. The sushi and sashimi were undoubtedly fresh and they were well presented. I was also impressed that there was a good variety of side dishes that offered different textures, acidity, and heaviness to enjoy each item and bring a good balance to the whole meal. I don‚Äôt know the names of the dishes but I especially liked the sweet and sour cold noodles with shrimps, lemon, and cucumber slices and the spinach with sesame seasoning. The portion was very generous and despite how delicious they were, I could not finish the dynamite rolls that came with the set.
The owners were very kind and professional; quick to help us when needed and checked up on us regularly to see if anything is needed. I, along with my two somewhat-picky kids and my parents, came out with full bellies and happy hearts after the meal. I truly appreciate their excellent services and food for making our night a very pleasant one.
I would definitely recommend O Sushi to anyone I know and will definitely revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOCN6_rXv_IOLQZ2TxkssBuHlrN07pzgbNZjHV&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Mia Banner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXo3YyYio9vqF7LApz-jbswxOpx_Sp7ljhFEieD1HcoYVfKW2b8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"overall O Sushi was a fantastic experience. the food was exceptional, the service was good and the place looked so cute, plus we got a miso and sunomono soup on the house! we only paid 30$ for 2 rolls and a meal set we almost couldn't finish because of the amount of food, we had a great time and will definitely come back soon :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3UsEnPjogymLXMB7jnrNb5J9kgDL5T-138Fpp&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"Canada RT","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4C6qox6x1Wgk4uK2xEpy2ZaXqNe2Qc2I1atkVwI9fwlu7bQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place changed ownership last week and was recommended by a friend,  and the chicken here is the best I've ever had. When I asked why, they told me they use raw chickens, not frozen, and only sell a set amount per day. I am now unable to eat any other ones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtAMiKP3OH-inwhPVxeLp99g_OJukJ1EkceEY7&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-3-19"},{"Name":"Paula Hlavacek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUEHsTUDREBV0VNUK6UGtTRNbBuCTOdBVYyLeZYC7hO1QTx25MLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so impressed with this sushi place! The aesthetic and the atmosphere is so nice compared to those average-Joe sushi joints. We had a 2-year old with us (which can be difficult at times) but they were so accommodating and understanding. 10/10 customer service, breath of fresh air when restaurant understands moms do their very best for little ones to behave but sometimes, it can get crazy. I was very impressed with the food; my favorite roll was the veggie roll + gomae roll, the peanut sauce was HANDS DOWN out of this world, I had to ask for extra! Definitely will be coming here again. Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOExB9Wg6z0ROGF-QGdSn0MYtLFO_GRfMtp1G3T&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Nancy Tian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXA9pyhOVC7-Kxqc8CAoujnMvQwIgaCs3eLnr8xR7YuMgUgZRo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I used to always order food from the old ownership. This is the first time I ordered from the new ownership. The chicken is pretty good. But there is a lid in my sushi when I have the first bite. I probably won‚Äôt order from them anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmm5ZGVowCac-AYt0CK54hJcpUgkaaz0KKwmcd&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"Angela","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGRULjSoPL401HdNCtHc43NeCeVNTq215E6FzMkKQFGuH-8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A true gem!! I got the sushi and sashimi dinner set, which came with ALL of the food pictured for only $23! I was stuffed and had leftovers for lunch the next day. The owners are super sweet and the food was both delicious and fresh. Can‚Äôt recommend this place enough. Lots of parking available in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrp8u6Dk73t8iYDEdYGZy6Gca4c-S1UT5vGDf5&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-5-1"}]

[{"Name":"A F Sidd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGDYN08fV6LM29cRcSDRaG5MvFASAFkWejOMDKL0j-lPeMRYj3rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 Stars - delicious Kabab and rice
This place serves the best halal Persian kebab cuisine in town! The food was incredibly fresh and flavorful. We tried a variety of kebabs, including lamb, beef, chicken, and the lamb shank, and everything was juicy, tender, and absolutely delicious. The Qabli rice and white rice were standout dishes‚Äîperfectly cooked and full of flavor.

Although the seating area is small, the quality and taste of the food make it well worth the visit. Prices are very reasonable for the generous portion sizes. To top off our meal, we enjoyed their refreshing saffron tea, which was the perfect ending.

A big shoutout to the lady who served us‚Äîshe was so polite, kind, and attentive, making our experience even better.

We‚Äôll definitely be coming back soon. Highly recommended for anyone looking for amazing Persian food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfTL7e6UuXBTlcSNnnx7QWZmgQTbOrInlGgi9h&fid=0x0:0x525b8aa9fd0793d"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"James Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwJo6T4E0NKsKnDpsBZaZfvtpSMVqQgbfnZDp8I06YSjhudP1t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first time having Persian food. [{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the better brunch places here in port moody and the neighboring areas.
The food tastes great, good atmosphere and service is fast.
We their the baileys flight, which in my opinion, could be improved. We couldn‚Äôt really make out the difference between the different flavors except for the peanut butter one.
The Maui Thai chicken burger was awesome and we was the Yorkshire Benny. I also loved their take on the hash browns.
They could definitely work on the pricing as we found it a bit on the expensive side.
Would def recommend this spot for anyone looking for a good brunch spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPToGwTm2g2cjL5bBjFYtzUui484e0jSqqK2tE&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Aaron Brousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrpCaHqR-XwUoFEei3pehP3F8y3p8zpxIo1yJXL2DI8WHkRvkE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing brunch at The Hard Bean Brunch Co. in Port Moody! The food was absolutely phenomenal‚Äîevery bite was bursting with flavor. The vibe of the place was spot on, cozy yet lively, and the beverage selection was outstanding. Whether you're into coffee, juices, or something a bit stronger, they've got you covered. Our server, Josh, was fantastic‚Äîattentive, friendly, and made the experience even better. If you're looking for a brunch spot that nails it on all fronts, this is the place! 10 out of 10 hits all key points for a brunch spots.  Ps the patio was Lovely And is dog friendly which is a huge plus for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNaHI05Lx6EisqaeHHwsYPAftWP6Jdr06aQfbG&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Parneet Kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqz_l5BzN5_mBY3QC7SEZWEVervEPkE_VocF-ECzkBQsGcdPO6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a nice brunch place in Port Moody.

The place had ample seating and since we had our puppy with us and patio seating was perfect for us.

Food we ordered was very delicious and prepared in a timely manner.

For drinks we ordered coke and mimosa. Mimosa was good but we were expecting a nice tall glass.

Maui teriyaki chicken burger - it was very juicy and delicious‚Ä¶. 10/10 for the flavour

Hard Chicken crunch - Again flavours 10/10 chicken was cooked perfectly

Last but not the least, Hard bean co burger, very nice vegetarian options. Bean patty was very nice not too dry..

Definitely hoping to visit soon, been looking at so many more options to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1KrvVRsRO_zbgmwGyZyuW9bPr71yR3bhKnNq5&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Billy Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSxOBk_c92Ol0FCdQI2uK9UOXNvJt85D76p4UHFqKR_gkp-zYHgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve been to a lot of brunch places this year and I‚Äôve always been underwhelmed by the concept of brunch. Well, The Hard Bean Brunch Co. broke the mold.

First off, amazing service, people were so friendly and helpful. $6 all day specials as well for drinks.

Ordered the Yorkshire pudding hard ham Benny. Out of this world. Probably will never order a Benny elsewhere ever again. The smashed potatoes were out of this world. Crispy on the outside soft on the inside. Wife ordered the quesadilla and that was equally amazing. One small knock was that ham waffle fries were a bit undercooked but don‚Äôt get that anyways, stick with the smashed potatoes!!

We will be back if we‚Äôre ever in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7JAnb6jeZFhYaQ6sJ8zdxRiRMdkaulczFv38U&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Mandy Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfdcmtmnw1QBUKzc568p_XlShrjauBmzaYnb3AklL4JCX7IFSL3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"On Sunday, I visited the restaurant with a group of four for a late lunch. Upon our arrival, we were informed that the wait time would be approximately 25 to 30 minutes, which we were happy to accommodate. While waiting, we took a leisurely stroll around the area. After 26 minutes, we received a notification that our table was ready, and we were promptly seated.

The restaurant's interior displayed a lively and welcoming ambiance, creating a wonderful atmosphere and vibe. Our server provided attentive service, checking in on us periodically. However, there were instances when we wanted to place additional orders but had to wait for a while before our server returned. We ordered a diverse selection of dishes, including the rose spaghettini, Julius salad, everything grilled cheese, hard bean co burger, and hard chicken crunch. The handheld dishes were pretty good. The hard chicken crunch lived up to its name, delivering an exceptionally crispy texture. The Julius salad was enjoyable, although the dressing could have benefited from a touch more acidity. Regrettably, the rose spaghettini seemed to lack in terms of flavor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2M-uiySMHfptiI6rZzA40nKLqNvQnsjzaLR6d&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Zain Bhanji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlgk8aN8btcOJZzZf5wvoL31ZimhDnrY-IWz_-xujZJutZcBjZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was an upbeat and lively brunch spot! Great music, cool set up and loved the colour scheme of the place. Service was quick and friendly here, however the serving sizes are quite small and not filling enough. I ordered the steak tacos and although I even ordered a side of fruit at the recommendation of the server, it still wasn‚Äôt enough to fill me up. I felt the resto could have been more generous with adding more meat to each of my tacos. Regardless, these tacos were quite small - pretty much a 2 bite eat, which in my opinion isn‚Äôt worth the $18 you pay for the plate.
Would consider coming back here but having something else hopefully more filling!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShnQT9frNbDmQjQgCIY3Hm7YQJsMWry9askrq&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried the yam waffle fries and Bacon Burger with a delicious Green Salad, and it was an exceptional dining experience. The burger, perfectly cooked and topped with crispy bacon, was juicy and flavorful, offering a delightful blend of savory and smoky tastes. I asked for lettuce wrap for the burger. The yam waffle fries were a standout, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, with a natural sweetness that complemented the burger perfectly. Accompanying the meal was a fresh and vibrant green salad, featuring a mix of crisp lettuce, juicy tomatoes, crumble feta cheese and quinoas. This combination made for a well-rounded and satisfying meal, balancing indulgence with a touch of freshness. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a delicious and hearty bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOUaR5a8FLR6B3otK7luPOQG3JxexiCAA5PCQA&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Mounota","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvpiSPg9AtpTNs-8JJvoJHojdmAI1FZcME9pprQbBKumVFhadS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The atmosphere was pleasant. I had their smoothie bowl. It was okay; tasted a little watery. It looked pretty though. I might return and try their other dishes because the reviews are so positive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW-NUkGkpjmqUH4iPJ4DTyhMBN9ZyBBys53Ycn&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-21"}]
