user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Met a friend at Saku and had a delightful experience. The waitlist link online didn't work but we didn't need to worry about that because there were tables open when we arrived. The atmosphere was both aesthetically pleasing and comfortable with bright, warm lighting, and the two waiters were very polite.
I tried the Saku on Broadway in Vancouver once years ago and loved it and was impressed again here. I got the veggie curry and also their seasonal cinnamon ginger drink. Their curry sauce is earthy and so rich; I am in love. The veggies were fried to be nice and soft inside and not too oily. The sides are also very good. I subbed out the tonjiru for a mini cold udon. The noodles were tender and the broth was also really flavourful. This was my first time trying cold udon and I was pleasantly surprised by how different flavours come out in the cold broth. The cinnamon ginger drink was very unique with the warm cinnamon ginger flavour in a refreshing soda.
My meal with tip was about $40. Although it‚Äôs a little expensive, the portions are generous as is and you can stretch the value even more by ordering complimentary refills for your sides. I didn‚Äôt need it since I was full with the first round.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1IZaWTu8bX8SPf3d-L1xEXrV5HEzVX_VUmDVw&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Paul Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVl2oVxJKLr_k_g4j5wg7lB9NsNfiBzRT5FNAPVPTrX-BeeOxpk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The store isn't very big, but the overall decor feels comfortable. Their deep fried dishes are done quite well‚Äîcrispy on the outside, tender inside, and not greasy. The other side dishes are also fine. The only slight disappointment is their sauce; in my opinion, it‚Äôs a bit too mild, which is a pity given the high quality of their fried items. Overall, it's a pretty good restaurant and worth recommending.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcCXhtj6e9MzBLZoso4yfUWVGe7VxVYEPfwB97&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Jooey V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYFca56bPZafMJtIyMb6Ij_VZ3XATQurm5TlOwXPZrmywf0QM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm someone who loves both Korean-style Dongasu and Japanese-style tonkatsu, and this dish is my soul food.

However, I was deeply disappointed by this franchise, which is said to have the best tonkatsu in Vancouver.

A good tonkatsu should taste heavenly even when dipped in just a bit of salt.
But their *Dokujyo rosu katsu*, which is supposed to be a premium menu item, was overly greasy, and the batter crumbled with just a touch of my chopsticks.
Despite being one of the first tables, there was a smell of oil.

Moreover, about a quarter of the *rosu katsu* was fat.
I've never seen this much fat in a pork loin cutlet before.

Both weren‚Äôt completely terrible, but for a dish that costs around $30, I would honestly recommend Costco‚Äôs frozen stuff instead.

It's a real shame because this place used to be known for its amazing food, but it seems they've completely lost their original touch.

P.s. but the service itself was very nice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTqJaHEDApsb1rWimsoqzCEokpp-vyjWlQvLOT&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Thomas Cyre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjxRtq3NoJ3VgRg8YkHsqwg3V2gkoydIp0o9cTSTsZPUk9ApYJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the Miso Katsu, my wife ordered the Kurobuta Special Katsu. Both were delicious. We really liked the variety of seasonings to eat with the katsu. The tonjiru soup was really good and its great to have free refills of rice, soup and salad. Service was good, will definately go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzeaC0Gg7PFJcJ_ODlhxk50bIzzoj9Uaui5yIK&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"B C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYvDpHvDtMb9gbzsqKNwxqjfCmk7W_UFxEZqOKOCis0fyIO58=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Do not be fooled by the upscaled decor or presentation.

Tried the cheese katsu, which is one of their "signature specials". $27 plus tax and tip for 6 glorified cheese sticks and rice.

In hindsight I should have ordered the regular katsu, as there would be more meat, but even the portion for those looked small.

The taste of everything was fine, but the steep prices for the food you get in return is unjustified.

Would not recommend or return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEkIJlmYiRZEGYZo_DSHV_g-B95WLRezTU4cI&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good, one of my favourite katsu places in the city. I‚Äôve been to this place so many times and in many of their locations across the GVA area. I get the premium pork katsu combo most of the time and it‚Äôs delicious. Their fried fish one is also really good and I recommend. They also offer free refills on salads, rice and soup which is amazing and fills me up every time. The house made sesame dressing for the salad is the best. Their meat also tastes super fresh and the interior of the restaurants are always clean!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSTrhy0W_gsEEVrnebp6SUvbS--8lRc8HtdfG8&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I brought my baby boy and my mother-in-law here for lunch. We ordered the pork and the cheese cutlet. We also got side orders of the ebi tempura and the curry sauce. My mother-in-law was very impressed. The presentation, she thought, was very nice, and the quality of the food was outstanding. She's never had katsu Like this in Ottawa where she is from. The servers were very nice to us as well despite my baby boy making a big mess while he was eating. Overall, food was great . Saku is one of those places that you have to eat at the restaurant. We'll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGlAhHO3tUA9ZdkaA8Ci0gSmqrsfJOOAjCYISg&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Yoshi O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXzpF5JXCGmarr1qa55T_-WQSAQqt7aKKnVaI2jByds0GoeWQJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had their special Kuro buta.
It was too oily as its bottom was still wet by oil even it's laid on a wire rack!! The rice, which I love as I am Japanese, it was bad. Hard, smelled old. No worth $32 before tip plus $5 for parking!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwIZaPje41m1UK5sCFbCz-T9BJh-ieqeoXYjIl&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-20"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Regie Sacdalan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVDuCV38ynK6mxDdP-HlWdoPODHVpBYeLjIOghxaV1fgHRoA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's no wonder why this place has such a high Google review rating! One of the best Peking Duck and Lettuce Wraps in Metro Vancouver and at a reasonable price.  The duck was plump and juicy. The lettuce wrap course had a perfect meat ratio. The best Deep Fried Squid I've had -- light, airy with just a hint of spice so my kids were able to enjoy it too. The squid at other places is often tough and this was not the case here. Everything tasted great and was high quality. Food was served hot. The servers were very attentive and kind. We will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP45SWEE9L8SmkSTJFyrr_zJmSoMsRDskWEqo_J&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Newly opened Hong Kong style restaurant. We went there for lunch and were pretty happy with the quality and flavour of the food.

The portion sizes are quite big so I‚Äôd highly suggest getting a dish or two less as we were a group of 8 people and 6 dishes were too much for us.

Service however, could be improved as the kitchen forgot to bring out two of our dishes until we reminded them about 30 to 40 minutes after we were done with the others.

Price isn‚Äôt that bad. About CAD20 per person.

I‚Äôd recommend making a reservation in advance as the place does tend to get pretty busy and parking can be a pain to find.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMptKLVmoMm8826G-woKe7UTtGCTE6Z_UlJ5MMX&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-7-10"},{"Name":"Bob","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkEC75mT1rTSBiWusD60B4Ypx_mMWrgo5mEAuPBQ7mgpfmDaoe4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When I went it was still considered a soft opening for the restaurant. The dim sum menu items were all very good. The seasoning was well balanced and not overwhelming. They were understaffed today and the customers were getting impatient, but there isn't much you could do. Come on guys. It's hard to hire people and they just opened.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-M6i5DzCOlWPhn8UH4RjKHzD8CMfstAiJ0E6n&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A wholesome Chinese restaurant good for family dinners with good portion sizes given for the dishes. The honey garlic spareribs and deep fried squid were well fried being crispy on the outside and moist on the inside. The Peking duck was standard. The complimentary choice of mango pudding or dessert soup at the end was nice. Solid place for standard Chinese food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPM7O1IwhE73us5iOTaBQDUKFzzcfIrATj9lDfY&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Tmo Jra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKu-bLJQalUBeL5kjDEs0RopDiDGGJMUE6USX1nrCypwPJTfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Newly opened dimsum restaurant that we decided to try on a whim. Very glad we did! The decor was nice, food was delicious, and the people there were quite friendly.
Also, the portions were huge! Got used to the small but pricey portions in most Vancouver restaurants, so was very pleasantly surprised with the size of the orders here. Our family of 3 ate till we were stuffed but only got through a 3rd of each order (we normally don't have enough left to take home).
Definitely get the bang for your buck here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtiSgEaA709o9eEKbxoIbV5FcseRz7ewMOhaXf&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best dimsum in the area! Formerly known as Rainbow Butterfly, Yan's House is the updated version of a neighbourhood favourite.

Dimsum is fresh, hot and served quickly. Main dish portions are massive. We ordered fried rice and we're surprised at the size. One portion will serve 4-6 people.

The Deep Fried Squid is wonderful. Crispy, light batter. The squid is tender and cooked beautifully. We crave this dish.

Spicy String Beans with Minced Pork is so satisfying to eat. Savoury on its own or delicious with rice. It's a family favourite.

Dimsum is served all day. It's quite busy in the morning but the restaurant is quite large. Make sure to put your name on the list and you'll be seated asap.

Great space for a group, or small parties. Once seated, you're provided a carafe of hot tea. There's free wifi available.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW9KvDGBCNNyd-yCe-Pda8deL6vOs2zEpruOf_&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Eveline Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZ_kiKNY5YBfaLOhaLW3SLnIfYj072uzzapXDuzRiVxziOnO0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First visit! Tried to come in the morning for dim sum but it was so busy, we decided to come for dinner instead. :)
Love the atmosphere - staff are friendly and helpful.
We had the 2 dish combo + a side of bbq pork.
Combo comes with soup, rice, and dessert. Such a great deal.

My kids liked the chicken cream corn soup.
Dessert was mango pudding.

We ordered the stir fried green beans & beef‚Ä¶ pretty tasty‚Ä¶ and big portions.
Broccoli, egg tofu, mushrooms was also yummy.

Overall, decent meal. Reasonably priced. Had leftovers to pack home. Will come again :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeNsl4u7Ms7hOZM-A7umSD_YQU9soxfp434hDm&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It‚Äôs a good Chinese restaurant for stir fry instead of dim sum.

Black bean chicken chow mein and congee are very good.  Shrimp dumplings skin was broken when it got picked up.  Siu mai has corn inside which is a bit weird.  Chicken mushroom e fu noodles in cream sauce is like pasta but exceptionally good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3_qnMWQVAsdNzG-__Hqhg8x2przBhr0AmAq0j&fid=0x0:0x8b30f4df92938c89"],"When":"2024-8-26"}]

[{"Name":"Kristopher Susilo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBtEhlXkRJMy2FnW55lvERwkpk2-F5eMFH_4N0FgO25PS_ew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can guarantee whoever gives this restaurant less than 5 stars either because they are not used to the typical ‚Äúrude‚Äù but caring service by the aunties OR they just dont know what to order thats actually good.

First time here and I was impressed with the food taste. Ordered 4 item combo: shanghai style crispy chicken, fish & tofu hot/clay pot, greenbeans with beef and house special chowmein. Combo includes free rice, (lobak, carrots & beef) soup and dessert (mango pudding or red bean soup). It was too much for 4 of us and we had to pack some home.

Will definitely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnhlxnsyLRRJEHh4fzVtiLgMOmMBDi22sds4lU&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Shirley Fung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSf2s-kJuEfRzH7n0u0o-Ty-eDTJZIvAb-cR6BzmkEs9eHNYN_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"we had the 2 dishes dinner combo and it was so disappointing‚Ä¶ the soup was the best thing about the meal. the crispy chicken was so bland. the server persuaded me to pay to upgrade the steamed fish to black cod but it was so disappointing. there‚Äôs no taste to it aside from few black beans on top. the sauce was watery and the texture of the fish was so mushy. you thought one thing you can count on for Chinese food is the saltiness of soy sauce, they didn‚Äôt even have that ü•≤ the servers were generally nice but the cleanliness of one of the chefs and bathroom was bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9FKinfJPsrJa8WvhmtHG9gBLSigOBIsDlKCi_&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"EVAN ETHAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUx4wFf5gaB1lR1A8XX5kn8xelbVXHG8-xFycDrpZ-n6j0ewpV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"ORDERED BEEF FRIED RICE - $20 w tax - NOT WORTH IT! Better off ordering a beef dish.

Taste is OK but hardly any beef inside ( probably just 1 table spoon of TINY BITS of beef in one order).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNypKE1WWfEfipQcw4XUmfNtSKtUTTkxRfhMFSD&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Ha Dinh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcQG83kIM9L7VU9GS6J74J_TBMCdyvkYzp1C5XJSr_quttlO0V2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really giving me the feeling of home-cooked meals. Tastes so similar to the food I had at home in Guangzhou. Dinner comes with soup and dessert. They keep rice warm in a small (red) bucket, really makes me reminisce the past. Portion is big, we ordered 3 dishes for 3 people, and still have enough for lunch the next day. Would totally come back üíõ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvaLQtA4z_pvmNVnI8Kh1Z7qHpl_QKC50N4LrF&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2024-5-21"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered delivery from here before and decided to visit in person once in the area. The interior has seen its better days, so the interior vibe is drab. However, our waitress was friendly and communicative. We decided to go for a combo for two, and she recommended against one of the options we chose. I'm not sure what it was about, but our food was outstanding. I should mention that portions are huge. We got at least half of it to go. Prices are very reasonable, and there are¬†many more options than listed in the delivery menu.¬†If you are after nice looking interior and a cozy atmosphere,¬†this place is not for you, but if you want yummy Chinese food for a very reasonable price, give it a chance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3Kz8AXC00TZcQEoR0U3SjODyiZU7llSsIe00y&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2022-8-9"},{"Name":"Daniel Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAxFTfz_ZYgM60gsStYArKOb4YgmHuHArMEsVm-TJD2WcKuo33=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Had dinner here at Chinese New Year, service is consider good during this busy days.  The food is just average, the Deep Fried spicy squid and the deep fried lobster with spice chilli is a must try, others are mostly on average.  I would not recommend the hot and sour soup nor the
Singapore Stir-fried Noodles to anyone, their signature chicken are just fine as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUZrsZslO2nY-auGLnWPWIk0Myi4-rLW0d4KVx&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2023-1-24"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a great experience here! One of the better Chinese restaurants in the lower mainland.

I really liked their crispy squid and the sweet and sour pork. I also highly recommend their egg and shrimp! The egg was very silky and rich which perfectly complemented the shrimp. I want to try their Peking duck next time.

I recommend this place if anyone is around the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJRfvhGAZpzBC7snM4pEnjwIvrGKpQzy8W21Cu&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2024-3-5"},{"Name":"Jaime Ricafrente","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAJwwcGATN2RuHMthkyt1rjxVqb7NF_uxVYPAzS1OSfFJWO9Wn6g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's my first time here.  I ordered the Crispy Chicken with Soy Sauce, Dp Fried Spicey Prawn, egg plant Clay Pot.  If you want a quick answer, EAT HERE ITS AMAZING!  Food is not salty, prawn not to coated, just AMAZING FOOD.  The Lotus soup was sooo good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_dl1fR5wGDp97NMcI-nCS-1kz2NQOLv04voK2&fid=0x0:0xd5411af39ffb3fa8"],"When":"2023-12-18"}]

[{"Name":"Yeshvi Mehta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVHHFZUwt0pnim38TVGVDQUhu3Obi33NtK1Ek9rBbru761t74M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I happened to be in the area, and was craving some thing Indian. Found this place nearby and we chose to dine in.
The service was super quick and kind, even though we were pretty close to last call on a weekday. The interiors are cute & cozy, felt like I was sitting comfortably at home.

The food was also great! We licked our plates clean!! I would totally come back.
We ordered:
- Daal makhani
- malai kofta
- paneer tikka

The only thing I wouldn‚Äôt order again is the masala papad, it‚Äôs a simple dish and I feel like I‚Äôve had it better and so worth a try here, but not worth ordering again. I could recommend using better quality papad (this tasted like the microwavable ones I buy) and adding cilantro on top!
I can also suggest skipping the rasamalai and gajar ka halwa.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSDjFW06q2OYUYcOeDlM0qXqAsx7PriBcfC29x&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Y L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKV887-1nS5R1_0KzCym2KWUc3U6pndK939JM55kJWey6Ce8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time we tried this place from map search. We ordered Chicken vindaloo and Kadai Paneer and some fish and veggie sidedish. Everything was very tasty, and the curry had lots of stuff inside. Their galric naan was very savory. The service was amazing! Sunday mid afternoon, and most tables were full. Will come back with family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOELPHUm52kqW3zDV3koxo5VImAINHyx18l_Jm&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Katie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJN3p8cZHE5md15OEErKZKNn97Wi4lfH4nosGtOcXvlYGz2XA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The sauce is delicious but I can definitely tell the chick is not fresh. I really want to like this place. I ordered butter chicken many times but the chicken*always* doesn't taste fresh. It tasted like they used frozen chicken or old chicken. Please make this place better!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ÈôàÊôìÊôØ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGC0re95jO_hDOolePpTdMH_6cWbYDgFuh210eUCCpyMpiSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is delicious and service is quick and good. Backgroud music volume could be a little lower. Nice a small but clean spot with a beautiful Indian style chandelier.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-JksCwe0tHsc-A7xhUiCTe9CsUtM0Cyc1Kmfg&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Linda N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuD1_pd2ly4vtFhb8M-kjUT3J9JuCYtyHfu9UlF8IRT0IUpuI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute and cozy Indian restaurant. I absolutely love their food! Their butter chicken is so mouth-watering good. Service was great and staff is extremely friendly. 10/10 recommend and will definitely be coming back for more :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXf8xMYxAiAkIocwrP_DFEwgjR_QP6IvaAPonY&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2023-7-16"},{"Name":"Dennis Chinatambi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGLJfwmSynbs1NwEL5QNU9ukic8SU2FJpZcOR9o9KT1JGzLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Milaap Indian Kitchen has become our goto spot for Indain food in the Tri-Cities. We mostly do take out and found the food to be tasty, authentic  and good portions. The food is aways ready on time for pickup and the staff is friendly and welcoming. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a small restaurant with about 4 tables. It wasn't too busy inside. They were able to put two tables together to accommodate our group of 5 adults and 4 kids. More customers were coming in for pick up.

My favorite dish was the Palak Paneer. The flavor was so good! The honey garlic cauliflower was something different which was also very good. I preferred the Butter Chicken rather than the Butterica. The Butter Chicken had a lot more flavor and spice. My main dish was the Goat Curry. The goat was nice and tender but I found the sauce a little salty. The garlic naan was very fresh tasting and had good flavor.

Overall, many of the dishes were good and the server was friendly and helpful with describing dishes.

I would definitely come back to try more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjVHWe5_Z1UvW7YTHaCkuTZGDbrNMCiP5Dy9-2&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2022-12-23"},{"Name":"wilsonjoshwilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPoK02al9DYZ9GLC0wDSU4FEAZAAPuuG6qlzOOh_26eyk877fT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered Milaap via UberEats.

I ordered the butter chicken, rice, garlic naan and two samosas.

Let‚Äôs start with the samosas..not great. I‚Äôve had a lot of samosas in my day, but unfortunately these are some of the worst.

Tasted like unseasoned potatoes with a slight hint of masala..Very underwhelming.

As for the butter chicken, it had a decent flavour. I ordered hot and the sauce had a good amount of kick. The taste itself was a bit lacking in the depth department, but still satisfied my craving.

Some chicken pieces were a tad dry and it felt like the chicken wasn‚Äôt overly seasoned. Again, I ordered via Uber, so the quality could be better if the food didn‚Äôt have to travel.

As for the rest of the food, I enjoyed the garlic naan and didn‚Äôt have issues with the rice.

If you do end up dining here, I would suggest eating at the establishment for a fresher experience.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Danielle Gvili","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtnY6VsiKEHflHe4AGhBj4D88CHraCtWDo_GuPMoru0OLneQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing experience at Blue Moon. The food was incredibly delicious, with a wide variety of options that cater to all tastes. The staff were friendly, attentive, and made sure we had everything we needed. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, perfect for a relaxed meal with colleagues. Highly recommend this place if you're looking for great food and excellent service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxPZ8KDssmgXA63tP0Nn7SJICxa2zkJxXfNqtM&fid=0x0:0x76800fbbe526d9f1"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"James Ellis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz27pZVS2aZphyeRTqr6VhVg7eIzU4aF32gub7FWgk7k6bwXB6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food. The fish and chips were good with a hint of added spices. The butter chicken was great with a lot of chicken not just the sauce.

There are so many items that we want to try.

We will definitely go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ally K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK20SxbQ29ElWudLMlWVmgifoTPMIKLn5ngtXDEReno3yju0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had another amazing dinner at blue moon. We love the fish and chips. They are the best we have ever had! We also always order the butter chicken with Naan. They always make it fresh. This time we phoned in our order ahead of time and then dined in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Navi Ahluwalia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-COlFW-2Zh3HKusSNtOKzSbLHJPyazzE-uT_L6XZOG247BSQT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got blue moon to cater our company lunch and they provided excellent service and great food! Butter chicken and goat kurhi were both made perfectly with good spice, thank you guys for the service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhBdXdItlh2dgvj6b_MFeDR66tCVRmNpGfZyxr&fid=0x0:0x76800fbbe526d9f1"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"wilsonjoshwilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPoK02al9DYZ9GLC0wDSU4FEAZAAPuuG6qlzOOh_26eyk877fT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried Blue Moon a few days ago due to the rave reviews.

Personally I wouldn‚Äôt give it the five stars that others have based on my experience.

I ordered the butter chicken take-out special which came with rice, naan and salad.

Pretty good value for the price, although it wasn‚Äôt the biggest portion.

As for the food, the butter chicken sauce was creamy and had a decent flavour. The chicken in the sauce was chewy/dry and lacked any seasoning for my taste.(could have been day old chicken, potentially?) I also noticed a bit of a burnt flavour coming from either the sauce or the chicken. It was subtle, but noticeable enough to catch me off guard.

The naan wasn‚Äôt the best and the rice was standard.

To sum it up, for me personally this isn‚Äôt ‚Äúfive star‚Äù Indian food.Although some aspects of the meal were good, I wouldn‚Äôt say it‚Äôs more than 3 stars.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chad Wren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCCG_FRbbnU7tf1MYgoCRTcjvRGAFleK9J2qF5E_n0ESex6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here is excellent!  Our kids love the fish n chips and our daughter said it‚Äôs the best butter chicken she has ever had.  Naan bread and pakora are great too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kimmi O'Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLmbqspM_MvGR5i7Jp2CjOogNS5DQDy78_ehOCKq6lz-DdsxhK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm not sure if all the five star reviews are just from friends/family trying to make the restaurant look good because it's new, but my experience was terrible.

I visited tonight and it was not busy at all--there were three other tables in the restaurant. One of the tables complained to the server about the food taking so long, and we ended up walking out after waiting over 45 minutes for our food. The server was not communicative and the atmosphere is non-existent.

There's so much other great Indian food within just a few blocks so unfortunately I won't be returning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sundeep Mahil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocImDDC_BiXlRgR1-zf1M5TJB0D081xc7eJJUI9qC9eOymte3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here is exceptional. We had the Chilli Chicken, Goat Curry, & Butter Chicken for dinner.

- All 3 of these dishes packed amazing flavour in each bite, I was licking my plate clean. Also had Mango Lassi which was made perfectly.

- The Service is awesome as well. We felt very welcomed the moment we stepped in.

Lots of food choices, we will definitely be coming back to try out the other dishes & drinks!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Old review, Nov 2022:
Incredible Vegetable Panang Curry!  I ordered delivery today for the first time and after my first bite I knew this was my new favourite place. I can‚Äôt wait to come back.
My food was cooked perfectly. Tasted very fresh and hot: I had Thai level spicy. The Spring Rolls were really good, big and lots of vegetables inside.
Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6BbEeS1BuJ7Y8b9VDiNAfiVpfFrnuMT37GnFj&fid=0x0:0x130d623528e88584"],"When":"2022-11-9"},{"Name":"Oindrilla Chatterjee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJm94R0PMP5L1aZDjmRRxz0E0-tAufioZ5Bi0a0wVzXdWXkyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a small mom and pop store in Coquitlam that we went to after our hike at Bunzten lake. We didn‚Äôt know what to expect  as the place didn‚Äôt have too many reviews but were pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food. We were a large group and got a variety of items like the vegan and chicken khao suey, panang curry, green thai curry, papaya salad. Everything was very delicious, very well plated and very good quantities too. The server seemed like the owner of the store who was also helping prepare the meals. Very homely and super value for money. Spice level 3 in the appetizers was definitely spicy for us, so we made it 2 for the main course items. Highly recommend if you like Thai food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnbf-uZeXo_KgjAIwmuXZllYb2LSr71zKgkhxu&fid=0x0:0x130d623528e88584"],"When":"2023-5-15"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love their beef rib kalguksoo - the noodles and the soup base was great.

Also like their rice cakes and sausages

The bulgogi hot pot was good with a lot of meat but it's a bit too sweet.

The seafood pancake was very crispy but not a lot of ingredients

The servers were attentive even though you ordered through the machine

Overall, it's a nice experience and we will come back for more signature food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-6WdDAeMZBYmWZJtZPAex39LhAvBj5zRytfUf&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Kevin (KC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrZpzDcm4xbgvb_oOynyP_bQvwIe7l-wMoPIs8L4UeVZ-waBkO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food was just ok for a Korean restaurant. Definitely a lot more expensive for what it is...

I believe the 5 star reviews here is from the promotion they have, however I don't care much about these 'freebies', so I'm here to provide an honest unbiased opinion.

We ordered the following for 6 people:
- spicy chicken (hot grill)
- soy chicken (hot grill)
- rose tteokbokki

The spicy chicken was decent but I honestly feel most Korean restaurants in Metro Vancouver have terrible value when it comes to price and portion. The spicy chicken plate is probably good for like 1.5 people...for 2 guys I would recommend ordering another side to feel a bit more full.

The Rose tteokbokki was just ok. It was basically just rice cakes smothered in KD Mac and Cheese sauce...at least that's how it tasted to me. You're better off just buying a box of KD Mac & Cheese on sale for under 1 dollar and cooking your own rice cakes with this sauce.

Getting a table was also quite difficult on a busy Saturday night. Interior and service was good.

Overall, it's not a bad restaurant, but it didn't blow me away...and for the price, there's definitely more options out there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFcKHNNPJK4GNYDXfAdPeGruK_89MtPuDMwSYd&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJs_km6RslliP6cTTiQcv7eI3BYv9_LkkJf-8xS0POhDRp70O4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fast paced, loud but fun, family style dinner environment. Ordered a little of everything to try out this restaurant. Everything was well cooked. My favourite was the seafood pancake. Service was quick but very kind. Place was clean. Wouldn‚Äôt mind coming back here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeyckBCREpcGOtrV4TiHX_Rg09VVukSQB5j_KR&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"andrew H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI2Wi9Ocgr9nl3zo2CZ5YD9JRspbdoiyoPc3OsJIyx9rFIGQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered the octopus/pork grill, katsu, and lunch pork.

The service was excellent‚Äîstaff were attentive and consistently checked on my table. The prices are reasonable, and parking is convenient since it's in a mall.

The food was average. I had these dishes between lunch and dinner when no one was in the restaurant.
The spicy pork wasn‚Äôt hot when served, despite being on a small grill plate. The octopus/pork belly main dish tasted good, but the pork belly was a bit too chewy, likely due to using frozen slices. The portion size for the katsu was generous.

There are many menu options, and I can tell the kitchen staff put in a lot of prep work every day.

Wishing them the best.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF1V1OgRVObatqtMLnx7ffc0ISBwVvfoJhJOb8&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Soung Son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHkihcNrKz3Cs19caeCuVOR-Yk29MFxtD_S6stmS9PXtHqts7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The ginseng chicken soup is a winner on those rainy days and the spicy squid! The fried giant squid is huge! Great appetizer to start the meal! If you guys are looking for a variety of Korean cuisine dishes this is the joint","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoLb_oLRj-ky5SumYTJ-riXnMxgH6tlde0TVNC&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a new restaurant in the Korea town and I wanted to check it out. We ordered two noodles - one with clam broth and another one with beef broth, and a cream cheese corn.

It was very busy with only couple waiters and about 30 minute wait. However, when we sat down, the service was quite fast and the food came out very quickly.

The noodles were hot, and very fresh and I could tell that they were hand made. The broth was savoury, and rich, with clean finish. It was perfect for a chilly day. I preferred the beef broth with the ribs, and my mom preferred the clam broth. They were both delicious.

The beef noodle came with two ribs and soy dipping sauce that was tasty but it was not fall-off-the-bone tender.

Cream cheese corn was fantastic, albeit a bit too rich for me. But I think this will be very popular if you ordered it with a large party.

Overall, it was a very solid first impression and I would definitely be back to try other items on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPiLrqP_2vPn_Qtd2EmjtT56x4AHUUY9b3pCvR&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2023-11-20"},{"Name":"Michael Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULDRH9Upm7RaDsdv5-9NJTh_dFOoUW6rNpRJuL2r1G2VRJjaEj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The amount of food, and  the presentation cannot be better for this price point. The side dishes are also perfect, it is not too sweet or salty. It‚Äôs a small family run restaurant and the gentleman at the front of it comes off as kinda stressed but let me tell you, he can cook. [{"Name":"yajun guo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLp7wWCAyL8N4BU9YzYEwjUr6kOHsh1skUFpYqXGLOUxa7J9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came to eat here for the third time. As a Chinese, I was curious about Korean-Chinese food for the first time. I found it very clean. The fried chicken and dipping sauce were very refreshing, not greasy at all, and felt very healthy. I continued to order fried chicken and special noodles when I passed by for the second time. I tried seafood rice and seafood noodles for the third time. If you like spicy food, you will like it very much. The portion is very large, and each time it is a super large portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTAfTwvHwymurp-J2vwBYPXXMnCbm0sXglvKGA&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"YumYumCha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4DHzC88idd6SgF253zU976cjh24MUZrbY8_smo4XhlzY0-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is neat, and the seasoning is just right. The crispy fried chicken was perfectly cooked, with a crunchy, tender, and juicy‚Äîit was delicious! I highly recommend the fried chicken. The black bean noodles also had chunk pieces of pork and onion, and the shrimp tempura on top was a nice touch. The server was very friendly, and since it was chilly outside, they offered warm tea, showing great thoughtfulness and attention to detail. I‚Äôve been a wanderer among Korean Chinese restaurants, but I think I‚Äôll settle here. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFsLKySnj8L1aFFgrRjiAYfGeU41qRSAV3M0b0&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Anthony Plaxen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0TosyGAQWTqM_XvTHaXfq2jDGHv6ifKWBgTGcJKYnap3ceipL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best spots in metro Vancouver for very delicious Korean food. Located in Coquitlam, the restaurant is tucked away in a small strip mall and is a real hidden gem.

We ordered a variety of different dishes for dinner.

The Pan fried black bean noodle was really nice. Quantity wise it was great the portion was massive. The different kinds of seafood, octopus, squid and shrimp really complimented the noodles.

The sweet and sour deep fried pork was also really good. It wasn‚Äôt overly greasy or soft, had a nice crunch on the outside and went well with a tangy sauce.

The fried chicken was good. A bit spicy but really solid. Crispy on the outside, soft in the middle and a nice mildly spicy tangy sauce to it with plenty of vegetables and onions. It was delightful.

The real star was the cream saewoo shrimp. They were giant, and the sweet mayonnaise drizzle to it was pleasant.

Overall, I would say that this place has better eats than most of the Korean spots around North road. Nice small location, cozy feeling to the place and the excellent portion sizes really make this a place I would return to and try other dishes at! Pleasantly happy, will come back again.

4.5/5 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbtAu5tsHye4FviiQk22PenEPzBEp38af73aQe&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Yuko H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInqidVGGQTic-c290lK_StdyV7mOrKdBnlV-toPbw96dF0KwA5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All the foods we ordered in this restaurant were awesome. Sauce and deep fried meats match very well and saltiness was perfect. Spicy noodle soup‚Äôs noodle and the soup were very well balanced. I would definitely come here again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYs9IA9ntiryCf_iH5tf4mZZGPC1UDeToksQ6O&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Steve B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfl0h7LBzTP2I19EaQ980hbd2gVAQ-0Kn286XLsVt3NEFo4W0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic Korean-Chinese restaurant! I have tried a few well-known Korean-Chinese restaurants (Heeraedeung, Chuihong, Mokran), and this one definitely competes with those that are my favourite. We ordered Ganjjajang, Guobarou and Gunmandu. Jjajang came with a fried egg and a shrimp tempura on top. Sauce was perfectly balances with saltiness and sweetness, lots of crunch onion pieces and big chunks of meat. Guobarou was delightfully crispy and meaty. Wonderful portion size with raw onion and Serrao peppers on the side to cut the richness. The crispi was lasted until my last bite. Gunmandu was crispy and packed with filling. You can tell there's a lot of thoughts went in to enhance flavours and customer experience. This has become one of my favourite spots and we will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXlTjvxd7uNO5JvJmPr1YW42O-UXN_nu90dgez&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Hyeonjin Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq_5Niw6_vOGJ1t98PmPXGiWLC5QW9gy12k8M5vGC5GBfyBZGn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered Combo A and it was absolutely delicious! Especially, jjampong was really flavourful with good amount of seafood and spice. The noodles came with prawn tempura on top which was unique. Recommend if you want good korean chinese food in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCfE9rkdwe366flRsP6tPaSax8nuJDYC-wX630&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Seunghoon Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJco2avqi0qfqFvGJWQxBmq-mkjU0lhL81N6HBRohekzVHhJw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently dined at Hwawon and ordered: Ja Jang Meon, Jjam Bbong, Jab Tang Bab, and Kkan Pung Gi. Each dish was impressively executed, with the Ja Jang Meon offering perfectly cooked noodles in a rich black bean sauce. The Jjam Bbong featured a robust, spicy broth with fresh seafood, while the Jab Tang Bab presented a balanced, savory blend of flavours. Also, the Kkan Pung Gi stood out with its crispy texture and flavorful sauce. Overall, a wonderful dining experience with attentive service. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNamWDmh0ALoCIN1cQO6MZLAK2XiNepXj1cuRoO&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"RUBY KIM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPj3_c2BjQE_GHSbl5NNgqCC71CfL6cEjGyHAXHVJziWQq0v2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Both crispy Tang su yuk, Urinki are so amazing!
The stir-fried flavor in the jjampong was bold and spicy, and the jajangmyeon was delicious too.
Good foods, Nice serviceü©∑","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRTg8cnPArFJO70eCDidGpzmNtfurym94qIuMD&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-20"}]

[{"Name":"Shiva Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzd9PGyiNJmwLm5yfA-sJl4BpBMAnWlGsSejcj9DY235f2_ZWo4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you‚Äôre looking for a place to enjoy delicious food and create lasting memories, this is where you need to be. Every visit feels like a treat, and the experience is as wonderful as the food.

Having visited many Persian restaurants in Greater Vancouver, I can confidently say this one is unmatched. From the moment you step inside, you‚Äôre greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere that immediately sets the tone for a memorable dining experience. The decor reflects Persian culture beautifully, creating a cozy yet sophisticated vibe.

Our friends and family come from all different backgrounds, but this restaurant has a way of bringing us together. No matter where we‚Äôre from, we all share a love for the incredible food and the warm, welcoming atmosphere here. It‚Äôs a place that feels like home for everyone.

The food is absolutely outstanding‚Äîevery dish bursts with authentic flavors, from the tender, perfectly seasoned kebabs to the aromatic saffron rice and hearty stews. The side dishes, like eggplants dips, fresh salads, and tangy yogurt dips, are equally delicious and pair perfectly with the main courses.

What truly sets this restaurant apart is the exceptional service. The staff are genuinely friendly, attentive, and always ready to make thoughtful recommendations. The chef‚Äôs skill and attention to detail are evident in every bite, and the management ensures everything runs smoothly, adding to the stress-free, enjoyable experience.

Whether you‚Äôre dining with family, celebrating a special occasion, or simply enjoying a night out, this restaurant delivers in every way. It‚Äôs not just a meal‚Äîit‚Äôs a journey into Persian culture and cuisine that leaves you excited to return for more.

We have dined here countless times, and each visit feels as special as the first. This place has never once disappointed us, consistently delivering a dining experience filled with warmth, flavor, and care.

The cleanliness of this restaurant, including its washrooms, is truly unmatched. It‚Äôs a reflection of the care and respect the team has for their guests, and it‚Äôs something we deeply appreciate. It‚Äôs rare to find such attention to detail, and it makes every visit even more comfortable and enjoyable.

A heartfelt thank you to the owners, the talented kitchen team, and all the lovely staff who make this place so special. Your hard work, kindness, and passion shine through in every detail, and we‚Äôre so grateful for the memorable experiences you create for us each time we visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMczAwKj4A_k1Za0keZhy-d5RactAuJsjO8MIQs&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a Turkish citizen, I decided to try this restaurant on the recommendation of my Iranian friend.
The dish we tried is called ‚ÄúKale Pache.‚Äù At first, it seemed like an unappealing meal, but with lemon and garlic, it was truly delicious. This restaurant prepares it exceptionally well. I‚Äôve had the chance to try it a few times in Turkey, but nowhere was as good as this place.
Secondly, I‚Äôd like to mention the cleanliness of the restaurant. Restaurants reflecting Middle Eastern culture usually look a bit shabby and not very modern. This restaurant was different; it was both very modern and very clean. When I asked to see their kitchen, I saw that everyone was working according to hygiene rules. Additionally, their kitchen was spotless.
Lastly, the owner of the restaurant hosted us wonderfully; he was very attentive. I haven‚Äôt had such delicious Iranian food in a long time.
I tried to think of a negative aspect, but honestly, there isn‚Äôt any. You must try this place.
They also offer other dishes besides Kale Pache.
Once again, I thank them for a lovely breakfast and their customer satisfaction-focused service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlo2r94f53qdKhg2n2HBwk-rYqotX-tFDPbO_5&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"JOANNE KADIR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5FtQlTqwnaEemJG-2BJY5ImgYhsbRGNlAyMyitnPajXzAiw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I went to Shemroon for lunch yesterday and I have to say, it was some of the best Persian food i've ever had! It was flavourful and authentic. My husband got the daily special, which was the celery stew with a bed of rice & I got the walnut stew, also with a bed of rice. We also tried their cucumber yogurt appetizer and it was so tasty! The atmosphere was so cute, I love the decor the owner chose for the store and the staff are so friendly. I was extremely happy with the service, and will definitely be back with my friends and family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPee-OFDpK2K4OsrZmG9aXxnyS5qydV-KqprIc&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Sean Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLa2nbdhfTAJwsejRS86C7FhvPUumsFGv-cHzJUBYr2iFqGJw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, warm ambiance, and awesome service. I ate here with two other friends and we all thought it was a great meal! Our server was very friendly and we enjoyed her suggestions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0PQ8ffrhN-6hmRD6tNqY-y4-Szyqo9npip6YC&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"pegah sedghi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJLiNV-UWi9udm3iXnF_xdi5sUEh1p7ESZZP-b8NmmVZr9yzw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had kalepache here, and I could say it was one of the most delicious one, the meat was well cooked, tasty and there was no bad smell. The bread was fresh, and the service was great, they behaviour was really friendly, and the tea after that in those glasses was great.
We are so thankful, Shemroon.
Unfortunately I forgot to take photo of the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCVHQxwknBRTr0bE_MH-4hgypr0zWsGChTL15M&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"amirali soltaniseresht","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4NItNzqz4vIRAjofhZXUA96PRthiJElTa31nxJnQMi0lTxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Shemroon and had the pleasure of trying their Vazirzi, and it was absolutely phenomenal!
The dish was a perfect blend of flavors‚Äîjuicy, tender skewers of lamb and chicken, beautifully seasoned and cooked to perfection. The saffron rice that accompanied it was fragrant and fluffy, making it a perfect pairing.

The ambiance of the restaurant was warm and inviting, with a traditional Persian touch that really enhanced the dining experience.
The staff was friendly and attentive, ensuring we had everything we needed.

Overall, if you‚Äôre looking for authentic Persian cuisine at Port Coquitlam, Shemroon is a must-visit. I‚Äôll definitely be back to try more of their menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP9kL87qKmKK1n-61Jx0xpsXZEMkXmALk_GWih&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Nima Ashrafkia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhCeBQhzwCFMHTX293urOtHgPZvp1N4dhP07LmlghewE6qkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Shemroon restaurant and was blown away by the authentic Persian cuisine. Every dish was a flavor explosion, from the perfectly grilled kebabs to the aromatic saffron rice. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, making it the perfect spot for both casual dinners and special occasions. The service was top-notch‚Äîattentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu. If you're looking for a true taste of Persian culture, this is the place to be. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfSvJnEkKP4h3Re6vWbBWdluHObgKKQtAkA5cn&fid=0x0:0xa44f41c917c99255"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Ferial Kabiri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNJSEzvc4IEHA3ToX2itau1biTjLXsZQYy6l6I_VjTX2j8eqY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tonight was my birthday at Shemroon restaurant ü•≥I can‚Äôt say enough about the incredible experience we had at this restaurant! From the moment we arrived, the service was outstanding‚Äîattentive, warm, and truly personalized. The staff went above and beyond to ensure everything was perfect.

The food? Simply phenomenal. Every dish was prepared to perfection, with flavors that left us speechless. You can tell they put thought and heart into every bite.

What made our evening even more special was the DJ they arranged just for us. It created the perfect ambiance and added so much fun to our celebration. It‚Äôs rare to find a place that nails the trifecta of amazing service, mouthwatering food, and exceptional entertainment.

Thank you for making our night unforgettable. I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a truly remarkable dining experience. We‚Äôll definitely be back!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped in for the first time in a long time actually. A friend of mine and myself were just going to stop in for a couple quick Beers, but decided on a couple Appetizers as well.

Had the Hot Wings and Salt and Pepper Dry Ribs, and both were actually very good, and great flavors on both of them.

After checking out the menu while having our first beers while waiting for our food to arrive, we definitely noticed that the menu was very nice with lots of different options to it. And lots of Gluten Free options as well since a friend of mine, as well as a few others I know definitely have problems with Gluten. ( Good to see ) As so many places don't really cater to that.

Also Orrange has a nice Gluten Free Beer as well. I had their own House Beer ( Lager ) that was pretty good. They also have Beer Flights and Margarita Flights as well.

Will definitely be back again, and bring some others along with us next time üòÄüëçüëç","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZGJGATFFuAYpoUIokeK4zkl6r3muGQxnN3Hln&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Shona Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_pDuq2IEOYnuAz5jc_iUm4vZrwZZuuI3aConifzRVQAv9FGWl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really enjoyed Orrange! Cute interior, friendly staff and tasty food. Cocktail menu wasn't incredible, but the wine was good. Will come back to try brunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh8Q4co7elXvu8jUVB_NVDD68mvgq9-gXJfW-I&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Will Desmarais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA0w2RDqHZeOd41COAUoFO6hnjotO4YccIPRzQzrfKQTCb31QR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Attended our company Xmas party. Service was good we were well looked after. Would definitely return. There was a shortage of steak and the staff went above an beyond too make it right. I couldn't be happier with the service and communication. Our server also treated the kids at our table with respect and even held the baby at one point. What a great overall experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jinnie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8gqt8IKnCRf4zl37GiLySrzoMAaxn28_yfYYzkVmL6ePwhw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"So I was there for a birthday party. Spent $150 and got the poutine to go‚Ä¶I think I count 6 pieces of cheese on my $15 poutine? I have not been there since it‚Äôs grand opening and my review remains the same‚Ä¶abysmal. Ordered deep fried pickles in the restaurant which was great. One server on a Sunday evening. Had to order via the bartender a few times but still got my orders at a timely manner. No complaints with the service‚Ä¶But this to go poutine had me at disgust. Will not be going back anytime soon‚Ä¶or ever.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwPzSJOyVyteL5QqYO9gjjGdN8MUga4DAgkPQm&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Zahra Tejpar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1CTlu2lI8PQ8gnAmixjyIsCtSXmQKDl1rHjt5y812Oda0Ww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Driven past the restaurant a few times but never really been in to try it out. It‚Äôs a very nice, clean restaurant. The ambiance was relaxing and enjoyable for us. We went here for happy hour. The staff were very friendly and helpful. The staff came by a few times to check on us. We tried the yam fries, chilli + lime chicken, and Korean fried chicken. It was really delicious and we left happy. A unique restaurant I would highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqbxFs_8Dnu0wgflWRFLU4ks6a1CCFqJ_MD4AO&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2023-4-30"},{"Name":"Kaitlyn Forester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkS1mVO5BCaF4vYxZsOQdUzbqxBXZ_kUF1c-SDQ-3HPYw5OR7q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My boyfriend took me here for date night last night and I LOVED it! I honestly don‚Äôt enjoy going out much, and although I don‚Äôt ever speak up or complain I feel like it‚Äôs been a long time since I‚Äôve been to a restaurant and everything‚Äôs just been enjoyable all throughout. This was one of those rare nights! The margarita flight was so yum and same with the sangria. The ribs, dill pickles and Yorkshire beef deep were also literally perfect. I wish I got our server‚Äôs name because she was SO lovely! Thank you guys again for such a good date night<3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVKhowrwMxC8CLpblw1iAfod41RPACmeva-SXP&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-4-23"},{"Name":"Daniel Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAxFTfz_ZYgM60gsStYArKOb4YgmHuHArMEsVm-TJD2WcKuo33=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This dining experience was a delightful surprise! We tried the Old School Spaghetti + Meatballs, Chili+Lime Chicken, Torched Butter New York Steak and Almost Famous Poutine, and they stole the show.

The crispy fries with just the right amount of gravy in the Poutine were a highlight, though a tad more cheese would have perfected it.  The steak was a crispy-tender delight, rivaling those at upscale downtown restaurants.

While the Old School Spaghetti + Meatballs lacked flavor, I wouldn't recommend it to anyone.

Not much to say about the Chili+Lime Chicken, it is a well made dish, but nothing special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNrR5Y8VOSYfX-rZRsNhpWYfbjfPvr_uUc1v60&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"Robert Cole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX83YQyO79dJPTx468i5SQq5-WjR3aJF2mZVO2kk8SSCEQjY6x7MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not sure where to start on this review. We arrived at 1:40pm. Brunch ends at 2pm as per their menu. We were quickly seated, but waited until after 2pm to have our order taken. They took my brunch order, came back and refused to serve us brunch because of the kitchen. Okay, so I ordered the Chicken and Waffles which is on their lunch menu. I asked if I could add eggs to the chicken and waffles and was told that the kitchen could not. Wait, what?! If a customer adds an egg to a burger, will they also say no? Its seems odd that they are unwilling to accommodate customers. I took off 2‚≠ê for both of those issues. The food was good, service was slow, and having to ask for coffee top-ups seemed like something that just added to my complaints. I've done a lot of reviews, and I usually try to be forgiving with concerns, but the service is unacceptable here. I won't be returning here anytime soon. Can't recommend at this time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-oMA0AFHBcWwp4ulRhvTvU_KC-OBfIJdMBqop&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2022-2-6"}]

[{"Name":"liberty facundo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNBp5rH1To4BVHWq1Mfj3iKJNDPtZ8CbWa3yq0RypDCjJicJtkRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went back to Cora‚Äôs after a long while of not eating here and I‚Äôd say nothing has changed in terms of menu. The portions are still pretty good though. We ordered two meals plus coffee and a strawberry banana smoothie. Everything came pretty fast except for the smoothie, it eventually got to us just before we finished eating. We asked multiple times and on the 3rd time I eventually told them to cancel since we were leaving and it finally made its way to our table üòÇ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5ShzMZ4vrxoEJh9xy45D97h8Pn4IqujvXSyeQ&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Y S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTmtWUtCZcs7qDdNKdjVbtcx5f5BcDfDU3YRp4zcFsXHKu1_WS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We have been to a couple different Cora in the past. This one is similar to the other ones when it comes to food and decor. The atmosphere is a bit dim, and could use some more light. The waitresses were working hard and serving everyone. We came on a weekday morning for breakdown and the restaurant was not even half full. Service was slow, so I wish it could be faster.
Food portion was huge and I couldn‚Äôt finish my food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeR34lpNB8jI3gquWa80NoA8iWSxrGkH_6Stq-&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Athena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxRdyVq8IaL3sj3MD9LrLk6g5ySnJURoeRwLHn6maKiEi-cDE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Portions were good, most of the food tasted pretty good and fresh, but the turkey sausage both my mother and I ordered tasted atypical. Had a bit of a sour aftertaste and off-putting texture, as if it had gone bad, but we were told it was fresh. The potatoes tasted okay but appeared very burnt on some sides yet didn‚Äôt taste fully cooked? Overall good portions though.
Service was lovely. Our server, Asia, was very sweet and did her best to take care of the turkey sausage situation. Very attentive and friendly!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Izmet Barranco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiQo1jy483UmDOGk0DLpOPmwFqDxOxzKBlrj-9MTXzn_Zhoww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cora is one of our default places. You will ALWAYS get good food. Service was good too.  I had the smoked salmon omelette which was fantastic. I also got the seasonal beet, strawberry, cucumber juice. It was tasty but a little on the sweet side. Seemed to me there was some sugar added, which I would had preferred not.

Overall though all was very yummy and it is always a good place to go","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq-iN23x9UPn3GuohlMnu11o5whB6fxViaQaL5&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2023-9-9"},{"Name":"Jenn G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNDOVgYon_axvacZ_mvoHqqTsa1nUbxI_LWx1GD2m9M5MmDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"TERRIBLE! DO NOT GO TO THIS CORAS LOCATION!  This is what I received when I ordered from DoorDash , and it was ice cold , over 20$ crepe and this is what they sent out , unbelievably dissatisfied","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-qUyRrhZEqNFlHfXk2cNjrHIGbwodXgQ9nOH0&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Vivien De paula mantovani joaquim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQVqZhANQr1FWr90HUIn1NJmqVGFj4vZ6ybTgy1-c9BPCKO1RIqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing place ‚Ä¶ the food is perfect .. polite and kind staff ‚Ä¶ clean and cozy‚Ä¶ I loved it","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcFuzKZeolfxG7UeoBSGPbi11vjM0ItFcTQzPZ&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Vivi Huynh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMQXaqA97j1efZZ95-88zCR3miBDJFxL0Uw-WoOvCOyZUP9VP_ZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time I came to Cora, and I'd say huge dessert-like breakfast menu. If you love sweets and fruits, Cora would be a quick, delicious breakfast place for you. There was some savoury options but to be honest, there were more sweet things than savoury. I had a April 89 crepe with half chocolate and half custard and the crepe was pretty good. I guess it wasn't the right choice for me though; it was a lot of sugar first thing in the morning which I should have thought about it so it was my bad. The fruit I really liked was the cantaloupe. Very ripe and sweet. The strawberry was a little sour and not really sweet but that's fine. All the other fruits were normal but the only one I really couldn't eat was the pineapple. It was almost like dry and flavourless. Also, it was a lot of crepe for me, so it'd probably be nice to share with someone. The person with the benedict didn't like the way the potatoes were done, it was like eating plain boiled potatoes, would prefer if it had some more crispness and season to it. Maybe if you ask for the potatoes to be done the way you'd prefer then you should do that. But overall the fruits were good except for a few that weren't, and the display of the food was spot on. Loved how they decorated the plates. The server was polite and nice and quick to serve us whatever we needed. I'd say it's nice enough to go back and try something else if I'm in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgwcWcIqYwV_-BbrvWiTxKE5th31f-r4SiUQx9&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2021-6-19"},{"Name":"Azi Jahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoCqSGFWxXVxJxNnyUrYmJjWJKEtREeG-G0RXpmBRv8kbELxEL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cora quality is the same in all branches so you don't have any difficulty on food's quality, it's always good.

Staffs are supportive and kind. We were a large group that reached there for brunch and they managed everything greatly.
üëçüèª","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPklye358qIIRWf5jRSpAE6kuEoClz-CzYrBEJs&fid=0x0:0x7e3c2850fb634809"],"When":"2022-6-30"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried the salted crispy chicken with noodle soup, the pan fried vegetable dumplings, and the steamed pork buns. I would say everything was okay but tasted very average and standard. Nothing was spectacular but everything was acceptable. The pan fried vegetable dumplings were unique with lots of veggies inside but the food quality was just okay. The prices are fair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEopXt7P9XaO398Ux0W5VH1g9lKsBQCc7hMr8Z&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a family-owned Shanghainese restaurant that offers a variety of authentic dishes, including classics like Xiao Long Bao (soup dumplings) and Sheng Jian Bao (pan-fried buns). The food arrived quickly and was served piping hot, showcasing the kitchen‚Äôs efficiency.

The Xiao Long Bao were exceptionally juicy, with flavorful broth and perfectly seasoned, firm filling, although it does have thicker skin than Wangs in Vancouver. The Sheng Jian Bao, a delicious pan-fried bun, had a crisp bottom and was packed with savory soup, offering a wonderful balance of textures. Another bonus was, it wasn‚Äôt too oily.

I‚Äôve tried the dan dan noodles and the peanuts were crunchy and provided an enjoyable contrast to the softer dishes. The noodles were slightly overcooked.

Bean paste noodles - huge portion and really flavorful.

Overall, the meal was satisfying, and the prices are reasonable for the quality and location.

This restaurant is truly a gem for anyone craving authentic Shanghai-style cuisine in the area. I‚Äôll definitely be returning to explore more of the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuxP5sLptB9ZcK4lC3Yc_W2-sYcT90eCwG1NlC&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Absolut YVR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAKKuJBhDjQ2yvrY0bCIOExStNeMzrxg1x0ksL6cHk4jqCNjYH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very simple , family owned Shanghainess restaurant.  Offering typical dishes like Xiao Long Bao and Seng Jian. (Soup buns and pan fried buns) Plenty of parking in the Henderson mall, this small restaurant is located in the heart of Coquitlam center.
Food came out quickly and hot. XLB was very juicy and tasted good. Stuffing was firm.  Seng Jian is a yeast type of pan fried buns.  Not much juice inside, yet very crunchy bottom. We tried a couple of the appetizers. Both of them are very good. Beef tripes and beef stomach are very tasty with enough spices which are suitable for most customers.  Personally,I can take a bit more heat on these dishe.  Peanuts were crunchy and gave a very good contrast of texture.  Overall, very good meals. Prices are acceptable for this area. One waiter was working during the non peak time. He got it under control. This restaurant definitely is a find of Shanghai style food in these areas. Will come back to try some other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPowPqVAQWIZmJTPGCbcenvK5pqxV7JGG_1LrFs&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Eagleridge He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyk6k_xeBUj_1KDLC2dilz6BOL-9JcNSoxnyXWuMM0QdJPvjOF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôve passed by this area quite often and only recently realized this place has a new owner. The inside is not quite big but enough to take about two dozens of people at the same time. Typical like many Chinese business makes you feel the floor is sticky and greasy. Server is super nice and friendly.
We ordered the Dan Dan noodle, spicy wonton, cold pig ear appetizer and fried bun. Overall tasty foodüëç Dan Dan noodle is not authentic Sichuan style but cooked right with a hint of shrimp sauce. Fried pork bun is very juicy inside with crunchy bottom. Cold pig ear with the garlic sweet and sour sauce is perfectly balanced in flavour and also cooked right to maintain its crispy texture. Spicy wonton is also adequately seasoned and the stuffing inside is tender and moist.
Compare this with the other similar restaurants in the Coquitlam centre area, this one so far I think is my favourite. Highly recommend ‚úåüèª","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPR7T1HRSYoe7KouNA4KPd0pKLjaJxYJUSpYZ1A&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-11-8"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Reminds me of Wang's Shanghai cuisine near Joyce. Affordable meals. Good food.

XLB - the skin is a little thicker but I didn't mind.

Dan dan noodle - gigantic portion. Great value. Not very nutty. The noodle could be less cooked to provide a bouncier texture.

Zha jiang noodle - also gigantic portion. Lots of meat sauce. Same noodle note.

Salt pepper chicken - $15 is pricey for a side dish but it did come with plenty of pieces. Taste was ok but fried very well with light crispiness.

The waitress was super friendly. I would like to come back to try their pan fried buns too.

One thing I am wary off is that they already raised the prices even though they recently opened. I hope this doesnt come frequently.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBKol3GnJ58qbwEfIbTrQmUDOncPgjvPvAX4ee&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-6-12"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Juicy and relatively big xiao long bao (steamed pork bun), I believe it was 6 for $9.99, but a bit lacking in taste. The spicy wonton in chili oil was a bit better and it wasn‚Äôt too spicy and much tastier. The beef noodle soup had no much taste but the meat was soft and plenty. Overall, the food and service was just ok. It‚Äôs conveniently located by the Coquitlam Library and Coquitlam Centre. There is a covered garage for your parking needs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkvj6uE_L1Id5WfwSfKpETnHabM3WaK8bHbCFn&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"ComicÂêç‰ΩúÂæ©Ê¥ª","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB807F1BS9C6IboDeJfeD8CJ-GjsvEK8ZHJI2Ry5ZDUkuF8BoWmQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want to taste delicious and authentic Chinese noodles, this is the best I have tried in the Greater Vancouver area. The owner is very enthusiastic and uses high-quality ingredients. Each person can eat to be really full with an average spending of 15-20 CAD. There is also an indoor parking lot nearby, so you can park your car and walk there within 1 minute. If you don't know what to order, I highly recommend trying the pan-fried dumplings (item A7) on the menu. It's worth driving for half an hour just to have those. The second recommendation is the steamed soup dumplings (item A1). If you like noodles, both the beef noodles (item B4) and the spicy dan dan noodles (item B2) are great choices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwlkeNxp8Dh9rLQ8AZ-Cw9Bt5qFimsz2SyzT2I&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-10-7"},{"Name":"Sara Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlSF6ADXHgyatqSj3RdRyjxWuJp2qz8rnQN-QdhLw0IaUlXFq2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Grand opening, so let‚Äôs go

we‚Äôve ordered pork chop noodles, dan dan noodle, salted fried chicken and spring rolls.  The pork chop and chicken is really good, crispy coating with juicy meat, we like the noodle texture is al dente, We would like the dan dan noodle to be more spicy, and the filling of the spring rolls is a bit too wet, other than that, we enjoyed the dinner very much, the lady who serve us are very friendly and helpful, we would definitely refer this restaurant to our friends","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBf9LHpkK_HZFEZELMjhQL0xT_sUMttsL7dVC-&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2022-10-1"}]
