user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Joseph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXbztcvJy0AIdqJzTOyFSntteOTg-h_qvbqjBrQ7R6H-ALXJr1JA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Of the Uyghur restaurants in Greater Vancouver still in business, this might be the best in terms of food quality and flavors. But there's a big caveat:

Be prepared to wait for a long time! With only one person in front of me, I still waited at least 20 min just to get my order taken and maybe another 20 min to get food. Some people who got in line shortly after me, didn't get to put in their order until sometime after I got my food. Meaning they probably waited 40 min just to order and who knows how long to eat.

This is because there's only one person (owner/operator?) working, who seems to come out to the front to take one or two orders, before disappearing into the kitchen for extended periods of time, hand pulling noodles and ensuring the food is as fresh as can be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6WA01U2fkQwvPSsJsMBVWnmcpb8dG78rjzNao&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Ryan Blight","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbpH73lI2xtK9WJxadw5s8Ist4ItI3NEBYZImc9aopB1Hhs9lf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time here and ordered the lamb shank with naan (menu #5). The lamb was tasty, but small portion. The bread portion was large, but quite hard texture. Fun to try, but wouldn't go out of my way to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNd7s8qRWgN_NekyShJi_banfr0VF74TJeXzT8X&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Stephen Jackson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWSabsYlgcq7pedZrrlJQtd6yY9XJwQ1Hy3QeRvPyBgE78_whI1Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food that's worth the wait and the setting.

It's set in a food court, so it's not like you're in the greatest of surroundings.  However, the food is more than worth it.  Went for the polo (lamb shank with rice) and a samsa (meat-filled pastry).  The samsa was delicious, and I would happily come again to buy 5 and take them away.  The portion of the polo was huge, the lamb tender, and the rice very flavourful, especially with the spicy cucumber salad mixed in, which added a bit of heat.

Don't come expecting fast food (its setting in a food court is a bit deceptive in this sense).  It does take a little while to get it (probably 15 mins for me, and I came at a quiet time of day).  But, I would much rather wait the time to get good quality food, than get instant food which was reheated / prepared poorly etc.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI-TbiA148s9Ddb0GyN_XZykDzr3fyxfn9zt4C&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"judy wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJT81G3KLQSjfqtTMAT9IHU_NfAgkAmzPpPLN2CsXTwBRAeBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a crave for ÊâãÊäìÈ•≠„ÄÇdid some googling and decided to try here which was the best decision of the day. We went a little before lunch time so the wait was not bad at all. ÊâãÊäìÈ•≠ was just fantastic. My husband ordered the soup, bread and lamb leg and it was just beyond the word. We ended up taking extra five bread home to share with friends and families. The owner is doing everything by himself including taking orders, prep of the food and serving it over the counter. So I understand it will take some time if it‚Äôs really busy. But definable worth the wait and drive!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxtxEQF3e3yIGulzImQI98imE328VDkMGYQXUN&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Amazing food. Poor experience. The entire operation is done by a single person, who appears to be cooking and on phone the entire time. He seems withdrawn and uninterested in taking orders from anyone. The wait for food is VERY long, almost 30 minutes for a bowl of lamb shank and nan. The lamb shank is super tender and the soup is very flavourful with a hint of spiciness. There could be more meat though. The nan is excellent, especially dipped into the soup. Unfortunately, I can't recommend this place due to the slow service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7TTuDTiSRVzXDv4-dn6uwcTqK7XQnEca6pi5M&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried the lamb shank with naan! The soup that comes with it tastes fresh and super hot! Lamb shank is juicy and soft.

The naan was crazy good, it was crispy on the outside and soft inside. Great for dipping with the soup, I wish there was more lamb sauce that came with it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjybpAz_um9IGqMZH_euQN_2H-1m6cyYW-lZaK&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-1-31"},{"Name":"Murat Arsin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKc6H-T457-oBccqNDru1kc6Jimk0kU403UqpJeWtj4Hgnawg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is real boutique place just for Uyghur cusine, as the owner does everything byhimself, it brings the real taste of Uyghur cusine.
Samsa and Somen is highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9tlahV-8SfTuzYMCibIrLR5vqlxFyRIHuurgZ&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"rayyan mansoor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIb6H6Bi4fHrAdb51oLLHmTed679NLLQywCKJ4cPUmMnfR5tA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is amazing, quality of ingredients as well as just the combination of flavors is awesome and to get anything similar you would have to travel hours.

Anyone complaining about how long it takes should order in advance rather than post invalid reviews, food like this HAS TO TAKE TIME which is why it tastes how good it is, if you can‚Äôt wait this long for something out of this world go get fast food.

City is blessed to have such a talented chef willing to share his food.","Images":null,"When":""}]

I recently ordered takeout from Hearthstone Pizza and was blown away by their unique Korean-style pizza. The flavors are incredibly distinct and delicious, featuring a wonderful blend of traditional and innovative toppings that make each bite exciting. The quality is top-notch, with fresh, vibrant ingredients that elevate the entire experience.

The customer service here also deserves a shout-out. The staff was exceptionally friendly and knowledgeable, offering great recommendations over the phone and ensuring the ordering process was smooth and easy. The pizza was ready right on time and still hot when I picked it up, which was fantastic.

If you're in the mood for something uniquely delightful and packed with flavor, I highly recommend Hearthstone Pizza for a takeout experience that goes above and beyond. Definitely a must-try for anyone looking to explore Korean-style pizza with excellent service!

[{"Name":"Debby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVj1FDmxBaGck5J8K_6foLYNC59Bk0g1TlSH1h2iqnrvGDOlREc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I accidentally tipped twice.
I ordered online and paid in store.
My order already had a tip included, but their machine does not recognize this, so it asks you for a tip. I thought maybe I made a mistake, so I added a tip. When I checked back at my car, I tipped on top of the amount that was already tipped, which means my second tip was based on the previous amount which included the tip. My 2nd tip, although same percentage was higher than the first tip. Not really happy about that, but now I know.

Asides from that, The cheese just is not cheesy. Almost like there is not enough cheese, or not seasoned right.

The presentation looks great.
The pizza was warm, crust was crispy.
Lots of veggies and meat.
My kids were ultimately happy about the pizza.

The staff was friendly.
They labeled the boxes, which I like because my son can't have tomato anything, so he had a separate pizza.

The missing star is because the cheese is just not cheesy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPibqZRuT1yML5oGaW7JRphug16QtnE7ZWFnJHC&fid=0x0:0xcfb41ac83671b9ff"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Phil Dufault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXddvyUjgQ_YO8GzkQuPay08OzzxyL4QPIRtWGcejX9JSKQFISI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm a regular. They've called me before when I have messed up my order, saving me both time and from disappointment.  I love their gluten free pizzas, crust is always crispy and the options are all pretty delicious. I recommend in particular the Chef Created Special, but everything is good.

My kid and wife love their gluteny options, pizza, wings, etc.

Give them a try, you'll be surprised. They make a better pizza than most.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mithila Karnik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh7y26jxgrcv2234K17s4LRS1t5EoXQp4TUPik7Ky5HNK7bWg_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best pizza I have had in PoCo that has the perfect ‚Äúdesi‚Äù flavours - our house favorites are the Three Musketeers and Taste Of India and we always go for adding on cilantro and ginger! The owner is amazing and service is spot on! Our regular and loved pizza place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHb3kgAZ1zh7lq6KxmqUUIt5wY73oWFc1xGKx8Xs6V7ttovemaIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent pizza, tasted fresh, and reasonably priced. Dough was great, toppings were evenly distributed, and even my girlfriend who doesn't like pizza's LOVED it.

My newest go-to pizza place in PoCo","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"lekha chhibba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5IZOD4JsMGF5_7w1R7tCN0PqrFQWQWiv9D61QkTEi5u0oCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had gone in for a meal and I regret it!! The absolute worst service! Excessive wait time, very rude staff, they are way too aggressive to speak with. The management really needs to work on training the staff on being a lot more respectful and polite! The food tasted unfresh and stale.. the place was extremely dirty.. and at the end of all of it, it's almost like they demand a tip, by repetitively saying, "oh no tip, no tip, sure?"
The place needs to either shut down or hire trained staff.

THERE ARE RODENTS IN THE STORE

It‚Äôs just horrible
With extremely disrespectful staff
Unexpected behaviour specially in canada","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dzenan J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXISZzTTcEVuyEWrUryNmL3YO_uwsvWO2Vmr-BxuaFzs5nMBEbgsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Large variety of pizzas, wings, pasta... The pizza is done in about 10 minutes so your wait won't be long but even if it is, you'll have a nice conversation with the staff. Comfortable seating and great location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpbqpKX7evKHsUGR2L1OyC-t84vxzEIAOTWaxM&fid=0x0:0xcfb41ac83671b9ff"],"When":"2020-2-9"},{"Name":"Mabel Castillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXI0sqw58dyQd6ULFtkPWOxij_VUv8D1Tqc87P_riBkAXx8HJR6xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious!! We ordered a small butter chicken pizza and it's so delicious! Also, crust is crunchy on the outside and fluffy on the inside, perfect! Very recommendable!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXDQfonII9ESOQmHtQxGEhrNJbrro3VpOS5E_A&fid=0x0:0xcfb41ac83671b9ff"],"When":"2022-10-25"},{"Name":"Tejas Medury","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVskEGAJ3WcMJMbXOuku1ttOHMDr2cbEoL30JxsWS9du-HqQ8L0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite pizzas in all of British Columbia and the staff are extremely friendly and incredibly accommodating to my customization!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pork burger and cold noodles are pretty good. I think lamb burger has lots of room for improvement. Meat was too hard to chew. In general, it‚Äôs nice to have this choice of Chinese street food here in Coquitlam. Keep working on the quality please!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAPGaY3irSFKuVpKjsYOUBsSZrssFCW0ZgVVDZ&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Cynthia Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzeJkq7FGsDfGgQXJWjS-SJOYYhnjPNUtm2wbKTNa_uJ8TyBMm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The burgers (more meat buns in my mind) were delicious and extremely juicy. The price is extremely affordable especially given how  substantial it is. 2 would be too much unless you're starving.

The lamb soup was surprisingly big. I thought it was just the broth, but it's a meal with tofu, lamb meat (a little dry but still good), and a few pieces of noodle to go with the bun.

I'll definitely come back in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gooseberry Bilberry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMJD-L9WmQytMhbODZNa3Nz3Kk8Z3fxnupE5Xvb8JG11rhZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered the Traditional Pork Belly Burger and the Braised Beef.  The cashier asked us if we wanted onions and chilli and we said no.  It turned out that the pork had no sauce at all and the taste was minimal.  It did not resemble the picture as shown online.  The Braised Beef was a lie (they gave us slices of beef shank instead of chunks of beef).  It was not braised; it was cold. You can check the photos on Uber Eats and Fantuan for the correct version. We were shocked by their misconduct.

Traditional dishes should not be altered and the cashier should not have asked us for modifications. How would you feel if the server asked you if you wanted bacon for Carbonara?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPs9nG1C-hVMn_YVN_kZk-oEQDEXHAp2hNAgIL8&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Amrita Nayak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgJ3b8LMBlPc7G1Rv8sy6cyH33IeJwYGYkw6c-i8ocBKF5odAKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We happened to walk pask this little kiosk inside Henderson mall and the menu caught our eye. We tried the lamb burger and we were very pleasantly surprised. No fillers, large portions of meat grilled juicy chunks of meat.
The burgers buns were pretty interesting and complimented the lamb very well. The buns tasted like a mix of paratha and bread.
This is a nice no frills place to grab a quick bite if you are in the area. Bonus - the terrace parking is free and it has pretty scenic views of the mountains.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhKcxCIz-Anvq5ip1ddI-7F5qC7kMykaHZpGAm&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2023-1-30"},{"Name":"David Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQn39r3brDL0VPq82Yr56T560Nm6tJ3AgkaLNo-GnVazotTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time trying this place and the service attitude is definitely 5 stars. Strong first impressions.
In terms of food, i got combo 2. The food here will be on the more salty/tasty side. Even the soup is heavily peppered. It suited my craving at the time so definitely 5/5.

I will be back to try it out again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuMBikXIet1rwoeR9DJqT_JR6_-tum0Nztj6QC&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2021-8-13"},{"Name":"L Q","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVtfWsdEk1EloorlnyAlXRuIG1y--1n0_hw_A-ZEXtjHCW1fU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"best chinese burger everrrrr! I live in richmond and have tons of chinese food all the time there, but no chinese burgers in richmond are comparable to this one. highly recommend the lamb burger, the tofu&egg burger (has a spicy sesame dressing) its so yummy. the pepper soup is good as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2cPBqQXXUqQZNeDq-0V32m6GA03RXFv_aqD3-&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2021-12-21"},{"Name":"Canucks rulz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3jtN7ZO2-RuhLqwAuEHna8L5B2XEBRrNmRUJeJaZ-sOfpYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried the Spicy Lamb Burger 2 days ago.  It was so good that I had to go back today and try the Traditional Pork Belly Burger and it did not disappoint.  I got one for my co-worker and she loved it as well.  She was shocked when I told her it was from the Henderson Place Mall Food Court.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9YQmsmKhqCSvMVPAZKT18eImIWQ2QjEOLJi24FjTkNMSIg53C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried the beef burger and the pork burger. The pork one was more moist than the beef. Both were very flavorful and spiced well. It reminds me of soup bones that your mother would use when making soup..and then they would take that meat, spice it up and pan fry it a bit and put it in between a bun. But they're tasty!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxqNe-kvjJFZ5Q0YRrjQMluin_SQdXq2W6v44l&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2021-9-29"}]

[{"Name":"Philip Raymond Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5EIBAgpBLsauhPMdjXym7mJ4fA8mtryDtWQIJCZfJxYXxupU8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Hansol seems to be a newer spot in town, offering great value with large portions. The taste, however, can be hit or miss. The beef bibimbap was enjoyable and well-prepared. Katsu is standard. Tempura is good. The bone soup lacked depth of flavor and was overpowered by spiciness. They do offer complimentary pumpkin soup, which was decent but not particularly memorable. Rice is very good. Overall, it‚Äôs worth a try for the portion sizes and value, though there‚Äôs room for improvement in flavor balance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7m7hbyxnfZJxK2Fvd6uuXD0kLrSVu3uRkycl-&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a pretty great Korean restaurant and we were thoroughly impressed by their food and service. They gave us some sweet pumpkin soup as a free appetizer which is always great! The texture was spot on and the flavour was subtle and delicate while being slightly sweet.

The side dishes were also quite tasty with not much to knit pick. The fried shrimps were decent but I could tell that it wasn‚Äôt their specialty.

But rest of the dishes were fantastic. My personal favourite was the Korean beef tartare. The beef soup was also very rich and flavourful. Finally, the intestine soup is not for the faint of heart, but it was savoury and spicy, just the way we like it.

Overall, we would definitely come back and try other menu items when we get the chance and we encourage you to try this place out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtMBNYjwqeLDnv1NwTnGPEUrJkm6t-6R5v1Wje&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"K H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVo2hR2qKHBGSuFyVVc1kqvuNnr23GVLd19IdZCsiU8tz8tbtW-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very impressed with the food here. It tastes like homemade quality and authentic Korean food. We loved the chicken wings and beef bulgogi. Banchan was great too. They are quite small inside and don‚Äôt take reservations. It was a longer wait for a 6 table on a Friday night so I would recommend going in smaller groups. But the food is really worth it. The service is by two older Korean man and woman and they work very efficiently and very hard.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMc3HGCCmg40DS3WNjXj6X3-AfC2ZapBmq8JPIm&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice small family restaurant.  I love the beef tartare and portion is very generous.  Spicy tofu soup is great too.

Complementary pumpkin soup is a warmhearted gesture.

Not recommend big party more than 4 people and good to have comfort food in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXHyraGjUlZA4zKuHJ5tY_Oagy3_CzwYGg52jH&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Jenn A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDNY1epuqFb0vEhEwK9bhTQ1dFwhkq_RQVEWkys2fxRxs7SO6V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place. Starter soup was delicious and the dishes we had were comforting. Donkatsu was so crispy and sweet potato noodle dish. Wings were a hit. Kimchi pancake had a crunchy crust.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3XJihg4gTXBUng6g9bCnJ9RIXo1l89npXooy3&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Arpitha Rao Annaji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrqsdkrs5T063w39fOONriV-UZmIT3JlCpCdqaNPFpHi43Hf6Hew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great little Korean restaurant! We ordered everything without meat (vegetarian)  bibimbap hot, tofu and mushroom soup, steam eggs and the best pumpkin soup on the house !! Loved everything so much!

This came with a side of rice and banchan ! (We‚Äôre obviously K-Drama and K-Food fans!)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPpcTDTEJv0T18wz-euaJTIlf74Bg8XyYJJ86b&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"justinmctavish","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEYVdRqmE_3oMTj7PunlTi-aFJRLulUFCNb37Cg7axAP4W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really like this place. I have been to many Korean restaurants in the area and this is by far the best. Small homey restaurant and super friendly staff. Feels like you are walking into someone‚Äôs home for an amazing home cooked meal. Every dish we have ordered has been outstanding!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQTcpEQfGkAEpAn03EUg0UV4wCAvlwChugK54&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Joe Caldow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPY1xctTIatziKXhwQ1piit73bdq1GENeVWggh9AnOsK3UZYpU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was amazing and service was incredible! Our family of 4 really enjoyed eating here.

I think it is a husband and wife couple that owns and runs it and they are the kindest people. When you get up to leave the hold the door open for their customers. He even held the door open for the Skip the Dishes driver that was there to pick up an order.

Very impressed and we will definitely be back!

Thank you for the great experience!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We finally tried Sweet Tiger's viral corn dogs and were thoroughly impressed! Ordering was seamless, with plenty of delicious options. We opted for the ultimate combo: half mozzarella, half sausage, topped with crispy potato and spicy sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeKsNz2IX6OS_mYCMj48M_swl1gUVYlxoe1MkA&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Located in the food court.  They ran out of cheddar cheese sauce so i ordered cheddar cheese powder and condensed milk.  You can have up to 3 toppings.  I also chose potato half and half corn dog.  With the price, i think sausage can be a bigger as the deep fried potato shell almost felt off half way instead of sticking with the sausage.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoKxUrTFQyL4j1cHwcsTKIgc6nXHGMBZw69xoK&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Sarah Yun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiczomq9QiXcqt71gzFXNKtuNZ7J-cpBOUdWhjtq9O9ILhF95e=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sweet Puffs' taste is the best in Vancouver, I usually order red bean and custard sweet puffs. Especially, red bean is not too sweet but so good! Cheese balls are very chewy, and Corn dogs are very crispy and yummy!! I really recommend it here!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM93a5T1lvEweZ3KriylvvQg7EM44SFe7IDnpG7&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Haerin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzvl1TEgLbmLgUGPLTOm6uWgtLU7DgTOaXCc47iibFb2LKWKE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best korean corndog in Vancouver and the redbean walnut pastry was also quite decent but few things you can take into consideration:

- When Customers are taking orders, ask how heavy or light they want the sauces to be on their corndogs. Mine was too saucy and it was overpowering.

- Put sauces on the side by default for takeout orders. My corndog got extremely soggy from all the sauces when I got home.

- The chopstick used for corndogs is too fragile. I ordered potato one and as I was holding it, I felt like the weight of it could easily break the stick.

- I was expecting the red bean walnut pastry to have nice crunch on the outside which was lacking. I hope the texture could improve a bit more since the flavour was totally on point.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX1VUXigTe1WrB2Uigghzbp44W7mqtTLKOua4Z&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Sue Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZ2EvZcUR-dfMDNY2VYPR1Z7MkBxqVhywlTTvbNTJFa5OcfSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is really awesome place for simple but yummy treats located by food court in Henderson mall, Coquitlam.
They have all different kinds of walnut cakes, hot dogs, cheese balls & special potato chips!
Any family, kids, even single could eat in there with very comfortable atmospheres.
We will come back again definitely more often for their  delicious foods and services.
Thank you for your serving, Sweet Tiger üòÄ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYHFl2AGq4eOPCQWXpHWcOGnb60k0XGwnUQlVC&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Saiya Yesmurzayeva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISiwtD9i4c1MNjLPrzx-OLYfUHniYq4GA5lFzoYMQMhIHMxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"it was incredibly crispy and full of flavor. The coating had the perfect crunch. I also gave the cocoa version a go, and to my surprise, it added a delightful twist with its rich, slightly sweet taste. The combination of savory and sweet was unexpectedly delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHvVuLRFUK3Ct3YlCwLfidoKvY1WlTLTTt96IQ&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"T Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV9O3iMvTpJunTNFo_HCtc8IFcoY_51SfTuPQACZh_FArdyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hot dog was soooo CRISPY and size was HUGE! The mozzarella cheese is so chewy and yummy.
Red bean sweet puff filled up with 80% of read bean and big piece of walnut! It was an amazing experience! Definitely I will come back for other puff and hotdog!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipON8E5EW7JrLbJ_kakdA1oB_qDT_jNa0t9UEqQ2&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"C S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKUfjSjSQ8TtxeVtpugr4HMqpSJ9RDlOmn7ek9WdL5q4b7GbHA4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Well packaged and portioned for a reasonable price! Product was prepared promptly and was a very enjoyable experience!

Pictured below is the fruity cereal and the original corndogs","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgBO16-MElivZmbma3XP1Fwos-JzxUIxqEXi9F&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-7-21"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Cinthia Carter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxCKtnLXcRtOq8N3koaZfmHaE8dGxh16NKhaW2jHYv2KMggWER=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered a delivery of the Chicken Briyani and Vegetable Pakora. Sizes are generous and tasteful. Comes with yogurt dip and sweet sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwQCorKsyXVqRtyeS_eUWRsZNmPiiBLHb7_OF0&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Gen Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0x4Eq9GRWvX9EA38H3GMWPqz4gj6UZw48zS61frnmQ0-oj3E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered take out for the first time at Spice Cart Indian Cuisine and we‚Äôll definitely order again! Great service as well, I had a question in regards to ordering and the person I was talking to on the phone and when I picked up our order was very friendly and helpful!

Everything we ordered was delicious and the portions were great! We ordered the mixed grill, jeera aloo, vegetable samosa, vegetable pakora, butter chicken, chicken curry, lamb curry, daal makhani, rice pulao and family size garlic naan. We ordered the rice pulao but the name written on the container was vegetable pulao which was still good but I wanted the flavour of the rice pulao as described in the menu.

We ordered for 6 adults and a few kids and that was plenty with leftovers. Love the option of family size naan too!

Various spice levels to choose from. I personally prefer the mild spice level as there is a bit of a kick to it already but we also tried the mild-medium and medium for a couple of the curries.

I was a little confused with the name though I thought it was Spice Art but found their website as Spice Cart. I had to check a few times before placing my order to ensure I was ordering from the location I wanted. Maybe they‚Äôre going through a name change?

Definitely recommend Spice Cart Indian Cuisine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORhwg6Z106k-utRilMEv5ub_jGowvjp5aiZZSG&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2023-8-9"},{"Name":"Andrea Montalvo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM85_tvYyazq3zpCbhXaoxAHQ8AFH9PyvgEoJARteWjTICLgM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service and food is so delicious and fresh. Their lunch special is something u can‚Äôt find anymore these days, such a great deal with more than enough food to fill one or even 2 people up!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGIcZSqsUP5fdacxYTpcTJcbncd7cC6yQtM_U&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Lu Kong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiVMtuHct0ut1Io0IRXiCox51SyCX5BuI9wBm4XQtwUdKlKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome!! Garlic naan is a must. Ordered butter lamb and chicken, prawn masala, fish pakora, chilli chicken and chicken roganjosh. Chai and mango lassi to finish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9ccpxZ5691vQJEqECNY6TQO-pNlZCzh_Dgxm5&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Aliah Penner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1TDYmKUFrTjDo4d_P5m90F8ZGophb_NfpYjPdV2J8RCVU6pmp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys are awesome. I consistently get the lunch special which is a good portion size at an exceptional price. Today I took my wife for dinner and we each got a butter chicken along with the "family size" garlic naan.

I was not prepared. Attached is a pic with a full size dinner plate for scale. Words cannot adequately describe this behemoth. It COVERS the lunch tray on which it is served. I'm not the type to take pictures of my dinner, but I was stunned.

Um, so suffice it to say the food is excellent and tasty, the portioning is incredibly generous for the very reasonable prices, and the service is great. Our family loves this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlfb_uW48LRZi-xtmIrSzaiHcSmtVDW4FaBnk6&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"EVAN ETHAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUx4wFf5gaB1lR1A8XX5kn8xelbVXHG8-xFycDrpZ-n6j0ewpV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TRICITIES HIDDEN GEM! Cosy causal Indian restaurant. One of the best in Tricities - Taste, authentic, portions, value & friendly service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0idsX1GkRrscRGEncB95mVmsU5uPRDgqsye7-&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food, value for money, and quick service, definitely a must visit. The restaurant has a lunch menu from 12pm-3pm each day with vegetable, chicken, paneer, and lamb combo ranging from $7.99 to $9.99. The combo comes with plenty of naan and a side of rice. The butter chicken was great with three large pieces of chicken and a buttery sauce with a slight hint of spicy. Dine in available. Located within plaza with parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOj1P-OKcJcIcVrjY0aY6npDxo6ixOAS77FMnzY&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2022-12-31"},{"Name":"Dilsher Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNMNLx9r_56qC0KfTM3Gvi9WvSjeIJDuQMhdv0AgCMlUgAwg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Indian food in town by far . Spice Cart service and food quality it second to none . Ash and staff are very accommodating and prices are very good . Always make me feel at home and go extra mile . I strongly recommend to try Spice Cart for unforgettable experience. Thank you Spice Cart . Keep up the great work !","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Sunny Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI24WPvgM-FfIlJLLr7IedglAHWoUtLRiaKg7As2_gjZs7wTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I worked at lots of Japanese restaurants all over Canada for all most 15years. I just found my go spot whenever I come to Port Coquitlam. Hands down üëç üòç
If you are sushi lover, won‚Äôt be disappointed here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-vyyowiFAyY0Gcda7FFUG_B6I9YBYmOKTO6-7&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Bill knox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSRV11XH3-3P7ySnqI01hySFkx75lkH_2ysCH7LkCeT5zF-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This should really be a fine dining restaurant. Exceptional food and service. What more can I say? Lots, apparently. Every dish is carefully crafted, not just thrown together. There was a remote-controlled light buried in the ice to high light the sashimi, and the server showed us all the different combinations to the delight of everyone, especially my 6 year old grandson. We're very surprised when  we were presented with deep fried ice cream. Delicious.
Food is key, but for me, service is always the lock that makes the meal. All the servers waited on all the tables. There was never an empty plate on the table and if the food was ready the first available server brought it.
That is what makes a first class restaurant, first class.
I will always go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCCHGqeHwmdR-Ci0vBcZx3zIorHb2hjpaNN9iB&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Stacey Robinsmith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_qFQLK010t5gOeaOzVIwWOPcgI7YdNFJni03OtXqoh_08R4sIAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kosho Sushi is a littlest treasure out in Port Coquitlam. Beautifully prepared and inventive sushi and sashimi at reasonable prices. I was very pleased with my meal at Kosho.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdr6lPpr5NkL1VSyjPq5BpayThmxigiz0TjCi_&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"L Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQvIh5w41NvNm69uuQ6fEFfx4_xCLgbz-lb793dTjac89L3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want fresh sashimi and sushi in Port Coquitlam this is definitely the spot to be at.  The sockeye salmon sashimi was fresh and delicious and presentation here is excellent making the whole experience very enjoyable.  The California roll and spicy salmon rolls were equally enjoyable.  If you come at lunch you can get lunch portions at a reasonable price.  For the price point it definitely is a must try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvhX_vpggJiL0Kmp4k48_WtKhbXe1TZ7FJUKeP&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Chan Andy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP8ZIfapwxhfTSOijijHjaOYybbetMTtbDMDr_n7A2U-HLr8E-jA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good food, very good presentation and very polite staff. Despite a little pricey, we still like the food here. The menu was complicated and had no picture, they promised they will come up with a new menu soon, hope it happens.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSDe1QEzN-mbqc7yqGx8k7BpaZuG0JEljHCFx9&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Last man eating‚Ä¶

In the area picking up something from a customer and options for a bite was dwindling down. Finally decided for a revisit to this place which I haven‚Äôt been to for years.

Inside is one of those smaller cozy place; clean, typical and nothing too fancy. I was glad the server seated me on a bigger table instead one of those midget size ones. The server informed me they have a Tri-city special set menu for $35, quick glanced and I opted out on that. Here were the food I ordered;

1. Miso soup (complimentary). Pretty basic but thank you, nice to have a hot soup to warm up to from the cold.
2. Appetizer tempura. Pretty basic and as it should be.
3. Oyster motoyaki. I was glad they were on the shell but didn‚Äôt know it‚Äôs their own version of it; cold, marinated with cold pan fried onions on top. The cold oysters didn‚Äôt really do it for me. Is it really that hard to find just the basic fresh oyster motoyaki baked with Japanese mayo anywhere? lol
4. Foie gras nigiri. Okay this is one of those must order item from here. Loved how the way it is put together and seared. Rich, buttery and creamy that literally melts in your mouth. Very nice!
5. Spider roll. A little bit too basic, could be more generous on the soft shell crab.
6. Saba shio yaki. It was okay, pretty straightforward dish.
7. Assorted sashimi. It was okay, the Akami could be a better cut.
8. Chopped scallops, uni, amaebi nigiris. The chopped scallop was fresh, the uni was a generous amount, I like how the amaebi head was prepared so easier to eat.
9. Albacore toro, Akami, chu toro. The albacore toro was a bit dry, the Akami was fresh, the chu toro just make it to the satisfactory level (as you can tell it lost some of its beautiful colour already).

The restaurant is conveniently located on the corner of Lougheed Hwy and Shaughnessy Street in Port Coquitlam. There are plenty of free parkings in the plaza. Inside the restaurant offers a causal comfortable dining atmosphere.

The food was okay, could be better in some departments, but overall satisfactory level.

As for the service, the staffs here were very friendly and welcoming. And quite accommodating to me being the last person left munching away (sorry over stayed 10mins after closing)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgz35zAf1EBI5VT4-S3OU-XjBlX1JuPyxUP2it&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-3-4"},{"Name":"eva lo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLG6_-zQP_odjQCD6-QyiUAohJJqHIlSZOxxzIrErs4yEpQng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love this place! Food is great. And their services are amazing as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS83AdNvfEIDJZZkV3DePelW_McN7Tj1FLm851&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Shirley Cha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpR8FGS-5KuK23fMRpnfaa4vxFgDGeGslPmJNLIpRzEPP553My=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I LOVE this place so much! I‚Äôve been here a lot of times, and each time I‚Äôve had a wonderful experience. Food is beautifully presented, service is exceptional, place is cozy and spotlessly clean, and most importantly the food tastes AMAZING!üç£ It‚Äôs always fresh and made with high quality ingredients. Their menu features variety of dishes that are creative and innovative. Whenever I want some sushi, this place is the first one that comes to my mind. I can‚Äôt wait to go back and have some more!üòç","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNurzGF_ST8dpEReGzlZ8wENSDXHDG8Zh9Wsq65&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2022-10-21"}]

[{"Name":"Nathan Edwardson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuxXGFWhKzNyAQzhtKHQn_iMh9h3zj59CMAh7A6cPStOWw5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice place located right next to my favorite game store. Food and portions are good, fresh sushi. They offer their own delivery which is amazing as I do not like to support third party businesses like skip the dishes. It's clean and beautiful inside nice comfortable chairs. Biggest thing the price is unbeatable for the quality ü´°","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpcgDlQcxQDWajER_dhKh905iid8PozxFPcIcF&fid=0x0:0x15f7f24083cf2842"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Jack Allaby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJocZqOWf-zpMv2b_LL8M0wLjOfBAWRR3Utds762Hzj7DWOmA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Avoid if anyone in your group is vegetarian. Myself and my wife have been regulars here for the last 4 years. Ordering on average once every 10 days. This USED to be out absolute favorite sushi place of all time, however, as you can see from other reviews, it has really gone downhill lately, my understanding is they let go of a bunch of the old staff and hired new staff that have no clue what they‚Äôre doing in many ways.

My wife is vegetarian so we would always request meat and vegetarian dishes be kept in separate containers. In the past they did so with no issues, but over the last 4-6 months they consistently fail this task which, to me. Seems like a basic food safety issue. What if someone with a severe allergy comes and gets food cross contaminated because staff will not read any fine details in an order? This is now the 6th time in the last few months its happened.

It makes me sad, but we wont be ordering from here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoflYVBrpwZEcUCpEC8izAdLqhGV8IZrGMQaZt&fid=0x0:0x15f7f24083cf2842"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food at affordable prices. Enjoyed our dinner here, excellent service. Only recommendation would be to add ice to the table water.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmkb4SO7-NCSEh7XZFhFVpIOvQruYEshE8nb0z&fid=0x0:0x15f7f24083cf2842"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered a party tray with 78 pieces for a dinner and the sushi all tasted fine. Liked the variety of sushi flavours offered in the party tray and the amount of food. The downside was that a lot of the rolls were unraveling and falling apart while in the tray which made it hard to eat in one piece. Otherwise, average, acceptable, and fresh sushi.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwBc3oEUTgyX41ZubxuAzARhwnR4cu1y5uxT02&fid=0x0:0x15f7f24083cf2842"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Sophie Pratt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLh7k6-21NBMQYIuK68Q8phU1orAC4H6O-_4MJL9UZbjYF-SnTT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Unfortunately we won't be returning to this establishment. I had placed an online order at 11am for a 6pm pick up for a large party tray and several other items. When my husband arrived at 6pm for pick up, he was told by a staff person it'd only be a few more mins. At 6:20pm my husband asked again if our order was ready and mentioned our pick up time was 6pm, the female staff person just gave him an awkward smile and said sorry and that they're making it.

He didn't receive our order until 6:40pm so 40 mins after the scheduled time. The food was fine and pricing was affordable but service was not dependable and if we didn't need this order we would have just canceled it due to the delay. I'm fairly confident they didn't start preparing the order until my husband actually arrived.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chantel L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX0TcjzqwikidGgR8ECofcjHJqDNcicSn1j3ilup0dRM-BrEdq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Edit, this place is amazing, the sushi RICE is cooked so well - it's so delicious and I'm Asian I know my rice!

I love how they pay attention to requests ie., little rice, extra sauce and attentive to packaging.  Cold dishes are never packaged in hot dishes/soups where as many sushi places don't even care.  The tempura always comes crispy and hot.

So glad I found this gem after recently moving to the area, they DELIVER including during the day too!  Since living here a month an a half I've ordered 4 times already. Thank you so much <3

[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! All I can say is they serve the perfect piece of pizza. The dough to sauce to topping ratio is just right and the ingredients are fresh and high quality! Will definitely be back. My favourites were the cheese and pepperoni pizza because their tomato sauce is particularly delicious with savouriness and tang. Really impressed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQoJx7_wzA3EbpOC8_CCBcxmc3Ce8LsytAcHZL&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"W L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK87lyILn2l1GNJGaxosGEolmCjP2Is4zUBq1wgU_yTgsuEnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Poco is lucky to have this gem of a pizza place. The pizzas are absolutely delicious and you can tell that everything they use is top notch. The dough is light with a slight crisp, not oily and greasy like most places- thank goodness. Generous with the toppings( it‚Äôs thin crust pizza so please keep that in mind) and baked in a gorgeous Italian oven. It had the perfect charred crust.
I think a lot of people compare this pizza to the other places next door not understanding that this is a completely different style. This is not your regular conveyor belt pizza with a thick bread like crust.
Was pleasantly surprised to see that they sell beer on tap and wine as well. They have an extensive menu with loads of options to choose from.
Friendly and knowledgeable staff too.
This place is a must try if you like quality pizza. 10/10 Reggianos, will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOw93I_3pXWCL818Bl_GgwtZK_YbmMbJJm8WPuL&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Jasmine Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuOzS967Hz_egt9IQZrMH1_TOYLzJMv0RljQ3XzcQT0pp3BA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For that size and quality and how soft and chewy it was, was definitely worth the experience! Sometimes other Neapolitan style pizzas in other stores can get too chewy and stiff but this one was perfect to the crust. Will order again for sure to try different kinds!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNoegTFGywrC7JrR_cikpDdceJJ8eUE6y8PFGO&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was in the area and needed a quick bite between appointments. They had a good selection of pizzas slices available and were also ready to make custom order pizzas. I got the last vegetarian pizza slice and it was good.

The dining room was spotless and they have a funky public washroom (see the video). A great place to get some fresh pizza!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIrFqONmLFOti0GvALnnj31WmTRqYBB_pYUuyh&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Kayleigh Chapman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXggIZcln7wZ5SbxNQJuMEWmRbeK0R52nrQoptdEmgNElWW-c4LNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza place in town. Pizzas baked in the stone oven were delicious. Price was very good - my partner and I spent about $40 and had enough pizza to last 2 days. Service was fast and friendly. They also have a decent selection of good beer to go with. Definitely check this place out if you haven't already.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmJlPBnmrd7vm1EyFdiehyVzbPEGK-9pin1iYH&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2023-7-28"},{"Name":"vanessa lucas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6tWx3DcZm7qvPeZqBDVhnPAzsGDyE0VLCDhzoWWLQT0ORjw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hopped into this Pizzeria to have a slice of pizza and had a slice of heaven instead. We ordered the Regianno‚Äôs Deluxe and it was a sheer delight. The toppings were generous and fresh. It had the right amount of cheese and the crust was one of the best we ever tasted. The staff were friendly and efficient.

Will definitely be having some more. Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1_3jEEnB25tL_TMPzn40R0ZU8O-Fw0-yN48Dj&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Alishya Shroff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzk4pbNxSWWBC4SdXDAth089lM_nR_IuBGHpbAw24vCEK5SjYzzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had ordered pizza for my kids birthday party recently. The pizza were not only delicious but the quality was excellent. Everyone at the party raved about the pizzas, especially the kids..they thoroughly enjoyed every bite of their pizza. We had ordered margarita, chicken pesto, Fungi and pizza Verde.. all of them were excellent and at a very reasonable price. They even cut slices in such a way so it's easier for kids to eat. They delivered it on time at the park as well which was amazing as it saved time and stress for us.

I highly recommend Reggiano pizza if you want supreme quality and scrumptious pizza!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUss3Xiky_ua2bDX8b8zSa1uC7sAzx8dANwSqBcBq6pELbRRfQi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We‚Äôve had the Tuscan chicken pizza from here. And it has been very good. The centre is usually soggy which we don‚Äôt like and we do wish that could be fixed. Sometimes the bottom is undercooked.  As I move back to being a vegetarian, and then, hopefully, vegan someday, I was excited to see they have a variety of vegetarian pizzas‚Ä¶ some with vegan cheese and vegan pepperoni. So I ordered that. Was very disappointed, the middle 3rd to 2/3 of the vegetarian pizza was so soggy, there was hardly any vegetarian pepperoni - maybe one round and a half per large slice of pizza‚Ä¶and where was the cheese? I will never ordered a vegetarian deluxe with vegan pepperoni and vegan cheese on it again. I will give Reggiano‚Äôs another chance as I said, we have loved the Tuscan chicken, hopefully the next vegetarian has more toppings on it, and isn‚Äôt soggy. See photo ‚Ä¶. Litterly a piece and a half of veggie pepperoni on each piece üòï","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2pBviGtRK3Lc7mIqDsth3Dx18EHRi28ebOY_L&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-1-24"}]

[{"Name":"N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXyajiM8jhhadmB24OL7xR6-3AcTWkbqu3nHe56zwz2EWFlpHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went with my friends during lunch on Saturday. Lots of seats available, which was great.
Service was great! We asked to watch a specific soccer game, and they put it on for us.
The only reason for a 4 star - is the food. We ordered party size nachos & cheese - it was fine. Not the best taste that I had, but was a decent size. Also ordered burgers, which were a bit ‚Äúdry‚Äù. But for the price it was good. Just not as good as it was when we had it last time.
Anyway, I‚Äôd definitely go there again, probably would order something else, not the burger.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"james corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXORPNpjn99AmypwXC5L8gqaCK1buk43veXhtLSzHUK1ZItjmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came in for drinks after dinner and the vibe as soon as you walked in was chill but energetic. We found seats and had a server greet us rather quickly and mentioned the specials. We had long island ice tea and they were well balanced and not sweet or strong ...I enjoyed and had 2 while one of the group had an enjoyable dark and stormy. The food looked good that I saw coming out of the kitchen. I would go back for drinks and meals as I enjoyed my first visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"E Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSf46GoVDYA6DwVd9VW9_YDSbB2ZybZwD8Gjg5Qpn6bN0v14Wr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Haven't been here for a long time (no minors allow, so tough to want to be here if you have kids). Used to be a great neighbourhood gem with good food and service, but kind of disappointed when we were here the other night. Arrived on a Friday night around dinner time a couple weeks back. Place was packed as expected, so we understand the service could be a bit slow. Very limited menu (when compares to other pubs in the area), and very pricy for the quality and portions they offered. Waited almost an hr for a few pieces of chicken wings and onion rings, taste was just meh. Our server was friendly, but pretty sure she brought me a lager instead of the honey lager I ordered. Maybe it was just one of those nights?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1WcCEBPc_TsMnRLBo1xDvfIsMTbep7KEKaj2d&fid=0x0:0xddd414d544844a6"],"When":"2023-9-18"},{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My brother and I frequent Samz often, and when friends are in town from the island, we usually take them there in the afternoon for lunch and a couple drinks while watching a few games on the TV's .

Our server on Friday was very nice, and took great care of us while having to deal with one of our Island friends, and his Shenanigans lol.

I do believe our servers name was Alexandra, and was great while dealing with the one friend. I blame the Limes Alexandra lol.

We always have a great time at Samz and the Staff and everyone is always so accommodating

And of course some of us walk home as Samz is close by, and the others took Uber home. Always do it right or don't do it at all I say...

Forgot all about our lunch, basically it was just my brother and I who ate. I had the Samz Burger Bacon and Cheese with Shrooms with Fries, and my brother had some Hot Wings and deep fried pickles. Every thing came out hot and ready to go. And I have to admit I really enjoy the bottomless Fries as well  ( great touch ) as our mom loves that as well when my brother and I take her to Samz for lunch.

And finally in the posted Video  Steve'd has left the building lol. Emphasis on the Steve'd part lol... ü•¥ü•¥ü•¥ü•¥ü•¥ü•¥ü•¥

Once again thanks to everyone at Samz for great hospitality as always üòÉüëçüëçüçª

Update...

We were back at Samz on Saturday May 24th 2024 and one of our friends is Vegan, and Samz accommodated him no problem at all and made a special Vegan meal just for him. He was extremely happy and really enjoyed it.

The Vegan meal picture is in with the pictures posted...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSSwz3WOtWUiRn9Y5dWWFbRRS984hH2nC8j6AL&fid=0x0:0xddd414d544844a6"],"When":"2023-11-25"},{"Name":"Christina Gompf-Alksne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhCy51p896p0hWTuQ2f6jBzuO5Habqt6RsYQFNNmstZzCLKuQ3VQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The burger is amazing. My husband and I both got one and we agreed, we were visiting from Calgary and found the best burger. The mushrooms were grilled before being put on the burger so it wasn‚Äôt sloppy, the fries & gravy were also great. Definitely recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pat Trinh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGKmpoLpVi9_ZLeKCQEZPnQ-vrekua-m32_C1oTE4XYHSsT8fY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This local pub has delicious burgers and pasta. The atmosphere is clean, quaint and chill. The service is friendly. We ordered the Same burger and Kobe burger. The yam fries are quite a bit better than the regular fries. We went on a Saturday lunch period and there was no wait but quite a few people enjoying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6fvq5sAV6cJ0e25feonHhUOE0BHs-tzcBaaIL&fid=0x0:0xddd414d544844a6"],"When":"2019-11-10"},{"Name":"Lang „É©„É≥„Ç∞Erich „Ç®„É™„ÉÉ„ÇØ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_fnBQbwZD7MujuZxz_w__in2Ebl1mFxa5cYrAsb2pWV0IGQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Probably one of the best Pubs in the area, great service, great food, comfortable surroundings, if there is any sporting events on the place tends to pack up quickly although they do have quite a large  capacity and plenty of TVs so you should be able to get a good view no matter where you sit. Lots of good specials every night and tasty food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNH9iw9DPYaPLRkUbk8NUgKa1bPSZW6-qKClvE1&fid=0x0:0xddd414d544844a6"],"When":"2023-3-12"},{"Name":"Janice Lemay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYaV_Cz4FnkW55dz-tNUpcnN3jiOUEhJxM6D-NWnqjJiTvoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My husband and I came in for Sunday breakfast/brunch . We both ordered the classic breakfast,  I ordered mine with sausage and my husband got bacon. When the order arrived I didn't notice right away but noticed the sausage was a Bavarian sausage not breakfast sausage.  I asked the waitress,  she didn't apologize or anything just that's what we always have served like I should know. The waitress,  I believe by the receipt her name is Lesli. She offered bacon instead and when brought out she just plunked it on the table , no apology at all....I have been in the customer service business since I was 18, I will be 60 next year. One thing to always do is apologize even if not your doing. ALSO your menu should say Bavarian Sausage 1 waste of money 2 is what if someone did not know it's a Bavarian sausage started eating and had an allergic reaction!!?? Not everyone thinks about mentioning food allergies.
Samz pub is convenient for us but standoffs staff does cut it. There are other pubs in the area.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Meghan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXx-nTmucE2EoJoVZKyDaURTIIYHhu2J5CMiEPqSTwPd9phTwUD5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"New Chow's Kitchen is now a family favorite. He is always so kind and cheerful when you go to pick up your food.

The food is good, good sized portions. Great combinations for single eaters as well! I recommend the almond chicken, sweet chili chicken and wonton soup.

They did at one point have a delivery service (not sure anymore) that I wouldn't recommend, they guy couldn't find my house and I had to go meet him on the main road.

Not really a place to eat in as it is a very small dining room and more of a take out joint.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7lq6mNAEZZa_oJ7lV4rradPoz4orT3T5kqQdn&fid=0x0:0x3d1366fce46751f5"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Zak Bindley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4ovldlD-FCx5UF-n_0kkGub31_grb4YIy5bC0ywiYGTUtgg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Purchased 80$ worth of food tonight and after a 25% tip to the driver it came to 100$. Once my wife and I began to open the food we realized that both the rice and chowmein were both filled to the brim. But the prawns, and sweet and sour pork weren‚Äôt even 1/2 full. Quite disappointed in the portions after spending the amount of money we did. The food here has always been great as it‚Äôs been our go to when we‚Äôre looking for takeout but after our experience tonight we will need to consider for future orders.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Renata Steele Vancouver / Kelowna area (Realtor Vancouver BC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVY5AYokNodhccb7bLk1A7kSxqiXee9yFcQzGTeTsQYbtPKFk2s-rk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New Chow‚Äôs Kitchen is an amazing restaurant they gave us the best service ever! The prices are great the food was fresh, hot and delicious and the owner is very friendly. We appreciate them serving us tea while we waited and delivering our Chow Mein to us that they forgot to include and they didn't charge us for it. We are looking forward to ordering from them again soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrRz0E8kC3cwnWuLuw7ufwKFT8Ok8lnqOYQVKL&fid=0x0:0x3d1366fce46751f5"],"When":"2020-5-22"},{"Name":"T K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBjs_8XvvkzBMG-1HmgIjTdYzywRXtx1m_K9OxV4qzE99dY0-d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you're looking for "fast" mediocre Chinese food; than you found your place at "New Chow Kitchen".

We ordered (to-go) 2 vegetable spring rolls, fried rice, vegetable lo mein and 2 cans of pop; all for $30.49 (including tax).

The portions were large; as we could not finish up our meal.

The food tasted "bland" not spicy. It was "okay".

The owner, Tom is very nice.

Our overall experience was nice, however; I "would-not" go back there again as I have compared the cost of what we ordered and paid for verses other Thai/Chinese Restaurants within the neighborhood that had much tastier food for almost the same price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzAF6Rjjl6Xo0ocMM5_82N4lNcZBL6cIxfWqM&fid=0x0:0x3d1366fce46751f5"],"When":"2018-8-19"},{"Name":"Mike Thibodeau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjwlKqXsi9nq3_I1QMglC4JRC7Mu0RfVuoPefhp4Jgu6CHnU8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very tasty food for an affordable price!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-dYzbvLqASgZfkUYzkB05piQPQAvQuZjDy9fX&fid=0x0:0x3d1366fce46751f5"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Pamela Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIALm97KrF-OTcDmOprNmRfL_LjyDGaRveMcz7dR_bLa1zYbg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Just ordered nearly $150 of food for my mom's birthday dinner. Got to the restaurant to be told they cancelled the order because they had a big party to cook for. No phone call or email to notify us. TERRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE. Will NEVER order from them again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Silvia Calero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZKA6Y9ywkVrqAmFKvNKcQ6zymLXDCtYAu4BdNAALEAPGQtTw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is very delicious is one off the best Chinese  restaurants  New Chows Kitchen

The hostess asked me if I would like Jasmine tea, I said no and asked for Chrysanthemum tea.  She didn‚Äôt understand me and brought me jasmine anyway but it wasn‚Äôt a big deal.

We marked off the dim sum we wanted on the paper and the dishes came out relatively quickly considering how busy it was, one at a time.

The food was steaming hot and delicious.  We had the egg tarts, fried tofu, shrimp rice rolls, beef balls, pan fried prawn and chive dumplings, chicken feet and beef brisket rice rolls in a clay pot.

Everything was absolutely delicious, the shrimp rice roll was loaded with prawns!  The servers aren‚Äôt the friendliest and don‚Äôt hide that they‚Äôre annoyed when you ask for other things such as hot sauce or a drink.  I understand that they‚Äôre busy though and I‚Äôm there for the food so it‚Äôs not a big deal.

The hostess also missed one item that I checked off on our order but we were full anyway.

Bottom line, yes I would absolutely return for dim sum!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnaVG2kGThAKwI_-1GwALL1JRsn48bC2BI75fc&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Ngoc Ha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBQDR7xuHV7zpmSmm8y3qArF6yv91O7Kuz_kGRJuYZ6FiARojF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a 3rd time I am here. There are long line up for brunch. I have never had to pay, so I can't tell about tipping thing. The service has room to improve certainly. For example, when we say today the food seem to be a little bit saltier than the last time we were here, and we ask if they have new chef or what; the server acts like we speak nonsense. I am attaching here the updated menu in case you need to know the increased price. Today is September 30, 2024. I recommend you to bring cash to pay and ask for promotion of cash payment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwhQqJazyjZJ780aB1nl5jFq0sJazfM_7PRRv9&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"---edit June 2024---
I tried different dim sum dishes.
Deep fried squid tentacles - really good. Portion is a bit small

Beef Rice rolls - good texture.

Shrimp paste on eggplant - came out piping hot

Shrimp patty with chives - this one came out cold... it was good but it probably sat there for a while

Deep fried glutinous rice balls with meat filling - the outside mochi was good but the filling was lacking in flavor and in portion

Beef brisket on chan chuen fan - love the noodles. Can't get this type of noodle in many places. Beef brisket was tough and not much flavor. Would try the pork riblets next time.

-------------
In terms of flavor, this has got to be one of the wosrt ones I have been to.

Century egg and pork congee - flavorless. No salt. No base whatsoever.

Hand shredded chicken salad - extremely small. Most places that give smaller portions have expensive jellyfish in the salad. This place is only chicken and preserved vegetables so there is no need for it to be half the size of the plate, smaller than other specialty chef items.

Deep fried chicken knees - giant pieces only to find out it is 80% batter. The garlic salt and spice just sat at the bottom and the chicken was never stirred with it.

Minced pork fried glutinous rice dumpling - the glutinous rice wasnt very sweetened. The insides were ok. The only good thing is that it came with 4 pieces instead of 3.

Overall, the dimsum dishes were not very good. The prices are high with poor quality dishes. Maybe their dinner menu makes up for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRL0bQXOdXOmLCPckVyE40kKNkpOpokL1auaQZ&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2023-5-27"},{"Name":"Brayden M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPBZNPVNqHW8dSCFike-NLUMkuCrsmT6ZW7ysivwMhyRbgUxkL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch again, and it's always a great experience here! Arrived around 2p, so we were seated promptly (wait time ~20 minutes during peak hours).
We ordered the Ëù¶È§É shrimp dumplings, ÁâõÁ≠ãËÇö beef stomach tendon, Ëè†ËòøÂèâÁáíÂåÖ BBQ bun with crispy topping, ÈππÊ∞¥Ëßí 'football' pork croquette, and ÁÇ∏ÂÖ©ËÖ∏Á≤â fried rice roll.
The Pineapple BBQ bun was sold out, so we replaced it with a regular BBQ bun. However our order was not properly registered, and we had to wait around half an hour for it to come out, though our server handled the situation very well.
The shrimp dumplings were large and fresh, the pork bun serving was generous, the croquette was hot and fresh, and the rice roll was super quick to come out.
Overall, we had a great experience, save the minor hiccup with the pork bun, and I look forward to coming back!
Total cost for 5 dishes: $48+tip","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLe2VHyhSpKyyCfA55fvKWDpIItEGlLqapxQWovhsqs48cXNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been getting deliveries and take outs from this restaurant during Covid-19. Loved the dishes that I tried before  and finally dined in for dinner. Food tasted so much better at the restaurant. Affordable price. Large portions. My favourite everyday restaurant. Cons: restaurant was quite busy today and 2-3waitress. We were lucky since it wasn‚Äôt busy when we arrived. But later, I saw others had to wait for long time to get serviced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBZRim4hfHTzin_sh6ZqIL_nKFFOeFZvGJ8GUy&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2022-10-16"}]

Overall, relatively expensive for the size (16.25) can get a better bang for your buck elsewhere but not bad.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3ZGnXgQsaPYTuppm3OhvJaou-Mj7j5eL9L45eo8YIXyf3Vg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The 2 ladies are nice. The chicken in the donair I had was dry, and not grilled after it was from the spit, like some other places do. Also the donair was not toasted after like other places do. The seats on the single bar area are a bit short which makes sitting along this area a little awkward. Very clean place though and all veggies were fresh.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtVwY8vXNvQu1mnJtoujIZvRzdgy8CHT2NWP9SUkOINxwk2Tg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Nice location, with 2 nice ladies working. They're both kind and easy to speak to.

The food portions however really annoyed me, they have 2 sizes for platers and I got the largest size possible but it's like they gave me a small in terms of meat. There is a lot of rice but a thin layer of meat.. Your super size should have piled up meat on it. It's disappointing because i live very close, and would love a good donair joint but this one is way too stingy with their meat","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Baggott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5de3eIIZ4GcnmYEfI5b5jgtudInhk1mWYvnNjye9w-9rmYvW-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Well we were on the search for a good Donair in our area, huge fan of Donair Dude so the bar is already high.
We had checked out a couple places around Coquitlam Center and nothing was jumping out.
Did a quick google search and Sultan‚Äôs Donair popped up, why not?
From the moment we arrived the place had a good clean and home kinda fell to it. The dinning are isn‚Äôt large however the place was very well kept and even decorated with a sense of humour.
The woman there were welcoming, happy and attentive.
The menu is quite simple with great options, including Tuna!!
I do enjoy the large Donair, so I went Sultan size, I was not disappointed!
Yes, Sultan‚Äôs Donair is comparable to Donair Dude!
I will be returning,... after my diet üòêüòâ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMZThtTo6kEWkHQZQCaJuVIFhxW6g_wB81IEfx&fid=0x0:0x7e000591943f3eb3"],"When":"2020-1-6"},{"Name":"Renata Steele Vancouver / Kelowna area (Realtor Vancouver BC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVY5AYokNodhccb7bLk1A7kSxqiXee9yFcQzGTeTsQYbtPKFk2s-rk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We looked up reviews for Donair restaurants since we were in the mood for something different. This restaurant had many great reviews so we decided to try it. The server was friendly but did not seem familiar with the menu. The Donair and falafel was very tasty. The Greek salad was very small but tasted great. The lamb and beef was dry. We feel that we were over charged, when we brought it up they ignored us. We may be back to try it again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxAFK_K5YaLjDgc_yETdDcQjrMuB6ZTuYgcXMp&fid=0x0:0x7e000591943f3eb3"],"When":"2020-1-10"},{"Name":"Mike Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtiC79KDVm1ALU6A2yCh2BRGkVPLJAypqZoVtI767OvfhHdLtb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It was OK. I had a caesar salad thing, but it was drenched in sauce. Didn't get much meat for ten bucks. The place has ample seating and it all seemed fairly clean. The prices on the board were fair. I would stick to the donairs and ask them to hold back on the sauce a little bit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTzkJySrhqH9EQoJcqX_MwvabRtbgSW3Avpw5p&fid=0x0:0x7e000591943f3eb3"],"When":"2018-1-15"},{"Name":"T Baker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNVurW8I51iuNJOCX1TOm9bF4fX7v1xLOtMBEa4_Wk_YPkFutD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent, great value and service. We came just before closing and they were still so sweet and helpful. Taste was awesome, portions are very large. Very fresh.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adam Quaas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJA48plOU5QotPkCw0lZxdjwYpssFcPHIiU3OZyyRFa0vyD9g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place wasn't bad for a donair but there are better out there still worth a stop if you are hungry","Images":null,"When":""}]
