user_reviews:
[{"Name":"SeifellAlmancht","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsxCJrR8TsN9fT21mw9fTGEMgFsRedfDhq-FibJJoaNU_Hzh2t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So to start this negative review I would like to mention that I work in food service in a very busy establishment on UBC campus so I understand it can get stressful but... this place was terrible.

Firstly, when my husband and I walked in there was only 2 other customers and about 5 workers working, yet every single table besides 1 were filthy. I've worked at Subway before my current job for 7-8 years and we would never allow the lobby to look like this. It was disgusting. That's not even mentioning their soft drink station that was also a sticky mess.

Secondly, they don't give napkins or utensils without you asking? What? It's basic practice where I work to ALWAYS give cutlery and napkins for all orders. And when I had to go up to ask I was waiting a while even though there were workers who saw me and ignored me. One worker, who I assume is the supervisor due to her different shirt, was working on a tablet for nearly the entire time I was waiting and she looked over at me more than once and didn't even bother to ask if I needed anything. She even walked fully by me and ignored me. I had to ask the cashier when she was available, though she was also intending on ignoring me until I spoke up and asked for the items I needed.

There was also a woman waiting several minutes to order when my husband and I were waiting on our food. Why?

Food establishments need to understand that their two most important things are CUSTOMERS and CLEANLINESS. This location seems to put both these things (especially cleaniness) at the bottom of their priority lists.

Lastly, while the food was passable, they stack EVERYTHING haphazardly into a single bag regardless of what you get. So are they stingy with bags and napkins? Or? It's very strange.

Terrible terrible location that has had these same issues for several years, it seems, looking at old reviews. This just tells me that the owners do not care. They haven't changed anything in years, so I would recommend NOT coming here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKuZFrgWOPQHt4eI8L_kWqd27VE-OVj0DqV6o3&fid=0x0:0xd49ddca9db87b135"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"eee envy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUv6ustbctHgayROab6GPATif-uph4IK_tRlciz6FR3y83NqpH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We waited almost 10 minutes to be helped at the counter and ended up having to go through the drive through to get help even though the inside was still open. While we were waiting at the counter, a woman walked up and got immediate help and we were ignored. Our food took a bit to come out and they gave us our Baja Blasts warm with no ice. Food was solid 5/10. America is better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Justin Pelletier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2gkbUSXW4RJZYfDgp0sS5i-Z60OKpGiL9VyTnYx9y35Kzr5Qm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is one of the worst Taco Bell‚Äôs in all of Canada. I don‚Äôt know how many times that I‚Äôve gone here and every time they keep giving me an old stale pita for my steak Chalupa. Every time every time I have to go back and exchange it. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Agni K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkDG9ralu9RS3nZ0v4vIcP6bNgjmOEKH-8N8DikYFi0AF_Esan=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbled upon this restaurant on Canada day after the fireworks at the nearby Lafarge lake. We were surprised it was still open so late! It‚Äôs not a Michelin style fine dining, but let me say this, if you are looking for an authentic Korean food experience, you‚Äôll find it here. Service is fast, no nonsense, no over exaggerated descriptions of the dishes, straight to the point meal options. And unlike the popular Korean bbq experience (which I also enjoy), this is different that it brings you the culinary experience of what a regular Korean family would cook and serve at home as their daily meals. I was so impressed by their pork feet meal, it took me back 20 years to the days I would enjoy this dish as a snack with beer. It was truly a nostalgic moment. Another thing to be mindful of‚Ä¶ do not assume you can handle these family size portions. They are there to bring you comfort not just in the duty of flavour packed dishes, but also in the size of the meals! We ended taking a lot of the food home cos we were bursting at the seams by the end.

I will absolutely come here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7X6ER0qKnJ7dWt1o5zVXTe9wxlPAEUmu9QQIG&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Rosella J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRmjzC8A0ZGYulX6CBBPewqPk_JLrMOysG31_3Kt3vO5eAJQeP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Even I dont have a car I go all the way down from downtown.
This place has amazing food.

Only problem is business hour can be different, I missed it few times. So I call them to check make sure they are open before I go.

Friendly staff too,
love table ring system. Easy and quick.

Go try now!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsfcMWxSGHqhITiKOSbBdw_d6uuRqviWB6y5rN&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Lily Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDGk1BBw-1vgJ9ulxVR0Qxl5Y2TOzVCkO980S0Usi15HFveto=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Spicy Garlic chicken was not spicy at all and soggy, not crispy and had chicken smell. Spicy pork feet(Jokbal) was unbelievably burnt and had a few pieces actually edible. Talked to server and they insisted it‚Äôs the way it should be, not burnt and everyone likes it. It was unbelievable. Because we didn‚Äôt eat at all In the end the owner deducted the dish from the bill but all in all it was very unpleasant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7JrEGU0-zvYMNSr2ELhHI8ByQ9px_nwJzenPJ&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favorite Korean BBQ restaurants ever! Been coming here for more then 10 years, it's a small family owned business with great food and service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMBCiJWmTZsr9c63H0wW7hZSOzbkO5Cq3OWPqL&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Susan Jin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXD2KDNwuO_tshKA7qOLehTxpKB4389udgDYJHckxaN38dH26c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Over the years, Vesta has become our go to place for Korean food. They don‚Äôt have everything we love about Korean food, but everything they have is the best version we have tried so far. Our favorites are the spicy pork with veggies, seafood tofu soup, stir fried chicken with soy sauce, kimchi fried rice, chive pancake and all versions of the cold noodle dish.  And the most mouth watering spicy octopus with noodles is not just a dish but an experience worth sharing. Most of their negative reviews were not about the food but the tipping, but come on, a tip less than 15% is an insult to the quality of food and the same people working there every day. Like most Korean restaurants, there is a bell on the table for service calls. We never had any problem getting the service or food using the bell. Please respect their way of doing business and leave your negativity outside the door.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5d8zUN1kGs7rJ5-IeBtgk1FTdF1JjTf0W7S4U&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2023-5-12"},{"Name":"Jason D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV14HLbc6Ze7JZiJufUEhwiQ1I37e9rPxJ7pjEPsypNxuqatRs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Average chicken in Coquitlam. We ordered bone in but lot of pieces were mostly bone. Sauce is decent but too sweet. Rice cake and sausage was good though.

Service is okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiG_Tl4mZHh98bolu1HrvwbOxC7JUKAAmo2CI&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2024-2-26"},{"Name":"Vero Vero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJqM6z3NvGgp8fOHPNYXy_sxK1l4a3Acl0A1wGDJ4i1AfuQXig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant is a hidden gemüíé that you must find. I am so happy to experience such an athentic cuisine at this restaurant. I and my friend were so ready to eat a lot today because we waited for right day to come here and today was the day :) we ordered chicken feet, pork entrails, and pork long feet. We assumed that it would be excessive portion for only two of us but we could not give up on  any of them. üòéFirst of all, the pork long feet exceeded our expectation. Both taste and portion were so great and 'prawn and chive pancake' was served as an appetizer before pork feet(it was complimentaryüòçüòç). And speaking of the pork feet, it was the best, and the best...ü§© I have never tasted this pork feet  ever since I came to Canada. I can feel how authentic it is. And I also was able to feel the enthusiasm of chef toward the food. It was obvious that the cuisine was cooked with lots of love and effort. And next surprising one was stir-fried entrails. Not many restaurants serves it in Vancouver because it is not easy to get rid of the bad smell of the pork intestine. However, this place did such an awesome job on it. I barely noticed that it is pork intestine. It was pleasantly chewy, and two sauces came along with it went perfectly well. It magnified the nutty flavor of the pork intestine. I loved and loved it. And last one that I expected even in my dream was spicy chicken feet. It was perfectly marinated with the sauce and I am personally not so good at dealing with spiciness, but it was not overly spicy. I did not drink a lot of water, which was good because I need some space in my stomach for the food!! And we also ordered a rice ball because chicken feet and rice ball must be ordered together. They go along so well! Overall, my experience at this place was truly the best. And although it is pretty far for me to visit here, I will be regularly going to this place to make my tongue and stomach happy. I must recommend this place for all, especially those who are having homesickness or just sick and tired of ordinary cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtCS1YYlVBeEban5iMJfh-iSxkWQ-gLpiIaYX4&fid=0x0:0x22e97376de3aac1b"],"When":"2020-9-29"},{"Name":"Daniel Yim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQasZok9PzRbGWAPT2JykQMeRGEE-9L_G4T1fQkEB1IiM4sw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing dining experience at Vesta Grill and Korean Cuisine, it caught my family with such a pleasant surprise! We ordered the five spice pork front feet, Korean sausage and pork in soup with rice, kimchi pork tofu soup with rice, and beef teriyaki. Every dish was packed with great flavors and offered at a fair price. The menu has a lot of food choices, and we definitely need to come back to try more. The vibe is perfect for enjoying soju and beer with friends, and it‚Äôs fantastic that they‚Äôre open till midnight! üëç","Images":null,"When":""}]

Pizza was ok. The chicken bites were burnt and so we called to ask for a refund on the chicken bites. I am giving it 1 star simply because there are so many better pizza places that I would rather give my hard earned money to.

When we called to ask for a refund on just the burnt chicken bites, we were told a refund for burnt food somehow wouldn‚Äôt be possible but no clear explanation given as to why. Then they actually tried to make excuses for sending burnt food to paying customers and I quote: ‚ÄúWe have to cook the chicken bites twice and when we cook them the second time, there is a possibility that they can burn.‚Äù So after a lot of back and forth over the phone and no manager making an effort to speak to us themselves, we finally agreed to have them send over more chicken bites. That was almost 2 hours ago and we have received nothing.

It is clear that they‚Äôre content to take money from their customers and deliver subpar product. There are better pizza places in the immediate area that have better customer service. We paid full price for burnt food and they tried to justify charging us for it.

I am interested to see what the owner‚Äôs response is going to be- so far, we are not impressed. In all fairness, we waited to see if they would be able to make things right but we‚Äôre still waiting for those chicken bites 2 hours after the fact.
